    '{"id":"01KAEFFPG29XJYZGZ39WC4XW5E","title":"GSS // MID Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content and Publishing Strategy**\n\nThe team is advancing key content projects to enhance operational efficiency messaging and maintain engagement momentum.\n\n- **A new blog post titled \"Building your finance function: The 103050 unit evolution\" is in progress, with an interview scheduled with Will Fleming to shape narrative and outline** (01:13)  \n    - This post supports the broader theme of operational efficiencies emphasized across content.  \n    - The episode on malware readiness is ready for scheduling, with a tentative publish window set for next week.  \n    - Guille Santana will coordinate all supporting assets once the publish date is confirmed.  \n    - These content efforts aim to drive thought leadership and nurture prospects aligned with service offerings.\n\n- **The expanded content capacity from the new website removes previous blog limits, enabling more frequent updates and SEO-driven optimizations** (18:05)  \n    - The team is preparing adjustments to the accounting services pages to counteract recent traffic decline identified in the latest SEO review.  \n    - This ongoing content refresh is designed to bolster organic search performance and client engagement.  \n    - Monthly management tasks and outreach sequence updates remain active priorities feeding into these content efforts.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) and Client Engagement**\n\nABM messaging is being refined to emphasize trust-building through results before presenting offers, with Will Fleming stressing its value for both cold prospects and current client retention.\n\n- **Will Fleming endorsed the revised email sequence that delays the free 30-day offer to build rapport based on results first** (02:45)  \n    - Leading with the free offer risks seeming like a cheap ploy, so sequencing focuses first on trust and results.  \n    - The 30-day free trial is positioned as a “no friction” way for prospects or clients to experience the service and gain comfort.  \n    - This approach is intended to reduce cost hesitation and uncertainty, key barriers in client acquisition.  \n    - Baylee Gunnell suggested placing the free offer around the 4th or 5th email to maximize its impact after trust is established.\n\n- **Will shared lessons from a challenging client retention case where the 30-day free offer acted as a tool to rebuild trust and upgrade existing clients** (04:27)  \n    - The client had enjoyed two years of good service before issues arose due to turnover, causing dissatisfaction.  \n    - Will’s direct involvement and explanation of CFO services, coupled with offering the 30-day free trial, re-engaged the client effectively.  \n    - Nick has since moved this client into the sales pipeline as a potential long-term revenue source.  \n    - This case reveals the 30-day free offer’s dual role in both new client acquisition and retention/upsell strategies.\n\n- **Will requested a professionally formatted PDF or collateral to support client conversations, but prefers linking to the live webpage \"try.GSS.com\" as a better user experience than attachments** (13:34)  \n    - The webpage allows clients to submit their information directly, improving ease of engagement.  \n    - Baylee confirmed plans to send this link post-call for Will’s follow-up use.  \n    - This digital asset enhances the credibility and accessibility of the 30-day offer.  \n    - Streamlining collateral supports sales efficiency and client responsiveness.\n\n- **The team plans to launch the updated ABM email sequence next week, post-Thanksgiving, pending final review and approval from Will** (15:12)  \n    - The timing avoids holiday disruptions and ensures readiness for optimal engagement.  \n    - LinkedIn messaging tied to the campaign will also be refreshed before relaunch.  \n    - Early results from LinkedIn outreach show good connection acceptance and some replies, supporting positive momentum.\n\n## **Website Migration and Infrastructure**\n\nThe website migration to a new WordPress staging environment is complete, with quality control underway and a planned midweek launch to ensure smooth transition.\n\n- **All pages have migrated to the new staging site, with the team performing detailed QC to check functionality and design** (16:05)  \n    - Internal reviews focus on button functionality and page appearance consistency before client review.  \n    - The launch is targeted for a Wednesday or Thursday to ensure immediate support and quick fixes if needed.  \n    - Baylee emphasized avoiding Friday launches due to higher risk of unresolved issues over the weekend.  \n    - The team’s swift execution reflects strong operational capability.\n\n- **Once the new site launches, Baylee confirmed the client can cancel the existing Duda subscription with confidence, as WordPress hosting includes a backup site** (17:16)  \n    - Backup ensures website availability despite routine technical issues, reducing operational risk.  \n    - This infrastructure upgrade centralizes hosting and aligns with long-term stability goals.  \n    - Clear communication on cancellation timing will follow launch confirmation to avoid service gaps.\n\n## **Client Portal and Workflow Transparency**\n\nThe client portal provides detailed visibility into ongoing tasks and projects, supporting transparency and prioritization.\n\n- **Currently, the portal shows 155 active points, primarily monthly management tasks along with outreach sequence updates and multiple blog optimizations** (18:05)  \n    - This volume reflects steady operational throughput supporting marketing and product initiatives.  \n    - The portal helps clients track progress and understand resource allocation in real time.  \n    - It also facilitates collaboration on SEO tweaks and upcoming website launch activities.  \n    - Maintaining this visibility supports client trust and smooth project management.\n\n## **Strategic Insights on Service Positioning and Customer Relationships**\n\nThe discussion highlighted the importance of trust and personalized service in overcoming friction in client acquisition and retention.\n\n- **Will Fleming explained the CFO service’s personal advisory role helps reduce hesitation during initial engagement and first payment months** (09:42)  \n    - The 30-day free period allows clients to experience value risk-free, increasing commitment likelihood.  \n    - This approach prevents dissatisfied clients from paying unnecessarily, protecting company reputation.  \n    - The trial period also helps tailor the service fit and structure for long-term success.  \n    - These insights shape the marketing and sales approach to emphasize trust and fit over hard selling.\n\n- **Will emphasized that trust-building is harder but equally critical with unhappy current clients and unknown prospects, making the 30-day offer a key friction remover in both cases** (10:34)  \n    - The offer is designed to be “almost irresistible,” turning trust into trial without pressure.  \n    - This philosophy underpins the ABM messaging strategy and client retention efforts.  \n    - The team recognizes that removing cost and commitment barriers early accelerates positive outcomes.  \n    - Such positioning differentiates the service in a competitive market focused on personalized CFO support.","outline":null,"keywords":["Content Updates","ABM Email Sequence","30-Day CFO Offer","Client Retention","Website Migration","LinkedIn Outreach"],"overview":"- **Content Strategy Update:** New blog post on finance functions is underway, plus upcoming malware readiness episode scheduled for next week.\n\n- **SEO Enhancements:** Website migration enables frequent updates; revamps for accounting pages aim to improve declining traffic.\n\n- **ABM Messaging Refinement:** Revised email sequence emphasizes trust before free offers; trial strategically placed for maximum impact.\n\n- **Website Launch Timing:** Migration to new WordPress site is complete; launch planned midweek to avoid weekend issues with immediate support.\n\n- **Client Portal Insights:** 155 active project points are highlighted in the portal, enhancing transparency and client engagement.\n\n- **Trust-Building Focus:** Personalized CFO services and a free trial help alleviate client hesitations, aiding both acquisition and retention strategies.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nFinalize and send updated ABM email sequence incorporating feedback and new 30-day offer timing; target launch next week post-Thanksgiving (15:12)\nShare link to ''try.GSS'' webpage with Will for client communication use (14:30)\nComplete website quality control check on new staging site and coordinate final client review before launch (16:05)\nNotify Will Fleming about Duda subscription cancellation timing after new site launch (17:10)\nContinue updates on outreach sequences, blog posts, and SEO optimizations in client portal (18:05)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nProvide input and participate in interview shaping blog post narrative for ''Building your finance function. The 103050 unit evolution.'' (01:13)\nUtilize ''try.GSS'' landing page in retention follow-ups with current clients and send link in client follow-ups (14:30)\nCoordinate internally to apply 30-day CFO service offer with current clients as retention or upsell tool using provided collateral (07:59)\nReview and confirm acceptance of ABM email sequence updates once shared prior to launch (15:12)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nAssist in publishing content updates including malware episode scheduling (01:56)\nSupport internal QC and website migration verification processes (16:05)\n"},"duration":19.229999542236328,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"id":2,"name":"Will Fleming"},{"id":3,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Thanksgiving.","index":0,"end_time":0.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m just doing family stuff.","index":1,"end_time":7.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.68,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Just normal family stuff.","index":2,"end_time":8.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.2,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just, I''m at home with family.","index":3,"end_time":15.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":8.88,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":4,"end_time":17.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Always a good time spend.","index":5,"end_time":19.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Spend it with family and eat.","index":6,"end_time":21.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hopefully some, some good food.","index":7,"end_time":22.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Too much food.","index":8,"end_time":25.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.88,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Too much.","index":9,"end_time":26.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":10,"end_time":27.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":11,"end_time":30.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Too much food.","index":12,"end_time":31.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, well, we will go ahead and get into it.","index":13,"end_time":36.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll go over some content updates, ABM updates, and I want to talk through that email you sent over Will too with just talking to some of your current clients there and then also just a few website updates.","index":14,"end_time":56.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But anything else you all want to chat through today?","index":15,"end_time":59.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":16,"end_time":64.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m good too.","index":17,"end_time":65.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Okay, cool, Cool.","index":18,"end_time":67.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll kick it over to Guille just to talk through some of the content updates.","index":19,"end_time":72.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":20,"end_time":74.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":73.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So here are the latest content updates on our site.","index":21,"end_time":77.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":74.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We have a new blog post in the works.","index":22,"end_time":80.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":78.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Building your finance function.","index":23,"end_time":82.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":80.69,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The 103050 unit evolution.","index":24,"end_time":85.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":82.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And we are meeting with Will today actually for the interview.","index":25,"end_time":90.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":86.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So we can start like shaping the narrative and the outline for it.","index":26,"end_time":93.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":90.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This topic, it ties directly into the operational efficiencies that we''ve been emphasizing across our content.","index":27,"end_time":102.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":94.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And we also have the episode regarding malware ready.","index":28,"end_time":110.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":103.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I just wanted to confirm with you guys, when would you like prefer to publish it?","index":29,"end_time":115.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":110.27,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Anytime.","index":30,"end_time":116.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.31,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Next week''s fine.","index":31,"end_time":117.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.91,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":32,"end_time":121.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":119.27,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":33,"end_time":122.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":121.909,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, once we have the date, I''ll schedule like all the supporting assets.","index":34,"end_time":127.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":123.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":35,"end_time":129.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":128.23,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Got it.","index":36,"end_time":130.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":129.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Great.","index":37,"end_time":132.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So the next is the email sequence for abm.","index":38,"end_time":135.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We got some feedback from you yesterday, Will.","index":39,"end_time":138.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think it sounds like you''re liking the updates we''re going to focusing more on like the results they can expect so we can build rapport before we jump into the free offer.","index":40,"end_time":149.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we were also able to add in that calendly link, but.","index":41,"end_time":154.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then you also sent over some updates.","index":42,"end_time":158,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like you''re offering this to some of your current clients.","index":43,"end_time":161.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''d love to hear more about that.","index":44,"end_time":163.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":45,"end_time":166.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I just want to first of all like on the sequence, like I think it''s.","index":46,"end_time":172.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":167.69,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s valuable to, to do the 30 day offer free, but it''s, it''s just not to lead with that.","index":47,"end_time":180.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.37,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like if they see that as the subject or we''re leading with that, it sort of cheapens the.","index":48,"end_time":184.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.49,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It sort of like a ploy.","index":49,"end_time":186.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":184.89,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"However, if you, if you.","index":50,"end_time":188.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":187.05,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I like the way that the sequence moves.","index":51,"end_time":191.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":188.57,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We''re trying to build trust based on results and that''s a good approach.","index":52,"end_time":197.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.18,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But then, so then imagine you get to a scenario where they''re interested and it''s kind of like, you know, Nick has to do this.","index":53,"end_time":206.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.26,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The way the sequence works now is Nick has to do this 15 minute consultation call to see what''s going on.","index":54,"end_time":216.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.22,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And not that, you know, maybe everything''s great.","index":55,"end_time":220.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.99,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And they say, oh, we really like this, we want to sign up and they pay from the get go.","index":56,"end_time":224.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.31,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But my sense is, because they don''t know us, these are impersonal emails.","index":57,"end_time":229.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":224.87,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"At some point in still in the automated sequence, we can hit them with, hey, this is a results oriented service or something like that and we can actually turn this on for the first 30 days without, without, you know, free or without a cost.","index":58,"end_time":249.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.59,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So you could really get a level of comfort in the, in the service and who we are.","index":59,"end_time":258.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So, so we''re, we''re, you know, so the, the idea is we''re building trust based on these results that are applicable to them.","index":60,"end_time":266.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":258.749,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then, and then it''s, there''s no friction.","index":61,"end_time":271.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.79,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"There''s like, oh, I''m interested in this but I''m worried about the cost or I don''t know how to do this or whatever.","index":62,"end_time":277.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":271.93,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so we remove that.","index":63,"end_time":278.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we, we had a customer.","index":64,"end_time":280.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.49,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Well, we have a customer who we''ve had some challenges with.","index":65,"end_time":286.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.61,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"As you probably can imagine.","index":66,"end_time":289.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.73,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Not everything we do is great.","index":67,"end_time":292.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":290.45,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And we have, it''s just like anything in a service business.","index":68,"end_time":297.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.81,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Sometimes we have challenges and we have turnover or whatever.","index":69,"end_time":301.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.41,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we have a customer, we had some turnover in their account.","index":70,"end_time":305.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.87,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They had a great experience with us for two years and then that two year period, it was two years as of about May of this year, earlier this year and from, I''d say June or July forward, we had about three or four months where it was really difficult and you know, it, they were, you know, there''s, I still don''t think they''re in a good place, but they''re, we''ve been working on improving that, making changes and I''ve met with them and, and they told us that, you know, things were great for two years and then they, they weren''t.","index":71,"end_time":345.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.27,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so we''re working to fix that.","index":72,"end_time":347.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.34,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And what I, and then in the, they hadn''t, they didn''t know me.","index":73,"end_time":352.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.86,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Just, you know, they didn''t, they.","index":74,"end_time":355.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I just wasn''t involved with this customer.","index":75,"end_time":358.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.7,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so I got involved in this retention moment and explained to them, you know, how we work and kinds of things we do and, and I got some insight on how they came to us.","index":76,"end_time":370.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.18,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They were a referral from a customer that had the CFO services at some point in the past and they asked about that because the meeting was going well.","index":77,"end_time":380.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.74,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They asked about the CFO services and I explained it to them and then I also told them that we''re kind of running a promotion for select customers, this 30 day scenario.","index":78,"end_time":394.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":380.43,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And they thought that sounded very interesting.","index":79,"end_time":396.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.35,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then I sent you know, as a follow up because I didn''t have any documentation.","index":80,"end_time":402.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.87,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I, you know, we have this campaign or whatever and I didn''t know where to, I could direct them to some of the collateral, but I had access to this, this mark markup IO interface that we use to edit.","index":81,"end_time":419.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.31,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, the offering.","index":82,"end_time":422.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.28,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I just went there and I pulled it out of there and did it, a PDF and I sent it to them.","index":83,"end_time":427,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It wasn''t the best but it worked.","index":84,"end_time":429.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":427.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And, and so we continue to talk about that.","index":85,"end_time":432.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I guess the first thing is it would be helpful to have kind of a PDF, a better version if that''s not too difficult.","index":86,"end_time":441.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.41,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I think in general what that showed me was it''s a little bit different scenario than we have when we''re going to people cold.","index":87,"end_time":453.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":442.05,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But the objective is the same thing.","index":88,"end_time":456.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.73,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s like build trust, remove friction.","index":89,"end_time":459.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.03,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And that''s what I was trying to do with that customer which was rebuild trust.","index":90,"end_time":467.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.95,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then to the extent that I could get them up and running on this 30 day scenario, that would be removing some of the friction of the recent past and our experience.","index":91,"end_time":479.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.99,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I was talking to Nick after the fact, I was like this 30 day scenario can be an effective approach for current customers that we want to upgrade or can be, if it''s applicable in this case, a retention tool.","index":92,"end_time":496.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.91,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Because when we find, when customers get to this stage, the more we leave them alone, the more they sort of are in this bad state and it sort of, it''s a self fulfilling sort of state, so to speak.","index":93,"end_time":512.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You know, they don''t feel, they''re not going to feel good unless there''s some kind of discussion, some change, they see progress.","index":94,"end_time":520.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.74,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So the CFO services in this case gives me an opportunity to get closer to the customer.","index":95,"end_time":527.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.82,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So it''s a, there''s a real incentive there for it to work and we''ve actually, as a result of this, Nick has put them into the pipeline and as a potential, you know, revenue stream.","index":96,"end_time":540.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":527.62,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Hopefully on the back, you know, they, they, after the 30 days they want to do something more long term, which would be the goal.","index":97,"end_time":547.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.1,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So yeah, you know, I think, yeah.","index":98,"end_time":550.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.66,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So what I''m finding is that there''s more to it than just the cold approach.","index":99,"end_time":555.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":550.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"There''s, there can be more.","index":100,"end_time":556.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.5,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I, I do see a lot of value in the 30 day scenario because it''s it''s a very personal service.","index":101,"end_time":565.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.7,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You know, have the cfo, you''re advising the owner and there is that get to know you period where they''re paying, you know, like the first or second month and there''s always this, oh, I''m paying, I''m not sure is this going to work, blah, blah, blah.","index":102,"end_time":582.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.51,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And by, by offering that 30 day period, it gives everybody more comfort.","index":103,"end_time":587.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.71,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You know, it''s, it allows us to sort of figure out exactly what the right fit is, structure that and then make sure everybody''s happy, there''s no pressure.","index":104,"end_time":599.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.91,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then in that second 30 day period, hopefully we''re better in a better situation to have a successful start.","index":105,"end_time":609.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":600.58,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s really great insight.","index":106,"end_time":614.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s definitely a lot easier to get a client to like retain or potentially upsell if they already have a relationship with you.","index":107,"end_time":624.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is that something that you want to explore doing more together or is that something just internally you''re going to want to focus on?","index":108,"end_time":633.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think if we have that PDF document, we can do that internally.","index":109,"end_time":638.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.1,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":110,"end_time":638.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":638.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, we know our customers, we know where it''s applicable and where it isn''t.","index":111,"end_time":645.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":639.7,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And now we would have this way to do it.","index":112,"end_time":648.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":645.4,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, and we can also decide, like, let''s just say we, we adjust the, the ABM approach or the campaign and all of a sudden we get a lot of inbound.","index":113,"end_time":660.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Then we would, you know, we don''t, we won''t necessarily approach customers to the extent, you know, we don''t want to be overloaded or whatever, but it does give us an option when the moment is right.","index":114,"end_time":674.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I think it was kind of a key moment for me, or light bulb moment was still.","index":115,"end_time":687.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":677.21,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The goal is to build trust.","index":116,"end_time":688.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.25,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s obviously easier to do that when you have a current customer and they''re happy.","index":117,"end_time":693.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":688.97,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You have a current customer and they''re not happy, you still need to build trust.","index":118,"end_time":697.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":694.09,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then if there''s somebody we don''t know, we need to build trust.","index":119,"end_time":702.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.11,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then, then stage two is getting them to commit to something is friction.","index":120,"end_time":709.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And when they don''t know us or they''re mad at us, that''s hard.","index":121,"end_time":712.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.11,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so if we can.","index":122,"end_time":715.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.869,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But the 30 day scenario kind of removes that and I think so that''s ideal because we''re willing to do that.","index":123,"end_time":724.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.15,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Coming back to what Tristan said is make it, make it like almost irresistible.","index":124,"end_time":731.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":724.11,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, I think you do that.","index":125,"end_time":732.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like once you have the trust by offering it free, it''s, it''s irresistible.","index":126,"end_time":737.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":732.9,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They''re like.","index":127,"end_time":738.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":737.86,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Because even if they trust you they''re like, well, I don''t know if I.","index":128,"end_time":741.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":738.5,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That''s going to work or.","index":129,"end_time":743.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Seems like a little bit more than I wanted to spend.","index":130,"end_time":746.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":743.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So, like, once the 30 day scenario allows them to enjoy it, see what it''s like.","index":131,"end_time":751.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.14,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And we don''t want to charge people that find out after 30 days that it''s not for them.","index":132,"end_time":757.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.12,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"If they were paying us, like, we don''t want them, we don''t want to misplace service.","index":133,"end_time":763.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":759.04,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like, that''s a bad place to be.","index":134,"end_time":765,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":763.52,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve had that scenario in the past and we don''t like that.","index":135,"end_time":769.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":765,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So that''s the beauty of it.","index":136,"end_time":772.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.52,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, it''s like.","index":137,"end_time":773.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":772.12,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we really need to.","index":138,"end_time":775.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.84,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, I think what you''ve done with the sequence is very good in terms of focusing on that trust through results.","index":139,"end_time":781.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I think we''re in good shape there.","index":140,"end_time":783.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":782.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The question is, how do we bring in the.","index":141,"end_time":786.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And what''s the right timing on the 30 day free scenario?","index":142,"end_time":790.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.16,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That''s.","index":143,"end_time":791.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I didn''t make any edits.","index":144,"end_time":793.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.88,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It was a little bit more than I wanted to discuss it.","index":145,"end_time":795.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":793.4,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You''d probably be a better idea on how to build that in there in terms of.","index":146,"end_time":799.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I probably Recommend like the 4th and 5th email.","index":147,"end_time":805.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So they''re towards the end, after they''ve seen a couple messages.","index":148,"end_time":809.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we could throw it in there a bit more firmly.","index":149,"end_time":813.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":150,"end_time":814.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":814.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then let me show you too.","index":151,"end_time":816.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nick, we also.","index":152,"end_time":819.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have you mentioned you had that PDF version.","index":153,"end_time":822,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We also have a webpage that you could send to your client.","index":154,"end_time":824.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I can send this link over after the call or I''ll.","index":155,"end_time":829.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I tried that because I''ve seen that link before.","index":156,"end_time":832.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":829.12,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t know if it says try.","index":157,"end_time":834.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Is there a gap between Try GSS lp?","index":158,"end_time":837.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.35,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Is there?","index":159,"end_time":838.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.11,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Again, there''s no space there because I try.","index":160,"end_time":842.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, there''s a dot.","index":161,"end_time":843.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":842.31,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I went to try gss.com.","index":162,"end_time":846.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":843.55,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":847.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":847.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And it took me to our website.","index":164,"end_time":850.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.19,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So let me see what happens if I do try.GSS.","index":165,"end_time":855.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.27,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"okay.","index":166,"end_time":858.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":857.79,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right.","index":167,"end_time":858.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I didn''t.","index":168,"end_time":859.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.96,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mistyped it.","index":169,"end_time":860.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.48,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So this is actually better than an attachment, I think.","index":170,"end_time":865.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t know if you.","index":171,"end_time":866.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I think this is better than sending a PDF.","index":172,"end_time":869.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":173,"end_time":870.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":869.64,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It definitely feels more like it''s a legit offer.","index":174,"end_time":874.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then they can also click on the.","index":175,"end_time":875.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, they can fill out their information here too.","index":176,"end_time":878.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this is a good user experience.","index":177,"end_time":881.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, this is fantastic.","index":178,"end_time":884.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":883.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I.","index":179,"end_time":885.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.76,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Unfortunately, I forgot the period or.","index":180,"end_time":887.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":885.6,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Good.","index":181,"end_time":888.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":182,"end_time":889.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.4,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we''re ready to go here.","index":183,"end_time":891,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"In fact, I think.","index":184,"end_time":891.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Because I''ve got to follow up with our.","index":185,"end_time":893.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.96,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Our customer.","index":186,"end_time":895,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":894.04,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Sort of that we''re in retention with.","index":187,"end_time":897.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":895.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And I''m going to re load.","index":188,"end_time":900.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I''m going to put this in the follow up as a.","index":189,"end_time":902.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":900.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"As a link.","index":190,"end_time":903.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":902.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":191,"end_time":904.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like it a lot.","index":192,"end_time":905.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.52,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":193,"end_time":905.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, this page turned out really, really well.","index":194,"end_time":908.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":195,"end_time":910.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":909.48,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":196,"end_time":913.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll make a couple updates then to the email sequence and then we should be able to get that rolling.","index":197,"end_time":919.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":913.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think let''s.","index":198,"end_time":921.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let''s try and aim to launch this new sequence sometime next week.","index":199,"end_time":925.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we''ll definitely want to wait till after Thanksgiving and we''ll send over those updates to make sure everything looks good to you before we send them over.","index":200,"end_time":935.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":201,"end_time":938.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.58,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But things seem to be doing decently well on Hayreach.","index":202,"end_time":944.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Still getting a lot of people accepting the connection requests.","index":203,"end_time":947.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And you''ve gotten a couple of replies as well.","index":204,"end_time":950.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, also want to update some of the messaging on LinkedIn as well when we relaunch the campaign.","index":205,"end_time":958.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any other questions or just thoughts on this?","index":206,"end_time":961.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":959.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":207,"end_time":964.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.67,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, then.","index":208,"end_time":967.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Our last super exciting update is that we have officially migrated all of the pages over to your new staging site.","index":209,"end_time":976.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So right now Guille and I and the entire team are going through and doing a QC check.","index":210,"end_time":982.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So making sure all the buttons work, that the pages are still looking really nice.","index":211,"end_time":989.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll go through and do all those checks internally first that.","index":212,"end_time":992.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we''ll send it over to you to do your final review and then we should be able to launch if.","index":213,"end_time":998.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, if everything''s going smoothly, we can launch that next week or maybe the week after that.","index":214,"end_time":1003.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We do recommend avoiding a Friday just because I can almost guarantee something''s going to go wrong like that something will need to be fixed.","index":215,"end_time":1013.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s just normal.","index":216,"end_time":1014.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if we can do it during the middle of the week, our team will be more available to fix this.","index":217,"end_time":1018.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll try and aim for like a Wednesday or a Thursday.","index":218,"end_time":1021.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1019.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But.","index":219,"end_time":1023.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":1023.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1023.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Any questions on this?","index":221,"end_time":1024.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":222,"end_time":1028.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1027.56,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I''m good too.","index":223,"end_time":1029.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.6,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":224,"end_time":1029.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1029.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re super excited.","index":225,"end_time":1031.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Our team was able to work really fast to get this all transferred over.","index":226,"end_time":1035.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":1036.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1036.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And so you''ll have to let me know in terms of like canceling the other system or the other setup with Duda, like when and all that.","index":228,"end_time":1051.049,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1036.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''ll.","index":229,"end_time":1052.569,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.449,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll let you know once we get the new site launched.","index":230,"end_time":1056.249,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.569,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You should be able just to cancel your Duda subscription.","index":231,"end_time":1061.209,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.369,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And.","index":232,"end_time":1062.409,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062.009,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we''ll also have a backup website so we keep.","index":233,"end_time":1066.249,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.529,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we have Everything hosted on WordPress for your live site, but we also will always have a backup because just stuff happens with websites.","index":234,"end_time":1076.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1066.489,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It just is a normal part of having a website.","index":235,"end_time":1079.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we''ll always have a backup if anything happens.","index":236,"end_time":1081.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":237,"end_time":1083.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.74,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, then just last thing, we''ll go ahead and take a look at your client portal.","index":238,"end_time":1090.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve got a ton of stuff and working right now.","index":239,"end_time":1095.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can see we''ve got 155 points in working, and a lot of that is just our monthly management tasks.","index":240,"end_time":1104.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we also are working on just updating that outreach sequence, working on several blogs and optimizations.","index":241,"end_time":1114.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I''m really excited again for the new site because there won''t be a limit to the number of blogs.","index":242,"end_time":1119.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we''re also working on doing an update to your accounting services pages from our last SEO review.","index":243,"end_time":1126.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That one just saw a little bit of downtick in traffic, so we''re going make some tweaks there.","index":244,"end_time":1130.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then you can see just planning on launching your website here soon and yeah, that''s pretty much everything.","index":245,"end_time":1137.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have any other questions?","index":246,"end_time":1138.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1137.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":247,"end_time":1140.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1140.23,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m all set too.","index":248,"end_time":1143.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.15,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":249,"end_time":1143.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1143.35,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":250,"end_time":1144.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, thanks for chatting.","index":251,"end_time":1145.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have a good day.","index":252,"end_time":1147.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1146.23,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You too.","index":253,"end_time":1147.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1147.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll see you.","index":254,"end_time":1148.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1147.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":255,"end_time":1149.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1148.79,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"}],"dateString":"2025-11-26T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83236942727?pwd=NaLGKm3JEGM6umJeSVS9pHPmDfNAYN.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nstauff@gsslp.com,wfleming@gsslp.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","nstauff@gsslp.com","wfleming@gsslp.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KAEFFPG29XJYZGZ39WC4XW5E","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed new blog post and malware episode are in production; publishing targeted for next week.","Will emphasized reframing ABM campaign to build trust before offering free 30-day trial.","Identified 30-day trial as effective for both retention and upsell with current clients.","Validated landing page is preferred over PDF for client outreach; follow-up link deployment planned.","Completed full migration to new staging site; final QC in progress for launch post-Thanksgiving."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The goal is to build trust...then stage two is getting them to commit to something is friction.","speaker":"Will Fleming"},{"quote":"We officially migrated all of the pages over to your new staging site.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"So we''re ready to go here...going to put this in the follow up as a link.","speaker":"Will Fleming"}],"topics":["abm","retention","content","launch"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-28T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content and Publishing Strategy**\n\nThe team is advancing key content projects to enhance operational efficiency messaging and maintain engagement momentum.\n\n- **A new blog post titled \"Building your finance function: The 103050 unit evolution\" is in progress, with an interview scheduled with Will Fleming to shape narrative and outline** (01:13)  \n    - This post supports the broader theme of operational efficiencies emphasized across content.  \n    - The episode on malware readiness is ready for scheduling, with a tentative publish window set for next week.  \n    - Guille Santana will coordinate all supporting assets once the publish date is confirmed.  \n    - These content efforts aim to drive thought leadership and nurture prospects aligned with service offerings.\n\n- **The expanded content capacity from the new website removes previous blog limits, enabling more frequent updates and SEO-driven optimizations** (18:05)  \n    - The team is preparing adjustments to the accounting services pages to counteract recent traffic decline identified in the latest SEO review.  \n    - This ongoing content refresh is designed to bolster organic search performance and client engagement.  \n    - Monthly management tasks and outreach sequence updates remain active priorities feeding into these content efforts.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) and Client Engagement**\n\nABM messaging is being refined to emphasize trust-building through results before presenting offers, with Will Fleming stressing its value for both cold prospects and current client retention.\n\n- **Will Fleming endorsed the revised email sequence that delays the free 30-day offer to build rapport based on results first** (02:45)  \n    - Leading with the free offer risks seeming like a cheap ploy, so sequencing focuses first on trust and results.  \n    - The 30-day free trial is positioned as a “no friction” way for prospects or clients to experience the service and gain comfort.  \n    - This approach is intended to reduce cost hesitation and uncertainty, key barriers in client acquisition.  \n    - Baylee Gunnell suggested placing the free offer around the 4th or 5th email to maximize its impact after trust is established.\n\n- **Will shared lessons from a challenging client retention case where the 30-day free offer acted as a tool to rebuild trust and upgrade existing clients** (04:27)  \n    - The client had enjoyed two years of good service before issues arose due to turnover, causing dissatisfaction.  \n    - Will’s direct involvement and explanation of CFO services, coupled with offering the 30-day free trial, re-engaged the client effectively.  \n    - Nick has since moved this client into the sales pipeline as a potential long-term revenue source.  \n    - This case reveals the 30-day free offer’s dual role in both new client acquisition and retention/upsell strategies.\n\n- **Will requested a professionally formatted PDF or collateral to support client conversations, but prefers linking to the live webpage \"try.GSS.com\" as a better user experience than attachments** (13:34)  \n    - The webpage allows clients to submit their information directly, improving ease of engagement.  \n    - Baylee confirmed plans to send this link post-call for Will’s follow-up use.  \n    - This digital asset enhances the credibility and accessibility of the 30-day offer.  \n    - Streamlining collateral supports sales efficiency and client responsiveness.\n\n- **The team plans to launch the updated ABM email sequence next week, post-Thanksgiving, pending final review and approval from Will** (15:12)  \n    - The timing avoids holiday disruptions and ensures readiness for optimal engagement.  \n    - LinkedIn messaging tied to the campaign will also be refreshed before relaunch.  \n    - Early results from LinkedIn outreach show good connection acceptance and some replies, supporting positive momentum.\n\n## **Website Migration and Infrastructure**\n\nThe website migration to a new WordPress staging environment is complete, with quality control underway and a planned midweek launch to ensure smooth transition.\n\n- **All pages have migrated to the new staging site, with the team performing detailed QC to check functionality and design** (16:05)  \n    - Internal reviews focus on button functionality and page appearance consistency before client review.  \n    - The launch is targeted for a Wednesday or Thursday to ensure immediate support and quick fixes if needed.  \n    - Baylee emphasized avoiding Friday launches due to higher risk of unresolved issues over the weekend.  \n    - The team’s swift execution reflects strong operational capability.\n\n- **Once the new site launches, Baylee confirmed the client can cancel the existing Duda subscription with confidence, as WordPress hosting includes a backup site** (17:16)  \n    - Backup ensures website availability despite routine technical issues, reducing operational risk.  \n    - This infrastructure upgrade centralizes hosting and aligns with long-term stability goals.  \n    - Clear communication on cancellation timing will follow launch confirmation to avoid service gaps.\n\n## **Client Portal and Workflow Transparency**\n\nThe client portal provides detailed visibility into ongoing tasks and projects, supporting transparency and prioritization.\n\n- **Currently, the portal shows 155 active points, primarily monthly management tasks along with outreach sequence updates and multiple blog optimizations** (18:05)  \n    - This volume reflects steady operational throughput supporting marketing and product initiatives.  \n    - The portal helps clients track progress and understand resource allocation in real time.  \n    - It also facilitates collaboration on SEO tweaks and upcoming website launch activities.  \n    - Maintaining this visibility supports client trust and smooth project management.\n\n## **Strategic Insights on Service Positioning and Customer Relationships**\n\nThe discussion highlighted the importance of trust and personalized service in overcoming friction in client acquisition and retention.\n\n- **Will Fleming explained the CFO service’s personal advisory role helps reduce hesitation during initial engagement and first payment months** (09:42)  \n    - The 30-day free period allows clients to experience value risk-free, increasing commitment likelihood.  \n    - This approach prevents dissatisfied clients from paying unnecessarily, protecting company reputation.  \n    - The trial period also helps tailor the service fit and structure for long-term success.  \n    - These insights shape the marketing and sales approach to emphasize trust and fit over hard selling.\n\n- **Will emphasized that trust-building is harder but equally critical with unhappy current clients and unknown prospects, making the 30-day offer a key friction remover in both cases** (10:34)  \n    - The offer is designed to be “almost irresistible,” turning trust into trial without pressure.  \n    - This philosophy underpins the ABM messaging strategy and client retention efforts.  \n    - The team recognizes that removing cost and commitment barriers early accelerates positive outcomes.  \n    - Such positioning differentiates the service in a competitive market focused on personalized CFO support.","outline":null,"keywords":["Content Updates","ABM Email Sequence","30-Day CFO Offer","Client Retention","Website Migration","LinkedIn Outreach"],"overview":"- **Content Strategy Update:** New blog post on finance functions is underway, plus upcoming malware readiness episode scheduled for next week.\n\n- **SEO Enhancements:** Website migration enables frequent updates; revamps for accounting pages aim to improve declining traffic.\n\n- **ABM Messaging Refinement:** Revised email sequence emphasizes trust before free offers; trial strategically placed for maximum impact.\n\n- **Website Launch Timing:** Migration to new WordPress site is complete; launch planned midweek to avoid weekend issues with immediate support.\n\n- **Client Portal Insights:** 155 active project points are highlighted in the portal, enhancing transparency and client engagement.\n\n- **Trust-Building Focus:** Personalized CFO services and a free trial help alleviate client hesitations, aiding both acquisition and retention strategies.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nFinalize and send updated ABM email sequence incorporating feedback and new 30-day offer timing; target launch next week post-Thanksgiving (15:12)\nShare link to ''try.GSS'' webpage with Will for client communication use (14:30)\nComplete website quality control check on new staging site and coordinate final client review before launch (16:05)\nNotify Will Fleming about Duda subscription cancellation timing after new site launch (17:10)\nContinue updates on outreach sequences, blog posts, and SEO optimizations in client portal (18:05)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nProvide input and participate in interview shaping blog post narrative for ''Building your finance function. The 103050 unit evolution.'' (01:13)\nUtilize ''try.GSS'' landing page in retention follow-ups with current clients and send link in client follow-ups (14:30)\nCoordinate internally to apply 30-day CFO service offer with current clients as retention or upsell tool using provided collateral (07:59)\nReview and confirm acceptance of ABM email sequence updates once shared prior to launch (15:12)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nAssist in publishing content updates including malware episode scheduling (01:56)\nSupport internal QC and website migration verification processes (16:05)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"27cacf3a-6b6c-4eda-9ca6-6a7036579b78","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
