-- Meeting: New North x Planon Weekly Meeting (2025-11-20 15:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ff2ef389-756d-4ece-b525-93fab32170d6',
    '2025-11-20 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KABZDPRNW2TW4YKNE8B475KQ',
    'New North x Planon Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Taylor Doerbaum","Lauren Poirier","Baylee Gunnell"}'::text[],
    774,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1',
    '{"id":"01KABZDPRNW2TW4YKNE8B475KQ","title":"New North x Planon Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Budget Adjustments**\n\nThe team decided to pause the ABM campaign temporarily and lower the budget while preparing for a relaunch.\n\n- **The ABM campaign budget will be reduced to 50% of the usual spend, charging only 5,000 points instead of the full 10,000 points this month** as Taylor Doerbaum explained to manage costs during the pause (03:45)\n    - The goal is to gather better audience data before fully restarting the campaign.\n    - Taylor emphasized maintaining the current sequence to continue learning from the audience once the campaign resumes.\n    - The pause reflects a strategic move to optimize spend efficiency and data quality before scaling.\n    - This adjustment will prevent overspending while keeping the campaign infrastructure ready to restart promptly.\n\n- **The team agreed to discontinue using AdRoll and redirect the monthly spend of $1,750 to other channels, pending confirmation from Merit** (03:45)\n    - Lauren Poirier is awaiting Merit’s approval before finalizing this budget reallocation.\n    - This decision stems from a review of channel effectiveness and aims to improve ROI on ad spend.\n    - Once approved, paid media specialists will be briefed to implement the new spend plan.\n    - Switching away from AdRoll will simplify campaign management and focus resources on higher-impact platforms.\n\n## **Creative Asset Updates and Brand Compliance**\n\nAdjustments to ad creative and brand assets will be carefully managed to align with brand guidelines and improve campaign effectiveness.\n\n- **The team confirmed that the black logo variant, previously used in ads, is in the brand guidelines but is not commonly applied, so they will seek feedback from Roderick before deciding on its future use** as Lauren Poirier noted (04:45)\n    - Lauren emphasized sticking to the primary logo with green art and the circle when possible to maintain brand consistency.\n    - Taylor highlighted occasional creative needs to use simpler logo colors for better visual blending.\n    - The final decision will depend on Roderick’s input to ensure brand alignment.\n    - This review aims to avoid visual conflicts that could weaken brand recognition.\n\n- **Taylor committed to updating the ad copy text on images based on Lauren’s feedback and sending revised versions for final approval before broader deployment** (05:40)\n    - Copy changes will be made promptly to correct link errors and improve messaging.\n    - This step-by-step approach ensures quality control and minimizes rework.\n    - Lauren confirmed no major design issues were found beyond copy corrections.\n    - This process will help accelerate the campaign relaunch with accurate assets.\n\n- **Webpage graphics were delivered to Lauren to finalize page readiness, with assets already updated on Showpad, enabling the team to proceed with relaunch preparations** (12:00)\n    - This milestone signals near completion of creative asset readiness.\n    - The updated graphics support a cohesive brand experience across digital touchpoints.\n    - Lauren confirmed all necessary materials are in place to go live.\n    - This coordination ensures no delays once the campaign restarts.\n\n## **Video Animation Revisions and Production Challenges**\n\nThe design team requested specific changes to video animations that will require balancing creative intent with technical feasibility and budget constraints.\n\n- **The design team requires adding facial expressions to characters and adjusting organic background colors to more natural tones for better viewer connection, as Lauren Poirier explained** (07:15)\n    - Facial expressions are seen as essential to making animations feel personal and engaging.\n    - Natural colors for buildings and backgrounds aim to enhance visual realism.\n    - The logo should remain static on screen throughout the video rather than appearing and disappearing.\n    - These changes reflect a shift toward more polished and audience-friendly content.\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell highlighted significant technical challenges in retrofitting facial expressions onto already completed animations, noting it may be difficult or costly** (09:30)\n    - The animations were originally created with faceless characters, making changes complex.\n    - Some elements like background color changes and static logos are easier to implement.\n    - The team plans to consult the creative director for feasibility and cost estimates.\n    - Lauren offered to check budget flexibility for extra costs before approving changes.\n\n- **The team will prepare static screen samples of proposed changes to get precise feedback from the design team before final animation work, ensuring alignment and reducing rework** (08:40)\n    - This approach will clarify expectations and confirm the exact nature of requested changes.\n    - It aims to avoid costly revisions after animation is finalized.\n    - Lauren will coordinate feedback cycles to keep the process efficient.\n    - This step balances creative quality with practical production constraints.\n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Communication Protocol**\n\nThe team agreed on flexible meeting scheduling around the Thanksgiving holiday to maintain project momentum without overburdening participants.\n\n- **The upcoming meeting originally set for Thanksgiving will be tentatively moved to Tuesday, allowing the team to adjust based on workload and preference, as agreed by Lauren and Taylor** (02:55)\n    - This change respects holiday plans while preserving communication opportunities.\n    - The team will decide closer to the date whether the meeting is needed or can be replaced with Slack updates.\n    - Taylor will send a calendar link with availability options to finalize timing.\n    - This flexibility supports work-life balance while keeping projects on track.\n\n- **Taylor offered to provide status updates via Slack or Teams if live meetings are inconvenient during the holiday period** (02:55)\n    - This alternative keeps stakeholders informed without requiring synchronous meetings.\n    - It supports asynchronous collaboration during busy or personal times.\n    - Lauren welcomed this approach as a backup communication method.\n    - This protocol ensures continuous progress even with limited live interaction.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","animation feedback","AdRoll discontinuation","logo guidelines","video updates","Thanksgiving scheduling"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Adjustments:** Budget reduced to 50%, from 10,000 to 5,000 points, to improve data quality before relaunch.\n\n- **AdRoll Discontinuation:** Monthly $1,750 redirected pending Merit’s approval, aiming for better ROI and streamlined campaign management.\n\n- **Creative Asset Updates:** Black logo use will be reviewed for brand compliance; focus on primary logo for consistency.\n\n- **Video Animation Changes:** Requested revisions include facial expressions and natural colors; feasibility and costs to be assessed.\n\n- **Flexible Meeting Scheduling:** Thanksgiving meeting moved to Tuesday to respect holiday plans, with Slack updates as an alternative.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend meeting availability link for rescheduled session on Tuesday and adjust calendar invites accordingly (03:33)\nImplement requested copy changes on ad images and send updated versions back to Lauren for review (06:50)\nCommunicate with Lauren once video update samples are ready for approval and incorporate any further feedback (11:22)\nUpon receiving final confirmation from Merit regarding email, forward all relevant data to paid media specialists to setup new campaigns (11:50)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum & Baylee Gunnell**\nConsult with creative director regarding feasibility and costs of adding facial expressions and other animation changes; report findings back (09:35)\n\n**Lauren Poirier**\nCoordinate with Roderick to clarify logo usage guidelines and provide official direction to marketing team (05:04)\nReview updated ad copies and artwork once submitted; provide feedback if further adjustments are needed (06:39)\nMonitor budget and potential additional costs related to animation changes and communicate limits to vendor team (11:03)\n"},"duration":12.899999618530273,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey there.","index":0,"end_time":4.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you?","index":1,"end_time":6.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":7.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you?","index":3,"end_time":8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.44,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I like your sweater.","index":4,"end_time":8.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":5,"end_time":10.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s finally starting to feel a little like a change of season here.","index":6,"end_time":13.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m like.","index":7,"end_time":14.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, how warm is it there now?","index":8,"end_time":17.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s probably going to be like 70 still today.","index":9,"end_time":20.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But it''s normally like in 90s, so I''m happy with the 70.","index":10,"end_time":25.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And there''s like actual clouds.","index":11,"end_time":26.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Um, so it''s nice.","index":12,"end_time":28.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s like a cozy day, which I love those.","index":13,"end_time":30.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Don''t get them all here.","index":14,"end_time":32.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you''re up in Boston, is that right?","index":15,"end_time":35.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Close.","index":16,"end_time":37.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":36.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m in Rhode Island.","index":17,"end_time":37.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":18,"end_time":39.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It must be so beautiful up there in the fall.","index":19,"end_time":41.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It is.","index":20,"end_time":42.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Fall is really, really great.","index":21,"end_time":44.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":22,"end_time":44.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s getting to the point now where it''s like 35 as the high.","index":23,"end_time":49.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":49.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, I missed the sun.","index":25,"end_time":51.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":52.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m from Buffalo, New York so I grew up with that.","index":27,"end_time":55.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My mom and dad keep sending me that too.","index":28,"end_time":57.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They''re like it''s 30.","index":29,"end_time":58.136,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"30 degrees here.","index":30,"end_time":58.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.164,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":31,"end_time":59.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":59.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s already snowed there this year.","index":33,"end_time":61.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":34,"end_time":61.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You always want what you can''t have.","index":35,"end_time":63.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right?","index":36,"end_time":63.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like I know old.","index":37,"end_time":65.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I want the 70 degree weather.","index":38,"end_time":67.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly.","index":39,"end_time":68.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s always how it goes.","index":40,"end_time":70.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you have anything fun planned for Thanksgiving?","index":41,"end_time":71.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nothing out of the ordinary.","index":42,"end_time":75.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just having dinner with my family and my husband''s family and.","index":43,"end_time":78.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.25,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Nice.","index":44,"end_time":79.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":79.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just the normal stuff.","index":46,"end_time":81.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Nothing crazy.","index":47,"end_time":82.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.25,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They do have up in Boston.","index":48,"end_time":83.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s called Snowport.","index":49,"end_time":85.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s in.","index":50,"end_time":86.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":85.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s in the Seaport district.","index":51,"end_time":87.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They have like a bunch of vendors outside side and they have food trucks and all sorts of like artsy.","index":52,"end_time":94.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s like a semi permanent structure where the vendors set up.","index":53,"end_time":97.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''m gonna go up with my sister and her boyfriend and explore that.","index":54,"end_time":102.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So.","index":55,"end_time":103.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":56,"end_time":104.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.23,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s awesome, you guys.","index":57,"end_time":105.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":58,"end_time":106.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My family''s actually going to be driving down from New York, so.","index":59,"end_time":110.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whoa.","index":60,"end_time":111.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":61,"end_time":111.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":111.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":62,"end_time":112.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My parents are actually moving down here to Texas.","index":63,"end_time":114.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m really excited about that.","index":64,"end_time":116.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So my sister is going to come with them and they''ll be here for Thanksgiving.","index":65,"end_time":120.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":66,"end_time":122.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are they doing that to be close to you?","index":67,"end_time":124.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":68,"end_time":125.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Their house just finished up construction, so I''m excited.","index":69,"end_time":129.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, that''s awesome.","index":70,"end_time":130.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''ll be fun.","index":71,"end_time":132.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nice.","index":72,"end_time":133.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.43,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Doing anything fun, Bailey.","index":73,"end_time":135.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":136.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re going up to see family.","index":75,"end_time":137.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We.","index":76,"end_time":138.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We were gonna just do stuff by ourselves because we have the dogs and we couldn''t find anywhere to stay because it''s like a three hour drive.","index":77,"end_time":148.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":138.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But they said that we could just leave them in their backyard.","index":78,"end_time":152.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":149.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that was very nice.","index":79,"end_time":153.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":152.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That last minute they called us and they''re like, don''t not come because you don''t have a place for your dog.","index":80,"end_time":157.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":153.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that was very nice of them.","index":81,"end_time":159.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":157.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":82,"end_time":161.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We got all the cousins.","index":83,"end_time":163.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":162.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Everyone gonna be there, so that''s fun.","index":84,"end_time":166.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":163.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s gonna be crazy.","index":85,"end_time":167.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":166.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":86,"end_time":168.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":87,"end_time":168.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My dogs are running around right now too.","index":88,"end_time":169.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''re always fun to watch on calls like running around.","index":89,"end_time":172.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, they got energy right now.","index":90,"end_time":175.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I love it.","index":91,"end_time":176.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know our next meeting is on Thanksgiving, so we can do it on Wednesday or Tuesday or if you would rather just get like a Slack update, whatever works for you.","index":92,"end_time":187.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you want to just let us know.","index":93,"end_time":188.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll cancel that one.","index":94,"end_time":190.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if you want to meet Wednesday or something, we can do that or we can just keep in touch through teams.","index":95,"end_time":195.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whatever''s easiest for you.","index":96,"end_time":196.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s tentatively move it to Tuesday at some point.","index":97,"end_time":202.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That works for you?","index":98,"end_time":203.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I mean, all day.","index":99,"end_time":204.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then if we decide we don''t need it, we can be in touch and always cancel it.","index":100,"end_time":209.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":101,"end_time":209.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":102,"end_time":210.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll send you a link with our availability for that day.","index":103,"end_time":213.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":104,"end_time":214.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":105,"end_time":215.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":106,"end_time":216.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, I know we have a few things to cover.","index":107,"end_time":219.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I was reading through your Slack messages this morning, but I just wanted to touch base first here on some ABM updates.","index":108,"end_time":225.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just want to let you know, because we paused the campaign and we''ve only been, you know, managing a couple of different things, we''re not going to charge a full 1010 points this month like we normally would, so we''ll only charge the five until we get that geared back up.","index":109,"end_time":239.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just wanted to let you know about that.","index":110,"end_time":241.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I know we''re going to keep the current sequence and learn the audience more once we have it running a little longer since we haven''t been able to get good data back yet.","index":111,"end_time":251.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I know we''ve been going back and forth about AdRoll, so we''re not going to use that anymore.","index":112,"end_time":256.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I just want to confirm that we''re going to switch that monthly spend to 1750.","index":113,"end_time":260.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think you might be waiting on merit, so go ahead.","index":114,"end_time":262.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just as far as the email, so we can just wait to hear confirmation.","index":115,"end_time":266.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":116,"end_time":268.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":267.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then as far as the ad copy and images I went through, I know you responded to the black logo this morning, so I just want to make sure we did have that one in the folder and so that''s why we used it.","index":117,"end_time":279.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So is this something we should avoid in the future or.","index":118,"end_time":283.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I think it was also in the brand guidelines.","index":119,"end_time":286.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, doc, it is.","index":120,"end_time":287.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it''s a good.","index":121,"end_time":289.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Definitely A good call out.","index":122,"end_time":290.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I. I don''t see it used very much.","index":123,"end_time":296.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.66,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''m kind of curious what Roderick says.","index":124,"end_time":298.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think this might be one of those.","index":125,"end_time":300.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You''ve probably noticed there''s some things that are a little wishy washy.","index":126,"end_time":303.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.82,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":304.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":304.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That we do and don''t do.","index":128,"end_time":305.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I feel like this might be one of those things.","index":129,"end_time":308.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.98,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''ll run it on him and see what he says.","index":130,"end_time":310.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.1,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think generally, if we can, we should try to stick to our normal logo with green art, the circle.","index":131,"end_time":318.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.26,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But we''ll see what he says.","index":132,"end_time":321.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, we try to use that one as much as possible.","index":133,"end_time":323.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"There''s a couple times we do like a different design and it doesn''t like blend as well.","index":134,"end_time":328.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It kind of like looks awkward up there.","index":135,"end_time":329.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we try to use like a more basic color.","index":136,"end_time":332.849,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if, if it is preferred to just do this one, then we can just use this always moving forward.","index":137,"end_time":337.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.849,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":138,"end_time":338.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll see what he says.","index":139,"end_time":339.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.65,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m curious too, because.","index":140,"end_time":341.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I really know.","index":141,"end_time":342.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So.","index":142,"end_time":344.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":143,"end_time":345.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And the feedback that you left in the copy document too, those are super easy changes to implement as far as on the images.","index":144,"end_time":351.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if you''d prefer, I can just go ahead and switch out the text on the images and send them back to you.","index":145,"end_time":356.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if you want to run it by Rodrick, besides that logo, was there anything else that you saw that you wanted change as far as the imagery or just the copy?","index":146,"end_time":365.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we can go ahead and send that back to you.","index":147,"end_time":367.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just the copy.","index":148,"end_time":369.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.99,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t think there was anything design wise that stood out to me.","index":149,"end_time":372.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The only thing was I think the last round looked like it was the.","index":150,"end_time":378.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Wrong one linked, it was linking to the wrong one.","index":151,"end_time":381.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can switch that out.","index":152,"end_time":382.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":153,"end_time":383.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A couple times when we switch out the links in Google, it''s.","index":154,"end_time":386.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It should be going to the right one and for some reason it defaults and sometimes shows an error.","index":155,"end_time":390.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s best to just clear it out completely.","index":156,"end_time":393.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":157,"end_time":393.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can swap that out.","index":158,"end_time":394.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s just go ahead and switch the copy and then we''ll send that over to him.","index":159,"end_time":398.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So one step at a time.","index":160,"end_time":399.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, definitely.","index":161,"end_time":400.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We will get, get on that.","index":162,"end_time":402.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then also the social update designs you sent over to, those are in progress.","index":163,"end_time":407.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":403.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just wanted to let you know about that.","index":164,"end_time":409.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I just wanted to pull up your message.","index":165,"end_time":412.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll just go off of this for.","index":166,"end_time":414.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I hate when it signs me out.","index":167,"end_time":417.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This has been happening so much lately to me.","index":168,"end_time":420.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whatever.","index":169,"end_time":421.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":170,"end_time":421.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t need it.","index":171,"end_time":422.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":172,"end_time":424.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just want to Go through your feedback.","index":173,"end_time":425.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we wanted to talk through this for the video.","index":174,"end_time":428.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So excited to get these back for the updates.","index":175,"end_time":433.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you said there''s, like, a difference between what''s nice to have and things that we want to change.","index":176,"end_time":439.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you want to just walk through the specifics?","index":177,"end_time":441.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":178,"end_time":442.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So this was our design team''s feedback, and basically it sounds like the facial expressions we have to change.","index":179,"end_time":451.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.31,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"He said they don''t have facial expressions.","index":180,"end_time":455.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''re only using characters with facial expressions to make it more personal.","index":181,"end_time":458.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think if we can somehow add just like, eyes, basic mouth, nose kind of thing.","index":182,"end_time":466.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It sounds like that''s important to them that we add natural colors.","index":183,"end_time":472.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think that''s mostly just like, if there''s a building that''s pink or orange, like, they want it to be a.","index":184,"end_time":479.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.65,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like a more realistic color for the buildings.","index":185,"end_time":482.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then the organic background shapes, I.","index":186,"end_time":485.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Think that''s just like this.","index":187,"end_time":487.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":188,"end_time":487.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The swaths of color.","index":189,"end_time":489.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.91,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think if we just make the whole wall the color, I think that should solve that problem.","index":190,"end_time":493.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then the static logo.","index":191,"end_time":497.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":495.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"At one point, I guess the logo pops up and then it kind of recedes again.","index":192,"end_time":501.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And they just want it to be there the whole time.","index":193,"end_time":503.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So if there''s any.","index":194,"end_time":506.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know there''s some nuance here.","index":195,"end_time":508.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.31,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So if there''s anything that your team''s not sure about, if you want to send over, like, a static, you know, screen of what they''ve changed, I can run that by our team to ensure, like, this is exactly what they''re talking about.","index":196,"end_time":522.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.23,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":197,"end_time":523.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":198,"end_time":524.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Before animating it just for, like, this one.","index":199,"end_time":526.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, like, for this, it looks like, you know, it''s the shadow under the table.","index":200,"end_time":530.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, the light''s not hitting it, but they''re saying that they want the light to hit it.","index":201,"end_time":535.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know if that''s what he means.","index":202,"end_time":538.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"He said they look a bit off visually.","index":203,"end_time":540.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like the legs.","index":204,"end_time":541.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.99,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s that they''re not touching the ground that he doesn''t like.","index":205,"end_time":545.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t personally have a problem with that.","index":206,"end_time":547.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And.","index":207,"end_time":548.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.04,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":208,"end_time":549.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s not in the must dos, so I think we can leave that alone.","index":209,"end_time":553.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.44,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":210,"end_time":554.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":211,"end_time":555.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just the facial expressions, I think, are the only thing about the people that they want us to change, which I.","index":212,"end_time":564.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s really unfortunate because I know that we''ve built out the full animation and it''s more work now to change all this.","index":213,"end_time":570.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So, yeah, these are going to be pretty hard to change.","index":214,"end_time":574.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":571.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":215,"end_time":575.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Especially, like, because we went through that whole storyboard and all those designs and stuff.","index":216,"end_time":582.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":576.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Were they pulled in at all during that storyboard phase.","index":217,"end_time":586.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They weren''t.","index":218,"end_time":587.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No.","index":219,"end_time":588.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think Pauline had wanted to engage them only when we had to, but in hindsight, we really should have pulled them in at that point.","index":220,"end_time":596.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":598.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, we''ll have to talk to our creative director to see which of these things are possible.","index":222,"end_time":602.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, Taylor and I, we don''t do these animations, so I don''t know the nitty gritty details, but I think some of these are going to be pretty tricky to change, but we''ll chat with them and see what''s possible.","index":223,"end_time":617.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think some of these things probably, like the backgrounds like that, those things should be pretty easy.","index":224,"end_time":623.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I''m worried about facial expressions because literally all of the animations are just faceless people.","index":225,"end_time":629.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So adding those in afterwards, I.","index":226,"end_time":632.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":629.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That, that''s one I''m.","index":227,"end_time":633.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":632.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think is going to be pretty hard to do.","index":228,"end_time":635.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":229,"end_time":635.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.46,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Static logo, that should be easy.","index":230,"end_time":637.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Some of these should be pretty reasonable.","index":231,"end_time":640.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah, we''ll.","index":232,"end_time":641.859,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll chat and see what we can figure out.","index":233,"end_time":643.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.859,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":234,"end_time":644.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.98,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If there''s something that you''re like, look, this is going to be an extra X amount of money to change or whatever it is, let me know and I''ll go back team, and hopefully there''s a little bit of wiggle room where my hope is that they''ll say, like, oh, no, don''t spend, you know, extra money.","index":235,"end_time":659.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":644.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just change what you can.","index":236,"end_time":661.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":659.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''ll see if that''s what they say.","index":237,"end_time":663.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":661.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":238,"end_time":664.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I really hope.","index":239,"end_time":665.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But yeah, okay.","index":240,"end_time":668.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll.","index":241,"end_time":668.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll chat and figure out what we can do there.","index":242,"end_time":671.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":668.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":243,"end_time":672.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thank you for your flexibility.","index":244,"end_time":674.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":672.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know it''s frustrating.","index":245,"end_time":676.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It is for me, too.","index":246,"end_time":677.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":676.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll.","index":247,"end_time":679.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll figure something out.","index":248,"end_time":681.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":249,"end_time":682.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll send that back and I''ll get back to you as soon as we do hear back about that.","index":250,"end_time":686.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But happy to have the feedback, though.","index":251,"end_time":688.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know you''ve been waiting on that.","index":252,"end_time":689.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s in progress for you.","index":253,"end_time":693.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":254,"end_time":694.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I will let you know when we send that back to the team.","index":255,"end_time":697.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":256,"end_time":698.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, as far as next steps, then for abm, I know that''s our priority.","index":257,"end_time":703.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ll get those implemented, the changes into the images, and then I''ll send those back over to you.","index":258,"end_time":708.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then whenever we get confirmation from Merit, I''ll send all of that data over or information over to our paid media specialists and get everything set up there so we can get rolling.","index":259,"end_time":718.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I know we''ll have to relaunch and stuff like that, so.","index":260,"end_time":722.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":261,"end_time":723.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":722.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And I know you sent over the webpage graphics today.","index":262,"end_time":726.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think that''s the last thing I need to get those pages live again.","index":263,"end_time":729.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then I''ve already replaced the assets on Showpad, so we''re good to go there and then.","index":264,"end_time":737.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I think from there, we''ll just.","index":265,"end_time":740.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''ll be ready.","index":266,"end_time":740.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.02,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":267,"end_time":742.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re excited to relaunch.","index":268,"end_time":743.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know.","index":269,"end_time":744.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Me, too.","index":270,"end_time":745.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I keep telling people, like, very soon, we''re launching an ABM campaign, and they''re probably thinking.","index":271,"end_time":750.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.1,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You''ve been saying that for months.","index":272,"end_time":751.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":273,"end_time":754.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''ll be good when we get it rolling.","index":274,"end_time":755.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":275,"end_time":757.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.3,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":276,"end_time":758.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Well, I hope you have a good rest of your week and a good weekend, and I''ll be in touch about our meeting change time.","index":277,"end_time":764.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":278,"end_time":765.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you both.","index":279,"end_time":766.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":280,"end_time":767.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Bye.","index":281,"end_time":768.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"dateString":"2025-11-20T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KABZDPRNW2TW4YKNE8B475KQ","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Aligned on ABM campaign relaunch; billing reduced this month due to reduced activity.","Confirmed $1,750 monthly spend shift away from AdRoll pending Merit’s email confirmation.","Agreed to update ad copy and swap imagery based on reviewed feedback and brand guidance.","Reviewed animation revisions; facial expressions change flagged as difficult but being evaluated.","Next ABM steps include implementing image edits and relaunch upon feedback and access confirmation."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''re excited to relaunch.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"We''ll chat and see what we can figure out.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"Just the facial expressions, I think, are the only thing about the people that they want us to change.","speaker":"Lauren Poirier"}],"topics":["delivery","budget","creative","feedback"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Budget Adjustments**\n\nThe team decided to pause the ABM campaign temporarily and lower the budget while preparing for a relaunch.\n\n- **The ABM campaign budget will be reduced to 50% of the usual spend, charging only 5,000 points instead of the full 10,000 points this month** as Taylor Doerbaum explained to manage costs during the pause (03:45)\n    - The goal is to gather better audience data before fully restarting the campaign.\n    - Taylor emphasized maintaining the current sequence to continue learning from the audience once the campaign resumes.\n    - The pause reflects a strategic move to optimize spend efficiency and data quality before scaling.\n    - This adjustment will prevent overspending while keeping the campaign infrastructure ready to restart promptly.\n\n- **The team agreed to discontinue using AdRoll and redirect the monthly spend of $1,750 to other channels, pending confirmation from Merit** (03:45)\n    - Lauren Poirier is awaiting Merit’s approval before finalizing this budget reallocation.\n    - This decision stems from a review of channel effectiveness and aims to improve ROI on ad spend.\n    - Once approved, paid media specialists will be briefed to implement the new spend plan.\n    - Switching away from AdRoll will simplify campaign management and focus resources on higher-impact platforms.\n\n## **Creative Asset Updates and Brand Compliance**\n\nAdjustments to ad creative and brand assets will be carefully managed to align with brand guidelines and improve campaign effectiveness.\n\n- **The team confirmed that the black logo variant, previously used in ads, is in the brand guidelines but is not commonly applied, so they will seek feedback from Roderick before deciding on its future use** as Lauren Poirier noted (04:45)\n    - Lauren emphasized sticking to the primary logo with green art and the circle when possible to maintain brand consistency.\n    - Taylor highlighted occasional creative needs to use simpler logo colors for better visual blending.\n    - The final decision will depend on Roderick’s input to ensure brand alignment.\n    - This review aims to avoid visual conflicts that could weaken brand recognition.\n\n- **Taylor committed to updating the ad copy text on images based on Lauren’s feedback and sending revised versions for final approval before broader deployment** (05:40)\n    - Copy changes will be made promptly to correct link errors and improve messaging.\n    - This step-by-step approach ensures quality control and minimizes rework.\n    - Lauren confirmed no major design issues were found beyond copy corrections.\n    - This process will help accelerate the campaign relaunch with accurate assets.\n\n- **Webpage graphics were delivered to Lauren to finalize page readiness, with assets already updated on Showpad, enabling the team to proceed with relaunch preparations** (12:00)\n    - This milestone signals near completion of creative asset readiness.\n    - The updated graphics support a cohesive brand experience across digital touchpoints.\n    - Lauren confirmed all necessary materials are in place to go live.\n    - This coordination ensures no delays once the campaign restarts.\n\n## **Video Animation Revisions and Production Challenges**\n\nThe design team requested specific changes to video animations that will require balancing creative intent with technical feasibility and budget constraints.\n\n- **The design team requires adding facial expressions to characters and adjusting organic background colors to more natural tones for better viewer connection, as Lauren Poirier explained** (07:15)\n    - Facial expressions are seen as essential to making animations feel personal and engaging.\n    - Natural colors for buildings and backgrounds aim to enhance visual realism.\n    - The logo should remain static on screen throughout the video rather than appearing and disappearing.\n    - These changes reflect a shift toward more polished and audience-friendly content.\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell highlighted significant technical challenges in retrofitting facial expressions onto already completed animations, noting it may be difficult or costly** (09:30)\n    - The animations were originally created with faceless characters, making changes complex.\n    - Some elements like background color changes and static logos are easier to implement.\n    - The team plans to consult the creative director for feasibility and cost estimates.\n    - Lauren offered to check budget flexibility for extra costs before approving changes.\n\n- **The team will prepare static screen samples of proposed changes to get precise feedback from the design team before final animation work, ensuring alignment and reducing rework** (08:40)\n    - This approach will clarify expectations and confirm the exact nature of requested changes.\n    - It aims to avoid costly revisions after animation is finalized.\n    - Lauren will coordinate feedback cycles to keep the process efficient.\n    - This step balances creative quality with practical production constraints.\n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Communication Protocol**\n\nThe team agreed on flexible meeting scheduling around the Thanksgiving holiday to maintain project momentum without overburdening participants.\n\n- **The upcoming meeting originally set for Thanksgiving will be tentatively moved to Tuesday, allowing the team to adjust based on workload and preference, as agreed by Lauren and Taylor** (02:55)\n    - This change respects holiday plans while preserving communication opportunities.\n    - The team will decide closer to the date whether the meeting is needed or can be replaced with Slack updates.\n    - Taylor will send a calendar link with availability options to finalize timing.\n    - This flexibility supports work-life balance while keeping projects on track.\n\n- **Taylor offered to provide status updates via Slack or Teams if live meetings are inconvenient during the holiday period** (02:55)\n    - This alternative keeps stakeholders informed without requiring synchronous meetings.\n    - It supports asynchronous collaboration during busy or personal times.\n    - Lauren welcomed this approach as a backup communication method.\n    - This protocol ensures continuous progress even with limited live interaction.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","animation feedback","AdRoll discontinuation","logo guidelines","video updates","Thanksgiving scheduling"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Adjustments:** Budget reduced to 50%, from 10,000 to 5,000 points, to improve data quality before relaunch.\n\n- **AdRoll Discontinuation:** Monthly $1,750 redirected pending Merit’s approval, aiming for better ROI and streamlined campaign management.\n\n- **Creative Asset Updates:** Black logo use will be reviewed for brand compliance; focus on primary logo for consistency.\n\n- **Video Animation Changes:** Requested revisions include facial expressions and natural colors; feasibility and costs to be assessed.\n\n- **Flexible Meeting Scheduling:** Thanksgiving meeting moved to Tuesday to respect holiday plans, with Slack updates as an alternative.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend meeting availability link for rescheduled session on Tuesday and adjust calendar invites accordingly (03:33)\nImplement requested copy changes on ad images and send updated versions back to Lauren for review (06:50)\nCommunicate with Lauren once video update samples are ready for approval and incorporate any further feedback (11:22)\nUpon receiving final confirmation from Merit regarding email, forward all relevant data to paid media specialists to setup new campaigns (11:50)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum & Baylee Gunnell**\nConsult with creative director regarding feasibility and costs of adding facial expressions and other animation changes; report findings back (09:35)\n\n**Lauren Poirier**\nCoordinate with Roderick to clarify logo usage guidelines and provide official direction to marketing team (05:04)\nReview updated ad copies and artwork once submitted; provide feedback if further adjustments are needed (06:39)\nMonitor budget and potential additional costs related to animation changes and communicate limits to vendor team (11:03)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"ecd967a2-1256-46a8-87bd-6b6b8f064310","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
