INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: New North x Planon Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Budget Adjustments**

The team decided to pause the ABM campaign temporarily and lower the budget while preparing for a relaunch.

- **The ABM campaign budget will be reduced to 50% of the usual spend, charging only 5,000 points instead of the full 10,000 points this month** as Taylor Doerbaum explained to manage costs during the pause (03:45)
    - The goal is to gather better audience data before fully restarting the campaign.
    - Taylor emphasized maintaining the current sequence to continue learning from the audience once the campaign resumes.
    - The pause reflects a strategic move to optimize spend efficiency and data quality before scaling.
    - This adjustment will prevent overspending while keeping the campaign infrastructure ready to restart promptly.

- **The team agreed to discontinue using AdRoll and redirect the monthly spend of $1,750 to other channels, pending confirmation from Merit** (03:45)
    - Lauren Poirier is awaiting Merit’s approval before finalizing this budget reallocation.
    - This decision stems from a review of channel effectiveness and aims to improve ROI on ad spend.
    - Once approved, paid media specialists will be briefed to implement the new spend plan.
    - Switching away from AdRoll will simplify campaign management and focus resources on higher-impact platforms.

## **Creative Asset Updates and Brand Compliance**

Adjustments to ad creative and brand assets will be carefully managed to align with brand guidelines and improve campaign effectiveness.

- **The team confirmed that the black logo variant, previously used in ads, is in the brand guidelines but is not commonly applied, so they will seek feedback from Roderick before deciding on its future use** as Lauren Poirier noted (04:45)
    - Lauren emphasized sticking to the primary logo with green art and the circle when possible to maintain brand consistency.
    - Taylor highlighted occasional creative needs to use simpler logo colors for better visual blending.
    - The final decision will depend on Roderick’s input to ensure brand alignment.
    - This review aims to avoid visual conflicts that could weaken brand recognition.

- **Taylor committed to updating the ad copy text on images based on Lauren’s feedback and sending revised versions for final approval before broader deployment** (05:40)
    - Copy changes will be made promptly to correct link errors and improve messaging.
    - This step-by-step approach ensures quality control and minimizes rework.
    - Lauren confirmed no major design issues were found beyond copy corrections.
    - This process will help accelerate the campaign relaunch with accurate assets.

- **Webpage graphics were delivered to Lauren to finalize page readiness, with assets already updated on Showpad, enabling the team to proceed with relaunch preparations** (12:00)
    - This milestone signals near completion of creative asset readiness.
    - The updated graphics support a cohesive brand experience across digital touchpoints.
    - Lauren confirmed all necessary materials are in place to go live.
    - This coordination ensures no delays once the campaign restarts.

## **Video Animation Revisions and Production Challenges**

The design team requested specific changes to video animations that will require balancing creative intent with technical feasibility and budget constraints.

- **The design team requires adding facial expressions to characters and adjusting organic background colors to more natural tones for better viewer connection, as Lauren Poirier explained** (07:15)
    - Facial expressions are seen as essential to making animations feel personal and engaging.
    - Natural colors for buildings and backgrounds aim to enhance visual realism.
    - The logo should remain static on screen throughout the video rather than appearing and disappearing.
    - These changes reflect a shift toward more polished and audience-friendly content.

- **Baylee Gunnell highlighted significant technical challenges in retrofitting facial expressions onto already completed animations, noting it may be difficult or costly** (09:30)
    - The animations were originally created with faceless characters, making changes complex.
    - Some elements like background color changes and static logos are easier to implement.
    - The team plans to consult the creative director for feasibility and cost estimates.
    - Lauren offered to check budget flexibility for extra costs before approving changes.

- **The team will prepare static screen samples of proposed changes to get precise feedback from the design team before final animation work, ensuring alignment and reducing rework** (08:40)
    - This approach will clarify expectations and confirm the exact nature of requested changes.
    - It aims to avoid costly revisions after animation is finalized.
    - Lauren will coordinate feedback cycles to keep the process efficient.
    - This step balances creative quality with practical production constraints.

## **Meeting Scheduling and Communication Protocol**

The team agreed on flexible meeting scheduling around the Thanksgiving holiday to maintain project momentum without overburdening participants.

- **The upcoming meeting originally set for Thanksgiving will be tentatively moved to Tuesday, allowing the team to adjust based on workload and preference, as agreed by Lauren and Taylor** (02:55)
    - This change respects holiday plans while preserving communication opportunities.
    - The team will decide closer to the date whether the meeting is needed or can be replaced with Slack updates.
    - Taylor will send a calendar link with availability options to finalize timing.
    - This flexibility supports work-life balance while keeping projects on track.

- **Taylor offered to provide status updates via Slack or Teams if live meetings are inconvenient during the holiday period** (02:55)
    - This alternative keeps stakeholders informed without requiring synchronous meetings.
    - It supports asynchronous collaboration during busy or personal times.
    - Lauren welcomed this approach as a backup communication method.
    - This protocol ensures continuous progress even with limited live interaction.',
  '2025-11-20 15:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send meeting availability link for rescheduled session on Tuesday and adjust calendar invites accordingly (03:33)","completed":false},{"text":"Implement requested copy changes on ad images and send updated versions back to Lauren for review (06:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Communicate with Lauren once video update samples are ready for approval and incorporate any further feedback (11:22)","completed":false},{"text":"Upon receiving final confirmation from Merit regarding email, forward all relevant data to paid media specialists to setup new campaigns (11:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Consult with creative director regarding feasibility and costs of adding facial expressions and other animation changes; report findings back (09:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Roderick to clarify logo usage guidelines and provide official direction to marketing team (05:04)","completed":false},{"text":"Review updated ad copies and artwork once submitted; provide feedback if further adjustments are needed (06:39)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor budget and potential additional costs related to animation changes and communicate limits to vendor team (11:03)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new) (2025-11-19 20:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ec1251b4-8dd8-4f12-ba68-1e923a54c460',
    '2025-11-19 20:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KA9QN4KY2BM4AB16QQK6J7MX',
    'Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)',
    '{"Taylor Doerbaum","Josh Bartel","Michael Jones"}'::text[],
    1277,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87549285494?pwd=ibWG4xRLddaHqf8JzJ7T48gg886wbu.1',
    '{"id":"01KA9QN4KY2BM4AB16QQK6J7MX","title":"Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)","summary":{"notes":"## **Survey Outreach and Email Sending Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to maintain a daily send rate of **around 480 emails** using four domains capped at **120 emails per domain** to avoid domain blacklisting risks (04:00).\n\n- Delivering emails through Lemlist involves a warm-up period and staggered send times, which delays clearing the list; the current estimate to finish sending is about **five working days** (06:00).\n- Michael emphasized avoiding sending follow-up surveys too soon, suggesting a pause between campaigns to prevent survey fatigue and maintain engagement quality (10:00).\n- The team is testing Smart Lead as an alternative platform due to Lemlist’s slower processing of large campaigns, aiming to improve sending speed and efficiency for December’s outreach (03:30).\n- LinkedIn outreach via Hey Reach is slow at about **20 messages per day**, leading Michael to propose narrowing LinkedIn targets by job titles, focusing on senior roles to increase relevance and speed up delivery (07:00).\n\n## **List Management and Targeting**\n\nEfforts are underway to refine the company lists by removing unwanted industry codes such as healthcare and enterprise, with a specialist manually coding and filtering results to improve targeting quality (11:30).\n\n- Taylor reported the current list is large but contains many irrelevant entries, so they are building a version 3 list with better filters to save time in review and increase campaign effectiveness (12:00).\n- Michael confirmed that he will compare the refined list against his own to avoid duplicates and ensure comprehensive coverage (13:30).\n- The team is integrating a new enrichment tool with Clay to automate filtering, reducing manual work and improving accuracy (13:15).\n\n## **Content Performance and Digital Marketing Metrics**\n\nJosh’s LinkedIn page gained **15 new followers in the past 28 days**, showing strong increases in reach and engagement, signaling effective organic content (14:20).\n\n- Paid campaigns on AdRoll produced significantly higher impressions and clicks in November compared to earlier periods, with **18,000 impressions and 122 clicks** noted, demonstrating growing ad visibility (14:30).\n- Michael highlighted recent supply chain posts as key drivers of traction across multiple domains, pinpointing content themes that resonate well with the audience (15:00).\n- Josh requested more granular data on ad impressions by geography, especially to confirm US-only traffic for accurate targeting and reporting (16:00).\n\n## **Analytics Reporting and Traffic Insights**\n\nTaylor committed to providing weekly Google Analytics reports focusing on US traffic and excluding countries like China, which have already been filtered out, to better track genuine engagement and improve decision-making (19:00).\n\n- Josh prefers week-over-week comparisons for traffic and engagement metrics to understand trends and adjust campaigns effectively (20:00).\n- Taylor will incorporate these analytics reports into the regular meetings for ongoing review and optimization of marketing efforts (20:10).\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed to hold off on sending reminder emails for the current survey until the backlog clears, avoiding overlap with December’s survey and potential audience fatigue (10:00).\n\n- Michael requested updated Lemlist credentials to ensure smooth access for campaign management and troubleshooting (08:45).\n- Taylor will follow up with Bailey to confirm sending capacity and platform adjustments to maintain the 120 emails per domain limit without risking blacklisting (08:30).\n- Plans are in place to meet again next week to review progress and finalize the December survey approach, with flexibility around Thanksgiving schedules (20:50).","outline":null,"keywords":["Survey Outreach","Lemlist","Smart Lead","Company List Refinement","LinkedIn Outreach","Google Analytics"],"overview":"- **Email Strategy:** Maintain daily send of around 480 emails, 120 per domain, to avoid blacklisting risks.  \n- **Email Warm-Up:** Lemlist requires warm-up period; expect full list sent in about five working days.  \n- **LinkedIn Outreach:** Targeting senior roles to refine LinkedIn messaging, as current outreach is slow at 20 messages daily.  \n- **List Refinement:** Creating a version 3 list with improved filtering to increase campaign effectiveness and reduce irrelevant entries.  \n- **Analytical Reports:** Weekly Google Analytics reports will focus on US traffic, refining decision-making and understanding engagement trends.  \n- **Next Meeting:** Plan to meet next week to assess progress and finalize December survey strategy before Thanksgiving.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nFollow up with Bailey to confirm increasing Lemlist daily sends to 120 and monitor campaign output (08:00)\nCoordinate receipt of updated Lemlist login credentials from Michael and ensure access restoration (09:06)\nHold off reminder emails for current survey campaign until initial batch is fully sent and evaluate need later (10:44)\nSend filtered company list V3 excluding unwanted industries to Michael for review and perform duplicate checks with Michael’s list (13:40)\nCompile and deliver week-over-week Google Analytics reports focusing on US traffic and exclusion of non-US sources for homepage visits and paid ads (19:40)\nMonitor and report on platform testing (Smart Lead) for email outreach efficiency (03:20)\n\n**Michael Jones**\nSend updated Lemlist account password to Taylor promptly to restore access (09:06)\nReview refined company list upon receipt to ensure proper targeting and exclude irrelevant industries (13:40)\nProvide duplicate company list to Taylor for filtering overlap with new data (13:44)\n\n**Josh Bartel**\nRequest and review detailed source data for homepage visits and AdRoll ad clicks with Taylor’s support (15:55)\nContinue monitoring social media and paid ad performance metrics, providing feedback for content focus (14:00)\n"},"duration":21.290000915527344,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Bartel"},{"id":2,"name":"Michael Jones"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello?","index":0,"end_time":0.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Hello?","index":1,"end_time":2.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Can''t hear you a second.","index":2,"end_time":4.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Can you hear me okay?","index":3,"end_time":12.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":11.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes, thank you.","index":4,"end_time":13.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can hear you now.","index":5,"end_time":14.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":13.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Don''t have a minute.","index":6,"end_time":15.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":14.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Might have just been lagging a little bit.","index":7,"end_time":18.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":18.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":18.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"How are you?","index":9,"end_time":20.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Good.","index":10,"end_time":21.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you doing this week?","index":11,"end_time":22.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, not bad, not bad.","index":12,"end_time":23.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":22.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":24.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Getting ready for Thanksgiving.","index":14,"end_time":26.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You doing anything fun?","index":15,"end_time":27.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No, we don''t really do anything, to be honest with you, because we have no one really around so we don''t really do much.","index":16,"end_time":33.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So it''s a.","index":17,"end_time":35.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":33.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s a day off.","index":18,"end_time":36.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":37.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How about you?","index":20,"end_time":38.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":37.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":21,"end_time":38.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ve got lots of family or.","index":22,"end_time":40.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, some of my family is going to be coming into town.","index":23,"end_time":43.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":24,"end_time":43.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Excited about that.","index":25,"end_time":44.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":26,"end_time":45.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s nice to have everybody here.","index":27,"end_time":46.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":28,"end_time":48.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":48.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, just looking forward to that.","index":30,"end_time":49.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then do all my Christmas shopping.","index":31,"end_time":51.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s usually what I do on the night of Thanksgiving.","index":32,"end_time":53.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like online.","index":33,"end_time":54.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I hate like in person shopping.","index":34,"end_time":56.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So do everything online.","index":35,"end_time":59.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":36,"end_time":61.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s getting ahead of the curve.","index":37,"end_time":63.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes, we this.","index":38,"end_time":67.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right.","index":39,"end_time":70.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So today just wanted to go through a couple updates.","index":40,"end_time":73.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just touch base.","index":41,"end_time":75.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we''re going to see about the newsletter, but for the survey I wanted to run through a couple of stats.","index":42,"end_time":80.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re up to almost 400 messages out of LEM list.","index":43,"end_time":83.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"154 for hay reach and around the same for HubSpot.","index":44,"end_time":87.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we have additional submission since my email Friday and 30 page views there.","index":45,"end_time":93.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as the rate at which we''re sending.","index":46,"end_time":96.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we were going to check back in as far as if we want it to come from your domains as well on lemlist, so.","index":47,"end_time":101.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, Josh and I were sort of briefly talking about this because I remember having this chat, I think with yourself and Bailey about LEM List versus, you know, mailchimp.","index":48,"end_time":112.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I think mailchimp is static emails and LEM List, it''s.","index":49,"end_time":116.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":112.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s sort of interactive emails.","index":50,"end_time":118.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":118.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And unfortunately I cannot remember why are we just limited by how many emails go out per domain through lemlist?","index":52,"end_time":126.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":118.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m sure we''ve had the same conversation before, so apologies if I''m repeating myself.","index":53,"end_time":130.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":126.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"No, that''s totally fine.","index":54,"end_time":131.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":130.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They do have.","index":55,"end_time":132.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I mean you could technically send like 250 a day.","index":56,"end_time":136.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But the problem with that is we have trouble with blacklisting then because then it''s.","index":57,"end_time":140.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It like flags it as spam almost.","index":58,"end_time":142.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then the email domain gets blacklisted and we can''t use it anymore, which we''ve seen happen before.","index":59,"end_time":147.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so what we did was we did increase it from 100 sends a day from each domain to 120.","index":60,"end_time":152.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Bailey thought that''s probably a safe one that we can do.","index":61,"end_time":155.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we increased that to 120 emails a day.","index":62,"end_time":158.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, the, the only harm in it is just we don''t want to risk getting the email domains but that''s the only reason why we limit it.","index":63,"end_time":165.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How many domains?","index":64,"end_time":166.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":166,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I believe we have four coming from Josh at the moment.","index":65,"end_time":171.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So there''s 120 coming out of those.","index":66,"end_time":173.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But sometimes it makes sense then because.","index":67,"end_time":177.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I mean how long has this been?","index":68,"end_time":178.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I suppose it does make sense.","index":69,"end_time":180.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":179.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":180.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we just increased it yesterday.","index":71,"end_time":182.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":183,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And there''s the warm up period too for the sequences and then sometimes the deliverable time in between.","index":73,"end_time":189.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It doesn''t send 120 at a time so it''s over like a period.","index":74,"end_time":192.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s kind of confusing the way lumlas does it.","index":75,"end_time":194.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ve been testing out using Smart Lead for a couple of different campaigns right now.","index":76,"end_time":198.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re going to see if that might be a good one to shift to for future.","index":77,"end_time":202.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"There''s so many different like pros and cons to different platforms.","index":78,"end_time":207.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Lummos has been good for a few of them but we''re starting to notice that they''ve had a little bit of delay in like getting larger campaigns out fast enough.","index":79,"end_time":216.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So yeah, we might shift to Smart Lead in the future.","index":80,"end_time":219.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re kind of testing that one out.","index":81,"end_time":221.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we still, we''re thinking we''ll be at, we''ll be at almost, we''ll be well over 400 a day it sounds like.","index":82,"end_time":227.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So that''s a, that''s a fine rate once.","index":83,"end_time":230.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":231.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I assume now that we''re warmed up when we send it next month we''ll be able to spend, ramp up faster like get to that 400 a day.","index":85,"end_time":239.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, we should be able to.","index":86,"end_time":240.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we might discuss maybe switching to Smart Lead for the, for the December one.","index":87,"end_time":245.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we''ll, we''ll keep tracking the analytics for this month and then maybe make our decision based off of that.","index":88,"end_time":249.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, I know sending through like.","index":89,"end_time":253.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Mailchimp or so we use mailchimp but not for this because it doesn''t support surveys.","index":90,"end_time":259,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Well, yeah, so mailchimp is more of like a static.","index":91,"end_time":261.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we use a newsletter like a 1:1 email.","index":92,"end_time":264.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This one since it''s two, it''s just better for that.","index":93,"end_time":268.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we can look into that is if it''s, if we just do like one of the emails on there and see if the rate goes faster.","index":94,"end_time":275.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can see if Bailey''s done that before with other surveys.","index":95,"end_time":278.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know she''s done a few of those before.","index":96,"end_time":279.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":97,"end_time":280.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then other tools like, you know, obviously like in sort of prosumer land, I''ve used like SurveyMonkey and other things that are dedicated survey platforms.","index":98,"end_time":287.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Are those, is it hard to integrate with those and make them look like they''re not Survey Monkey?","index":99,"end_time":293.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We, we could test that out.","index":100,"end_time":295.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can, I can chat with Bailey about that.","index":101,"end_time":297.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know that everything was set up in HubSpot this time around, but potentially we could switch over to that.","index":102,"end_time":302.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think it was just easier because we had been working with HubSpot for a lot of your materials.","index":103,"end_time":306.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But that could be something we look into if it''s able to produce more output faster.","index":104,"end_time":312.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"She''s run a few different before.","index":105,"end_time":315.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so we''re using, I''m sorry, Lemlist is survey outreach requests.","index":106,"end_time":322.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yes.","index":107,"end_time":323.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And that''s sent to the entire list of people who want to get the survey.","index":108,"end_time":328.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":328.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I''m sorry, hey reach, HubSpot.","index":110,"end_time":330.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And what''s, what''s the difference between these?","index":111,"end_time":332.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So Lemlist was that bigger list that we had that wasn''t necessarily clients.","index":112,"end_time":337.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that one is running in Lemlist.","index":113,"end_time":339.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then hey Reach, we''re using the same list there to send out the LinkedIn.","index":114,"end_time":343.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then HubSpot is the current contact list that we had already in there.","index":115,"end_time":347.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But the form itself, it lives in HubSpot.","index":116,"end_time":350.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s where that landing page goes and that''s where that data is collected.","index":117,"end_time":353.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":118,"end_time":354.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":119,"end_time":355.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So perfect.","index":120,"end_time":356.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay, so that''s clear.","index":121,"end_time":357.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So it''s about 480 a day.","index":122,"end_time":359.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And once we''re up and running, I''m going to estimate another what, five working days before we clear the list.","index":123,"end_time":367.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Would that be about right?","index":124,"end_time":368.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So the same.","index":125,"end_time":368.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Imagine it''s like 2500 left or whatever it is.","index":126,"end_time":371.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":372.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just want to make sure.","index":128,"end_time":373.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, because again, I didn''t realize it was the sort of warm up, ramp up and all the rest of it.","index":129,"end_time":379.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I was just getting a bit concerned and I was looking at the rate.","index":130,"end_time":382.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":379.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, understandable.","index":131,"end_time":383.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we, we did increase it.","index":132,"end_time":385.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If it takes 10 days to clear the thing, I think that''s fine.","index":133,"end_time":389.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Again, we want to be clear that not like five minutes later we''re giving them another survey and.","index":134,"end_time":395.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":135,"end_time":395.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You know, want to make sure there''s some break in between for sure.","index":136,"end_time":399.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":137,"end_time":399.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the other, the other thing we''ve got to think about is pay Reach.","index":138,"end_time":403.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That doesn''t make sense at the moment.","index":139,"end_time":407.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If it''s like 20 a day, we''ll just never get through it before the next one comes along.","index":140,"end_time":413.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I think we might Want to just have a.","index":141,"end_time":415.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"This might be a Hydrian thing.","index":142,"end_time":417.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We might want to maybe look at that list and maybe say, and if this is possible, why don''t we just go ahead and concentrate on either specific job titles or whatever it is that would.","index":143,"end_time":428.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Should get the LinkedIn thing.","index":144,"end_time":430.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":428.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Maybe more senior people get the LinkedIn thing and, you know, that way.","index":145,"end_time":434.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because again, yeah, otherwise it''s just pointless doing it through LinkedIn if we can''t do it any other way.","index":146,"end_time":439.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":434.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m going to advocate we don''t bother through LinkedIn because it just takes forever.","index":147,"end_time":443.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":444.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it does take a little bit longer to go through us.","index":149,"end_time":446.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":150,"end_time":446.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can send that list over and we can discuss maybe just breaking out, like you''re saying.","index":151,"end_time":450.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as job titles specifically, that might be.","index":152,"end_time":453.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Does that make.","index":153,"end_time":454.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Does that make sense to you?","index":154,"end_time":456.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Try and look at it differently.","index":155,"end_time":458,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":456.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"He''s ignoring me.","index":156,"end_time":463.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Hello?","index":157,"end_time":465.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":158,"end_time":467.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, I can.","index":159,"end_time":467.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can send it over and we could make those adjustments for the December one specifically.","index":160,"end_time":474.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":161,"end_time":474.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":162,"end_time":475.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":475.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":475.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":164,"end_time":476.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Five submissions.","index":165,"end_time":477.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I mean, four of them came from the HubSpot list, I''m assuming.","index":166,"end_time":481.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think that''s.","index":167,"end_time":482.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":168,"end_time":482.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I know it''s all anonymous, so I can''t see who it sent it, but I''m fairly certain that''s where it came from.","index":169,"end_time":487.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So one is from wherever.","index":170,"end_time":489.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I don''t know where it came from.","index":171,"end_time":490.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So that''s not exactly.","index":172,"end_time":492.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Well, you know, surveys are a pain to do.","index":173,"end_time":496.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"They really are.","index":174,"end_time":497.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So.","index":175,"end_time":497.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we might want to think about that.","index":176,"end_time":500.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":502.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I know we''re making adjustments for the December edition too, right now that you had sent over to.","index":178,"end_time":507.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So to a couple of questions at.","index":179,"end_time":510.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This stage, then just to wrap all this up.","index":180,"end_time":513.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We don''t have to do my domain then.","index":181,"end_time":515.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":513.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It can still come from Josh.","index":182,"end_time":516.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"As long as we.","index":183,"end_time":517.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":516.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We.","index":184,"end_time":517.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We keep with the 120, the four domains, that''s fine.","index":185,"end_time":521.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I know Bailey adjusted to 120 yesterday, so I''m just going to touch base with her later this afternoon and make sure we can get that up to actually produce that.","index":186,"end_time":529.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then.","index":187,"end_time":529.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we shouldn''t need to.","index":188,"end_time":530.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I did have a question, though.","index":189,"end_time":532.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"When I was logging into Lemlist in your account, it was telling me we had the wrong credentials.","index":190,"end_time":536.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Did you by any chance change that login or.","index":191,"end_time":539.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m not sure if I think I had to change the password.","index":192,"end_time":542.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay, so if you need that, I will send you the password.","index":193,"end_time":546.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, if you could just zip that over.","index":194,"end_time":547.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"When I was looking in there yesterday, it wouldn''t.","index":195,"end_time":549.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Wouldn''t let us into your Side.","index":196,"end_time":550.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yeah, for some reason it had a bit of a.","index":197,"end_time":554.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":550.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Might have locked you out.","index":198,"end_time":556.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s what it was.","index":199,"end_time":557.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I don''t know why.","index":200,"end_time":558.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Why I had a problem with me, but I changed it.","index":201,"end_time":561.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And.","index":202,"end_time":561.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I will get that to you.","index":203,"end_time":563.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":204,"end_time":564.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":205,"end_time":565.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I will make sure to follow up on those things.","index":206,"end_time":570.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":207,"end_time":571.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":570.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then as far as.","index":208,"end_time":574.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, just very quick.","index":209,"end_time":575.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sorry, before we move away from.","index":210,"end_time":576.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":575.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"From.","index":211,"end_time":577.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":576.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, as soon as you can.","index":212,"end_time":579.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":578.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because again, I. I think we''re thinking about the whole reminder email thing.","index":213,"end_time":587.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":581.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That might not work either.","index":214,"end_time":589.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thinking about it, it''s taking such a long time.","index":215,"end_time":591.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":589.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You mean too close to the December one?","index":216,"end_time":595.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":217,"end_time":596.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Well, unless, of course, because don''t forget, it''s like, imagine it''s 10 days to send the thing.","index":218,"end_time":602.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right.","index":219,"end_time":603.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We wanted to wait two weeks and then we''re going to send another 10 days to send the reminder.","index":220,"end_time":607.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It just doesn''t seem to make sense to me.","index":221,"end_time":609.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we changed it to eight days from our last discussion in between the emails, by the way.","index":222,"end_time":614.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":609.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not that big of a difference, but.","index":223,"end_time":615.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, we want to make sure that we can get through without them being too close together.","index":224,"end_time":620.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Why don''t we address that near the time?","index":225,"end_time":623.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Let''s just get rid of everything.","index":226,"end_time":624.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"See.","index":227,"end_time":625.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"See how many results we actually get.","index":228,"end_time":627.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If we think it''s good enough to produce a report with them, we''ll just get on with it.","index":229,"end_time":632.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If we don''t and we think a reminder is necessary, we should address that.","index":230,"end_time":636.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So let''s just clear it first and then we can maybe address it next week.","index":231,"end_time":641.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Just sort of see where we are.","index":232,"end_time":643.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay.","index":233,"end_time":644.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you don''t want the reminder going out, is that what you''re saying?","index":234,"end_time":646.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or.","index":235,"end_time":647.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m just thinking at this stage it doesn''t.","index":236,"end_time":648.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It may not make sense because again, the time, whatever, get.","index":237,"end_time":652.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So imagine it''s like next week we finally clear the backlog.","index":238,"end_time":656.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":652.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You want to wait eight days, so it''s 18 days in total before, you know, the reminder emails have gone through.","index":239,"end_time":665.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":657.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then we''re actually going to be sending the December server.","index":240,"end_time":667.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":665.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right?","index":241,"end_time":669.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can.","index":242,"end_time":670.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can prevent that second one from going out just so we can get through that list for sure.","index":243,"end_time":675.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think so.","index":244,"end_time":676.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":245,"end_time":677.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":246,"end_time":679.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":247,"end_time":681.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":680.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then the next thing just companies list.","index":248,"end_time":685.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we created a V2 based on the codes that we sent in.","index":249,"end_time":688.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A couple of things that we were going back and forth about.","index":250,"end_time":690.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A couple of the industry industry codes, though, did end up producing company results that fell under some of these specifically still.","index":251,"end_time":698.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So right now we have one of our specialists going through that clay list that we created and we''re working on like a coding to make sure that we can like weed out those particular ones because it produced some still with those industry codes.","index":252,"end_time":712.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we saw a couple like healthcare ones and then like Enterprise popped up.","index":253,"end_time":717.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So obviously those weren''t.","index":254,"end_time":718.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Weren''t ones that we wanted to follow.","index":255,"end_time":720.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we used those specific like industry code examples into a coding and so now we''re trying to filter out that list to create like kind of a V3 version and then we''ll send that over to you for review.","index":256,"end_time":731.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know it''s a hard one.","index":257,"end_time":734.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Top of your head.","index":258,"end_time":735.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"How many companies did you manage to find from that?","index":259,"end_time":738.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":735.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It was a large list.","index":260,"end_time":740.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":261,"end_time":741.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s what we want.","index":262,"end_time":742.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It is good.","index":263,"end_time":742.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We just wanted to save you the time of going through it because we like off the bat, when Bailey and I were reviewing it, there were some like Enterprise.","index":264,"end_time":750.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Obviously we knew that wasn''t a good one.","index":265,"end_time":751.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A couple healthcare companies that didn''t fall under.","index":266,"end_time":754.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we were like, we don''t want Michael to go through these because so many produced.","index":267,"end_time":757.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re trying to um.","index":268,"end_time":759.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":269,"end_time":759.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Put in a code to weed out these specific ones here.","index":270,"end_time":762.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":271,"end_time":762.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I gotta say the 150 or whatever example still took me a while to plow through.","index":272,"end_time":766.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":273,"end_time":767.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":767.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was more than that.","index":275,"end_time":768.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we don''t want to give you that.","index":276,"end_time":769.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was great to have the explanations.","index":277,"end_time":771.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It was a bit like this doesn''t quite.","index":278,"end_time":773.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":771.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I had a look at the website and I was going, I''m not too sure.","index":279,"end_time":775.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then how to make the decision.","index":280,"end_time":777.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So.","index":281,"end_time":777.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":778.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":283,"end_time":778.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":284,"end_time":779.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m looking forward to the list so that we can do it.","index":285,"end_time":781.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":779.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And again, it''s interesting because we obviously want to expand the list but we need to be careful that we are sending things out and it takes such a long time to get out the door.","index":286,"end_time":791.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":781.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We gotta be conscious of that.","index":287,"end_time":793.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So.","index":288,"end_time":793.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":793.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":289,"end_time":794.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You know, maybe re looking at new tools is not a bad idea.","index":290,"end_time":798.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":291,"end_time":801.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re integrating one of the enrichment side of the tools that we use with Clay right now.","index":292,"end_time":805.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s a newer one to try to weed those out and it''s been successful so far.","index":293,"end_time":809.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we tested like a portion of the list this morning and we''re finishing the rest now.","index":294,"end_time":814.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So yeah, we want to try to make it as.","index":295,"end_time":816.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As close as we can without having to do it manually.","index":296,"end_time":819.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":297,"end_time":821.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":298,"end_time":822.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I know you sent over this list to us too to compare.","index":299,"end_time":824.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can use this once we have our finalized list that weeds out these ones and you just want us to compare for duplicates?","index":300,"end_time":832.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sure.","index":301,"end_time":833.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":833.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":302,"end_time":835.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep, we can do that.","index":303,"end_time":836.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":304,"end_time":839.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":837.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Just additionally here a couple stats for organic.","index":305,"end_time":844.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Josh''s page is looking really good.","index":306,"end_time":845.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ve had 15 new followers in the last 28 days.","index":307,"end_time":848.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Very high increased reach and engagement rates.","index":308,"end_time":852.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":849.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then same with Hydrien, a couple of upticks here and just a little bit of a drop for reach.","index":309,"end_time":858.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then as far as paid, I just compared so far the first couple weeks of November to now the full up to the 19th.","index":310,"end_time":865.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So seeing good impressions there.","index":311,"end_time":867.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And ad roll also is seeing a much higher impressions and clicks over the past 30 days.","index":312,"end_time":873.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we continue to.","index":313,"end_time":875.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I did notice those last, like the four posts, particularly on that like supply chain version.","index":314,"end_time":882.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":875.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we had those two things.","index":315,"end_time":883.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"The supply one particularly had some really good traction across all three domains, mine, Drew''s and Josh''s.","index":316,"end_time":891.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":883.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So that was.","index":317,"end_time":892.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That was good.","index":318,"end_time":893.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s exactly what we need to.","index":319,"end_time":894.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We need to try and find these things that are, you know, getting a lot more traction in terms of interest and things like that from.","index":320,"end_time":903.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":894.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"From other sort of people.","index":321,"end_time":904,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Are you talking about.","index":322,"end_time":904.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Can we look at where the impressions are coming from really quick?","index":323,"end_time":907,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Taylor, I''m sorry.","index":324,"end_time":907.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":907,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries.","index":325,"end_time":909.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me pull up Poplar over here.","index":326,"end_time":910.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Taylor, I feel like you''ve changed your hair since the last time I saw you.","index":327,"end_time":914.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I did, I did.","index":328,"end_time":915.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I went dark.","index":329,"end_time":916.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I really like it.","index":330,"end_time":917.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Looks great.","index":331,"end_time":918.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":332,"end_time":919.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it was a big change.","index":333,"end_time":920.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I wanted to do something different for fall and yeah, went from very blonde to very dark.","index":334,"end_time":925.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just keep this gray because I think, what the hell, it works.","index":335,"end_time":928.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, it''s blonde.","index":336,"end_time":930.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s not.","index":337,"end_time":931.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I tell my kids all the time, I don''t have gray hair.","index":338,"end_time":933.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"White hairs.","index":339,"end_time":933.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I have blonde hairs.","index":340,"end_time":934.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"My wife has stopped coloring her hair now.","index":341,"end_time":937.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":935.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s gone a really nice sort of like a blondie gray.","index":342,"end_time":941.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So it''s like I never realized.","index":343,"end_time":944.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I thought she''d still color followed it and all the rest of it.","index":344,"end_time":945.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":944.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":345,"end_time":946.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So you have a lot.","index":346,"end_time":948.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You have a few more years to go.","index":347,"end_time":949.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We have to worry about that.","index":348,"end_time":950.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, Taylor, what I was hoping to look at was the source of.","index":349,"end_time":955.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Of those.","index":350,"end_time":956.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"The homepage visits.","index":351,"end_time":959.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Oh, the homepage visits.","index":352,"end_time":962.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":960.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":353,"end_time":962.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":354,"end_time":962.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I should have been more specific.","index":355,"end_time":964.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We''re sorry.","index":356,"end_time":965.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Well, the ad rule, basically, I wanted to look at like.","index":357,"end_time":966.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Oh yeah, the 122 clicks and the 18,000 impressions.","index":358,"end_time":969.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":966.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, where are they coming from?","index":359,"end_time":970.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Are they from the US Are they.","index":360,"end_time":972.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":970.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Let me see if I can pull up the specific data through just our dashboard.","index":361,"end_time":978.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"While you''re doing that Josh.","index":362,"end_time":1003.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think Kaylin''s still chatting with Tim, so that''s why he didn''t join the call.","index":363,"end_time":1007.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1003.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Well, thanks.","index":364,"end_time":1009.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Have it pulled up here on our dashboard for the specifics though landing pages.","index":365,"end_time":1014.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I may have to pull a report for you after.","index":366,"end_time":1016.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then also we have to reconnect LinkedIn here, which we noticed disconnected this morning.","index":367,"end_time":1025.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So let me see if I can pull.","index":368,"end_time":1028.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I might have to pull up AdRoll and download that report and send it to you in the recap.","index":369,"end_time":1032.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":370,"end_time":1033.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1032.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Can we look at our Google Analytics really quick just to look at homepage visits to see where those are coming from?","index":371,"end_time":1038.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I don''t know if you guys noticed, there''s a couple things down.","index":372,"end_time":1043.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The Lemlist was down the other day because the cloud fair and then Google went down last week, so been affecting a lot of different things.","index":373,"end_time":1051.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"See if I can pull this up.","index":374,"end_time":1055.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1054.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sorry, it''s making me log in and do all the two factor stuff.","index":375,"end_time":1064.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"See if I can pull it in.","index":376,"end_time":1066.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right.","index":377,"end_time":1092.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is there a specific page you wanted to look at?","index":378,"end_time":1096.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1094.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You said the, the home page.","index":379,"end_time":1097.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1096.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So by country this is saying last week we got 150 visits.","index":380,"end_time":1105.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"This is the last 28 days.","index":381,"end_time":1108.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1106.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The filter.","index":382,"end_time":1109.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, sorry.","index":383,"end_time":1110.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, let me see if I can go to traffic acquisition here.","index":384,"end_time":1114.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s more of an overall snapshot.","index":385,"end_time":1117.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Got it.","index":386,"end_time":1119.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Okay.","index":387,"end_time":1120.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You should be able to do country as well, shouldn''t you?","index":388,"end_time":1126.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because I think I''ve done that.","index":389,"end_time":1127.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Oh, you''re an analytics.","index":390,"end_time":1129.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes.","index":391,"end_time":1131.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do a custom report.","index":392,"end_time":1134.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1133.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I thought we had like a specific button for that that we had created a filter.","index":393,"end_time":1149.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I see it in your.","index":394,"end_time":1151.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1150.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"In the portal one.","index":395,"end_time":1152.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1151.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":396,"end_time":1154.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1153.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The other ones.","index":397,"end_time":1157.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, we don''t have to.","index":398,"end_time":1160.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m sorry, we don''t have to do.","index":399,"end_time":1161.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It on the call.","index":400,"end_time":1161.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I guess my main question is confirm that we''re not counting non US contacts in the.","index":401,"end_time":1166.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":402,"end_time":1167.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Visit numbers and then it would be great to understand because.","index":403,"end_time":1171.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Because the big thing to me is the 90000 impressions.","index":404,"end_time":1173.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That''s an enormous difference.","index":405,"end_time":1174.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1173.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I just want to understand what, what kind of contacts are those?","index":406,"end_time":1177.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What''s.","index":407,"end_time":1178.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What''s driving that?","index":408,"end_time":1179.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1178.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":409,"end_time":1180.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we did the China exclusion, so that is running here specifically.","index":410,"end_time":1183.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1180.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But as far as just US specific traffic, we could just pull the report and if it would be helpful.","index":411,"end_time":1188.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I do this for a couple of my other clients.","index":412,"end_time":1190.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I do a week over week or a month over month comparison the weekly, weekly meetings so I can have those stats as far as Google Analytics specifically, if you would prefer.","index":413,"end_time":1200.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1190.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great because that''s how I think about it too.","index":414,"end_time":1201.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1200.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Is like change from last report.","index":415,"end_time":1203.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":416,"end_time":1204.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would week over week be most helpful?","index":417,"end_time":1206.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":418,"end_time":1209.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1208.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I don''t have a strong preference.","index":419,"end_time":1209.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Week over week''s great.","index":420,"end_time":1210.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":421,"end_time":1211.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I pull that together usually for some of my other clients that want to see those.","index":422,"end_time":1215.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Google index each week.","index":423,"end_time":1216.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1215.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I can start incorporating that into our weekly meetings.","index":424,"end_time":1219.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"For sure.","index":425,"end_time":1219.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1219.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Cool.","index":426,"end_time":1220.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Great.","index":427,"end_time":1220.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":428,"end_time":1221.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll make sure we''re excluding any additional traffic out of there.","index":429,"end_time":1223.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1221.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we do China, but.","index":430,"end_time":1225.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I can pull that report out.","index":431,"end_time":1226.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":432,"end_time":1229.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1228.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":433,"end_time":1232.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that was all my updates.","index":434,"end_time":1234.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I will get back to you.","index":435,"end_time":1235.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just confirm on the sends for the survey.","index":436,"end_time":1238.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We want to make sure we get those out and then.","index":437,"end_time":1240.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll keep in touch about the company''s list as well as we continue to refine.","index":438,"end_time":1244.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1241.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds like a plan.","index":439,"end_time":1246.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1244.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":440,"end_time":1247.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t know about you, Josh, but we''re still planning to meet next week.","index":441,"end_time":1252.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1248.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I don''t know, you guys are off for Thanksgiving or anything like that, or you still working Wednesday?","index":442,"end_time":1257.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1252.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll still be here.","index":443,"end_time":1258.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll Wednesday.","index":444,"end_time":1258.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But it''s up to you guys.","index":445,"end_time":1260.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can.","index":446,"end_time":1260.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can send an email.","index":447,"end_time":1261.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can meet earlier.","index":448,"end_time":1262.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whatever works.","index":449,"end_time":1263.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m.","index":450,"end_time":1264.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1263.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m around, so we can meet if you want to.","index":451,"end_time":1267.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":452,"end_time":1268.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":453,"end_time":1269.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":454,"end_time":1271.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Have a good rest of your day.","index":455,"end_time":1272.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"dateString":"2025-11-19T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87549285494?pwd=ibWG4xRLddaHqf8JzJ7T48gg886wbu.1","participants":["josh@hydrian.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,michael.jones@hydrian.com,taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","josh@hydrian.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","michael.jones@hydrian.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KA9QN4KY2BM4AB16QQK6J7MX","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.76,"bullets":["Increased daily email send cap from 100 to 120 across four domains to accelerate outreach.","Team discussed potential shift from Lemlist to Smartlead due to campaign delivery delays.","Michael recommended pausing LinkedIn outreach unless targeted by seniority to improve ROI.","Taylor confirmed V3 of company list is being refined to remove irrelevant industry matches.","Josh requested weekly GA traffic reports excluding non-US sources to track ad campaign ROI."],"highlights":[{"quote":"If it takes 10 days to clear the thing, I think that''s fine.","speaker":"Michael Jones"},{"quote":"We tested like a portion of the list this morning and we''re finishing the rest now.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"topics":["delivery","tools","survey","audience","analytics"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T20:42:29Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Survey Outreach and Email Sending Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to maintain a daily send rate of **around 480 emails** using four domains capped at **120 emails per domain** to avoid domain blacklisting risks (04:00).\n\n- Delivering emails through Lemlist involves a warm-up period and staggered send times, which delays clearing the list; the current estimate to finish sending is about **five working days** (06:00).\n- Michael emphasized avoiding sending follow-up surveys too soon, suggesting a pause between campaigns to prevent survey fatigue and maintain engagement quality (10:00).\n- The team is testing Smart Lead as an alternative platform due to Lemlist’s slower processing of large campaigns, aiming to improve sending speed and efficiency for December’s outreach (03:30).\n- LinkedIn outreach via Hey Reach is slow at about **20 messages per day**, leading Michael to propose narrowing LinkedIn targets by job titles, focusing on senior roles to increase relevance and speed up delivery (07:00).\n\n## **List Management and Targeting**\n\nEfforts are underway to refine the company lists by removing unwanted industry codes such as healthcare and enterprise, with a specialist manually coding and filtering results to improve targeting quality (11:30).\n\n- Taylor reported the current list is large but contains many irrelevant entries, so they are building a version 3 list with better filters to save time in review and increase campaign effectiveness (12:00).\n- Michael confirmed that he will compare the refined list against his own to avoid duplicates and ensure comprehensive coverage (13:30).\n- The team is integrating a new enrichment tool with Clay to automate filtering, reducing manual work and improving accuracy (13:15).\n\n## **Content Performance and Digital Marketing Metrics**\n\nJosh’s LinkedIn page gained **15 new followers in the past 28 days**, showing strong increases in reach and engagement, signaling effective organic content (14:20).\n\n- Paid campaigns on AdRoll produced significantly higher impressions and clicks in November compared to earlier periods, with **18,000 impressions and 122 clicks** noted, demonstrating growing ad visibility (14:30).\n- Michael highlighted recent supply chain posts as key drivers of traction across multiple domains, pinpointing content themes that resonate well with the audience (15:00).\n- Josh requested more granular data on ad impressions by geography, especially to confirm US-only traffic for accurate targeting and reporting (16:00).\n\n## **Analytics Reporting and Traffic Insights**\n\nTaylor committed to providing weekly Google Analytics reports focusing on US traffic and excluding countries like China, which have already been filtered out, to better track genuine engagement and improve decision-making (19:00).\n\n- Josh prefers week-over-week comparisons for traffic and engagement metrics to understand trends and adjust campaigns effectively (20:00).\n- Taylor will incorporate these analytics reports into the regular meetings for ongoing review and optimization of marketing efforts (20:10).\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed to hold off on sending reminder emails for the current survey until the backlog clears, avoiding overlap with December’s survey and potential audience fatigue (10:00).\n\n- Michael requested updated Lemlist credentials to ensure smooth access for campaign management and troubleshooting (08:45).\n- Taylor will follow up with Bailey to confirm sending capacity and platform adjustments to maintain the 120 emails per domain limit without risking blacklisting (08:30).\n- Plans are in place to meet again next week to review progress and finalize the December survey approach, with flexibility around Thanksgiving schedules (20:50).","outline":null,"keywords":["Survey Outreach","Lemlist","Smart Lead","Company List Refinement","LinkedIn Outreach","Google Analytics"],"overview":"- **Email Strategy:** Maintain daily send of around 480 emails, 120 per domain, to avoid blacklisting risks.  \n- **Email Warm-Up:** Lemlist requires warm-up period; expect full list sent in about five working days.  \n- **LinkedIn Outreach:** Targeting senior roles to refine LinkedIn messaging, as current outreach is slow at 20 messages daily.  \n- **List Refinement:** Creating a version 3 list with improved filtering to increase campaign effectiveness and reduce irrelevant entries.  \n- **Analytical Reports:** Weekly Google Analytics reports will focus on US traffic, refining decision-making and understanding engagement trends.  \n- **Next Meeting:** Plan to meet next week to assess progress and finalize December survey strategy before Thanksgiving.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nFollow up with Bailey to confirm increasing Lemlist daily sends to 120 and monitor campaign output (08:00)\nCoordinate receipt of updated Lemlist login credentials from Michael and ensure access restoration (09:06)\nHold off reminder emails for current survey campaign until initial batch is fully sent and evaluate need later (10:44)\nSend filtered company list V3 excluding unwanted industries to Michael for review and perform duplicate checks with Michael’s list (13:40)\nCompile and deliver week-over-week Google Analytics reports focusing on US traffic and exclusion of non-US sources for homepage visits and paid ads (19:40)\nMonitor and report on platform testing (Smart Lead) for email outreach efficiency (03:20)\n\n**Michael Jones**\nSend updated Lemlist account password to Taylor promptly to restore access (09:06)\nReview refined company list upon receipt to ensure proper targeting and exclude irrelevant industries (13:40)\nProvide duplicate company list to Taylor for filtering overlap with new data (13:44)\n\n**Josh Bartel**\nRequest and review detailed source data for homepage visits and AdRoll ad clicks with Taylor’s support (15:55)\nContinue monitoring social media and paid ad performance metrics, providing feedback for content focus (14:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"80624f37-5f20-4fc5-8591-ad130cca4fea","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
