INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)',
  '## **Survey Outreach and Email Sending Strategy**

The team decided to maintain a daily send rate of **around 480 emails** using four domains capped at **120 emails per domain** to avoid domain blacklisting risks (04:00).

- Delivering emails through Lemlist involves a warm-up period and staggered send times, which delays clearing the list; the current estimate to finish sending is about **five working days** (06:00).
- Michael emphasized avoiding sending follow-up surveys too soon, suggesting a pause between campaigns to prevent survey fatigue and maintain engagement quality (10:00).
- The team is testing Smart Lead as an alternative platform due to Lemlist’s slower processing of large campaigns, aiming to improve sending speed and efficiency for December’s outreach (03:30).
- LinkedIn outreach via Hey Reach is slow at about **20 messages per day**, leading Michael to propose narrowing LinkedIn targets by job titles, focusing on senior roles to increase relevance and speed up delivery (07:00).

## **List Management and Targeting**

Efforts are underway to refine the company lists by removing unwanted industry codes such as healthcare and enterprise, with a specialist manually coding and filtering results to improve targeting quality (11:30).

- Taylor reported the current list is large but contains many irrelevant entries, so they are building a version 3 list with better filters to save time in review and increase campaign effectiveness (12:00).
- Michael confirmed that he will compare the refined list against his own to avoid duplicates and ensure comprehensive coverage (13:30).
- The team is integrating a new enrichment tool with Clay to automate filtering, reducing manual work and improving accuracy (13:15).

## **Content Performance and Digital Marketing Metrics**

Josh’s LinkedIn page gained **15 new followers in the past 28 days**, showing strong increases in reach and engagement, signaling effective organic content (14:20).

- Paid campaigns on AdRoll produced significantly higher impressions and clicks in November compared to earlier periods, with **18,000 impressions and 122 clicks** noted, demonstrating growing ad visibility (14:30).
- Michael highlighted recent supply chain posts as key drivers of traction across multiple domains, pinpointing content themes that resonate well with the audience (15:00).
- Josh requested more granular data on ad impressions by geography, especially to confirm US-only traffic for accurate targeting and reporting (16:00).

## **Analytics Reporting and Traffic Insights**

Taylor committed to providing weekly Google Analytics reports focusing on US traffic and excluding countries like China, which have already been filtered out, to better track genuine engagement and improve decision-making (19:00).

- Josh prefers week-over-week comparisons for traffic and engagement metrics to understand trends and adjust campaigns effectively (20:00).
- Taylor will incorporate these analytics reports into the regular meetings for ongoing review and optimization of marketing efforts (20:10).

## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**

The team agreed to hold off on sending reminder emails for the current survey until the backlog clears, avoiding overlap with December’s survey and potential audience fatigue (10:00).

- Michael requested updated Lemlist credentials to ensure smooth access for campaign management and troubleshooting (08:45).
- Taylor will follow up with Bailey to confirm sending capacity and platform adjustments to maintain the 120 emails per domain limit without risking blacklisting (08:30).
- Plans are in place to meet again next week to review progress and finalize the December survey approach, with flexibility around Thanksgiving schedules (20:50).',
  '2025-11-19 20:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Follow up with Bailey to confirm increasing Lemlist daily sends to 120 and monitor campaign output (08:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate receipt of updated Lemlist login credentials from Michael and ensure access restoration (09:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Hold off reminder emails for current survey campaign until initial batch is fully sent and evaluate need later (10:44)","completed":false},{"text":"Send filtered company list V3 excluding unwanted industries to Michael for review and perform duplicate checks with Michael’s list (13:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Compile and deliver week-over-week Google Analytics reports focusing on US traffic and exclusion of non-US sources for homepage visits and paid ads (19:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and report on platform testing (Smart Lead) for email outreach efficiency (03:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Send updated Lemlist account password to Taylor promptly to restore access (09:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Review refined company list upon receipt to ensure proper targeting and exclude irrelevant industries (13:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide duplicate company list to Taylor for filtering overlap with new data (13:44)","completed":false},{"text":"Request and review detailed source data for homepage visits and AdRoll ad clicks with Taylor’s support (15:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue monitoring social media and paid ad performance metrics, providing feedback for content focus (14:00)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
