-- Meeting: New North x Sedra Solutions: Weekly Meeting (2025-11-19 16:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '292bf658-a285-4fdd-a6e5-d352a30347c9',
    '2025-11-19 16:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KA9CN7JHFQ4826CWEYJ5NKJ7',
    'New North x Sedra Solutions: Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Taylor Doerbaum","Jackie Wheeler","Baylee Gunnell"}'::text[],
    614,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88927304763?pwd=asbbQolEtVpMuYX5uccJpOibhnlog1.1',
    '{"id":"01KA9CN7JHFQ4826CWEYJ5NKJ7","title":"New North x Sedra Solutions: Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Organic Social and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to refine social copy and leverage certification announcements to enhance messaging without overwhelming followers (00:00).\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum confirmed plans to adjust social copy** based on feedback and to coordinate with Fahad for timely posts (00:00)  \n    - Jackie Wheeler had already created a certification announcement on Fahad’s page to share (00:28)  \n    - To avoid redundancy, Jackie suggested shifting focus to security importance with SoC2 and ISO certifications instead of another announcement (00:50)  \n    - Taylor will edit copy using the data sheet to explain certification significance clearly to the audience (01:13)  \n    - This approach aims to reinforce messaging while maintaining audience engagement without announcement fatigue  \n\n- **Email and LinkedIn campaign sequences will be shortened and simplified** to improve engagement and reduce contact frequency (01:26)  \n    - Fahad’s availability issues delayed feedback, so Jackie approved proceeding with the new copy immediately (02:02)  \n    - The existing eight-email sequence will be cut to two emails focusing on clear calls to action for demo scheduling (03:02)  \n    - Baylee Gunnell supported reusing these new emails to re-engage previously contacted audiences, effectively creating a fresh campaign cycle (03:59)  \n    - This streamlining is expected to accelerate campaign progress and reduce recipient fatigue (03:37)  \n\n## **Paid Advertising and Budget Allocation**\n\nThe team agreed on reallocating ad spend to prioritize LinkedIn for demo engagement while maintaining a minimal Google branded campaign (04:39).\n\n- **Monthly LinkedIn ad budget will increase from $1,500 to $2,500** by shifting $1,000 from Google Ads while retaining $500 for branded Google campaigns (04:39)  \n    - This shift aims to drive more traffic directly to the demo landing page and boost demo scheduling rates (04:39)  \n    - New image ad creatives are in development to support this focused effort, with launch targeted for next week (04:39)  \n    - The change reflects a strategic preference for LinkedIn’s demo conversion potential over general Google ad reach (04:39)  \n    - Jackie Wheeler and Taylor Doerbaum expressed optimism this adjustment will increase engagement and demo bookings (05:34)  \n\n## **Demo Video Development and Engagement Tactics**\n\nJackie Wheeler initiated creating a short demo video to provide prospects with an immediate product preview, aiming to increase demo interest (05:53).\n\n- **A 2–5 minute demo video with scripted voiceover will be produced** to offer a quick platform overview without requiring scheduling (05:53)  \n    - Jackie will handle the screen walkthrough and voiceover, requesting production support for polishing visuals (05:53)  \n    - Taylor and Baylee expressed strong support for using this video as a campaign hook within email sequences to boost engagement (07:09)  \n    - This “give to get” strategy targets prospects hesitant to commit to full demos by lowering the barrier to entry (06:36)  \n    - The video is expected to increase demo conversion rates by offering tangible value upfront (06:36)  \n\n- **Budget constraints may delay full production polish**, with a rough version potentially used initially and a refined version scheduled for next year when points balance improves (08:02)  \n    - Baylee highlighted the current negative points balance of approximately **50 points**, limiting immediate resource allocation (07:48)  \n    - Jackie noted budget control lies with Fahad, emphasizing caution to prevent further negative balance (08:30)  \n    - The team remains committed to supporting video production within financial limits and open to future refinements (09:29)  \n\n## **Account Management and Financial Oversight**\n\nThe team acknowledged the current negative points balance but emphasized partnership strength and flexible support to maintain momentum (07:48).\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell reported a negative balance nearing negative 50 points**, improved from negative 171 considering ongoing work (08:04)  \n    - The agency commits to not charging extra despite the negative balance but requests budget attention to avoid worsening (08:04)  \n    - Jackie confirmed budget responsibility rests with Fahad and stressed the need to monitor and control spending (08:30)  \n    - The team agreed to balance project ambitions with financial realities, adjusting deliverables as needed (09:26)  \n    - This transparency supports trust and ensures continued collaboration without service interruptions (09:29)","outline":null,"keywords":["Organic Social","ABM Campaign","Demo Video","Paid Ads","Security Certification","Budget Management"],"overview":"- **Refined Social Messaging Strategy:** Adjust social copy will focus on security importance, using certification data for clearer audience engagement.\n\n- **Streamlined Email Campaigns:** Email sequence shortened from eight to two, focusing on clear calls to action to improve engagement.\n\n- **Increased LinkedIn Ad Budget:** Monthly LinkedIn budget rises from $1,500 to $2,500, reallocating funds for better demo engagement.\n\n- **Demo Video Development:** A 2–5 minute demo video will be created to boost demo interest, lowering commitment barriers for prospects.\n\n- **Negative Points Balance Awareness:** Current balance at negative 50 points, improved from negative 171; budget monitoring emphasized for future stability.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend reminder to Fahad for social post updates or create content from blogs to announce certification (00:00)\nEdit and send updated social media copy emphasizing security certification details to Jackie for review (01:13)\nProceed with new LinkedIn sequence and first email copy immediately and implement campaign adjustments (02:02)\nSend the updated second email copy to Jackie for review and implement the shortened two-email sequence (03:37)\nFinalize and share details of new paid ad image creative packages and budget changes to initiate launch next week (04:18)\nAssist with production of Jackie’s demo video to add professional touches after receiving raw content and script (06:32)\nProvide ongoing Slack updates regarding campaign progress and coordinate next steps (10:00)\n\n**Jackie Wheeler**\nReview second email copy post-meeting and adjust call-to-action content as needed (03:30)\nContinue working on the 5-minute demo video including script, on-screen navigation, and voiceover (05:53)\nCoordinate sending raw demo video to Taylor and team for production enhancement (06:30)\nMonitor project budget status with Fahad and adjust production ambitions based on points availability (08:30)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nMonitor and report on current project points balance and communicate budget status to the team (07:48)\nSupport discussions with leadership about possibly gifting points for future video production needs (08:04)\n"},"duration":10.239999771118164,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Organic Social.","index":0,"end_time":1.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thank you for your feedback.","index":1,"end_time":2.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re going to implement those additional adjustments to just the copy on the edits that you had said and then it would be great to hear back from Fahad too.","index":2,"end_time":10.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can send him a reminder for posts for him but as we get a little bit closer to his running out, I may just create some like just from blogs or stuff on the site and we can use the announcement of the certification on his too to just have that going from both.","index":3,"end_time":26.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I''ll wait to hear about, you.","index":4,"end_time":28.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Know, so there again like I already did an announcement and he already, and I, yeah created an announcement for him on his page to share and then to add his own comments.","index":5,"end_time":37.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.3,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So that''s already been done.","index":6,"end_time":39.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.7,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So I don''t know if we want to do another announcement from his page.","index":7,"end_time":41.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.06,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I think that would be, it''s totally up to you.","index":8,"end_time":43.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We could either spread them out and do it that way or we can just skip the announcement if you, if you want to stick with the one.","index":9,"end_time":49.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Rather than doing it as an announcement.","index":10,"end_time":51.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.02,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"We could talk about the importance of security in forensic accounting data.","index":11,"end_time":56.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.74,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So and talking about, you know, we have have both SoC2 and ISO certification and that''s the, you know, bank grade security is essential when you''re dealing with forensic accounting because you''re dealing with very sensitive data.","index":12,"end_time":67.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.82,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So we could say something along those lines to reiterate the message without making another announcement.","index":13,"end_time":73.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.16,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So maybe explain a little bit more what it is and why it''s important like to the audience.","index":14,"end_time":78.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can, we can tweak that a little bit and I can pull from what''s on the data sheet and edit that copy so I can send that back to you.","index":15,"end_time":85.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":16,"end_time":86.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.82,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":17,"end_time":87.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, great.","index":18,"end_time":88.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just now talking through the ABM campaign.","index":19,"end_time":92.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, just curious, I don''t know if you know, if they were able to reschedule that demo.","index":20,"end_time":95.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I hope so.","index":21,"end_time":96.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, Fahad has been so busy this week that I wasn''t able to have my one on one with him on Monday so.","index":22,"end_time":102.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.18,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And he couldn''t make it today so I have no idea where we''re at with that.","index":23,"end_time":105.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.22,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Okay, I hope we can get that rescheduled.","index":24,"end_time":107.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":25,"end_time":107.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know, I know.","index":26,"end_time":109.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We made the updates to LinkedIn sequence already and you made those edits to the first email.","index":27,"end_time":114.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just wanted to see where we''re at if here.","index":28,"end_time":116.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know if Fahad got a chance to look it over, but I.","index":29,"end_time":122.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":116.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Don''T know that he''s had a chance or will have a chance.","index":30,"end_time":125.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.77,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I would say just Go ahead and start using this copy and you know, and if he has comments later we can change it again.","index":31,"end_time":133.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.93,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that sounds good.","index":32,"end_time":135.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So currently we have all the different campaigns running and we would have.","index":33,"end_time":142.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We have several emails.","index":34,"end_time":144.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So do you want us to update the second one as well or.","index":35,"end_time":149.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because.","index":36,"end_time":149.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because it''ll start going through them.","index":37,"end_time":152.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think Bailey, also you mentioned potentially pulling a different audience into.","index":38,"end_time":156.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if you want to say more to that, but it may work for separate audiences specifically or if you just want this to be like the main blanket one that we send out to all of the campaigns that we have running, then we would just probably need to tweak the sequence to only be the two emails, if that makes sense.","index":39,"end_time":175.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because right now we have eight.","index":40,"end_time":176.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that was his concern is that we''re sending too many emails.","index":41,"end_time":180.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.87,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":42,"end_time":180.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Shorten that.","index":43,"end_time":182.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think he wanted to just send.","index":44,"end_time":183.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.31,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Or was that more the LinkedIn.","index":45,"end_time":187.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.35,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"LinkedIn.","index":46,"end_time":187.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We have one message running which we did update.","index":47,"end_time":190.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":48,"end_time":191.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Email side of it.","index":49,"end_time":192.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We could update to just be two, which is what we had suggested here.","index":50,"end_time":195.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think that makes sense.","index":51,"end_time":196.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.35,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":196.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.55,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And so what is the second one again?","index":53,"end_time":198.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.87,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I think I looked at this, but I think it was fine.","index":54,"end_time":200.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.63,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":55,"end_time":201.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll need to be updated because I think we discussed getting rid of this like open ended question and more so making it like a call to action to schedule a demo.","index":56,"end_time":209.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me.","index":57,"end_time":210.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.18,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Okay, let me take a look at this.","index":58,"end_time":211.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.7,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"After the meeting I''ll take a look at this email.","index":59,"end_time":213.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.9,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":60,"end_time":214.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.94,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I thought I reviewed that, but I think that needs some tweaking.","index":61,"end_time":217.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.38,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":62,"end_time":218.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And yeah, I think it would just be better like we''re saying to do more like a blanket copy that would work for the audiences and then eliminate the 8 email sequence that we currently have to get through the campaigns faster too.","index":63,"end_time":231.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I know we have a lot of different lists that we have implemented.","index":64,"end_time":234.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I think it''ll just help across the board to.","index":65,"end_time":237.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To progress through.","index":66,"end_time":239.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Makes sense where these are brand new emails too.","index":67,"end_time":243.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can send them to people like the same people you''ve already reached out to.","index":68,"end_time":248.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s like this is almost a whole new campaign so we can try again with the same people.","index":69,"end_time":254,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":70,"end_time":254.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":71,"end_time":258.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":257.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then as far as the offer, probably don''t have any updates here, but just want to check in on that.","index":72,"end_time":263.929,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.969,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":73,"end_time":264.489,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.929,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can just go ahead and implement the.","index":74,"end_time":266.729,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.569,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The two new ones.","index":75,"end_time":268.169,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.729,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll send the second one over to you so at least we can get that running.","index":76,"end_time":271.049,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.169,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if we are able to create an offer after that, then we could always circle back in.","index":77,"end_time":275.929,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.209,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, agreed.","index":78,"end_time":277.049,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.929,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I think that''s, that''s a great approach.","index":79,"end_time":278.729,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.049,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it''s great.","index":80,"end_time":280.649,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.449,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''ll be how we move forward then.","index":81,"end_time":282.009,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.649,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":82,"end_time":283.769,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.289,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just wanted to give you an update on the paid ad updates.","index":83,"end_time":286.089,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.929,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know last week we presented the change up that we''re going to do, but just wanted to walk through this.","index":84,"end_time":291.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.089,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re working on the new image ad creative package to create a campaign strictly around getting users to the demo landing page to create more engagement around there and hopefully increase demos that we have scheduled.","index":85,"end_time":302.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So what we currently have running, this is outside of ABM ads, but the 1500 on LinkedIn.","index":86,"end_time":308.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s going to be adjusted to 2,500 because we''re going to pull the $1,000 from Google Ads, but we''re going to keep 500 in Google each month to make sure we run that branded campaign that you had mentioned.","index":87,"end_time":319.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we want to continue to have that running.","index":88,"end_time":321.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ll just allocate the 500 there and move the grand over to LinkedIn.","index":89,"end_time":326.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re working on those ad packages now and I''ll send you all the details once we finalize them in the image ads and then we can go ahead and get those launched next week.","index":90,"end_time":333.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":91,"end_time":334.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.15,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":92,"end_time":335.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So excited to change that up and hopefully get more engagement to that demo landing page.","index":93,"end_time":341.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, here''s hoping.","index":94,"end_time":342.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.11,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"That''s our number one goal.","index":95,"end_time":343.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":96,"end_time":343.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yes, but yeah, that''s all the updates we have.","index":97,"end_time":347.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll send you back those social posts too and that email so you can take a look at that.","index":98,"end_time":352.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":99,"end_time":353.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then another thing that I''m working on is I am working on doing a short, like five minute demo video that walks through the platform and has a script associated with it.","index":100,"end_time":363.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.19,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And one thing that I''m not great at is production, you know, in terms of like adding interstitial screens and all that kind of stuff.","index":101,"end_time":373.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.67,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So I probably am going to send that over to you guys to make it pretty and you know, make it look professional so I can do, you know, voiceover.","index":102,"end_time":380.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.22,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I''ve got the script, you know, I''m going to work on the actual movements of the mouse and doing the right thing through the, through the, the screen.","index":103,"end_time":386.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.14,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"But, but yeah, I''m probably going to need your help with a little bit of production on it.","index":104,"end_time":392.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.18,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s exciting.","index":105,"end_time":393.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds like a cool, cool thing to have.","index":106,"end_time":395.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just figured, you know, rather since people don''t schedule a damn demo, let''s send them a five minute video, you know, short demo so they can actually get A taste of it.","index":107,"end_time":404.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.07,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And hopefully that''s enough to get them interested in actually having a conversation.","index":108,"end_time":409.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.99,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So it''s this whole thing of like, I feel like we''re not giving to get.","index":109,"end_time":413.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.59,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"We''ve talked about this.","index":110,"end_time":414.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.43,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"That''s why we want to do the offer.","index":111,"end_time":415.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.23,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And we need to give to get.","index":112,"end_time":417.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.75,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":113,"end_time":417.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.31,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And so giving them something to look at, so to whet their appetite, I think will help.","index":114,"end_time":422.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.75,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Do you know how you would utilize that video yet?","index":115,"end_time":424.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is that something.","index":116,"end_time":425.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Send it out.","index":117,"end_time":426.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''d like to make it like, send it out as part of an email campaign.","index":118,"end_time":429.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.34,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"That''s what I was thinking.","index":119,"end_time":430.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m like, that actually might be great to implement into our sequence now.","index":120,"end_time":434.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":430.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, here''s something you can look at right now.","index":121,"end_time":436.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.3,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"You know, you don''t have to wait to schedule a demo with us.","index":122,"end_time":438.819,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.58,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Here''s a.","index":123,"end_time":439.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.819,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Here''s a sneak peek at what you''ll be seeing in a demo call with us.","index":124,"end_time":443.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.26,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"It would be like the hook to maybe get them to exactly that.","index":125,"end_time":446.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":126,"end_time":446.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":127,"end_time":447.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.98,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So if I could make it, you know, two to five minutes.","index":128,"end_time":450.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.06,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Two is probably too short, but if I can make it a little bit in somewhere in there to give them a taste of it, then they''ll be like, oh, yeah, it just, you know, here''s hoping.","index":129,"end_time":460.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.87,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":461.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you going to do the voiceover?","index":131,"end_time":463.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":464.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I love this.","index":133,"end_time":465.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is awesome.","index":134,"end_time":466.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":135,"end_time":467.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Really quick, Jackie.","index":136,"end_time":470.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll just pull up your portal so you can see where we''re at.","index":137,"end_time":473.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just like so many projects going on.","index":138,"end_time":477.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":475.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Lots of stuff going on right now.","index":139,"end_time":479.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But just so you do know, we are in a negative points balance.","index":140,"end_time":482.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":483.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"With that being said, we love our partnership with you.","index":142,"end_time":487.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we.","index":143,"end_time":488.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We want to do really good work for you.","index":144,"end_time":490.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let us know once you''re ready to work on that next video and we can talk with leadership about maybe gifting some points to do that.","index":145,"end_time":499.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So just let us know when we get there because we don''t want to get farther into the negative points bound.","index":146,"end_time":505.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll never like charge you extra because of that, but we do need to keep an eye on that.","index":147,"end_time":510.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, absolutely.","index":148,"end_time":511.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.47,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":511.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.51,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And I have no control over the budget or any of that, you know, so that''s totally up to Fahad.","index":150,"end_time":517.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.87,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"And so, yeah, if we''re getting.","index":151,"end_time":519.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.23,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"If we''re getting into negative, that''s pretty negative territory.","index":152,"end_time":522.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.79,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"We want to get that, pull that back in.","index":153,"end_time":524.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.39,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So, yeah, I will.","index":154,"end_time":526.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"There is like a little bit of nuance to this.","index":155,"end_time":528.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If, like, this is a.","index":156,"end_time":533.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This subtracts what''s currently in working.","index":157,"end_time":535.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":533.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''re really only negative, like 50 points.","index":158,"end_time":538.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":159,"end_time":539.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Considering everything that we''re working on right now, but still, like, negative 50 isn''t great, but that''s better than negative 171.","index":160,"end_time":547.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, for sure.","index":161,"end_time":548.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.42,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll just keep that.","index":162,"end_time":550.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.18,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"You know, it might be that I can do something that''s, you know, not as polished as you guys would do, and maybe we do our, you know, a second version of it, you know, in the new year when we''ve got more points available, that kind of thing.","index":163,"end_time":563.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.54,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So.","index":164,"end_time":563.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.02,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah, video projects are expensive.","index":165,"end_time":564.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.38,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"I know.","index":166,"end_time":565.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.82,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"They take a lot of time.","index":167,"end_time":566.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.1,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":566.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You know, just being conscious of the budget.","index":169,"end_time":569.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.14,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":170,"end_time":569.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we love doing them with you.","index":171,"end_time":571.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Don''t be a stranger.","index":172,"end_time":573.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let let us know.","index":173,"end_time":574.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":573.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we want to make something work for you.","index":174,"end_time":576.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":175,"end_time":577.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.1,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":176,"end_time":578.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I love that idea.","index":177,"end_time":578.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would be really cool to implement in.","index":178,"end_time":580.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yeah, you know, I think, you know, some people are scared to, you know, put their IP out there in the world or whatever, but it''s like, um, you''ve got screenshots, you''re going to do a demo anyway.","index":179,"end_time":592.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.54,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Just, you know, put it out there, let people see it, because I think it speaks for itself.","index":180,"end_time":597.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.88,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"So.","index":181,"end_time":598.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":598.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s awesome.","index":183,"end_time":600.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Love that idea.","index":184,"end_time":601.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Definitely keep us updated there.","index":185,"end_time":602.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''d love to help.","index":186,"end_time":603.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":187,"end_time":605.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, I hope you have a good rest of your week and I''ll be updating you in slack.","index":188,"end_time":608.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, talk soon.","index":189,"end_time":609.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.36,"speaker_name":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"text":"Bye.","index":190,"end_time":609.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":609.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"dateString":"2025-11-19T16:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88927304763?pwd=asbbQolEtVpMuYX5uccJpOibhnlog1.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,j.wheeler@sedrasolutions.com,i.hamshari@sedrasolutions.com,f.almutawa@sedrasolutions.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","j.wheeler@sedrasolutions.com","i.hamshari@sedrasolutions.com","f.almutawa@sedrasolutions.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KA9CN7JHFQ4826CWEYJ5NKJ7","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Agreed to consolidate eight-email sequence into a two-message campaign to streamline outreach.","Taylor confirmed reallocation of $1,000 from Google Ads to boost LinkedIn campaign budget.","Jackie proposed a self-guided demo video to increase engagement without live scheduling.","Baylee noted 50-point overage but offered to coordinate with leadership for potential solution.","Team aligned to implement simplified email copy and demo hook to drive conversions."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''re working on the new image ad creative package... to create more engagement around there.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"Since people don''t schedule a damn demo, let''s send them a five minute video.","speaker":"Jackie Wheeler"},{"quote":"We love our partnership with you... maybe gifting some points to do that.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["delivery","campaign","budget","engagement"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Organic Social and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to refine social copy and leverage certification announcements to enhance messaging without overwhelming followers (00:00).\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum confirmed plans to adjust social copy** based on feedback and to coordinate with Fahad for timely posts (00:00)  \n    - Jackie Wheeler had already created a certification announcement on Fahad’s page to share (00:28)  \n    - To avoid redundancy, Jackie suggested shifting focus to security importance with SoC2 and ISO certifications instead of another announcement (00:50)  \n    - Taylor will edit copy using the data sheet to explain certification significance clearly to the audience (01:13)  \n    - This approach aims to reinforce messaging while maintaining audience engagement without announcement fatigue  \n\n- **Email and LinkedIn campaign sequences will be shortened and simplified** to improve engagement and reduce contact frequency (01:26)  \n    - Fahad’s availability issues delayed feedback, so Jackie approved proceeding with the new copy immediately (02:02)  \n    - The existing eight-email sequence will be cut to two emails focusing on clear calls to action for demo scheduling (03:02)  \n    - Baylee Gunnell supported reusing these new emails to re-engage previously contacted audiences, effectively creating a fresh campaign cycle (03:59)  \n    - This streamlining is expected to accelerate campaign progress and reduce recipient fatigue (03:37)  \n\n## **Paid Advertising and Budget Allocation**\n\nThe team agreed on reallocating ad spend to prioritize LinkedIn for demo engagement while maintaining a minimal Google branded campaign (04:39).\n\n- **Monthly LinkedIn ad budget will increase from $1,500 to $2,500** by shifting $1,000 from Google Ads while retaining $500 for branded Google campaigns (04:39)  \n    - This shift aims to drive more traffic directly to the demo landing page and boost demo scheduling rates (04:39)  \n    - New image ad creatives are in development to support this focused effort, with launch targeted for next week (04:39)  \n    - The change reflects a strategic preference for LinkedIn’s demo conversion potential over general Google ad reach (04:39)  \n    - Jackie Wheeler and Taylor Doerbaum expressed optimism this adjustment will increase engagement and demo bookings (05:34)  \n\n## **Demo Video Development and Engagement Tactics**\n\nJackie Wheeler initiated creating a short demo video to provide prospects with an immediate product preview, aiming to increase demo interest (05:53).\n\n- **A 2–5 minute demo video with scripted voiceover will be produced** to offer a quick platform overview without requiring scheduling (05:53)  \n    - Jackie will handle the screen walkthrough and voiceover, requesting production support for polishing visuals (05:53)  \n    - Taylor and Baylee expressed strong support for using this video as a campaign hook within email sequences to boost engagement (07:09)  \n    - This “give to get” strategy targets prospects hesitant to commit to full demos by lowering the barrier to entry (06:36)  \n    - The video is expected to increase demo conversion rates by offering tangible value upfront (06:36)  \n\n- **Budget constraints may delay full production polish**, with a rough version potentially used initially and a refined version scheduled for next year when points balance improves (08:02)  \n    - Baylee highlighted the current negative points balance of approximately **50 points**, limiting immediate resource allocation (07:48)  \n    - Jackie noted budget control lies with Fahad, emphasizing caution to prevent further negative balance (08:30)  \n    - The team remains committed to supporting video production within financial limits and open to future refinements (09:29)  \n\n## **Account Management and Financial Oversight**\n\nThe team acknowledged the current negative points balance but emphasized partnership strength and flexible support to maintain momentum (07:48).\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell reported a negative balance nearing negative 50 points**, improved from negative 171 considering ongoing work (08:04)  \n    - The agency commits to not charging extra despite the negative balance but requests budget attention to avoid worsening (08:04)  \n    - Jackie confirmed budget responsibility rests with Fahad and stressed the need to monitor and control spending (08:30)  \n    - The team agreed to balance project ambitions with financial realities, adjusting deliverables as needed (09:26)  \n    - This transparency supports trust and ensures continued collaboration without service interruptions (09:29)","outline":null,"keywords":["Organic Social","ABM Campaign","Demo Video","Paid Ads","Security Certification","Budget Management"],"overview":"- **Refined Social Messaging Strategy:** Adjust social copy will focus on security importance, using certification data for clearer audience engagement.\n\n- **Streamlined Email Campaigns:** Email sequence shortened from eight to two, focusing on clear calls to action to improve engagement.\n\n- **Increased LinkedIn Ad Budget:** Monthly LinkedIn budget rises from $1,500 to $2,500, reallocating funds for better demo engagement.\n\n- **Demo Video Development:** A 2–5 minute demo video will be created to boost demo interest, lowering commitment barriers for prospects.\n\n- **Negative Points Balance Awareness:** Current balance at negative 50 points, improved from negative 171; budget monitoring emphasized for future stability.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend reminder to Fahad for social post updates or create content from blogs to announce certification (00:00)\nEdit and send updated social media copy emphasizing security certification details to Jackie for review (01:13)\nProceed with new LinkedIn sequence and first email copy immediately and implement campaign adjustments (02:02)\nSend the updated second email copy to Jackie for review and implement the shortened two-email sequence (03:37)\nFinalize and share details of new paid ad image creative packages and budget changes to initiate launch next week (04:18)\nAssist with production of Jackie’s demo video to add professional touches after receiving raw content and script (06:32)\nProvide ongoing Slack updates regarding campaign progress and coordinate next steps (10:00)\n\n**Jackie Wheeler**\nReview second email copy post-meeting and adjust call-to-action content as needed (03:30)\nContinue working on the 5-minute demo video including script, on-screen navigation, and voiceover (05:53)\nCoordinate sending raw demo video to Taylor and team for production enhancement (06:30)\nMonitor project budget status with Fahad and adjust production ambitions based on points availability (08:30)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nMonitor and report on current project points balance and communicate budget status to the team (07:48)\nSupport discussions with leadership about possibly gifting points for future video production needs (08:04)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"3ccc2824-c0dd-48e9-8c95-4eacb2929cd2","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
