INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: New North x Sedra Solutions: Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Organic Social and Messaging Strategy**

The team decided to refine social copy and leverage certification announcements to enhance messaging without overwhelming followers (00:00).

- **Taylor Doerbaum confirmed plans to adjust social copy** based on feedback and to coordinate with Fahad for timely posts (00:00)  
    - Jackie Wheeler had already created a certification announcement on Fahad’s page to share (00:28)  
    - To avoid redundancy, Jackie suggested shifting focus to security importance with SoC2 and ISO certifications instead of another announcement (00:50)  
    - Taylor will edit copy using the data sheet to explain certification significance clearly to the audience (01:13)  
    - This approach aims to reinforce messaging while maintaining audience engagement without announcement fatigue  

- **Email and LinkedIn campaign sequences will be shortened and simplified** to improve engagement and reduce contact frequency (01:26)  
    - Fahad’s availability issues delayed feedback, so Jackie approved proceeding with the new copy immediately (02:02)  
    - The existing eight-email sequence will be cut to two emails focusing on clear calls to action for demo scheduling (03:02)  
    - Baylee Gunnell supported reusing these new emails to re-engage previously contacted audiences, effectively creating a fresh campaign cycle (03:59)  
    - This streamlining is expected to accelerate campaign progress and reduce recipient fatigue (03:37)  

## **Paid Advertising and Budget Allocation**

The team agreed on reallocating ad spend to prioritize LinkedIn for demo engagement while maintaining a minimal Google branded campaign (04:39).

- **Monthly LinkedIn ad budget will increase from $1,500 to $2,500** by shifting $1,000 from Google Ads while retaining $500 for branded Google campaigns (04:39)  
    - This shift aims to drive more traffic directly to the demo landing page and boost demo scheduling rates (04:39)  
    - New image ad creatives are in development to support this focused effort, with launch targeted for next week (04:39)  
    - The change reflects a strategic preference for LinkedIn’s demo conversion potential over general Google ad reach (04:39)  
    - Jackie Wheeler and Taylor Doerbaum expressed optimism this adjustment will increase engagement and demo bookings (05:34)  

## **Demo Video Development and Engagement Tactics**

Jackie Wheeler initiated creating a short demo video to provide prospects with an immediate product preview, aiming to increase demo interest (05:53).

- **A 2–5 minute demo video with scripted voiceover will be produced** to offer a quick platform overview without requiring scheduling (05:53)  
    - Jackie will handle the screen walkthrough and voiceover, requesting production support for polishing visuals (05:53)  
    - Taylor and Baylee expressed strong support for using this video as a campaign hook within email sequences to boost engagement (07:09)  
    - This “give to get” strategy targets prospects hesitant to commit to full demos by lowering the barrier to entry (06:36)  
    - The video is expected to increase demo conversion rates by offering tangible value upfront (06:36)  

- **Budget constraints may delay full production polish**, with a rough version potentially used initially and a refined version scheduled for next year when points balance improves (08:02)  
    - Baylee highlighted the current negative points balance of approximately **50 points**, limiting immediate resource allocation (07:48)  
    - Jackie noted budget control lies with Fahad, emphasizing caution to prevent further negative balance (08:30)  
    - The team remains committed to supporting video production within financial limits and open to future refinements (09:29)  

## **Account Management and Financial Oversight**

The team acknowledged the current negative points balance but emphasized partnership strength and flexible support to maintain momentum (07:48).

- **Baylee Gunnell reported a negative balance nearing negative 50 points**, improved from negative 171 considering ongoing work (08:04)  
    - The agency commits to not charging extra despite the negative balance but requests budget attention to avoid worsening (08:04)  
    - Jackie confirmed budget responsibility rests with Fahad and stressed the need to monitor and control spending (08:30)  
    - The team agreed to balance project ambitions with financial realities, adjusting deliverables as needed (09:26)  
    - This transparency supports trust and ensures continued collaboration without service interruptions (09:29)',
  '2025-11-19 16:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send reminder to Fahad for social post updates or create content from blogs to announce certification (00:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Edit and send updated social media copy emphasizing security certification details to Jackie for review (01:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Proceed with new LinkedIn sequence and first email copy immediately and implement campaign adjustments (02:02)","completed":false},{"text":"Send the updated second email copy to Jackie for review and implement the shortened two-email sequence (03:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize and share details of new paid ad image creative packages and budget changes to initiate launch next week (04:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist with production of Jackie’s demo video to add professional touches after receiving raw content and script (06:32)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide ongoing Slack updates regarding campaign progress and coordinate next steps (10:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Review second email copy post-meeting and adjust call-to-action content as needed (03:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue working on the 5-minute demo video including script, on-screen navigation, and voiceover (05:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate sending raw demo video to Taylor and team for production enhancement (06:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor project budget status with Fahad and adjust production ambitions based on points availability (08:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and report on current project points balance and communicate budget status to the team (07:48)","completed":false},{"text":"Support discussions with leadership about possibly gifting points for future video production needs (08:04)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
