    '{"id":"01KA758A13350BZTY2CR1A17HA","title":"BioSAFE Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **SEO Performance and Website Traffic**\n\nThe current website traffic remains stable with notable increases in direct and referral visits, but organic traffic has declined due to lack of new content.\n\n- **Website traffic showed a significant spike in January and April, with overall stability in recent months and a big rise in direct traffic this year** as explained by **Baylee Gunnell** (04:13)  \n    - The homepage and primary medical waste disposal page saw the largest increases in visits.  \n    - Referral traffic rose sharply, likely from external websites linking to BioSafe, while paid search also contributed to traffic growth.  \n    - The organic search decline aligns with the absence of new website content, emphasizing the need for fresh updates to boost organic reach.  \n    - Spam traffic from countries like China and Singapore was noted but considered normal and non-impactful on core markets.\n\n- **Search term analysis from Google Search Console reveals that top queries align well with BioSafe’s brand and products, including ‘Effluent Decontamination System’ and ‘Biomedical Waste Management’** according to **Baylee Gunnell** (06:04)  \n    - The queries reflect relevant customer interests and product focus, supporting current SEO targeting strategies.  \n    - Baylee will download the detailed query data for **Dan Nelsen** to review and Taylor Doerbaum will include it in the meeting recap email.  \n    - This data will help refine content and keyword focus aligned with business goals.\n\n## **Content Development and Marketing Strategy**\n\nContent production is scheduled to accelerate with cleared materials and filming planned next week to support website updates and traffic growth.\n\n- **Dan Nelsen committed to clearing most content pieces by the end of the week and scheduling filming for new content next week to refresh the website and drive engagement** (07:38)  \n    - This effort is critical to reversing organic traffic declines and sustaining inbound interest.  \n    - Taylor Doerbaum has prepared a new content calendar in Notion, allowing topic selection or suggestion, focusing currently on industry topics (07:59).  \n    - The planned content refresh will provide fresh material to boost SEO and support marketing campaigns.\n\n## **ABM Campaign and Sales Proposals**\n\nSales and marketing efforts are progressing with proposals being prepared and no major updates yet on account-based marketing campaigns.\n\n- **Dan Nelsen is finalizing several proposals expected to be cleared within the next day or so, enabling next steps in sales outreach** (01:54)  \n    - No new updates on the ABM campaign or website blogs were reported, indicating a need to prioritize these areas soon.  \n    - These proposals and campaign progress directly influence lead generation and revenue growth timelines.\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is aligned on next deliverables with clear responsibilities and communication plans to maintain momentum.\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum will send a detailed recap email including the SEO query data and content calendar link to ensure clarity and follow-up** (07:33)  \n    - Dan Nelsen will review the SEO query data to fine-tune focus areas for content and marketing.  \n    - Content approvals by Dan are expected by week’s end, enabling filming and website update scheduling next week.  \n    - This structured workflow aims to streamline content delivery and marketing activation aligned with business priorities.","outline":null,"keywords":["SEO Analytics","Website Traffic","Google Search Console","Content Calendar","ABM Campaign","Medical Waste Disposal"],"overview":"- **Stable website traffic:** Direct and referral visits increased; organic traffic declined due to lack of new content.  \n- **Search term alignment:** Google queries matched BioSafe’s brand, indicating effective SEO targeting strategies.  \n- **Content production acceleration:** New content filming scheduled next week to enhance website engagement and combat traffic decline.  \n- **Proposals in progress:** Sales proposals being finalized, crucial for lead generation and revenue growth.  \n- **Team alignment:** Clear responsibilities established, with follow-up recap email and structured workflow for marketing activities.  \n- **Spam traffic noted:** Normal spam from China and Singapore observed but doesn’t affect key market performance.","action_items":"\n**Dan Nelsen**\nClear content pieces related to ongoing projects by end of this week (07:38)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nPull up Google Analytics data during the meeting for review (01:13)\nDownload and send keyword search query data from Google Search Console (07:33)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend recap email including downloaded search term data and meeting notes (07:34)\nProvide and maintain the new content calendar on Notion for team collaboration and topic selection (07:58)\n"},"duration":8.4399995803833,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"sentences":[{"text":"I''m doing fine.","index":0,"end_time":1.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yourself?","index":1,"end_time":1.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":2.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Having a good week so far?","index":3,"end_time":4.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, going fine.","index":4,"end_time":6.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"How are you guys?","index":5,"end_time":7.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Good.","index":6,"end_time":9.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Busy.","index":7,"end_time":10.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Busy.","index":8,"end_time":10.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":10.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep.","index":9,"end_time":13.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Pull up our agenda here.","index":10,"end_time":16.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":15.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I know today we''re just going to walk through some updates.","index":11,"end_time":23.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have the meeting deck here, so I can just go in order what we have here.","index":12,"end_time":28.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know if you have any questions to start off or any.","index":13,"end_time":31.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I really want to.","index":14,"end_time":32.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.82,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I really want to take a look at just what the SEO search pieces are looking like right now.","index":15,"end_time":40.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.18,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can pull that up.","index":16,"end_time":44.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me see if I can pull up another slide, see if I can log in.","index":17,"end_time":49.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":44.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you wanting to just like, look at Google Analytics and go through that?","index":18,"end_time":52.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can definitely go through that too.","index":19,"end_time":56.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Dan.","index":20,"end_time":56.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know if Taylor has some stuff specifically, but I don''t think we''re going to see a lot of improvements until we get the new website launched because there haven''t been a lot of new updates made.","index":21,"end_time":68.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bailey, are you by any chance logged into the analytics?","index":22,"end_time":77.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s not pulling up for me.","index":23,"end_time":79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":77.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I can get that pulled up.","index":24,"end_time":82.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":25,"end_time":84.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":83.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"While she pulls that up, Dan, did you have any additional updates on a couple of the other things that we were planning, just like the ABM campaign?","index":26,"end_time":97.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":27,"end_time":101.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.25,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''ve had a couple things come up in the last couple weeks.","index":28,"end_time":104.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":29,"end_time":106.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Probably the same within website updates, blogs.","index":30,"end_time":110.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":107.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just want to see if you had any updates here.","index":31,"end_time":113.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No updates.","index":32,"end_time":114.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We''re getting a couple proposals out today, so I''ll try to get those cleared for you in the next day or so.","index":33,"end_time":119.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":34,"end_time":120.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":120.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is there any specific things specifically you''re wanting to look at with the SEO analytics, Stan?","index":35,"end_time":135.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just website traffic, search traffic.","index":36,"end_time":138.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Just run through if those have moved at all and if they''re staying safe or if they''re staying stable.","index":37,"end_time":145.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s take a look at it.","index":38,"end_time":148.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like I mentioned before, there''s.","index":39,"end_time":152.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":150.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, we haven''t really made any big changes since the website hasn''t launched.","index":40,"end_time":156.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, just over this last year, you have seen a big increase in traffic.","index":41,"end_time":163.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I do think some of this is likely spam traffic, especially when we look at where a lot of the increase in traffic is coming from.","index":42,"end_time":174.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like China is not really your target market.","index":43,"end_time":178.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I''m not sure about Singapore, but yeah, I do think some of that is spam.","index":44,"end_time":185.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":45,"end_time":186.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Which is normal.","index":46,"end_time":187.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":186.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like that is pretty normal on.","index":47,"end_time":190.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"On websites.","index":48,"end_time":192.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But you.","index":49,"end_time":194.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But most of that spike happened back in January and April, and then you''ve been pretty consistent the last few months with just traffic in general.","index":50,"end_time":203.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just.","index":51,"end_time":209.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":208.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If we want to look at this last calendar year you can see which pages have had the most increases in traffic.","index":52,"end_time":221.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So not sure what page this is off the top of my head with this title, but your homepage has seen a big increase in traffic and then your medical waste disposal is also seen.","index":53,"end_time":237.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Now that''s the net net.","index":54,"end_time":238.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That''s the primary med waste page as opposed to the 13 below it.","index":55,"end_time":243.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":56,"end_time":248.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":57,"end_time":251.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yep.","index":58,"end_time":253.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then let''s also take a look at where the traffic is coming from.","index":59,"end_time":259.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just taking a minute to load.","index":60,"end_time":267.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this year you''ve seen the biggest uptick in direct traffic coming to your site.","index":61,"end_time":275.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So people just already like having your link and hopping right on it.","index":62,"end_time":278.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There has been a decrease in organic, but that''s what I would expect when we''re not adding new content to your website.","index":63,"end_time":285.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That is just really important to get new traffic.","index":64,"end_time":288.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But referral traffic has increased a lot.","index":65,"end_time":292.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s either going to be through like just other links, like probably from other websites.","index":66,"end_time":299.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"People just linking to Bio Safe.","index":67,"end_time":302.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then Paid search has also been doing well here, getting increased traffic.","index":68,"end_time":307.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":69,"end_time":308.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Did you have any other questions or anything else you wanted to look at on here?","index":70,"end_time":312.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No.","index":71,"end_time":313.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If we could take a look at what the primary search, what the leading.","index":72,"end_time":318.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Search terms are, we''ll need to pull that up on a different.","index":73,"end_time":324.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let me get that pulled up.","index":74,"end_time":325.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It.","index":75,"end_time":338.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so we have to pull this up on a different tool called Google Search Console.","index":76,"end_time":370.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if we want to look at the last three months, we can see your most popular queries and then let''s take off this filter.","index":77,"end_time":379.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So the most popular ones is Biosafe Engineering, Bio Safe and then followed by tissue Digester and then BioSafe.","index":78,"end_time":391.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let''s actually filter this by impressions because that was not in order, so.","index":79,"end_time":395.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, this is actually great.","index":80,"end_time":396.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Effluent decontamination system is the top one.","index":81,"end_time":399.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then BioSafe, Biomedical Waste Management.","index":82,"end_time":404.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Biomedical waste disposal.","index":83,"end_time":407.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.329,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean that one''s probably not a great fit but like in the right ish category, Biomedical waste Affluent Decontamination systems to tissue digester.","index":84,"end_time":419.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Biosafe engineering disposal of medical biomedical waste.","index":85,"end_time":423.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Biomedical waste disposal methods.","index":86,"end_time":426.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I can download this too and send it over.","index":87,"end_time":428.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You want to.","index":88,"end_time":429.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":89,"end_time":430.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''m trying to do a quick cut in my head of what our brand, what are product and what our goal.","index":90,"end_time":435.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":430.88,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But yeah, if you just send that to me, that''d be great.","index":91,"end_time":439.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, but this is looking really good.","index":92,"end_time":441.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like these are the terms the queries people are looking at.","index":93,"end_time":445.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They seem on target from what I can tell.","index":94,"end_time":448.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that seems pretty spot on.","index":95,"end_time":452.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.41,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":96,"end_time":453.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''LL download that and Taylor can send that over in our recap email.","index":97,"end_time":457.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":98,"end_time":458.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":99,"end_time":460.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.45,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I know we''ve got a couple pieces I need to clear a few and then we want to film some new content.","index":100,"end_time":464.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let''s aim to film next week and then I should have most if not all of the content pieces cleared for you end of this week and then we can talk about anything outstanding around the recording next week.","index":101,"end_time":478.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":102,"end_time":479.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":103,"end_time":480.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I put together a new content calendar and notion where we can talk about the different topics or you can choose one from there if there''s one not listed that you think would be good.","index":104,"end_time":490.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s just industry topic right now.","index":105,"end_time":491.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can work through that too.","index":106,"end_time":493.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":107,"end_time":494.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":108,"end_time":494.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.19,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":109,"end_time":495.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":495.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I will go ahead and send an email recap with these things but yeah, hope you have a good rest of your week.","index":110,"end_time":500.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":495.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks, you too.","index":111,"end_time":502.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"}],"dateString":"2025-11-18T18:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81421883896?pwd=9iHNOeWOt9gp3Uqm9ajWXxGhOvoFVO.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,dnelsen@biosafeeng.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","dnelsen@biosafeeng.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KA758A13350BZTY2CR1A17HA","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.72,"bullets":["Reviewed SEO and Google Analytics, traffic mostly stable with earlier rise tied to spam.","Baylee noted referral and paid traffic are increasing despite stale web content.","Dan confirmed no ABM campaign updates; proposals expected to be cleared within days.","Search terms like ''Effluent decontamination system'' and ''Biomedical waste'' ranked highest.","Next content filming targeted for next week; Dan to finalize approvals by week''s end."],"highlights":[{"quote":"There has been a decrease in organic, but that''s what I would expect when we''re not adding new content to your website.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["SEO","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **SEO Performance and Website Traffic**\n\nThe current website traffic remains stable with notable increases in direct and referral visits, but organic traffic has declined due to lack of new content.\n\n- **Website traffic showed a significant spike in January and April, with overall stability in recent months and a big rise in direct traffic this year** as explained by **Baylee Gunnell** (04:13)  \n    - The homepage and primary medical waste disposal page saw the largest increases in visits.  \n    - Referral traffic rose sharply, likely from external websites linking to BioSafe, while paid search also contributed to traffic growth.  \n    - The organic search decline aligns with the absence of new website content, emphasizing the need for fresh updates to boost organic reach.  \n    - Spam traffic from countries like China and Singapore was noted but considered normal and non-impactful on core markets.\n\n- **Search term analysis from Google Search Console reveals that top queries align well with BioSafe’s brand and products, including ‘Effluent Decontamination System’ and ‘Biomedical Waste Management’** according to **Baylee Gunnell** (06:04)  \n    - The queries reflect relevant customer interests and product focus, supporting current SEO targeting strategies.  \n    - Baylee will download the detailed query data for **Dan Nelsen** to review and Taylor Doerbaum will include it in the meeting recap email.  \n    - This data will help refine content and keyword focus aligned with business goals.\n\n## **Content Development and Marketing Strategy**\n\nContent production is scheduled to accelerate with cleared materials and filming planned next week to support website updates and traffic growth.\n\n- **Dan Nelsen committed to clearing most content pieces by the end of the week and scheduling filming for new content next week to refresh the website and drive engagement** (07:38)  \n    - This effort is critical to reversing organic traffic declines and sustaining inbound interest.  \n    - Taylor Doerbaum has prepared a new content calendar in Notion, allowing topic selection or suggestion, focusing currently on industry topics (07:59).  \n    - The planned content refresh will provide fresh material to boost SEO and support marketing campaigns.\n\n## **ABM Campaign and Sales Proposals**\n\nSales and marketing efforts are progressing with proposals being prepared and no major updates yet on account-based marketing campaigns.\n\n- **Dan Nelsen is finalizing several proposals expected to be cleared within the next day or so, enabling next steps in sales outreach** (01:54)  \n    - No new updates on the ABM campaign or website blogs were reported, indicating a need to prioritize these areas soon.  \n    - These proposals and campaign progress directly influence lead generation and revenue growth timelines.\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is aligned on next deliverables with clear responsibilities and communication plans to maintain momentum.\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum will send a detailed recap email including the SEO query data and content calendar link to ensure clarity and follow-up** (07:33)  \n    - Dan Nelsen will review the SEO query data to fine-tune focus areas for content and marketing.  \n    - Content approvals by Dan are expected by week’s end, enabling filming and website update scheduling next week.  \n    - This structured workflow aims to streamline content delivery and marketing activation aligned with business priorities.","outline":null,"keywords":["SEO Analytics","Website Traffic","Google Search Console","Content Calendar","ABM Campaign","Medical Waste Disposal"],"overview":"- **Stable website traffic:** Direct and referral visits increased; organic traffic declined due to lack of new content.  \n- **Search term alignment:** Google queries matched BioSafe’s brand, indicating effective SEO targeting strategies.  \n- **Content production acceleration:** New content filming scheduled next week to enhance website engagement and combat traffic decline.  \n- **Proposals in progress:** Sales proposals being finalized, crucial for lead generation and revenue growth.  \n- **Team alignment:** Clear responsibilities established, with follow-up recap email and structured workflow for marketing activities.  \n- **Spam traffic noted:** Normal spam from China and Singapore observed but doesn’t affect key market performance.","action_items":"\n**Dan Nelsen**\nClear content pieces related to ongoing projects by end of this week (07:38)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nPull up Google Analytics data during the meeting for review (01:13)\nDownload and send keyword search query data from Google Search Console (07:33)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend recap email including downloaded search term data and meeting notes (07:34)\nProvide and maintain the new content calendar on Notion for team collaboration and topic selection (07:58)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"c50d9d42-989b-4ae4-ad0f-a0c09a935814","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
