INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: BioSAFE Weekly Meeting',
  '## **SEO Performance and Website Traffic**

The current website traffic remains stable with notable increases in direct and referral visits, but organic traffic has declined due to lack of new content.

- **Website traffic showed a significant spike in January and April, with overall stability in recent months and a big rise in direct traffic this year** as explained by **Baylee Gunnell** (04:13)  
    - The homepage and primary medical waste disposal page saw the largest increases in visits.  
    - Referral traffic rose sharply, likely from external websites linking to BioSafe, while paid search also contributed to traffic growth.  
    - The organic search decline aligns with the absence of new website content, emphasizing the need for fresh updates to boost organic reach.  
    - Spam traffic from countries like China and Singapore was noted but considered normal and non-impactful on core markets.

- **Search term analysis from Google Search Console reveals that top queries align well with BioSafe’s brand and products, including ‘Effluent Decontamination System’ and ‘Biomedical Waste Management’** according to **Baylee Gunnell** (06:04)  
    - The queries reflect relevant customer interests and product focus, supporting current SEO targeting strategies.  
    - Baylee will download the detailed query data for **Dan Nelsen** to review and Taylor Doerbaum will include it in the meeting recap email.  
    - This data will help refine content and keyword focus aligned with business goals.

## **Content Development and Marketing Strategy**

Content production is scheduled to accelerate with cleared materials and filming planned next week to support website updates and traffic growth.

- **Dan Nelsen committed to clearing most content pieces by the end of the week and scheduling filming for new content next week to refresh the website and drive engagement** (07:38)  
    - This effort is critical to reversing organic traffic declines and sustaining inbound interest.  
    - Taylor Doerbaum has prepared a new content calendar in Notion, allowing topic selection or suggestion, focusing currently on industry topics (07:59).  
    - The planned content refresh will provide fresh material to boost SEO and support marketing campaigns.

## **ABM Campaign and Sales Proposals**

Sales and marketing efforts are progressing with proposals being prepared and no major updates yet on account-based marketing campaigns.

- **Dan Nelsen is finalizing several proposals expected to be cleared within the next day or so, enabling next steps in sales outreach** (01:54)  
    - No new updates on the ABM campaign or website blogs were reported, indicating a need to prioritize these areas soon.  
    - These proposals and campaign progress directly influence lead generation and revenue growth timelines.

## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**

The team is aligned on next deliverables with clear responsibilities and communication plans to maintain momentum.

- **Taylor Doerbaum will send a detailed recap email including the SEO query data and content calendar link to ensure clarity and follow-up** (07:33)  
    - Dan Nelsen will review the SEO query data to fine-tune focus areas for content and marketing.  
    - Content approvals by Dan are expected by week’s end, enabling filming and website update scheduling next week.  
    - This structured workflow aims to streamline content delivery and marketing activation aligned with business priorities.',
  '2025-11-18 18:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Clear content pieces related to ongoing projects by end of this week (07:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Pull up Google Analytics data during the meeting for review (01:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Download and send keyword search query data from Google Search Console (07:33)","completed":false},{"text":"Send recap email including downloaded search term data and meeting notes (07:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide and maintain the new content calendar on Notion for team collaboration and topic selection (07:58)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Numeric x New North Weekly Meeting (2025-11-18 18:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'c8bd9166-2a8e-4824-9bbb-304f1d8ce014',
    '2025-11-18 18:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KA758A13QSKSTF3119ZW7X4W',
    'Numeric x New North Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Nigel Sapp","Nigel Sapp","Taylor Doerbaum"}'::text[],
    1138,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85923034376?pwd=NBFhbUd6g4vmM0MK2Nj6S8W5axpYvz.1',
    '{"id":"01KA758A13QSKSTF3119ZW7X4W","title":"Numeric x New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Publishing Schedule**\n\nThe team is prioritizing publishing select podcast episodes around the Thanksgiving holiday to maximize audience focus.\n\n- **Nigel Sapp confirmed two to three upcoming episodes from Alan and Barrett are ready to publish, with Barrett’s episode tentatively set for release the week after Thanksgiving, around Wednesday, to avoid holiday noise (06:08).**  \n    - Barrett’s episode is considered a strong candidate for next week’s launch but may be delayed for better focus.  \n    - Lynn’s episode is planned to be published about two weeks after Barrett’s to ensure it receives undivided attention.  \n    - Nigel noted that no new episodes are expected to be filmed through the end of the year due to limited time and resources.  \n    - Taylor Doerbaum agreed to accommodate flexible publishing dates, even same-day decisions, to fit Nigel’s schedule.\n\n- **The team is finalizing caption edits on two episodes featuring Heather and Kevin, targeting completion by Thursday for review and publication (04:08).**  \n    - Taylor will send early versions if available prior to Thursday to accelerate the process.  \n    - Nigel aims to pass one remaining video to Heather and Kevin for review before release.  \n    - The current focus is on wrapping up existing content rather than initiating new recordings this quarter.\n\n## **Podcast Highlight Compilation Project**\n\nA strategic highlight video is being developed to promote the podcast’s first season and build hype for the second season.\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum proposed creating a season one recap highlight video using clips from existing episodes to engage new and returning listeners and boost season two anticipation (07:08).**  \n    - The concept involves mashing together key moments or recurring questions from guests to form a cohesive narrative.  \n    - Taylor shared examples from similar projects, including a format where a host asks the same question across episodes for thematic unity.  \n    - Nigel responded positively and emphasized selecting the best clips and guests rather than relying on repeated questions, citing limited consistency in questions asked.  \n    - Nigel volunteered to identify favorite episodes and key moments to guide clip selection and ensure the video highlights the strongest content.\n\n- **Nigel suggested adding a creative intro segment featuring repeated host introductions from various episodes to showcase the podcast’s evolution and personalities (14:30).**  \n    - This segment would feature multiple hosts saying their opening lines from different times, creating a nostalgic and engaging start.  \n    - Taylor endorsed this idea as a unique way to brand the highlight video and agreed to begin work on this intro first.  \n    - Nigel proposed combining this intro with the highlight reel in one video, possibly separated by a branded transition animation, to maintain flow and reinforce branding.  \n    - The implementation plan involves Taylor’s team compiling clips, creating the intro, and sending draft versions to Nigel for feedback before final editing.\n\n## **Content Curation and Guest Selection**\n\nThe selection of episodes and guests for promotion is focused on quality, guest impact, and audio/video clarity.\n\n- **Nigel identified top favorite episodes to feature in the highlight reel, including those with guests RJ, Colin, Chris Canals (a Numeric employee), Thomas Neal, Nate Carver, and Ruthie from Public (13:22).**  \n    - He noted some audio and video quality issues with certain episodes (Ruthie) but emphasized content value over technical flaws.  \n    - Newer episodes like Heather and Lynn are also considered strong candidates for inclusion upon release.  \n    - Nigel plans to provide Taylor with a list of preferred episodes and specific standout moments to guide the highlight video’s content.  \n    - Taylor will cross-reference these with existing edited clips and show notes to streamline selection and editing.\n\n## **Process and Workflow Adjustments**\n\nThe team is adapting workflows to accommodate year-end constraints and maximize impact around holidays.\n\n- **Nigel and Taylor agreed on a flexible, just-in-time publishing process for episodes around Thanksgiving, allowing quick decisions on exact release dates based on external factors like holiday noise (06:17).**  \n    - This approach avoids rigid scheduling and helps optimize audience engagement.  \n    - No new recordings are planned through the end of the year, focusing resources on post-production and promotion of existing content.  \n    - The highlight video project is a new engagement tactic intended to complement the existing publishing workflow without adding recording demands.  \n    - Nigel committed to timely communication regarding episode readiness and publishing decisions to support this flexible approach.\n\n- **Taylor’s team will handle all technical production for the highlight video, including clip selection, editing, and creation of intro segments, requiring only Nigel’s feedback for final approvals (08:50).**  \n    - This minimizes workload on the Numeric team and leverages external expertise.  \n    - Feedback loops are established for Nigel to review proposed clips and themes before final assembly.  \n    - The project is positioned as a holiday gift, reflecting a collaborative and positive client-vendor relationship.  \n    - The new process emphasizes ease, speed, and quality to maintain momentum during a busy year-end period.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Highlights","Episode Publishing","Content Compilation","Podcast Editing","Season Recap","Host Introductions"],"overview":"- **Podcast Schedule:** Two to three episodes ready for release, with Barrett''s episode targeting post-Thanksgiving for better audience focus.  \n- **Highlight Video:** A season one recap video using existing clips aims to engage listeners and promote season two excitement.  \n- **Content Quality Focus:** Selection criteria for highlights emphasize quality, guest impact, and audio/video clarity, despite some technical issues.  \n- **Flexible Workflows:** Just-in-time publishing allows quick release date decisions, focusing on existing content through year-end.  \n- **Team Collaboration:** Taylor’s team manages highlight video production while Nigel provides feedback, ensuring a smooth and efficient process.  \n- **Holiday Engagement:** Highlight video positioned as a holiday gift to reinforce client-vendor relationships, enhancing audience connection.","action_items":"\n**Nigel Sapp**\nSend one to two additional podcast episodes to Taylor for editing review (04:42)\nDecide on publishing timing for Barrett’s episode and notify Taylor by Monday or Wednesday of next week (06:13)\nIdentify favorite podcast episodes and key clips to be included in the highlight reel and communicate selections to Taylor (12:00)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nFinalize caption edits for Heather and Kevin’s two podcast episodes and aim to deliver by Thursday or earlier if possible (04:08)\nBegin creation of the season one highlight compilation video using best clips selected from Nigel’s favorite episodes and the discussed intro compilation concept (18:26)\nShare examples of highlight reels with Nigel for feedback and eventually share selected clips for approval before final editing (09:26)\n"},"duration":18.959999084472656,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"id":1,"name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"id":2,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"sentences":[{"text":"This meeting is being recorded.","index":0,"end_time":174.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.26,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, guys.","index":1,"end_time":189.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.19,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":189.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.27,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Good, how are you?","index":3,"end_time":191.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Doing a lot.","index":4,"end_time":195.109,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.79,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Staying busy.","index":5,"end_time":198.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just.","index":6,"end_time":200.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.99,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I mean, it''s what I expected you.","index":7,"end_time":203.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.71,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Well, sorry.","index":8,"end_time":204.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.67,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It''s good to see you both.","index":9,"end_time":205.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":204.53,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s just like particularly busy times for us because of.","index":10,"end_time":213.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":207.41,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Because of a few things and then like some big product launch announcements.","index":11,"end_time":219.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.93,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But also obviously Thanksgiving is next week, so kind of after next week, like the year stops to matter, but it matters next Thursday.","index":12,"end_time":230.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.33,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"That''s funny.","index":13,"end_time":232.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, I''m kind of in that boat and just a bit like.","index":14,"end_time":235.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.68,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, just gotta get to next.","index":15,"end_time":239.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Next week.","index":16,"end_time":239.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll see.","index":17,"end_time":243.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.84,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Anywho, anywho.","index":18,"end_time":247.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.64,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":19,"end_time":249.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me pull up our agenda here.","index":20,"end_time":252.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":249.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not too much to review with you today.","index":21,"end_time":256.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just wanted to touch base on the podcast.","index":22,"end_time":259.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":256.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the two episodes for Heather and ke, I reviewed those yesterday.","index":23,"end_time":263.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just sent them back.","index":24,"end_time":264.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":263.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"There are a couple things we need to change for the captions, but super quick edit.","index":25,"end_time":269.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we should have those two by Thursday.","index":26,"end_time":270.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if I get them any earlier, I''ll send them to you and frame in Google and then just want to touch base and see if you had any more for this month or if any more are ready to get published.","index":27,"end_time":280.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":270.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just kind of hear, hear from you on that.","index":28,"end_time":282.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":280.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes, I do have, I believe, one more that I need to send over from our guy Alan.","index":29,"end_time":288.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Maybe two more.","index":30,"end_time":290.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"One more.","index":31,"end_time":290.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.39,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Two more.","index":32,"end_time":291.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.83,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And then any more that are ready to be published.","index":33,"end_time":293.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.79,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think, I think our next one might be Barrett, who we filmed ages ago.","index":34,"end_time":302.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.79,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But yeah, because I would love to do.","index":35,"end_time":307.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.43,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I would love to publish Lynn''s episode, but.","index":36,"end_time":310.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.27,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":311.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh me, Pardon me.","index":38,"end_time":312.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.39,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I love to publish Lynn''s episode, but Lynn, I think Open Air, Open AI is going to want to watch that video.","index":39,"end_time":320.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.67,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So that''s a bit of a bummer, but so be it.","index":40,"end_time":324.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.38,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So I think next week, probably like on Wednesday, we''ll maybe go live with Barrett''s episode because love Barrett, great guy.","index":41,"end_time":335.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.34,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But if his pot.","index":42,"end_time":337.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.02,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"If his episode gets a little drowned out by the like holiday noise, I won''t be too upset about that.","index":43,"end_time":344.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.26,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Versus, like Lynn.","index":44,"end_time":345.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.73,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I do want her to get kind of a.","index":45,"end_time":348.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"A week of real focus and time.","index":46,"end_time":350.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.73,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So I''ll probably.","index":47,"end_time":352.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.53,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"We could probably go live with that like two weeks after that.","index":48,"end_time":357.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.49,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So we''ll see.","index":49,"end_time":360.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.73,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":361.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.57,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"No, no, defend.","index":51,"end_time":363.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.09,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I will let you know whether or not we should go Barrett next week or not.","index":52,"end_time":367.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.89,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But you''ll.","index":53,"end_time":368.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.45,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"We''re.","index":54,"end_time":368.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Either way, it''s easy.","index":55,"end_time":370.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.01,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Right?","index":56,"end_time":370.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.37,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like we''re just going to put it live on out, so.","index":57,"end_time":372.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.61,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":58,"end_time":373.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":372.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can tell you even Like Monday of next week, maybe.","index":59,"end_time":376.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.73,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, Day of two, if you don''t know till the day that works.","index":60,"end_time":380.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s.","index":61,"end_time":380.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":380.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s process.","index":62,"end_time":381.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.49,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So whatever is easiest for you.","index":63,"end_time":383.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":381.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, we can definitely do that.","index":64,"end_time":385.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":383.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just want to touch base there.","index":65,"end_time":386.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":66,"end_time":387.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.77,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But then other than that.","index":67,"end_time":390.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.89,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, so I have one.","index":68,"end_time":392.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I.","index":69,"end_time":392.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.37,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"One video in the.","index":70,"end_time":393.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.69,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"In the holster, I think, to pass over Heather and Kevin.","index":71,"end_time":397.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.69,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"That''s great, because I need to pass that over to Heather and Kevin so they can review, and t