text":"Sure.","index":111,"end_time":523.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.36,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I''m not gonna.","index":112,"end_time":524.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.6,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I''m not gonna say no.","index":113,"end_time":525.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.2,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, let me share.","index":114,"end_time":526.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I gotta share for sound, and then I can share these Examples.","index":115,"end_time":530,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":527.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me just.","index":116,"end_time":530.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, this is just one of my favorite things to do.","index":117,"end_time":533.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They''re fun.","index":118,"end_time":534.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":533.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s a good way to promote your podcast.","index":119,"end_time":536.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And yeah, we''ll handle everything.","index":120,"end_time":539.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":537.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Usually we just need feedback on, like, if there''s any specific themes you want us to focus on in the video or certain things we should leave out.","index":121,"end_time":552.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like if there was an episode, you''re like, no, don''t highlight that one.","index":122,"end_time":554.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":552.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or.","index":123,"end_time":555.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, just get your feedback on stuff.","index":124,"end_time":557.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":125,"end_time":560.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.89,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":126,"end_time":561.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.45,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"This is from Bailey''s podcast.","index":127,"end_time":568.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":566.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"What is your biggest content marketing ick?","index":128,"end_time":573.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.66,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Oh, that is such a juicy question.","index":129,"end_time":577.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.02,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Oh, so many.","index":130,"end_time":579.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.74,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Oh, my gosh.","index":131,"end_time":582.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.74,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I want.","index":132,"end_time":583.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.94,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I want to find something, like, super unique.","index":133,"end_time":585.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":583.42,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Oh, well, I think it would be what I just posted about in.","index":134,"end_time":589.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.9,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"In my.","index":135,"end_time":590.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.59,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"My viral LinkedIn message, which is basically fluff that is just regurgitated from God knows what AI tool.","index":136,"end_time":599.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.23,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think people that are always posting stuff like, here''s how I had a $10,000 month or a $30,000 month.","index":137,"end_time":607.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.23,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So that''s like just an example of one of them, like how you can cut together the responses.","index":138,"end_time":612.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Here''s another.","index":139,"end_time":615.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":140,"end_time":616.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":615.45,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"This one is more like Bailey sent this example me over when I had suggested maybe the season idea because the host, like, gives like a narration intro, so this one could work too.","index":141,"end_time":627.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Welcome to Synchronized, where industry leaders share expert insights on all things MSP and it the idea that what does a customer need?","index":142,"end_time":638.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.85,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Not just what do they want, but what do they really need in order to move their business forward.","index":143,"end_time":643.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.77,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And spoiler alert, IT people have not always been the best at understanding what businesses need to move forward.","index":144,"end_time":648.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.03,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"If you''re with an MSP or you''ve got one IT in house, it''s going to take some time to make that transition.","index":145,"end_time":655.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.55,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Interviewing MSPs has got to be close to interviewing dentists.","index":146,"end_time":658.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.19,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"There''s like, another example of, like, how it could be edited together.","index":147,"end_time":662.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":148,"end_time":663.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":662.63,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But yeah, so just a couple.","index":149,"end_time":666.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Couple examples of how it could look and we could do it based on also, like, what you''re thinking, like if there is a particular question you guys always ask or if we want to like, mash together a bunch of specific controllers that you had on that they talk about something specific.","index":150,"end_time":681.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":151,"end_time":681.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":682.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.21,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Any ideas there?","index":153,"end_time":685.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":682.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think probably I kind of like the second a little bit more.","index":154,"end_time":691.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I don''t think we''ve asked a question to everyone enough to.","index":155,"end_time":695.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.93,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"To have a.","index":156,"end_time":696.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.56,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"A reel like that.","index":157,"end_time":697.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.4,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So I think it would have to be just some of our best, like, like really just some of our best hits, you know, across the board and probably coming from a few of our.","index":158,"end_time":711.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.64,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Of our guest.","index":159,"end_time":713.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.36,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like, I. I can think of what were my favorite episodes.","index":160,"end_time":715.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.24,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Right.","index":161,"end_time":716.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.88,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like, probably want to put those all together and probably also do it with maybe some of our new people as well, potentially.","index":162,"end_time":725.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":716.52,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":163,"end_time":726.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.85,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":164,"end_time":726.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.33,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But.","index":165,"end_time":727.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.01,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But anyway, yeah, I mean, that sounds cool.","index":166,"end_time":731.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.01,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Sounds like a fun, fun thing to have.","index":167,"end_time":734.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.97,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Sure.","index":168,"end_time":735.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My CEO might like that.","index":169,"end_time":736.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.17,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m happy to.","index":170,"end_time":739.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"What would I say?","index":171,"end_time":742.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.49,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":172,"end_time":747.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.7,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think it''s cool.","index":173,"end_time":748.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.06,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think maybe I''ll tell you which.","index":174,"end_time":751.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.94,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Which episodes are my favorite.","index":175,"end_time":752.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.46,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Maybe that''s where we begin.","index":176,"end_time":753.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.62,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":177,"end_time":754.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.66,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":178,"end_time":755.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you want to just tell us which ones you like.","index":179,"end_time":757.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That was a great clip.","index":180,"end_time":757.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":757.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We could use that.","index":181,"end_time":758.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":757.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":759.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.5,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So I think, I think RJ and Colin were my.","index":183,"end_time":765.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.94,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Were two of my favorites for sure.","index":184,"end_time":767.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.66,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Okay.","index":185,"end_time":768.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.9,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think I''m trying to think Chris Canals, who was that was internal Chris or not internal, but Chris is a numeric employee.","index":186,"end_time":777.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.38,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I thought I liked Chris''s episode.","index":187,"end_time":779.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.63,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think Thomas Neal had a really great, strong episode.","index":188,"end_time":782.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.19,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So I put that in there.","index":189,"end_time":784.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.23,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Our first episode, Nate Carver, I think Nate Carvey did a.","index":190,"end_time":787.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.43,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Did a swell job.","index":191,"end_time":788.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.15,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So those would be my favorites.","index":192,"end_time":790.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.67,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Ruthie from Public, I think did a good job as well.","index":193,"end_time":793.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.27,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think that at times are like, her video or audio may not have been the best, but I digress.","index":194,"end_time":800.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.39,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And that''s not a comment on you guys, more of a comment on like, what.","index":195,"end_time":805.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.24,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":196,"end_time":805.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":805.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Her recording.","index":197,"end_time":807.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.36,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So those are a few of my favorites.","index":198,"end_time":809.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.88,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And although of the people upcoming, I think like, you know, we''ll go live with Lynn''s episode pretty soon.","index":199,"end_time":818.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.56,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Lynn is great.","index":200,"end_time":818.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.2,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Heather was excellent.","index":201,"end_time":820.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.88,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Everyone else is.","index":202,"end_time":823.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.61,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Is good.","index":203,"end_time":824.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.57,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So those are a few.","index":204,"end_time":825.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.77,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think we probably have good clips.","index":205,"end_time":827.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.65,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And honestly, I''m trying to think.","index":206,"end_time":832.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.05,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And then highlights.","index":207,"end_time":834.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.89,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I can''t remember the highlights from each of like, oh, that was a great thing that he said.","index":208,"end_time":838.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But yeah, and we can go through and like look at the clips that we chose and through your show notes, I know you probably called out a few that you were like, that''s a great clip.","index":209,"end_time":846.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can just go through those video snippets that we had already edited in the podcast package with the assets and.","index":210,"end_time":852.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And choose a few of those.","index":211,"end_time":853.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''d probably send them to you.","index":212,"end_time":855.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, I''d create a folder with, yeah, I think clips from each and then if you''re like, let''s switch this out with something else.","index":213,"end_time":861.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":855.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But before we like edit it and mash it together, I can send you what I think might be the best ones that we could use for each of those that you just mentioned.","index":214,"end_time":869.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":862.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Of course.","index":215,"end_time":870.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.22,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Another thing I was thinking about as well, if you were to do this is like.","index":216,"end_time":874.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.86,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like, I would almost love to have a small compilation that''s like.","index":217,"end_time":883.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":880.23,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"You see it sometimes with.","index":218,"end_time":886.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.79,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"In.","index":219,"end_time":888.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.91,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"In, like, in like someone who''s retiring from broadcast television or where they''re like.","index":220,"end_time":892.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.23,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It''s a compilation of them introducing their show, right?","index":221,"end_time":896.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.87,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like, hello, hello, hello, hello.","index":222,"end_time":898.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.11,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So from, you know, it''s like, hi, I''m Alex Trebek.","index":223,"end_time":901.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.35,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, Alex Trebek here.","index":224,"end_time":903.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.75,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hi, I''m Alex Trebek.","index":225,"end_time":904.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.15,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, everyone.","index":226,"end_time":905.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.59,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Welcome to Jeopardy.","index":227,"end_time":905.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.03,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I''m Alex Trebek.","index":228,"end_time":906.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.79,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Right.","index":229,"end_time":906.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.47,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And you can imagine a compo.","index":230,"end_time":909.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.91,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"A compilation that, like, shows him in the 80s and the 90s and the early 2000s, whatever.","index":231,"end_time":914.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.75,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And so in a way, there''s like, a bit there that I think is, you know, from.","index":232,"end_time":919.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":914.43,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"From our end of, like, Anthony has done this a number of times, right?","index":233,"end_time":925.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.39,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And there''s like the.","index":234,"end_time":926.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":925.23,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, Anthony Alvarez, and welcome to Incoming Statements.","index":235,"end_time":928.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.07,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And so I think that there''s something kind of interesting there where you''re able to have, like, Anthony doing it probably five times.","index":236,"end_time":936.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":928.63,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, I''m Anthony Alvin.","index":237,"end_time":937.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":936.12,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello.","index":238,"end_time":937.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937.32,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, I''m Anthony Alvin.","index":239,"end_time":938.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937.56,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello.","index":240,"end_time":939,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.6,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"You know, and then it''s.","index":241,"end_time":940.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.08,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And then you can add in Sam or Eli.","index":242,"end_time":942.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.2,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Right?","index":243,"end_time":942.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.48,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like, hello, I''m Sam Isaac.","index":244,"end_time":944.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.68,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Right.","index":245,"end_time":944.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.4,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And so kind of this how the season did evolve, right.","index":246,"end_time":947.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.56,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"To start with, and then move into the other guest.","index":247,"end_time":949.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.12,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like, even something like that strikes me as quite interesting where you''re able to show, you know, the repetition in the way that we start each episode.","index":248,"end_time":958.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.4,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, I''m so.","index":249,"end_time":959.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.77,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And so this is another episode of Incoming Statements.","index":250,"end_time":962.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":959.61,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I''m your host.","index":251,"end_time":963.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.45,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Oh, no.","index":252,"end_time":964.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.57,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, and welcome back to another episode of Incoming Statements.","index":253,"end_time":966.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.09,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I''m your host.","index":254,"end_time":967.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":966.97,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Right.","index":255,"end_time":968.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.05,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Like, that has been our continuation.","index":256,"end_time":970.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.41,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And then.","index":257,"end_time":971.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":970.85,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Hello, welcome back to another episode of Incoming Statements.","index":258,"end_time":974.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":971.57,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I am not Anthony Alvarez.","index":259,"end_time":975.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.13,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I am Sam Isaac.","index":260,"end_time":976.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.61,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I am Eli Geshwith.","index":261,"end_time":977.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.81,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So that.","index":262,"end_time":979.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":977.69,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"That would be cool.","index":263,"end_time":980.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":979.69,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And then maybe that''s how we start this off.","index":264,"end_time":982.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.41,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"That on the back end is like the highlight reel of all the different, you know, the different clips from people''s episodes.","index":265,"end_time":991.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.49,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a very great idea.","index":266,"end_time":994.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":992.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You''re.","index":267,"end_time":995.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You''re consistent every time.","index":268,"end_time":996.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":995.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We should get your face in there, too.","index":269,"end_time":998.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":996.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I. I did make one cameo appearance, but.","index":270,"end_time":1003.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.1,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But no, no, no.","index":271,"end_time":1005.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.58,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I think that would probably be, I think, a pretty fun, cool thing.","index":272,"end_time":1010.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.7,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":273,"end_time":1011.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1010.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can start with that for sure.","index":274,"end_time":1012.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1011.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And that''ll be the one we start with.","index":275,"end_time":1014.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if we want to pull together, like you said, the clips after that, for sure, so we can focus on, are you wanting them to be the same video?","index":276,"end_time":1021.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1014.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, like, it starts off with those hellos, and then it finishes in the same video with highlights from other episodes or two different videos.","index":277,"end_time":1030.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1021.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think I thought about it working together as one video, but, you know, you could always make them separately, and then they either exist separately or go together.","index":278,"end_time":1043.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.87,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"I don''t really know.","index":279,"end_time":1044.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.38,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"But overall, when I was saying it, like, I think it''s like you probably start with all that, and then you probably have to have, like, how Synchro kind of had that.","index":280,"end_time":1055.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1046.14,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"The.","index":281,"end_time":1057.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.86,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"The like, intro animation reel.","index":282,"end_time":1058.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.18,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"It''s like after all of.","index":283,"end_time":1061.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.82,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"After probably all of those, maybe there''s like a middle transitioning intro reel that''s like, probably just our intro reel a little bit.","index":284,"end_time":1068.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.38,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And then after that is then the clips of all the people.","index":285,"end_time":1072.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.66,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"So I don''t really know what that middle transition thing should be, but, yeah, I think that''s kind of how I envision these things all working together.","index":286,"end_time":1081.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.82,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be definitely cool to have that intro.","index":287,"end_time":1087.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think it''d be fun to edit that too, for our team, go back through and like you said, because there are different hosts too, like, as episodes went on.","index":288,"end_time":1094.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yeah, I''m gonna probably steal this idea.","index":289,"end_time":1097.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nigel, this is awesome.","index":290,"end_time":1100.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1097.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, happy to help.","index":291,"end_time":1102.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.72,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"That''s funny.","index":292,"end_time":1104.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.44,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Cool.","index":293,"end_time":1105.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.2,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"For sure.","index":294,"end_time":1106.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1106,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can get started on that, those intros, and also just compiling some clips and send that over to you.","index":295,"end_time":1113.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1106.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right on, right on.","index":296,"end_time":1115.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.72,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Sweet, guys.","index":297,"end_time":1117.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1116.32,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Well, I appreciate it.","index":298,"end_time":1118.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.04,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And yeah, we can check in next week, talk more about this, talk more about podcast stuff and.","index":299,"end_time":1126.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.13,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"And the, like.","index":300,"end_time":1127.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1126.41,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":301,"end_time":1128.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":302,"end_time":1129.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1128.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Hope you have a good rest of your week.","index":303,"end_time":1130.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, you guys as well.","index":304,"end_time":1131.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1130.65,"speaker_name":"Nigel Sapp"},{"text":"Bye.","index":305,"end_time":1132.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"dateString":"2025-11-18T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85923034376?pwd=NBFhbUd6g4vmM0MK2Nj6S8W5axpYvz.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,tierney@numeric.io,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,nigel@numeric.io","tierney@numeric.io","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","nigel@numeric.io"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KA758A13QSKSTF3119ZW7X4W","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Confirmed two podcast episodes reviewed with minor caption edits; delivery expected by Thursday.","Nigel plans to publish Barrett’s episode next week; Lynn’s delayed pending OpenAI review.","Agreed no new podcast filming through year-end due to holiday availability constraints.","Team proposed and aligned on a gifted podcast highlight video to recap season one.","Nigel identified favorite episodes for inclusion; Taylor to compile and share draft clips."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think it''s cool... maybe I''ll tell you which episodes are my favorite.","speaker":"Nigel Sapp"},{"quote":"We wanted to gift you a project that we beneficial for numeric.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"topics":["delivery","planning","creative"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T18:24:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Publishing Schedule**\n\nThe team is prioritizing publishing select podcast episodes around the Thanksgiving holiday to maximize audience focus.\n\n- **Nigel Sapp confirmed two to three upcoming episodes from Alan and Barrett are ready to publish, with Barrett’s episode tentatively set for release the week after Thanksgiving, around Wednesday, to avoid holiday noise (06:08).**  \n    - Barrett’s episode is considered a strong candidate for next week’s launch but may be delayed for better focus.  \n    - Lynn’s episode is planned to be published about two weeks after Barrett’s to ensure it receives undivided attention.  \n    - Nigel noted that no new episodes are expected to be filmed through the end of the year due to limited time and resources.  \n    - Taylor Doerbaum agreed to accommodate flexible publishing dates, even same-day decisions, to fit Nigel’s schedule.\n\n- **The team is finalizing caption edits on two episodes featuring Heather and Kevin, targeting completion by Thursday for review and publication (04:08).**  \n    - Taylor will send early versions if available prior to Thursday to accelerate the process.  \n    - Nigel aims to pass one remaining video to Heather and Kevin for review before release.  \n    - The current focus is on wrapping up existing content rather than initiating new recordings this quarter.\n\n## **Podcast Highlight Compilation Project**\n\nA strategic highlight video is being developed to promote the podcast’s first season and build hype for the second season.\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum proposed creating a season one recap highlight video using clips from existing episodes to engage new and returning listeners and boost season two anticipation (07:08).**  \n    - The concept involves mashing together key moments or recurring questions from guests to form a cohesive narrative.  \n    - Taylor shared examples from similar projects, including a format where a host asks the same question across episodes for thematic unity.  \n    - Nigel responded positively and emphasized selecting the best clips and guests rather than relying on repeated questions, citing limited consistency in questions asked.  \n    - Nigel volunteered to identify favorite episodes and key moments to guide clip selection and ensure the video highlights the strongest content.\n\n- **Nigel suggested adding a creative intro segment featuring repeated host introductions from various episodes to showcase the podcast’s evolution and personalities (14:30).**  \n    - This segment would feature multiple hosts saying their opening lines from different times, creating a nostalgic and engaging start.  \n    - Taylor endorsed this idea as a unique way to brand the highlight video and agreed to begin work on this intro first.  \n    - Nigel proposed combining this intro with the highlight reel in one video, possibly separated by a branded transition animation, to maintain flow and reinforce branding.  \n    - The implementation plan involves Taylor’s team compiling clips, creating the intro, and sending draft versions to Nigel for feedback before final editing.\n\n## **Content Curation and Guest Selection**\n\nThe selection of episodes and guests for promotion is focused on quality, guest impact, and audio/video clarity.\n\n- **Nigel identified top favorite episodes to feature in the highlight reel, including those with guests RJ, Colin, Chris Canals (a Numeric employee), Thomas Neal, Nate Carver, and Ruthie from Public (13:22).**  \n    - He noted some audio and video quality issues with certain episodes (Ruthie) but emphasized content value over technical flaws.  \n    - Newer episodes like Heather and Lynn are also considered strong candidates for inclusion upon release.  \n    - Nigel plans to provide Taylor with a list of preferred episodes and specific standout moments to guide the highlight video’s content.  \n    - Taylor will cross-reference these with existing edited clips and show notes to streamline selection and editing.\n\n## **Process and Workflow Adjustments**\n\nThe team is adapting workflows to accommodate year-end constraints and maximize impact around holidays.\n\n- **Nigel and Taylor agreed on a flexible, just-in-time publishing process for episodes around Thanksgiving, allowing quick decisions on exact release dates based on external factors like holiday noise (06:17).**  \n    - This approach avoids rigid scheduling and helps optimize audience engagement.  \n    - No new recordings are planned through the end of the year, focusing resources on post-production and promotion of existing content.  \n    - The highlight video project is a new engagement tactic intended to complement the existing publishing workflow without adding recording demands.  \n    - Nigel committed to timely communication regarding episode readiness and publishing decisions to support this flexible approach.\n\n- **Taylor’s team will handle all technical production for the highlight video, including clip selection, editing, and creation of intro segments, requiring only Nigel’s feedback for final approvals (08:50).**  \n    - This minimizes workload on the Numeric team and leverages external expertise.  \n    - Feedback loops are established for Nigel to review proposed clips and themes before final assembly.  \n    - The project is positioned as a holiday gift, reflecting a collaborative and positive client-vendor relationship.  \n    - The new process emphasizes ease, speed, and quality to maintain momentum during a busy year-end period.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Highlights","Episode Publishing","Content Compilation","Podcast Editing","Season Recap","Host Introductions"],"overview":"- **Podcast Schedule:** Two to three episodes ready for release, with Barrett''s episode targeting post-Thanksgiving for better audience focus.  \n- **Highlight Video:** A season one recap video using existing clips aims to engage listeners and promote season two excitement.  \n- **Content Quality Focus:** Selection criteria for highlights emphasize quality, guest impact, and audio/video clarity, despite some technical issues.  \n- **Flexible Workflows:** Just-in-time publishing allows quick release date decisions, focusing on existing content through year-end.  \n- **Team Collaboration:** Taylor’s team manages highlight video production while Nigel provides feedback, ensuring a smooth and efficient process.  \n- **Holiday Engagement:** Highlight video positioned as a holiday gift to reinforce client-vendor relationships, enhancing audience connection.","action_items":"\n**Nigel Sapp**\nSend one to two additional podcast episodes to Taylor for editing review (04:42)\nDecide on publishing timing for Barrett’s episode and notify Taylor by Monday or Wednesday of next week (06:13)\nIdentify favorite podcast episodes and key clips to be included in the highlight reel and communicate selections to Taylor (12:00)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nFinalize caption edits for Heather and Kevin’s two podcast episodes and aim to deliver by Thursday or earlier if possible (04:08)\nBegin creation of the season one highlight compilation video using best clips selected from Nigel’s favorite episodes and the discussed intro compilation concept (18:26)\nShare examples of highlight reels with Nigel for feedback and eventually share selected clips for approval before final editing (09:26)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"341cc64e-b8fe-48f9-83ea-fc75f7055468","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
