INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Numeric x New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Podcast Production and Publishing Schedule**

The team is prioritizing publishing select podcast episodes around the Thanksgiving holiday to maximize audience focus.

- **Nigel Sapp confirmed two to three upcoming episodes from Alan and Barrett are ready to publish, with Barrett’s episode tentatively set for release the week after Thanksgiving, around Wednesday, to avoid holiday noise (06:08).**  
    - Barrett’s episode is considered a strong candidate for next week’s launch but may be delayed for better focus.  
    - Lynn’s episode is planned to be published about two weeks after Barrett’s to ensure it receives undivided attention.  
    - Nigel noted that no new episodes are expected to be filmed through the end of the year due to limited time and resources.  
    - Taylor Doerbaum agreed to accommodate flexible publishing dates, even same-day decisions, to fit Nigel’s schedule.

- **The team is finalizing caption edits on two episodes featuring Heather and Kevin, targeting completion by Thursday for review and publication (04:08).**  
    - Taylor will send early versions if available prior to Thursday to accelerate the process.  
    - Nigel aims to pass one remaining video to Heather and Kevin for review before release.  
    - The current focus is on wrapping up existing content rather than initiating new recordings this quarter.

## **Podcast Highlight Compilation Project**

A strategic highlight video is being developed to promote the podcast’s first season and build hype for the second season.

- **Taylor Doerbaum proposed creating a season one recap highlight video using clips from existing episodes to engage new and returning listeners and boost season two anticipation (07:08).**  
    - The concept involves mashing together key moments or recurring questions from guests to form a cohesive narrative.  
    - Taylor shared examples from similar projects, including a format where a host asks the same question across episodes for thematic unity.  
    - Nigel responded positively and emphasized selecting the best clips and guests rather than relying on repeated questions, citing limited consistency in questions asked.  
    - Nigel volunteered to identify favorite episodes and key moments to guide clip selection and ensure the video highlights the strongest content.

- **Nigel suggested adding a creative intro segment featuring repeated host introductions from various episodes to showcase the podcast’s evolution and personalities (14:30).**  
    - This segment would feature multiple hosts saying their opening lines from different times, creating a nostalgic and engaging start.  
    - Taylor endorsed this idea as a unique way to brand the highlight video and agreed to begin work on this intro first.  
    - Nigel proposed combining this intro with the highlight reel in one video, possibly separated by a branded transition animation, to maintain flow and reinforce branding.  
    - The implementation plan involves Taylor’s team compiling clips, creating the intro, and sending draft versions to Nigel for feedback before final editing.

## **Content Curation and Guest Selection**

The selection of episodes and guests for promotion is focused on quality, guest impact, and audio/video clarity.

- **Nigel identified top favorite episodes to feature in the highlight reel, including those with guests RJ, Colin, Chris Canals (a Numeric employee), Thomas Neal, Nate Carver, and Ruthie from Public (13:22).**  
    - He noted some audio and video quality issues with certain episodes (Ruthie) but emphasized content value over technical flaws.  
    - Newer episodes like Heather and Lynn are also considered strong candidates for inclusion upon release.  
    - Nigel plans to provide Taylor with a list of preferred episodes and specific standout moments to guide the highlight video’s content.  
    - Taylor will cross-reference these with existing edited clips and show notes to streamline selection and editing.

## **Process and Workflow Adjustments**

The team is adapting workflows to accommodate year-end constraints and maximize impact around holidays.

- **Nigel and Taylor agreed on a flexible, just-in-time publishing process for episodes around Thanksgiving, allowing quick decisions on exact release dates based on external factors like holiday noise (06:17).**  
    - This approach avoids rigid scheduling and helps optimize audience engagement.  
    - No new recordings are planned through the end of the year, focusing resources on post-production and promotion of existing content.  
    - The highlight video project is a new engagement tactic intended to complement the existing publishing workflow without adding recording demands.  
    - Nigel committed to timely communication regarding episode readiness and publishing decisions to support this flexible approach.

- **Taylor’s team will handle all technical production for the highlight video, including clip selection, editing, and creation of intro segments, requiring only Nigel’s feedback for final approvals (08:50).**  
    - This minimizes workload on the Numeric team and leverages external expertise.  
    - Feedback loops are established for Nigel to review proposed clips and themes before final assembly.  
    - The project is positioned as a holiday gift, reflecting a collaborative and positive client-vendor relationship.  
    - The new process emphasizes ease, speed, and quality to maintain momentum during a busy year-end period.',
  '2025-11-18 18:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send one to two additional podcast episodes to Taylor for editing review (04:42)","completed":false},{"text":"Decide on publishing timing for Barrett’s episode and notify Taylor by Monday or Wednesday of next week (06:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Identify favorite podcast episodes and key clips to be included in the highlight reel and communicate selections to Taylor (12:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize caption edits for Heather and Kevin’s two podcast episodes and aim to deliver by Thursday or earlier if possible (04:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Begin creation of the season one highlight compilation video using best clips selected from Nigel’s favorite episodes and the discussed intro compilation concept (18:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Share examples of highlight reels with Nigel for feedback and eventually share selected clips for approval before final editing (09:26)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Ponce bank - Hubspot Series: Product, Service & Operations (2025-11-20 19:00:15+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '059db008-bde9-43e2-b5ea-2d8080194a92',
    '2025-11-20 19:00:15+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KAHA708A841HVB1NKN5B6R0Y',
    'Ponce bank - Hubspot Series: Product, Service & Operations',
    NULL,
    3468,
    NULL,
    '{"id":"01KAHA708A841HVB1NKN5B6R0Y","title":"Ponce bank - Hubspot Series: Product, Service & Operations","summary":{"notes":"## **Customer Journey and Lead Management**\n\nThe team agreed that current customer journeys are fragmented and overly complex, and simplifying them will improve lead qualification and conversion.\n\n- **Valerie highlighted** that the existing website requires too many clicks and has siloed areas like Mortgage World and Ponce Bank Foundation, confusing customers and slowing navigation (10:53)  \n    - This fragmentation leads to a disjointed experience that hampers customer engagement and brand clarity  \n    - Christina explained the plan to unify these siloed sites into a single platform to better track customer interests and improve user flow  \n    - The goal is to enable customers to reach key journeys within one or two clicks from the homepage  \n    - This consolidation will also help marketing better understand customer behavior and needs\n\n- **Lead qualification challenges** in the mortgage area were discussed by Sunita, who noted that about **95% of the 300 national leads received recently were fake** with invalid contacts, wasting sales resources (18:00)  \n    - Currently, lead validation is manual and time-consuming, requiring sales to call and verify each lead  \n    - Marketing aims to automate lead nurturing for inquiries, reserving sales efforts for warm leads only  \n    - Christina emphasized the need for more educational content on the website to reduce unqualified lead volume and better prepare prospects  \n    - Automated workflows will nurture leads digitally until they are sales-ready, improving efficiency\n\n- **Post-sale customer journeys and cross-selling** are largely manual and disconnected (14:00)  \n    - Wilma shared that welcome letters and account onboarding are manual and could benefit from automation  \n    - Sales teams currently do not receive automatic alerts about customers’ new accounts or products, limiting cross-sell opportunities  \n    - The team sees an opportunity to trigger targeted marketing based on product ownership and customer actions, such as deposits or mortgage applications  \n    - This approach aims to grow wallet share organically without increasing manual workload\n\n## **Product and Service Organization**\n\nSimplifying product presentation and terminology on the website is critical to improve customer understanding and reduce overwhelm.\n\n- **Sunita and Victor are leading** efforts to simplify the residential mortgage section by sunsetting the confusing Mortgage World domain and integrating mortgage content directly under Ponce Bank (27:50)  \n    - The new structure focuses on simplicity and avoiding jargon to better serve customers unfamiliar with banking terms  \n    - A clean product taxonomy and hierarchy will help users quickly find relevant products without drilling through many pages  \n    - Christina stressed the need for consistent naming across all products to prevent confusion, especially between residential mortgages and commercial loans  \n    - The team will collect product specs, rate sheets, and other details to ensure accuracy during website build\n\n- **Organizing community and educational content** as a separate section on the website is planned, combining financial literacy programs, events, and investor relations (32:30)  \n    - This approach aims to increase site traffic by hosting more content directly rather than via social media or email  \n    - Jag manages investor relations content, which is seen as a product offering for investors and will be integrated thoughtfully  \n    - The content workshop tomorrow will focus on messaging and storytelling to make products and services more cohesive  \n\n- **Financial Mastery program improvements** include simplifying participant data collection and moving away from external platforms like Zoom for registrations (32:15)  \n    - This will streamline internal workflows and create a better user experience  \n\n## **Data Integration and Automation Opportunities**\n\nUsing customer data to trigger personalized marketing journeys and automate processes is a key goal for the HubSpot implementation.\n\n- **Tristan outlined** plans to leverage HubSpot data to identify customer behaviors and trigger cross-sell or upsell offers based on product ownership and transactions (38:00)  \n    - Examples include targeting customers who make large deposits with CD offers or mortgage customers with deposit product promotions  \n    - Automation will reduce manual effort for marketing and sales teams and generate organic growth  \n    - A phased approach is necessary due to data complexity, system integration needs, and compliance requirements  \n\n- **Current challenges** include data siloing and manual lead tracking, especially between Salesforce, loan origination systems (LOS), and marketing databases (47:30)  \n    - Wilma tracks leads manually across LOS and Salesforce to reconcile discrepancies and improve accuracy  \n    - There is an existing patch from LOS to Salesforce, but it is not seamless and requires ongoing work to automate fully  \n    - The team aims to build end-to-end lead tracking from campaign click through application conversion  \n    - Monitoring and improving these integrations is critical for accurate performance measurement and efficient lead management\n\n- **CRA compliance limits product promotion timing**, so marketing must carefully separate educational content from product marketing (40:45)  \n    - Educational programming aims to raise awareness and generate leads without direct sales pressure  \n    - After compliance periods, marketing can promote products more directly  \n    - This distinction shapes content strategy and automation rules\n\n## **Performance Tracking and Reporting**\n\nImproving marketing performance metrics and reporting to link activities to revenue is a top priority for 2026.\n\n- **Tristan shared** that currently marketing reports focus on engagement metrics like clicks and registrations but lack direct ties to revenue or account openings (47:00)  \n    - Executives want clear KPIs such as number of loans, deposits, account openings, and related dollars  \n    - The plan is to build dashboards showing high-level revenue metrics supported by engagement data for deeper insights  \n    - Integrating campaign data with Salesforce and LOS through MuleSoft will enable tracking customer journeys from prospect to customer  \n    - This will help justify marketing spend and demonstrate business impact\n\n- **Desiree and other business areas** track loan pipelines and processing through platforms like GPS and CREW, which integrate partially with Salesforce (52:45)  \n    - The team will coordinate with IT and leadership to map these data flows and fill gaps with custom fields or code if needed  \n    - This will ensure lead and loan tracking supports marketing and sales alignment\n\n- **Nonprofit and external affairs teams** are piloting automation workflows in HubSpot to improve efficiency and are key early adopters for process improvements (54:40)  \n    - Lessons learned here will inform broader rollout across teams  \n\n## **Project Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe discovery phase continues with a deliverable planned for the end of April 2026, providing a roadmap for content, design, and build phases.\n\n- **Tristan emphasized** that findings from these workshops will feed into a comprehensive plan to guide the website and CRM build (03:00)  \n    - The next workshop focuses on content, messaging, and user experience to complement today’s taxonomy and journey discussions  \n    - Additional workshops will address foundation, investor relations, and Policy Bank Direct micro-sites within the main site umbrella  \n    - Victor is the point person for internal questions and document collection, with follow-up emails expected by end of day tomorrow (56:30)  \n    - The phased approach will prioritize what is feasible for go-live versus longer-term enhancements  \n    - The team will maintain ongoing collaboration to refine customer journeys, product organization, and data strategies through the project lifecycle","outline":null,"keywords":["Customer Journeys","Product Taxonomy","Marketing Automation","HubSpot Implementation","Lead Qualification","Website Consolidation"],"overview":"- **Customer Journey Improvement:** Simplifying customer journeys will enhance lead qualification and conversion, reducing complexity and confusion.  \n- **High Lead Fraud Rate:** 95% of 300 recent mortgage leads were invalid, highlighting the need for automated lead validation.  \n- **Post-Sale Automation:** Manual onboarding and alerts limit cross-selling; automating these processes can enhance marketing opportunities.  \n- **Product Simplification:** Streamlined product terminology will improve understanding, with plans to integrate mortgage content directly under Ponce Bank.  \n- **Data Integration Goals:** Using HubSpot data will automate personalized marketing and improve tracking across platforms like Salesforce and LOS.  \n- **Performance Metrics Focus:** The aim is to connect marketing activities directly to revenue by enhancing tracking and reporting capabilities.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Santana**\nReceive and incorporate mortgage world content format from internal team and integrate it into the Ponce Bank website structure (26:37)\nCoordinate with Christina and team to gather product specifications, rate sheets, promotional materials from all departments for website and HubSpot content development (30:53)\nDevelop marketing automation workflows and customer journey maps, incorporating feedback and distributed to participants for review (22:09)\nFollow up on issues with LOS patch integration to Salesforce and assist in exploring API or MuleSoft integration improvements (50:01)\nCollaborate with IT (Ashley) and Victor to review existing data flows and integrations for lead and product data (53:16)\nFacilitate email communications requesting documentation and inputs from product owners by end of day following meeting (57:20)\nImplement dashboards to report campaign engagement and business impact metrics aligned with sales results (47:01)\n\n**Victor**\nServe as primary point of contact for collecting Ponce Bank team inputs and queries for project (57:20)\nCoordinate with Tristan and internal resources on integrating various tracking systems like GPS and LOS with marketing and sales databases (53:16)\n\n**Christina**\nClarify product/service definitions and collaborate on simplifying website content and language for better customer comprehension (26:37)\nMonitor compliance requirements for CRA educational materials and define timelines for marketing outreach to CRA segments (40:00)\nAssist in defining manual versus automated touchpoints in post-onboarding customer journey to augment customer service (36:53)\n\n**Product and Team Representatives**\nProvide product matrices, marketing collateral, terms and rate sheets for respective product lines to marketing team promptly (30:53)\nIdentify key customer journeys and pain points in existing website navigation and share relevant customer insights (07:08)\n"},"duration":57.79999923706055,"speakers":[],"sentences":[{"text":"On.","index":0,"end_time":0.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, Colin''s on vacation, so he.","index":1,"end_time":1.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":0.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":2,"end_time":2.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hopefully he''s not joining.","index":3,"end_time":4.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, no.","index":4,"end_time":5.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":5.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Would definitely not expect that.","index":5,"end_time":7.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":5.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":6,"end_time":9.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":8.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We do have a.","index":7,"end_time":10.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":9.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A packed agenda.","index":8,"end_time":11.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":10.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what I''m going to say is we''ll give it another minute, Justin, for everyone to join, and I''ll just kind of tee up for everyone.","index":9,"end_time":19.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":11.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What we''re going to focus on today.","index":10,"end_time":20.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":19.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you want to bring up the.","index":11,"end_time":25.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":22.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The agenda.","index":12,"end_time":26.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":26.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We can also do that.","index":13,"end_time":27.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":26.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So today is our second of three workshops where we''re going to bring key people together to discuss certain necessary requirements and components for our HubSpot and website project.","index":14,"end_time":42.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":28.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Today''s call is going to be focusing on Kirby Femoral, the products and services after operations.","index":15,"end_time":49.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":43.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":16,"end_time":50.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":50.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This one.","index":17,"end_time":51.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":51.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":18,"end_time":52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so you are all on the call today because you in some way, shape or form have been identified as either a product owner or someone that, you know, works with certain products or has knowledge of our product services or operations and procedures.","index":19,"end_time":71.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":53.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so we are trying our best as we go through this process to bring everyone in the room in order to be able to have decisions made, understand, you know, kind of how Ponce does things.","index":20,"end_time":84.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":71.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we make sure that we build that into the.","index":21,"end_time":86.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":84.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The project plan and take into account anything that, you know, you guys might be working on, anything that maybe we can do better.","index":22,"end_time":92.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":86.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And.","index":23,"end_time":93.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":93.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so at the end of the day, when we implement HubSpot and the website, we have something that we''re all going to be, you know, collectively happy with.","index":24,"end_time":101.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":93.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s kind of the goal of bringing us all together.","index":25,"end_time":104.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":102.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have our agency on marketers in demand.","index":26,"end_time":108.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":105.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s your.","index":27,"end_time":109.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":108.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"See, Tristan, and I apologize.","index":28,"end_time":114.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":109.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have a new.","index":29,"end_time":115.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":115,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How do you pronounce your name?","index":30,"end_time":118.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":116.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is it G?","index":31,"end_time":118.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":118.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s G. G. Okay.","index":32,"end_time":123.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":120.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have G on, and she''s a new face for the agency to help with this project.","index":33,"end_time":127.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":123.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then, like I said, various members of our team.","index":34,"end_time":131.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":129,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we don''t have time to necessarily go through introductions.","index":35,"end_time":135.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":131.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But please, when something that you feel you have value to add comes up, just please chime in, especially if a question is directed to your product area.","index":36,"end_time":144.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":136.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So without further ado, I''ll turn it over to Tristan.","index":37,"end_time":147.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":145.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"He''ll go through the agenda, and then like I said, if anything comes up questions, please, just chime in.","index":38,"end_time":154.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":147.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, well, thank you, Christina.","index":39,"end_time":157.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can everyone see my screen?","index":40,"end_time":158.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can you see it, Christina?","index":41,"end_time":160.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I just want to make sure it''s shown.","index":42,"end_time":161.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, so we got the agenda pulled up, and like Christina mentioned a second ago, this is the second workshop in a series of three that dives into really specific areas that we''re looking to uncover more information and build upon some of the survey responses that we received.","index":43,"end_time":178.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I did want to, before I get into the agenda itself, I just did want to jump over to our high level project plan so you get a sense of where we are in the grand scheme of things.","index":44,"end_time":189.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We covered this in yesterday''s meeting as well.","index":45,"end_time":191.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But for those that weren''t in attendance there we have tasks outline through towards the end of April 2026.","index":46,"end_time":200.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And right now we are in the midst of the discovery and audit phase of the project.","index":47,"end_time":205.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And this is the HubSpot Implementation Project which encompasses really two key components.","index":48,"end_time":212.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The CRM itself, which is the data, the customer data that we''re able to track for marketing purposes and get information from other sources at Ponce Bank.","index":49,"end_time":222.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then the other piece is the website itself, which is the external facing marketing flavor of the product itself.","index":50,"end_time":231.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s what allows us to connect with prospects and customers on the outside part of the project is consolidating a lot of different website entities that we have now and assets into one cohesive view for Ponce Ponce Bank.","index":51,"end_time":246.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s what we''ll get into some today around the products and services, get an understanding of some of the gaps that we have, we want to explore and make that a little bit more seamless for both prospects and customers moving forward.","index":52,"end_time":260.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So today I just want to mention.","index":53,"end_time":263.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sorry, one thing.","index":54,"end_time":264.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for everyone on the call, I just want to be clear.","index":55,"end_time":267.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":264.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when we think about this system, HubSpot, it''s essentially our marketing system.","index":56,"end_time":272.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you may hear the term CRM floated around, but that''s not to be confused with Salesforce.","index":57,"end_time":278.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":272.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Salesforce is still going to be our system of record, right, for everything that we do on the account downside.","index":58,"end_time":284.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":278.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But sometimes marketers do refer to HubSpot as a CRM also.","index":59,"end_time":289.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":284.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But essentially what we''re looking to use HubSpot is, is to be that central place where we''re going to store data, marketing campaigns, you know, things that will help us make more informed decisions, cross sell opportunities, email marketing, social media, and also, you know, obviously our website management.","index":60,"end_time":309.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":289.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I just wanted to clear that up in case anyone was not aware of how we''re going to kind of use the system in tandem with Salesforce.","index":61,"end_time":316.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":309.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, thanks for that, Christina.","index":62,"end_time":320.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s big picture and where we are at the moment.","index":63,"end_time":323.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then really a lot of the findings that we have in these workshops and then some of the research that we''ve done already and the conversations we''ve had and the survey responses will get rolled into a deliverable that we have planned for the end of the month that we''ll distribute to the team.","index":64,"end_time":339.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s what will effectively kickstart a lot of what we do on the content, strategy, design, and then actually on the build side with both the CRM and the website itself.","index":65,"end_time":348.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, let me jump over to now.","index":66,"end_time":353.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So workshop two, like we mentioned a second ago, this focuses on the product, service and operations area.","index":67,"end_time":359.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And you know, the, the key component for today is to really talk about some of the operations from a customer standpoint.","index":68,"end_time":368.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we''re, we''re excited to get some of your feedback around some of the, the key customer journeys that we have in play.","index":69,"end_time":375.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What gaps do we have?","index":70,"end_time":377.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If you think about from a digital perspective, what gaps do we have on the marketing side, what information is lacking on the educational side, what can we enhance for both prospects and customers?","index":71,"end_time":389.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We want to get that from an intake perspective today so that we can incorporate when we go to develop the actual information architecture for the new site that we''ll build.","index":72,"end_time":399.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''ll get into some of the customer journeys, get your feedback, there''s, and then dive into some of the products and services that we need to either build out further and get more detail or to incorporate in the new website.","index":73,"end_time":412.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we''ll also talk about the hierarchy of information and any thoughts around what needs to be featured more prominently and perhaps what doesn''t even exist now externally that we need to consider folding in as well.","index":74,"end_time":427.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I thought I would start with customer journey mapping and, and to really try to get into some of the key journeys that we envision for the website itself.","index":75,"end_time":439.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I thought I would just ask, to throw this question out there, if you all could really present or pinpoint four to five key customer journeys that do stretch across a digital experience and then within a bank branch itself, what do you think those four to five journeys would be?","index":76,"end_time":462.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And perhaps what are the gaps that exist right now?","index":77,"end_time":467.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And the reason we ask is because whatever those primary journeys are, we want to make sure that we do make very easily accessible right away from the homepage that people are able to, you know, within one to two clicks get to where they need to go.","index":78,"end_time":482.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll start there.","index":79,"end_time":483.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Christine, I don''t know if there''s someone or, you know, a team that we should start with, but I was.","index":80,"end_time":490.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":484.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Going to actually say it might be helpful for everyone on the line if you maybe give an example or just explain kind of what a journey is, because it''s somewhat of a marketing kind of term and we haven''t historically done a lot of customer journey and segmentation.","index":81,"end_time":506.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":490.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''m not necessarily sure if everyone''s familiar with that, but I''m sure if once you explain that they might, you know, something might connect.","index":82,"end_time":512.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":506.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sure.","index":83,"end_time":513.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when we think about a journey, it''s really when a customer thinks about, you know, solving a problem or searching for a product, whether that be online or from peers and colleagues, etc.","index":84,"end_time":527.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But they, they have identified a need on their side, they''re looking for a solution and then all of a sudden, you know, they, they do come upon Ponce Bank.","index":85,"end_time":537.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s where the journey really starts.","index":86,"end_time":539.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Once they have identified Ponce as being a possible fit for whatever that that need is.","index":87,"end_time":546.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It could be a personal bank account.","index":88,"end_time":549,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, if you''re a small business, maybe you''re looking for a partner financial institution to partner with.","index":89,"end_time":555.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"On the small business banking side, perhaps you''re looking for working capital, SBA loan, etc.","index":90,"end_time":561.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But once you then arrive on Ponce Bank''s website or come in contact with the brand, that''s like that first initial reaction or first impression, first activity, what happens after that, how do we get that person from a prospect or you know, a pre customer, how do we get them to get more information about a product or service and then how do we ultimately convert that individual or small business into a customer so that they''re actually on the revenue generating side.","index":91,"end_time":596.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I guess in broad terms that''s how we, we think about it is really, you know, starting from a prospect, someone who is slightly unaware of Ponce bank or unaware of a specific solution and then ultimately getting them to become a customer.","index":92,"end_time":611.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So did that help Christina?","index":93,"end_time":615.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I think that that helps me, me and it''s a good overview.","index":94,"end_time":621.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":616.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, I''ll give a minute for anyone that wants to, to jump in and then you know, if there''s no comments, I''ll, I''ll kind of chime in with what I think is, is our customer journey and then that might help people kind of chime in.","index":95,"end_time":636.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":622.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll give it a second, I''ll pause and does anyone have anything to add in that regard?","index":96,"end_time":642.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":636.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or if you don''t feel comfortable, you could also type it in in the chat as well.","index":97,"end_time":645.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":642.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hi everyone, this is Valerie, I''m director of External affairs here.","index":98,"end_time":653.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think the journey at the moment seems pretty self explanatory, but considering how the website is currently set up, I think that there''s a lot of clicks that need to be done before you get to exactly what you need.","index":99,"end_time":672.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that for example, like we have different areas of the bank.","index":100,"end_time":678.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have mortgage world bankers, we have Ponce bank, we have foundation.","index":101,"end_time":681.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And not everything is set up in one location.","index":102,"end_time":685.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That kind of really says everything that Bonse bank is and then leads you to the other sites.","index":103,"end_time":691.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I think the journey might be a little bit confusing there for the customer because I think that the person would want to, if they come in contact with Monster bank, they would like to just kind of right away see, okay, what does this bank have and what do they have to offer and kind of quickly be able to navigate and get to where they want to be.","index":104,"end_time":712.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, that, that''s a, that''s a great point, Val.","index":105,"end_time":716.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":714.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I think that that''s one of the biggest things that I noticed and, you know, in my assessment when I first joined, you know, we have a lot of things to offer, but it''s often a disjointed experience.","index":106,"end_time":725.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":716.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so one of the things that we''re looking to do is kind of integrate all of the different siloed websites that we have into one unified website where the customer could kind of, you know, explore within the one site, and then it''ll give us a better understanding of really what they''re interested in.","index":107,"end_time":742.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":726.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, so like regular products and services on the consumer side, also on the commercial and, you know, lending side, residential lending, foundation even, and investor relations are all going to be kind of integrated into this one site.","index":108,"end_time":757.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":743.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if you notice, you have, you know, people that currently manage a lot of those things on, on this, on this call.","index":109,"end_time":764.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":757.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What I, what I will add is that I think, Tristan, for you, we have a lot of traditional kind of touch points.","index":110,"end_time":773.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":764.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, we have our sales teams, we have our external affairs teams, we have business development folks, we have branches.","index":111,"end_time":781.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":774.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And a lot of times we develop relationships with customers in the community and then we kind of nurture the lead process somewhat manual.","index":112,"end_time":792.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":782.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":113,"end_time":792.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":792.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so it takes a lot of effort from the individuals to, you know, get a lead from any source.","index":114,"end_time":799.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":792.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":115,"end_time":800.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":799.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Either from an event, from a scanned form that might have been where a customer interpreting some information from a virtual webinar, or even from a form that we have.","index":116,"end_time":811.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so it''s somewhat of a disjointed process because a lot of those leads fall through the cracks, maybe because they''re either not necessarily ready to close or it''s just because there''s a lot of things that are going on and the teams don''t always get to them.","index":117,"end_time":829.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":812.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so one of the things that I think that we can have the opportunity to do is, is define a Process where the front facing staff, anyone that''s going to be actually working with a customer, gets more qualified leads through this process and marketing nurtures more of the leads that come in where they''re just of interest.","index":118,"end_time":847.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":829.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":119,"end_time":848.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":847.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so that''s one of the things that I want everybody to kind of weigh in on, you know, what your experience has been so far with the leads process.","index":120,"end_time":858.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":849.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s one thing.","index":121,"end_time":859.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":858.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then second thing, there''s journeys that need to happen even after the customer closes the account or opens the account.","index":122,"end_time":870.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":860.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":123,"end_time":870.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":870.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I say close because closing is like a loan terminology.","index":124,"end_time":873.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":870.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But when they actually become a customer, there''s other marketing journeys and cross sell opportunities and touch points that are not happening today that we often lose opportunities on.","index":125,"end_time":884.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":873.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So marketing is looking for you guys to start to think about, you know, once a customer onboards, is there things that you want us to automate that would help you guys better service the customer, better cross sell your products and services and just overall growth of the share wallet for the customer.","index":126,"end_time":901.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":884.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So as we go through, those are some of the things that you guys should start to think about when you think about the setup of journeys.","index":127,"end_time":907.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":901.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I guess based off of that, does anybody have any, you know, ideas?","index":128,"end_time":919.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":914.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, we can start with, you know, Val on your side, you know, because you guys are more customer facing.","index":129,"end_time":926.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":920.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":130,"end_time":926.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":926.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when you think about a customer and they open up an account, what are some of the things that, you know, maybe you do manually now that could be automated or some of the touch points that are not happening right now that maybe could help your team and the customer?","index":131,"end_time":941.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":926.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, you brought up great points.","index":132,"end_time":945.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that for us is even a little bit more peeled back because we''re not necessarily the ones that would like, we would bring in more of a referral and that would kind of go fall more into the sales team.","index":133,"end_time":957.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I think that in our case, the journey could be a little bit more like the handoff follow up piece.","index":134,"end_time":963.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the follow up piece will be very important for external affairs because, you know, we''re going to make that connection and put them in the right, you know, place or house it in the right location.","index":135,"end_time":971.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":963.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then that team would have to be the one that would do the push there to kind of bring in and close the customer, like you said.","index":136,"end_time":979.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":137,"end_time":980.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Tristan, that''s a good point.","index":138,"end_time":982.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":980.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when you think of the journey mapping, it''s not just necessarily the customer journey, but it''s also the flow from our teams.","index":139,"end_time":989.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":982.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''ll be something that we would build in as a bidirectional back to Salesforce in setting up some of the sales components and lead generation.","index":140,"end_time":999.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":989.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s probably more of a sidebar conversation but good point.","index":141,"end_time":1006.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":999.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know Val, for, for today because there is a difference between the Legion and the actually the sales cycle, so to speak.","index":142,"end_time":1014.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1006.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know we have a couple of lending folks on the the line.","index":143,"end_time":1019.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1016.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Christina, I can, I can weigh in basically referring to what you were saying about the lead and the journey.","index":144,"end_time":1030.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1021.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What we get now I''ll tell you that first is we.","index":145,"end_time":1036.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1032.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s the difference between a warm lead and just an inquiry perhaps.","index":146,"end_time":1040.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1036.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And the feedback I''ve gotten from the sales team is that sometimes it''s not even a real lead, never mind a warm lead.","index":147,"end_time":1051.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1041.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And what happens, it''s like a fake phone number or so the sales team is taking the time to call and you know, every call actually ends up taking at minimum 15 minutes to sort it out and to stop what you''re doing and so forth.","index":148,"end_time":1068.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1051.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s a feedback of what we have now.","index":149,"end_time":1072.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1068.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I do agree with what you''re saying as far as like if it''s an inquiry versus a warm lead, the warm lead would be passed on to us right away and the inquiries could be what is nurtured through the marketing effort, if that makes sense.","index":150,"end_time":1087.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1072.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":151,"end_time":1089.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Sunia, if is it Sunita?","index":152,"end_time":1092.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yes.","index":153,"end_time":1092.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1092.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":1093.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1092.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If I may, what are some of those products and services?","index":155,"end_time":1096.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the, the lead for like what specifically are they searching for and kind of what from your perspective there?","index":156,"end_time":1104.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, so for my area it''s residential mortgages.","index":157,"end_time":1107.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1104.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s inquiring about first time home buyer information or just the process to apply or get pre approved and so forth.","index":158,"end_time":1121.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1109.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But we do, you know, I''m jumping ahead maybe but we do plan on expanding our market area more to national and for a little while I think we had something turned on and we, it, you know from our reporting it looks like we got like 300 leads and basically like you know, 95 of them were like bought the bot ones or something because they were not real.","index":159,"end_time":1150.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1121.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They were not real phone numbers, they were like fake email addresses, things like that.","index":160,"end_time":1155.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1150.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s been our experience.","index":161,"end_time":1158.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1157.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And right now how, how is that determination made as to whether it''s real or fake?","index":162,"end_time":1164.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is there like enrichment done?","index":163,"end_time":1165.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is there testing or, or is it literally a phone call that''s made to determine that?","index":164,"end_time":1170.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, it''s hands on.","index":165,"end_time":1173.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1171.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So like we have a point person that gets the leads, it''s passed on to us through from the website and you know, if they look at, at the email address and you could tell that it''s not, it''s like a, a curse word or a weird word.","index":166,"end_time":1193.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1173.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it doesn''t have.com or.net or something like that.","index":167,"end_time":1197.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1193.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They can tell right off the bat.","index":168,"end_time":1199.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1197.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that one is like not going to be entertained.","index":169,"end_time":1201.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1199.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But if it has a phone number, it''s passed on to one of our sales, one of our loan officers, and they''re actually taking the time to stop what they''re doing, get on the phone and call, and then even if there''s no answer, they''re calling again.","index":170,"end_time":1216.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1202.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, so it is time consuming when our bandwidth is not dedicated to that.","index":171,"end_time":1224.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1217.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''d much rather have them spend time on the warm leads.","index":172,"end_time":1228.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1224.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":173,"end_time":1229.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1229.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we, you know, from a high level standpoint, we get more inquiries and not warm leads than we do warm leads.","index":174,"end_time":1239.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1229.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":175,"end_time":1240.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Christina, I won''t speak for you, but like, that is one of the, the things that we''re looking for is to find those, find those opportunities where perhaps, you know, someone does fill out a contact form, maybe there is a nurture sequence that we can still put in to provide more education around whatever that specific product was that they were searching for.","index":176,"end_time":1261.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can we give some, some, some background information, educate a bit to where we can convert them into more of a warmer state so that it does make sense to engage.","index":177,"end_time":1271.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So those are the types of things that we would probably be looking for but didn''t want to speak for you.","index":178,"end_time":1275.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, no, you hit the nail on the head.","index":179,"end_time":1277.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1276.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I think one of the things that''s lacking on our website right now is it''s not educational enough in nature.","index":180,"end_time":1284.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1277.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so sometimes because of that, plus the fact that it''s a lot of siloed, you know, information and experience, the customer can''t necessarily find basic things.","index":181,"end_time":1293.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1284.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then they''re filling out these lead forms and they, they really just want information, but they''re not necessarily ready for the actual sales rep to speak with them.","index":182,"end_time":1302.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1293.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so one of the things that we want to do to be more effective marketing partners is going to get ahead of some of that stuff and take that load off the, the team so you guys can focus on, you know, actually closing the deals.","index":183,"end_time":1314.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1302.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":184,"end_time":1314.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1314.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so that''s kind of the, the way the relationship between sales and marketing is supp.","index":185,"end_time":1318.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1314.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I''m not specifically talking about Maria''s team, but it''s more just like anyone that, you know, is, is in a role where you''re closing accounts or deals, right?","index":186,"end_time":1326.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1318.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s the, the goal.","index":187,"end_time":1329.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1327.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So as you go through this process, you''re gonna See a lot of recommendations for journeys that''ll have marketing building out workflows that''ll essentially be okay if this happens.","index":188,"end_time":1341.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1329.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, they go into this journey for communication.","index":189,"end_time":1345.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1341.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":190,"end_time":1345.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1345.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And all those things will just be automated until either, you know, the, the customer closes, you know, an account or, you know, maybe they decide that they don''t want to get those communications anymore.","index":191,"end_time":1357.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1345.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Another thing that we''re going to be able to do with the website, and I''ll kind of just stop at this point, because I want to be conscious of time, is that we''re going to be able to.","index":192,"end_time":1366.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1357.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Since the website is being built into HubSpot and we have data in the system, we''re going to be able to understand where the customer is spending time on the website, what links they''re clicking.","index":193,"end_time":1375.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1366.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then those links could even be kind of mapped to journeys, because if they''re clicking on lending information or apply now for a career or, you know, let me get information on investor relations.","index":194,"end_time":1392.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1376.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":195,"end_time":1392.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1392.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, we''re gonna be able to put them into different categories and, you know, once we kind of determine if you''re okay with us communicating with them, because I know there''s still certain regulations around certain communications and when they can happen and when they can''t happen, but then we can set those up and we''ll partner with you.","index":196,"end_time":1409.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1392.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So today is just to kind of get that thought process started as we go through this project.","index":197,"end_time":1415.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1409.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, marketing is going to have a.","index":198,"end_time":1417.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1415.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A map of different journeys built out.","index":199,"end_time":1420.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1417.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll share that with the team, and you''ll have the ability to kind of weigh in, you know, either add, remove, or, you know, or make decisions on how we communicate with the customers.","index":200,"end_time":1431.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1420.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But it''s pretty exciting because it''ll give us a lot of opportunities to do things automatically and be less reactionary.","index":201,"end_time":1437.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1431.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll leave it at that.","index":202,"end_time":1439.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1437.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And if there''s no other kind of thoughts or ideas on the journey mapping, Tristan, I''ll let you move on to the next topic.","index":203,"end_time":1446.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1440.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sure.","index":204,"end_time":1447.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The next big area is really product and service configuration.","index":205,"end_time":1451.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1448.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And this really are two sides to this.","index":206,"end_time":1456.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"One is externally, how do we organize information that is back to one of the original points in the meeting?","index":207,"end_time":1464.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1456.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How do we prevent someone from going five, six levels deep on the website to try to uncover what they''re.","index":208,"end_time":1469.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1464.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They''re really looking for?","index":209,"end_time":1470.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1469.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How do we bubble that up to the top?","index":210,"end_time":1473.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1470.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The.","index":211,"end_time":1473.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1473.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The most important starting points for a journey?","index":212,"end_time":1476.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1473.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How do we get those very visible right away on the homepage or in the header navigation?","index":213,"end_time":1483.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s one piece.","index":214,"end_time":1484.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1483.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Why product and service Configuration is important and then the other component is what information do we have around customers now that we can potentially kick off a workflow or an offer when they do land on the page like Christina mentioned.","index":215,"end_time":1499.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, if a, if an existing customer that is in HubSpot and they''re recognized, they''ve accepted cookies that come to the Ponsse bank website, if they''re on, you know, small business website or small business banking services.","index":216,"end_time":1515.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then you know, can we have an offer on the personal side?","index":217,"end_time":1519.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, is there, you know a consumer product that we can get in front of them?","index":218,"end_time":1523.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1520.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There, there are some ways that we could cross sell upsell with the individual contact that, that does arrive to the site.","index":219,"end_time":1531.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1524.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So those are some things to think through that we can do on the technical side, but it''s more about like on the business process.","index":220,"end_time":1537.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1531.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What, what are some opportunities that you all see or maybe you''re unable to, to take advantage of right now that perhaps we could built out on our side on the, on the HubSpot implementation side.","index":221,"end_time":1549.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1537.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll start there.","index":222,"end_time":1551.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1550.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe we just look at the product taxonomy itself.","index":223,"end_time":1554.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like how do you all feel products are organized right now on the website?","index":224,"end_time":1558.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1554.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What are some of the ways you would like to see it organized for customers and then we can go from there.","index":225,"end_time":1565.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1558.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I, it''s, it''s Sunita again for mortgage.","index":226,"end_time":1571.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1567.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ve been speaking to Victor and Jane about this to some degree and they''ve given Christina feedback as well.","index":227,"end_time":1580.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1571.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"As far as the website goes, my, my big thing is mortgage is overwhelming in general to most people and I think that the simpler the better like as far as the flow and everything.","index":228,"end_time":1597.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1580.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And basically when I look at our page, it''s overwhelming and if it''s overwhelming to me and this is my everyday life, I can''t imagine what it''s like for a customer that has no contacts to finance and business and mortgage and financial stuff like that.","index":229,"end_time":1618.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1597.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it''s not their everyday business.","index":230,"end_time":1620.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1619.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you know, I have been spending time with Victor and, and, and Jane too work on a way that it''s user friendly, consumer friendly and, and streamlined.","index":231,"end_time":1635.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1621.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I think the biggest thing is keeping it simple and using words that they understand because that''s one of the other things that we tend to use mortgage work a lot and a customer doesn''t necessarily know what that means.","index":232,"end_time":1648.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1635.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''m trying to think of it from their perspective and what, when they''re looking at the website I want them to know what, what we''re talking about.","index":233,"end_time":1656.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1649.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Tristan, what I''m going to do on My end is I created a format for the, for the new mortgage world side of things for what we currently have on Bonser Bank.","index":234,"end_time":1666.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1658.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll send that over to you.","index":235,"end_time":1668.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1666.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That was already agreed upon by Sunita and Christina.","index":236,"end_time":1671.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1668.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s just a matter of us actually creating the text for it, but the infrastructure of it was there because she liked the simplicity of what I put together.","index":237,"end_time":1680.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1671.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll send that over to you shortly after this meeting.","index":238,"end_time":1682.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1680.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":1683.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1683.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Tristan, just so you know what, what Victor''s mentioning is that we''re sunsetting kind of the, the use of Mortgage World and kind of just building a residential mortgage lending kind of umbrella for Ponce bank, because it is truly under Ponce Bank.","index":240,"end_time":1699,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1683.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so as a stopgap, because a lot of the mortgage world content on the website, like Tiny said, is confusing or, you know, siloed and things like that, we''re just going to sunset that mortgage world website domain at this point.","index":241,"end_time":1711.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1699.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''re going to keep the domain for a little bit just to make sure there''s no, you know, the operational flow is, is good.","index":242,"end_time":1716.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1711.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But we''re going to add that landing page essentially to ponzi bank.com when we get to the process of content development, we''ll be one, I guess, one step ahead on the residential mortgage side because we''ll already have had that insight shared from Sunita, you know, so that, that''s great.","index":243,"end_time":1736.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1717.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But just to let you know that that''s where we''re kind of coming from for that.","index":244,"end_time":1739.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1736.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Another thing that I will add, and to piggyback off what, you know, what Sunita said, is that I think that the problem right now is that our navigational menus are all over the place.","index":245,"end_time":1750.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1740.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have, you know, terminology that makes sense to us as bankers.","index":246,"end_time":1756.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1751,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like Sunita said, you know, we''re not, we''re using industry jargon, which is kind of one of the biggest qualms, you know, a lot of customers have.","index":247,"end_time":1763.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1756.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We don''t have any kind of resource.","index":248,"end_time":1767.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1764.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, we have some minor FAQs on the direct side, but we don''t have an aggressory of terms.","index":249,"end_time":1772.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, we don''t have anything that will help the customer through the, the kind of experience.","index":250,"end_time":1779.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1772.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":251,"end_time":1779.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1779.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so as we go through the next workshop, a lot of you will be invited to tomorrow''s.","index":252,"end_time":1786.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1780.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s essentially going to talk a lot about that, you know, what kind of content, what, what is the story, how do we want to talk about our products and services?","index":253,"end_time":1793.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1786.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s going to be pretty exciting today.","index":254,"end_time":1797.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1794.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s going to be more so Focused on just making sure that we have everything documented.","index":255,"end_time":1803.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1797.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":256,"end_time":1803.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1803.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So an understanding of the hierarchy of our products, making sure that we don''t miss anything.","index":257,"end_time":1808.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1803.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":258,"end_time":1808.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1808.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because there is so many styles, making sure that we agree as an organization on what we''re going to call these products.","index":259,"end_time":1814.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1808.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":260,"end_time":1815.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1814.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because like Sunita said, there is sometimes confusion between our use of the word mortgage and what a residential mortgage is versus what a commercial loan is.","index":261,"end_time":1826.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1815.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so, you know, we kind of gotta align with how the industry and customer is gonna see that across all other bank sites.","index":262,"end_time":1834.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1826.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so we''re doing some of that research as well.","index":263,"end_time":1836.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1834.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then when we think about products, I want you guys to all keep in mind if there''s any specifics, terms, spec sheets, rate sheets or anything that you have for your specific products, please start to share those with.","index":264,"end_time":1853.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1837.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"With my team, we''re going to send out an email requesting that, but start to gather those because that''s going to be helpful for when we start to build out the site to make sure that we are communicating the product correctly.","index":265,"end_time":1867.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1853.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then, you know, we''ll go through the whole review process.","index":266,"end_time":1871.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1868.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But that''s kind of the structure of how we''re going to set up and the difference between tomorrow''s meeting and today''s.","index":267,"end_time":1877.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1872.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, and essentially what we have to get to is, is really that the true product, what we have here, taxonomy, how we organize the products in a logical way.","index":268,"end_time":1888.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1879,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because, because Sunia, you just mentioned yourself, you know, even on the mortgage side it''s very overwhelming.","index":269,"end_time":1893.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1888.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And you know, if we, if we don''t categorize things appropriately with the proper, you know, hierarchy, then it does become a little confusing for users.","index":270,"end_time":1905.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1894.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s why we want to get as, as high level as possible to, you know, the key areas that they need to go to to find what they''re.","index":271,"end_time":1913.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1905.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They''re looking for.","index":272,"end_time":1914.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1913.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are there any.","index":273,"end_time":1916.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1915.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It sounds like Sunit, you''ve been working with Victor in your area to, to really formulate that a little bit better for customers.","index":274,"end_time":1924.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1916.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are there any other areas in Ponce, like where perhaps we don''t even have the proper products in place now, or they need to be organized in a different way.","index":275,"end_time":1933,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1924.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are there any thoughts around on that side of it?","index":276,"end_time":1936.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1933,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yes, the journey for our financial mastery section at the moment we use how we gather the information of the registrants and participants and things of that nature.","index":277,"end_time":1952.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1942.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We need to kind of simplify that a little bit better to maybe create some sort of internal form that is easier to access other than using our outside zoom source right now.","index":278,"end_time":1964.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1952.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s another one yeah.","index":279,"end_time":1968.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1964.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, Tristan, when you think about, you know, what we offer, it''s a combination of physical products, right?","index":280,"end_time":1975.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1968.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, loans, but it''s also service, expertise, education, you know, and really like a trusted partner.","index":281,"end_time":1985.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1976.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s the kind of the focus that I''m taking for the site.","index":282,"end_time":1989.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1985.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when you think about the events and the education and our financial mastery programs, which is essentially the industry, financial literacy, we just, we.","index":283,"end_time":1999.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1990.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s what we just call it.","index":284,"end_time":2000.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1999.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then all of the different, you know, things that we do in the, in the community, we''re going to look to organize that in a.","index":285,"end_time":2008.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2001.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"In what I''m going to call a community page.","index":286,"end_time":2011,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2009,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"One of the things that, you know, we''ll talk a little bit about, just so everybody knows in the content meeting, is how we structure that, how we use the site to be able to put content out to the, to the customer.","index":287,"end_time":2024.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2012.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it always drives back to our website, versus, like now we just post articles on social media or sending emails, but that''s not helping us get traffic to the site where customers can get more information.","index":288,"end_time":2036.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2024.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s one of the things that we''re going to be doing, you know, as well.","index":289,"end_time":2040.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2036.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then because I have JAG here, I just want to mention.","index":290,"end_time":2045.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2040.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Jag, you know, works in the finance team, but he kind of manages the investor relations component.","index":291,"end_time":2052.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2045.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so while that''s not a specific product or service of Ponce bank, when an investor is, you know, doing a, a website search on, you know, the different stocks that they could potentially invest in there, that''s their product.","index":292,"end_time":2069.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2054.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":293,"end_time":2070.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2069.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so, Tristan, when you start to think about how we''re going to incorporate the investor relations piece into this, we''ll have to think about that from the customer lens of a bit of an investor, and then talk about, you know, all the great work that we do in the community, you know, why investing in community banks matters, you know, things of that nature.","index":294,"end_time":2090.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2070.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, Jack, you know, I have you on the line in case you wanted to, you know, add anything to that, but I consider, you know, that a product and service in a way, because there''s a market for it.","index":295,"end_time":2104.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2090.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s why you''re here.","index":296,"end_time":2107.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2104.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, I guess we can move on.","index":297,"end_time":2119.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2116.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Tristan, if there''s no other comments or questions about kind of the structure of the products.","index":298,"end_time":2125.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2119.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":299,"end_time":2126.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2125.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So one area I wanted to focus in on, which is like, after, after we do have a customer in place, how do you all think about segmenting customers?","index":300,"end_time":2139.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2127.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, like, if someone is on the consumer, how do the teams now maybe share?","index":301,"end_time":2145.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2139.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, do you.","index":302,"end_time":2147.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2146.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How does the upsell process work?","index":303,"end_time":2148.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2147.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How can maybe marketing provide alerts or notifications, cross teams?","index":304,"end_time":2154.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2149.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, how can we use data to our advantage?","index":305,"end_time":2156.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2154.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How does that work now as far as like getting notifications when a customer does on board with a new product, like, how do you share, you know, those resources, et cetera?","index":306,"end_time":2169.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2157.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Tristan, when a customer opens an account.","index":307,"end_time":2171.77,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2170.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Tristan, this is Wilma.","index":308,"end_time":2173.45,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2172.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"When a customer opens an account, basically the new account process, the aftermath is basically manual as it relates to the welcome letter.","index":309,"end_time":2184.97,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2174.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have to send out a welcome letter notifications advising them that we are in consent of overdraft.","index":310,"end_time":2193.05,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2185.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There are quite a few things that we could probably automate based off the new account boarding.","index":311,"end_time":2197.6,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2193.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So far, that''s it.","index":312,"end_time":2200.59,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2199.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Those are the number.","index":313,"end_time":2201.43,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2200.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Those are the areas that I''m focusing on right now.","index":314,"end_time":2203.59,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2201.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":315,"end_time":2205.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2204.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll be good to.","index":316,"end_time":2206.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2205.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, if there are specific requirements that you identify, there''s always things we can build in as well where there''s like a marketing layer to it.","index":317,"end_time":2213.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2206.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And sometimes it doesn''t even have to be a replacement.","index":318,"end_time":2216.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2213.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, I think Christina alluded to this earlier.","index":319,"end_time":2218.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2216.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It might just be like another layer to customer service where you know, we reinforce something through a digital channel or email flow.","index":320,"end_time":2227.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2218.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But then, you know, you''re still doing things on the manual side as well.","index":321,"end_time":2231.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2228.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So there''s kind of those different touch points.","index":322,"end_time":2233.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2231.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So just wanted to point that out too.","index":323,"end_time":2236.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2233.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It doesn''t always have to be, you know, replacing something.","index":324,"end_time":2238.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2236.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We could just augment it through, through digital as well.","index":325,"end_time":2241.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2238.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":326,"end_time":2243.26,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2242.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, and I think.","index":327,"end_time":2244.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2243.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, go ahead.","index":328,"end_time":2245.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2245.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m sorry, I was gonna piggyback off Wilma, also, if you were touching on the subject of like Cross stone, there is, as far as I know, there isn''t anything.","index":329,"end_time":2257.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2245.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for example, if someone opens a deposit account, unless someone manually physically reaches out to the mortgage department and says, oh, someone opened an account, there is nothing that happens, automated, in an automated fashion that reaches out or solicits the customer to say, we do mortgages, this is what we offer, so forth and so on and vice versa.","index":330,"end_time":2285.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2257.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If someone''s doing a mortgage, I don''t think anybody''s knowing and reaching out to them to say we do deposits and we have this for CD rates and so forth.","index":331,"end_time":2295.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2285.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I think that might have been part of what you were asking.","index":332,"end_time":2301.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2295.709,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a key piece.","index":333,"end_time":2303.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2302.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And part of our conversation yesterday was on the data side.","index":334,"end_time":2306.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2303.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But, but, but Sunita, it is some of the, the data that we''re trying to pull in.","index":335,"end_time":2312.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2306.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, because we do, like Christine said, this is the, the Marketing database.","index":336,"end_time":2316.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2312.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''re not getting all of the details from Core or even Salesforce.","index":337,"end_time":2319.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2316.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But are there perhaps product attributes?","index":338,"end_time":2322.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2320.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, can we just have a, you know, if we think about the, the service or the products that maybe a customer has access to or they''re enrolled in, can we have that, you know, in a multi select box where we at least are able to say, you know, they, they do have a personal checking account in place.","index":339,"end_time":2340.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2322.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, perhaps we get them in a flow, you know, for another product that would be related almost like hey customer, have you ever thought about this?","index":340,"end_time":2349.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2340.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And those are the types of relationships perhaps that we can build out.","index":341,"end_time":2354.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2349.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s what we''re trying to get to on the data side.","index":342,"end_time":2356.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2354.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we could have some of those triggers.","index":343,"end_time":2357.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2356.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it sounds like there is some opportunity do there.","index":344,"end_time":2360.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2357.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, because at the end of the day, you know, no one''s getting a mortgage unless they have savings and checking and, and investment and so forth.","index":345,"end_time":2369.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2360.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s an.","index":346,"end_time":2370.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2369.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It to me it''s a big opportunity that the deposit side can take advantage of because you know there''s, that''s an opportunity to take, take some business from the cons that consumer that''s doing a mortgage and most of the mortgages we do, they don''t have ponce savings and checking and CDs and so forth.","index":347,"end_time":2393.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2370.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we know that because we''re looking at their bank statements.","index":348,"end_time":2396.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2393.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"See it.","index":349,"end_time":2398.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2397.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right?","index":350,"end_time":2398.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2398.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":351,"end_time":2399.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2398.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I think we, because we mentioned the, the financial literacy piece too.","index":352,"end_time":2404.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2401.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that''s an interesting way to get other education around without even you know, presenting a product to a customer like so if we could go back to that for a second.","index":353,"end_time":2415.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2404.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How are we using that?","index":354,"end_time":2416.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2415.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Perhaps is it to nurture leads mostly or is it to educate customers around existing products and services?","index":355,"end_time":2424.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2416.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe if we could speak to that real quick.","index":356,"end_time":2428.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2425.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, so technically, I mean right now it''s, it''s.","index":357,"end_time":2433.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2431.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can you guys hear me?","index":358,"end_time":2434.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2433.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":359,"end_time":2437.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2436.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So yes, it''s, it''s not to technically tell them about products because this is part of our CRA component.","index":360,"end_time":2446.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2437.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we do have some obligations to.","index":361,"end_time":2448.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2446.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not sell products and services.","index":362,"end_time":2450.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2448.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But in for the most part it is general knowledge and information just a way to educate the community at mass and advise them.","index":363,"end_time":2459.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2450.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So yes, while we potentially are, while we are educating them, we are kind of potentially hoping that they would come back on like a one on one and obviously open an account with us or ask for more services like Mortgage World, excuse me, for a residential mortgage and, and see from there or any other services because there, there''s an array of, of Educational material that we put out.","index":364,"end_time":2483.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2459.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We, we work, you know, we have components in small businesses, we have non profit services.","index":365,"end_time":2488.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2483.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So there''s, there''s a lot that we have in the programming that will definitely do exactly that.","index":366,"end_time":2493.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2488.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Provide more leads and potential cost prospects.","index":367,"end_time":2496.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2493.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, really quick, just based on timing, I know that we can''t promote a specific product or service to those people based on cra.","index":368,"end_time":2504.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2497.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is there a timeline that it would fall after that you could promote those products and services?","index":369,"end_time":2510.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2504.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yes.","index":370,"end_time":2513.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2513.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"My understanding is that you''re after.","index":371,"end_time":2515.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2514.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":372,"end_time":2517.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2516.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, so, so one of the things that I think that would be interesting for us to talk about is how we kind of position and manage CRA eligible, you know, components and educational materials versus just general, you know, education materials and marketing campaigns.","index":373,"end_time":2537.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2517.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because you know, there, there is a, if there''s a difference, even though it''s, it''s, you know, it''s subtle.","index":374,"end_time":2544.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2537.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s something that we can do.","index":375,"end_time":2546.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2544.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then another thing I wanted everybody to, to think about is, you know, right now we''re not using data on the, the marketing side because it''s a little bit, there''s a couple different places we have to get it from to really understand what our customers have from a product perspective and what stage of kind of life that they are.","index":376,"end_time":2569.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2547.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for example, when we talked about the data yesterday, we did a lot of talking about transaction data, account level data, things that would help tell a story about the customer.","index":377,"end_time":2580.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2569.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so I want you guys to start to think about and there''ll be some homework later on, basically what are those transaction types or activities that a customer would do that would provide kind of an opportunity for something next?","index":378,"end_time":2594.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2580.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":379,"end_time":2595.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2594.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I think of like if a customer comes in and makes a large deposit, I, I think it''s more beyond just like the compliance requirements for what you do when customers make a large deposit.","index":380,"end_time":2605.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2595.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But is that an opportunity to say, hey, you made a large deposit into, you know, a checking account.","index":381,"end_time":2610.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2605.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe, you know, maybe that''s a good offer for a cd or let''s just say they, you know, open up a mortgage that''s across offer checking.","index":382,"end_time":2624.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2610.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We could look at things like, you know, age and kind of what branch they''re in and kind of customize things.","index":383,"end_time":2633.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2624.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, obviously, you know, taking into account the regulatory, you know, requirements for all that type of segmentation, but within what''s allowed, we can start to use the data to make decisions to cross sell our products.","index":384,"end_time":2645.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2634.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And the beauty about that is this is going to bring in customers organically and help the organization grow without really putting a strain on the marketing team to have to do things manually and also, you know, the sales teams to have to do, you know, bring in things, you know, organically.","index":385,"end_time":2661.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2645.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s one of the biggest goals and kind of beauties of this system is having some data in the system to help us make more informed decisions.","index":386,"end_time":2668.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2661.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So start to think about some of those things and we''ll send a follow up email after this call, probably by end of day tomorrow with a few extra additional things that we want you to start to gather.","index":387,"end_time":2679.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2668.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So like I said before, the product matrix for your, your specific area is going to be one of them, many rate term sheets, you know, on the lending side or any other things that you could think of that would help us build out automation and some journeys.","index":388,"end_time":2694.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2680.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''ll be some homework right after this.","index":389,"end_time":2697.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2694.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Christina, if I may, as everyone works on that exercise, it''s probably important to highlight the faced approach to what, what''s kind of being surfaced.","index":390,"end_time":2708.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2697.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because one thing is to be able to say we can do this based on simple basic information, like I have children.","index":391,"end_time":2718.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2708.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You can see that very quickly.","index":392,"end_time":2719.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2718.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it''s not a triggering event, it''s not a large deposit or specific information that will need to be fed into HubSpot to trigger other kind of major events.","index":393,"end_time":2729.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2719.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it, it''ll be important to have that distinction as part of the assessments that each of you make and understand that, you know, there will be a phase one versus what we can do long term.","index":394,"end_time":2742.199,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2730.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s a, that''s a good point.","index":395,"end_time":2746.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2745.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I think like right now it''s just kind of a big data dump kind of, so to speak.","index":396,"end_time":2750.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2746.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''re taking, we''re intaking, like just all of the information to help us kind of put together, you know, a formulated plan.","index":397,"end_time":2758.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2750.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The project plan that Tristan brought up, you''ll notice it''s kind of very high level to one line item for every single phase of the project.","index":398,"end_time":2766.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2759.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But really in reality there''s multiple tasks as, you know, under each of those line items.","index":399,"end_time":2771.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2766.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so that''s definitely included in there and you guys will be part of that process, you know, and we''ll align on what''s feasible for go live, you know, and then what we can work towards over, you know, over time because there''s a lot of other systems, you know, integrations, there''s processes and procedures that would, you know, maybe have to be modified and that all can''t happen, you know, day one to Betty''s point.","index":400,"end_time":2793.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2771.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, Tristan, how are we looking on time?","index":401,"end_time":2798.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2796.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, one area I definitely wanted to touch on is just performance tracking and how the different folks on, on this call are getting information from a marketing perspective now or what you would like to see.","index":402,"end_time":2812.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2799.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like if we just think fundamentally about leads or you know, where prospects or customers come from, like what kind of information do you have now?","index":403,"end_time":2821.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2812.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What, what gaps exist and then how do you report on, on these types of activities and that''s performance.","index":404,"end_time":2830.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2821.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, I guess that''s a marketing related question.","index":405,"end_time":2833.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2831.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll say right now a lot of the marketing that we do is, is specific to brand.","index":406,"end_time":2838.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2833.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean we did do a couple of little things for products but it hasn''t been anything where you know, we have tangible metrics that we can share.","index":407,"end_time":2847.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2838.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so that''s one of the things that we''re looking to change for 2026 is you know, run more product specific campaigns and communications to show how we''re driving traffic to branches, how we''re driving traffic to certain website pages and overall kind of account opening.","index":408,"end_time":2863.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2848.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''ll be the nice thing to track back to Salesforce and through mulesoft.","index":409,"end_time":2867.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2863.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So then once kind of a customer goes through the journey of a prospect to a campaign, when we go and have the bi directional data and they come back as a customer, we''ll then be able to have that direct correlation and report that out.","index":410,"end_time":2883.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2868.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right now we can report out on engagement and how many registrants and clicks and things like that, but it''s not very substantial.","index":411,"end_time":2892.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2883.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And sometimes I like to tease, it''s like it''s not anything executives really would care about.","index":412,"end_time":2896.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2892.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They just want get to like dollars and cents, right?","index":413,"end_time":2899.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2897.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like they want to see, okay, how many loans and checking accounts and deposits and new customers.","index":414,"end_time":2904.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2899.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like that''s the four things that they care about.","index":415,"end_time":2906.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2904.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right?","index":416,"end_time":2906.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2906.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because it hits the bottom line.","index":417,"end_time":2908.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2906.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so what I want to do is build out a dashboard that kind of has that as a high level and then underneath kind of just gives them all of the nicer metrics like the engagement and the views and all of that stuff to show like the penetration.","index":418,"end_time":2922.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2908.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But from now it''s, it''s pretty much non existent across the teams.","index":419,"end_time":2928.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2922.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are there any reports that your specific teams have that, you know, I''m sure there might be like pipeline reports and things like that.","index":420,"end_time":2936.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2928.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know actually I''m sure there''s reports it''s on the line.","index":421,"end_time":2940.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2937.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m sure there''s reports that are existing.","index":422,"end_time":2942.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2940.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ve saw a few, but I don''t think we''ve ever used them from a marketing perspective.","index":423,"end_time":2945.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2942.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I, I live by reports.","index":424,"end_time":2949.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2945.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I have reports from my loan origination system that I track and keep, I reconcile to Salesforce for the leads that we get through internal leads.","index":425,"end_time":2967.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2950.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I. I''ve kind of been a little bit of a monster about it as of recent, because I wanna track all the leads that we''re getting from an internal source, so we make sure those go into Salesforce.","index":426,"end_time":2981.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2967.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And also I''m forcing my sales team to input their source in the loan origination system and just kind of comparing, because at some point, our loan origination systems was speaking to Salesforce and it was updating the status.","index":427,"end_time":3001.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2982.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then it''s not necessarily always consistent or have a good flow.","index":428,"end_time":3008.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3001.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this way, if.","index":429,"end_time":3011.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3008.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If there''s a gap, I have it from two places where I can tie it together and know that where that.","index":430,"end_time":3020.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3011.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Where that lead ended up.","index":431,"end_time":3022.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3020.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So to touch specifically on one point is like, Salesforce will track the lead, and once it becomes an application, it''s better tracked in the LOS system.","index":432,"end_time":3033.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3022.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if that makes sense.","index":433,"end_time":3035.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3033.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But yeah, I do joke it.","index":434,"end_time":3038.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3036.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We might wanna.","index":435,"end_time":3039.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3038.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We might wanna, you know, just put that as a note to discuss with Sunita offline, because if there''s any opportunity to kind of revisit that integration to make sure that it''s working.","index":436,"end_time":3048.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3039.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because essentially, like, you know, Sunita, if you''re doing manual work now to track those leads, we''re gonna be building a lot of different new lead, you know, flows through HubSpot.","index":437,"end_time":3057.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3048.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so essentially what we''ll want to do is just make sure that we can track end to end even more than a lead, even from a campaign perspective, from like one click all the way through to applications.","index":438,"end_time":3069.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3057.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So a lot of times the LOS systems will have, you know, additional APIs where you can plug directly into Salesforce.","index":439,"end_time":3078.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3069.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''ll be an interesting thing to, you know, to explore, you know, if it''s not already coming in through mulesoft.","index":440,"end_time":3085.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3078.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":441,"end_time":3085.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3085.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, yes, it does.","index":442,"end_time":3087.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3086.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we do have a patch.","index":443,"end_time":3089.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3087.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Patch from the LOS to Salesforce.","index":444,"end_time":3092.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3089.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I have a open ticket to investigate what the issue was.","index":445,"end_time":3099.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3093.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The problem was initially, and I don''t want to get sidetracked here, but initially when we started using the patch, we didn''t have any loans to test.","index":446,"end_time":3113.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3099.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so then when we had loans to test or leads that became loans to test, then we discovered that it wasn''t seamless.","index":447,"end_time":3121.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3113.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s.","index":448,"end_time":3123.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3121.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s in the works.","index":449,"end_time":3124.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3123.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But yeah, it would be nice if it was more automated, of course, because it is kind of a.","index":450,"end_time":3129.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3124.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A manual process now.","index":451,"end_time":3131.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3130.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, so we''ll make a note of.","index":452,"end_time":3134.329,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3132.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Of that.","index":453,"end_time":3134.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3134.329,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then I know we have about Seven minutes left.","index":454,"end_time":3137.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3135.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, Tristan, is there.","index":455,"end_time":3139.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3137.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is there anything else that, you know, we need to kind of COVID in the agenda?","index":456,"end_time":3143.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3139.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If not, we''ll just open it up to just, you know, random questions that the team might have.","index":457,"end_time":3148.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3143.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I had a few other things I could go into, but I''ll open it up and see if there''s anything maybe we haven''t touched on yet.","index":458,"end_time":3154.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3149.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That would be a priority.","index":459,"end_time":3156.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3154.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Anything from the team?","index":460,"end_time":3166.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3164.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Nobody be shy, because all insights is good insights.","index":461,"end_time":3174.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3170.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Christina.","index":462,"end_time":3179.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3179.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Unrelated, we.","index":463,"end_time":3180.39,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3179.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We are tracking in.","index":464,"end_time":3182.39,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3180.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"In crew on the commercial side as well, tracking loans, the.","index":465,"end_time":3187.03,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3182.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"When they''re in qualification through to them onboarding into the system.","index":466,"end_time":3192.87,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3187.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we do track any generated reports from there.","index":467,"end_time":3195.59,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3193.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Desiree, if I''m not mistaken, that''s the.","index":468,"end_time":3197.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3196.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The program that Bonus uses, right?","index":469,"end_time":3199.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3197.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":470,"end_time":3200.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3200.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, it was GPS and crew for us.","index":471,"end_time":3203.33,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3200.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Us Film rebranded.","index":472,"end_time":3205,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3203.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Got it.","index":473,"end_time":3205.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3205.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Same thing.","index":474,"end_time":3206.52,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3205.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I believe the loan officers use it when they''re.","index":475,"end_time":3209.96,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3207.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"When they have loans in prospecting.","index":476,"end_time":3211.8,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3209.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t know if anybody''s here to speak to that, but they do.","index":477,"end_time":3214.52,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3211.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t know how much they utilize it, but we do track once the loan is.","index":478,"end_time":3220,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3215.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is given to us for.","index":479,"end_time":3221.48,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":3220,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"For processing.","index":480,"end_time":3222.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3221.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":481,"end_time":3224.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3224.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, Victor, make a note of.","index":482,"end_time":3226.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3224.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Of that system.","index":483,"end_time":3226.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3226.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And when we talk to Ashley, engage on the more like the IT side of things.","index":484,"end_time":3232.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3226.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll make a note of.","index":485,"end_time":3234.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3232.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Of kind of what funnels through to Salesforce to Mulesoft.","index":486,"end_time":3238.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3234.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And if everything is.","index":487,"end_time":3240.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3239.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is there, you know, it''ll.","index":488,"end_time":3241.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3240.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''ll be captured.","index":489,"end_time":3242.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3241.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll just build custom code, custom fields for it if needed.","index":490,"end_time":3246.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3242.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then as we go through the.","index":491,"end_time":3248.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3246.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A comparison of what we have in Mulesoft and in.","index":492,"end_time":3251.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3249,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"In HubSpot, we''ll see the gaps.","index":493,"end_time":3254.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3251.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then, you know, if there''s any integration into any other systems that we need to think about, we''ll, you know, we''ll obviously think about that.","index":494,"end_time":3261.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3254.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And if we need to put it for a phase two, we''ll put it, you know, for a phase two.","index":495,"end_time":3264.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3261.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I think that that''s definitely a good thing to.","index":496,"end_time":3267.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3264.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"To add to, because that''s another element of leads that we could track.","index":497,"end_time":3272.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3267.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":498,"end_time":3275.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3275.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then probably the last thing.","index":499,"end_time":3277.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3275.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":500,"end_time":3277.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3277.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":501,"end_time":3278.4,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":3277.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, no.","index":502,"end_time":3278.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3278.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So sorry, Tristan.","index":503,"end_time":3279.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3278.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t see Wanda on.","index":504,"end_time":3281.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3279.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I would say that on our side, the nonprofit search services is mostly the one that uses GPS at the moment for the external affairs team.","index":505,"end_time":3288.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3281.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s probably an avenue of definitely I would need a little looking into.","index":506,"end_time":3293.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3288.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then for us in general, is literally, you know, migrating into being a lot more automated.","index":507,"end_time":3299.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3293.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So just to give you a little bit of insight on that, the, the small project that we''re working on with Wanda, that information I am bringing over to the HubSpot side of things.","index":508,"end_time":3310.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3300.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s kind of like the, the little test run to find out what are her pain points, how can we better suit that side of things so that we can do a little bit more automation on the HubSpot side of things to make her job with her team a little bit more easier?","index":509,"end_time":3322.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3310.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, right now we''re kind of testing to, you know, certain, just workflows and things, you know, obviously with, without any data because we didn''t do anything there yet.","index":510,"end_time":3333.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3325.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But you know, I think that, that it''s, it''s good for everyone to raise these things because it''ll give us opportunities to kind of test and see what works.","index":511,"end_time":3340.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3333.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think in the last four minutes, what I, what I would say is one, you know, thank you everyone for, for attending.","index":512,"end_time":3347.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3342.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know this is a little bit overwhelming and some things might seem a little bit confusing, but I promise as we kind of continue, there''ll be more opportunities, you know, to have discussions and raise things.","index":513,"end_time":3358,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3347.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I''m going to give you guys the opportunity, like I said, to share documentation and, you know, insights and lists and things like that that we''ll need.","index":514,"end_time":3366.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3358.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So just be on the lookout for those emails.","index":515,"end_time":3369.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3367.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Anyone invited to the call tomorrow, it''ll focus more on, like I said, content and the experience, it''s, it''s going to be more of a lift from marketing to kind of figure out how to make everything kind of be cohesive.","index":516,"end_time":3384.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3370.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":517,"end_time":3384.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3384.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And make all of the products and services that we offer seamless to the, to the customer.","index":518,"end_time":3389.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3385.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s going to be a really big difference from the current website.","index":519,"end_time":3392.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3389.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right now when we get into the discussions for foundation, for Investor Relations and for Policy Bank Direct, we''re going to have a couple of additional workshops that might pop up because there''s going to be specific needs because those pages will be built as micro sites and basically essentially what that is, it''s like their own mini website within a website.","index":520,"end_time":3417.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3393.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So rather than have like a separate domain, it''ll live within the umbrella of Ponce Bank.","index":521,"end_time":3423.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3418.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But then there''ll be opportunities to have like the foundation logo and, or the Investor Relations logo, different content and disclosures if needed.","index":522,"end_time":3432.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3423.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":523,"end_time":3432.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3432.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so we''ll talk about those intricacies more in the, the meeting for, you know, for tomorrow and so forth.","index":524,"end_time":3439.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3432.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Victor and Tristan, we can discuss offline and make a list of all of the, the things that we need the teams to send us and send that email.","index":525,"end_time":3448.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3440.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, out by end of day tomorrow.","index":526,"end_time":3450.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3448.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But in case anybody has anything that comes up, just feel free to reach out to me and Victor.","index":527,"end_time":3455.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3450.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Victor is going to be kind of the lead on my team for any direct questions or emails or things like that.","index":528,"end_time":3462.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3455.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''re pretty excited to move this project ahead and thank everyone for their time.","index":529,"end_time":3467.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3462.29,"speaker_name":null}],"dateString":"2025-11-20T19:00:15.000Z","host_email":null,"meeting_link":null,"participants":[],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KAHA708A841HVB1NKN5B6R0Y","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.88,"bullets":["Kicked off second of three HubSpot website workshops focused on product and customer journey mapping.","Valerie flagged user confusion due to disjointed navigation across multiple siloed bank websites.","Sunita noted high volume of unqualified mortgage leads; marketing to handle early education steps.","Team agreed to consolidate resources into one unified website with audience-specific product paths.","Christina outlined plans for automated onboarding, lead nurturing, and personalized cross-sell journeys."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The journey might be a little bit confusing... not everything is set up in one location.","speaker":"Valerie"},{"quote":"We get more inquiries and not warm leads than we do warm leads.","speaker":"Sunita"},{"quote":"This is going to bring in customers organically and help the organization grow.","speaker":"Christina"}],"topics":["journey","leads","automation","website","CRM","data"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Customer Journey and Lead Management**\n\nThe team agreed that current customer journeys are fragmented and overly complex, and simplifying them will improve lead qualification and conversion.\n\n- **Valerie highlighted** that the existing website requires too many clicks and has siloed areas like Mortgage World and Ponce Bank Foundation, confusing customers and slowing navigation (10:53)  \n    - This fragmentation leads to a disjointed experience that hampers customer engagement and brand clarity  \n    - Christina explained the plan to unify these siloed sites into a single platform to better track customer interests and improve user flow  \n    - The goal is to enable customers to reach key journeys within one or two clicks from the homepage  \n    - This consolidation will also help marketing better understand customer behavior and needs\n\n- **Lead qualification challenges** in the mortgage area were discussed by Sunita, who noted that about **95% of the 300 national leads received recently were fake** with invalid contacts, wasting sales resources (18:00)  \n    - Currently, lead validation is manual and time-consuming, requiring sales to call and verify each lead  \n    - Marketing aims to automate lead nurturing for inquiries, reserving sales efforts for warm leads only  \n    - Christina emphasized the need for more educational content on the website to reduce unqualified lead volume and better prepare prospects  \n    - Automated workflows will nurture leads digitally until they are sales-ready, improving efficiency\n\n- **Post-sale customer journeys and cross-selling** are largely manual and disconnected (14:00)  \n    - Wilma shared that welcome letters and account onboarding are manual and could benefit from automation  \n    - Sales teams currently do not receive automatic alerts about customers’ new accounts or products, limiting cross-sell opportunities  \n    - The team sees an opportunity to trigger targeted marketing based on product ownership and customer actions, such as deposits or mortgage applications  \n    - This approach aims to grow wallet share organically without increasing manual workload\n\n## **Product and Service Organization**\n\nSimplifying product presentation and terminology on the website is critical to improve customer understanding and reduce overwhelm.\n\n- **Sunita and Victor are leading** efforts to simplify the residential mortgage section by sunsetting the confusing Mortgage World domain and integrating mortgage content directly under Ponce Bank (27:50)  \n    - The new structure focuses on simplicity and avoiding jargon to better serve customers unfamiliar with banking terms  \n    - A clean product taxonomy and hierarchy will help users quickly find relevant products without drilling through many pages  \n    - Christina stressed the need for consistent naming across all products to prevent confusion, especially between residential mortgages and commercial loans  \n    - The team will collect product specs, rate sheets, and other details to ensure accuracy during website build\n\n- **Organizing community and educational content** as a separate section on the website is planned, combining financial literacy programs, events, and investor relations (32:30)  \n    - This approach aims to increase site traffic by hosting more content directly rather than via social media or email  \n    - Jag manages investor relations content, which is seen as a product offering for investors and will be integrated thoughtfully  \n    - The content workshop tomorrow will focus on messaging and storytelling to make products and services more cohesive  \n\n- **Financial Mastery program improvements** include simplifying participant data collection and moving away from external platforms like Zoom for registrations (32:15)  \n    - This will streamline internal workflows and create a better user experience  \n\n## **Data Integration and Automation Opportunities**\n\nUsing customer data to trigger personalized marketing journeys and automate processes is a key goal for the HubSpot implementation.\n\n- **Tristan outlined** plans to leverage HubSpot data to identify customer behaviors and trigger cross-sell or upsell offers based on product ownership and transactions (38:00)  \n    - Examples include targeting customers who make large deposits with CD offers or mortgage customers with deposit product promotions  \n    - Automation will reduce manual effort for marketing and sales teams and generate organic growth  \n    - A phased approach is necessary due to data complexity, system integration needs, and compliance requirements  \n\n- **Current challenges** include data siloing and manual lead tracking, especially between Salesforce, loan origination systems (LOS), and marketing databases (47:30)  \n    - Wilma tracks leads manually across LOS and Salesforce to reconcile discrepancies and improve accuracy  \n    - There is an existing patch from LOS to Salesforce, but it is not seamless and requires ongoing work to automate fully  \n    - The team aims to build end-to-end lead tracking from campaign click through application conversion  \n    - Monitoring and improving these integrations is critical for accurate performance measurement and efficient lead management\n\n- **CRA compliance limits product promotion timing**, so marketing must carefully separate educational content from product marketing (40:45)  \n    - Educational programming aims to raise awareness and generate leads without direct sales pressure  \n    - After compliance periods, marketing can promote products more directly  \n    - This distinction shapes content strategy and automation rules\n\n## **Performance Tracking and Reporting**\n\nImproving marketing performance metrics and reporting to link activities to revenue is a top priority for 2026.\n\n- **Tristan shared** that currently marketing reports focus on engagement metrics like clicks and registrations but lack direct ties to revenue or account openings (47:00)  \n    - Executives want clear KPIs such as number of loans, deposits, account openings, and related dollars  \n    - The plan is to build dashboards showing high-level revenue metrics supported by engagement data for deeper insights  \n    - Integrating campaign data with Salesforce and LOS through MuleSoft will enable tracking customer journeys from prospect to customer  \n    - This will help justify marketing spend and demonstrate business impact\n\n- **Desiree and other business areas** track loan pipelines and processing through platforms like GPS and CREW, which integrate partially with Salesforce (52:45)  \n    - The team will coordinate with IT and leadership to map these data flows and fill gaps with custom fields or code if needed  \n    - This will ensure lead and loan tracking supports marketing and sales alignment\n\n- **Nonprofit and external affairs teams** are piloting automation workflows in HubSpot to improve efficiency and are key early adopters for process improvements (54:40)  \n    - Lessons learned here will inform broader rollout across teams  \n\n## **Project Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe discovery phase continues with a deliverable planned for the end of April 2026, providing a roadmap for content, design, and build phases.\n\n- **Tristan emphasized** that findings from these workshops will feed into a comprehensive plan to guide the website and CRM build (03:00)  \n    - The next workshop focuses on content, messaging, and user experience to complement today’s taxonomy and journey discussions  \n    - Additional workshops will address foundation, investor relations, and Policy Bank Direct micro-sites within the main site umbrella  \n    - Victor is the point person for internal questions and document collection, with follow-up emails expected by end of day tomorrow (56:30)  \n    - The phased approach will prioritize what is feasible for go-live versus longer-term enhancements  \n    - The team will maintain ongoing collaboration to refine customer journeys, product organization, and data strategies through the project lifecycle","outline":null,"keywords":["Customer Journeys","Product Taxonomy","Marketing Automation","HubSpot Implementation","Lead Qualification","Website Consolidation"],"overview":"- **Customer Journey Improvement:** Simplifying customer journeys will enhance lead qualification and conversion, reducing complexity and confusion.  \n- **High Lead Fraud Rate:** 95% of 300 recent mortgage leads were invalid, highlighting the need for automated lead validation.  \n- **Post-Sale Automation:** Manual onboarding and alerts limit cross-selling; automating these processes can enhance marketing opportunities.  \n- **Product Simplification:** Streamlined product terminology will improve understanding, with plans to integrate mortgage content directly under Ponce Bank.  \n- **Data Integration Goals:** Using HubSpot data will automate personalized marketing and improve tracking across platforms like Salesforce and LOS.  \n- **Performance Metrics Focus:** The aim is to connect marketing activities directly to revenue by enhancing tracking and reporting capabilities.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Santana**\nReceive and incorporate mortgage world content format from internal team and integrate it into the Ponce Bank website structure (26:37)\nCoordinate with Christina and team to gather product specifications, rate sheets, promotional materials from all departments for website and HubSpot content development (30:53)\nDevelop marketing automation workflows and customer journey maps, incorporating feedback and distributed to participants for review (22:09)\nFollow up on issues with LOS patch integration to Salesforce and assist in exploring API or MuleSoft integration improvements (50:01)\nCollaborate with IT (Ashley) and Victor to review existing data flows and integrations for lead and product data (53:16)\nFacilitate email communications requesting documentation and inputs from product owners by end of day following meeting (57:20)\nImplement dashboards to report campaign engagement and business impact metrics aligned with sales results (47:01)\n\n**Victor**\nServe as primary point of contact for collecting Ponce Bank team inputs and queries for project (57:20)\nCoordinate with Tristan and internal resources on integrating various tracking systems like GPS and LOS with marketing and sales databases (53:16)\n\n**Christina**\nClarify product/service definitions and collaborate on simplifying website content and language for better customer comprehension (26:37)\nMonitor compliance requirements for CRA educational materials and define timelines for marketing outreach to CRA segments (40:00)\nAssist in defining manual versus automated touchpoints in post-onboarding customer journey to augment customer service (36:53)\n\n**Product and Team Representatives**\nProvide product matrices, marketing collateral, terms and rate sheets for respective product lines to marketing team promptly (30:53)\nIdentify key customer journeys and pain points in existing website navigation and share relevant customer insights (07:08)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8a9243f7-5431-499b-8d88-8ba4b381a339","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
