    '{"id":"01KAKWQF6TJJDGF8TPFTD8JA5A","title":"Ponce Bank - Hubspot Series: Content & Experience","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Content & User Experience**\n\nThe meeting identified key content gaps and usability issues on the current Ponce Bank website that hinder customer navigation and engagement.\n\n- **Maria** highlighted the confusing scroll-and-reveal layout on cash management product pages, where users must keep clicking to see new information, which negatively impacts accessibility and user experience (03:18).\n    - This layout causes frustration and could deter customers from exploring products fully.\n    - The team agreed this needs a structural redesign to display content more clearly and reduce excessive scrolling.\n    - Tristan was tasked with noting this for overall site infrastructure improvements.\n    - Fixing this will improve customer satisfaction and potentially increase product inquiries.\n\n- **Jackie** emphasized that dense information and hidden disclaimers at the bottom of pages reduce usability and compliance visibility (04:39).\n    - She proposed a centralized promotions page to consolidate campaign information and disclosures for better tracking and regulatory compliance.\n    - This page would allow toggling promotions on or off to support digital campaigns with clearer messaging.\n    - Creating this resource aligns with regulatory needs and marketing agility, improving campaign effectiveness.\n\n- The mortgage team, represented by **Santana** and **Cindy**, called for simplified content structures with clear bullet-point navigation targeting specific customer needs like first-time buyers or refinancing (06:05).\n    - They stressed reorganizing mortgage content to group similar products logically, e.g., by loan type or purpose, to improve flow.\n    - This restructuring would reduce confusion and speed up customer decision-making.\n    - The team will soon begin sitemap development to establish hierarchical content frameworks.\n    - This will serve as the foundation for consistent and intuitive navigation.\n\n- **Nanette** and others noted inconsistent branding and color usage across personal and business sections undermines brand trust and creates a disjointed customer experience (15:09).\n    - The current site uses multiple conflicting colors, which confuse users about brand identity.\n    - A recent brand guide aims to modernize the look while preserving community ties, standardizing colors, icons, and imagery (20:32).\n    - The new style includes hand-drawn illustrations and documentary-style photos to evoke authenticity.\n    - Consistent visual language will strengthen brand recognition and user comfort across all site sections.\n\n- **Ingrid** requested elevating key service links like remote help to top navigation positions to improve customer access and reduce support calls (28:54).\n    - Currently, critical tools are buried at the bottom of pages, making them hard to find.\n    - The plan includes building a dedicated resource page with prominent placement.\n    - This will enhance self-service capabilities and reduce friction for customers needing assistance.\n\n- The group agreed that common features such as online banking and debit card information should be presented consistently between personal and business sections to avoid confusion (31:30).\n    - Harmonizing content presentation will make cross-segment customers feel more seamless and reduce cognitive load.\n    - This consistency supports customers who hold both personal and business accounts.\n\n## **Site Architecture & Integration**\n\nThe team is prioritizing a clear, adaptable site architecture to organize existing content and support future updates efficiently.\n\n- The next major step is creating a comprehensive **site map** that defines page hierarchies and content groupings for personal, business, mortgage, and other verticals (12:06).\n    - This sitemap will serve as a blueprint for content placement and navigation design.\n    - Teams will review and validate the sitemap for accuracy and completeness.\n    - This will enable centralized content management and reduce duplication.\n\n- There is a strong focus on automating rate updates with centralized rate tables that propagate changes site-wide to reduce manual errors and delays (12:06).\n    - This system will improve accuracy and speed for rate changes.\n    - It also reduces operational risk and maintenance burdens.\n\n- The team will introduce a **content audit and gap analysis** to identify missing products, partnership programs, and services currently absent from the website (13:29).\n    - This includes emerging mortgage products, ESD partnership loans, and new service launches like Glia and Zell for business.\n    - The goal is to ensure all offerings are represented clearly to prospects and customers.\n\n- Integration opportunities include syncing branch event calendars, alerts, social media feeds, and content sharing features to increase engagement (47:21).\n    - Automation will help content stay current and reduce manual upkeep.\n    - Adding social share buttons will boost organic reach and visibility.\n\n- Accessibility compliance and API setups are key technical priorities to meet legal standards and improve user experience (48:48).\n    - This ensures the site is usable by all customers and integrates smoothly with backend systems.\n\n- Online banking login areas will be enhanced with potential links to loan portals like Encompass to streamline customer access to loan status and document uploads (53:04).\n    - **Santana** emphasized using technology to reduce manual processes and improve customer self-service.\n    - Coordination with IT and third-party vendors will be necessary to brand and customize these integrations.\n\n## **Branding & Visual Identity**\n\nThe meeting confirmed a strategic push to modernize and unify Ponce Bank’s brand identity across all digital touchpoints.\n\n- The new **brand guide** establishes a consistent color palette, typography, iconography, and illustration style that balances modern design with authentic local elements (20:32).\n    - This includes sketch-style illustrations from real New York scenes to build community connection.\n    - The brand refresh aims to create a clean, fresh, and recognizable look across all products and pages.\n\n- The design will reduce the current visual clutter and inconsistent color usage that weakens brand recognition (16:09).\n    - Consistency will be maintained across personal, business, mortgage, and investor relations sites.\n    - This will help customers instantly identify they are within the Ponce Bank ecosystem regardless of entry point.\n\n- Photography style will shift to documentary, candid images to reflect real customers and branches, enhancing emotional connection (23:39).\n    - This approach contrasts with generic stock photos and supports authenticity.\n\n- The branding refresh supports the website’s goal to reduce clicks and simplify navigation, improving overall user satisfaction (26:20).\n    - A consistent brand language will also support marketing campaigns and communications.\n\n## **Multi-Brand & Microsite Strategy**\n\nThe team addressed how to cohesively manage multiple brands and specialized sites under the Ponce Bank umbrella.\n\n- **Ponce Bank Direct** will remain a separate microsite within the main Ponce Bank website to preserve its distinct digital-only offering (34:44).\n    - This microsite will have its own landing page but remain visually connected to Ponce Bank.\n    - The approach prevents customer confusion while supporting national marketing outside local branch areas.\n\n- There are ongoing discussions on how to position **Ponce Bank Direct** and other entities like **Foundation** and **Investor Relations** in navigation (35:56).\n    - Options include pop-up journey selectors on entry, separate menu items, or IP-based routing to tailor the experience.\n    - The team is evaluating user flow impacts and mobile navigation constraints to finalize placement.\n\n- The goal is to help customers self-select the right journey, whether local banking, digital-only, community foundation, or investor relations (37:15).\n    - This segmentation will reduce confusion and improve conversion for targeted campaigns.\n\n- Clear branding and navigation are especially important as some customers currently get confused between Ponce Bank and Ponce Bank Direct sites, leading to login and service issues (43:08).\n    - The team plans further discussions to create clear pathways and links between brands.\n    - Messaging will emphasize that all entities are part of the same bank, just with different service channels.\n\n## **Content Strategy & Ongoing Governance**\n\nThe meeting set the foundation for a dynamic, evolving content strategy with shared team ownership.\n\n- The website will not be static; teams will be responsible for **monthly or quarterly audits** of their pages to keep content accurate and up to date (27:35).\n    - This process will address frequent product changes, regulatory updates, and campaign shifts.\n    - Collaboration between marketing, IT, and business units is essential for success.\n\n- The team plans to develop an **annual content calendar** focused on trending topics, leadership pieces, and community engagement articles to drive ongoing site traffic and social sharing (48:48).\n    - Content will focus on answering customer questions rather than just listing facts to match modern search behaviors.\n    - Social share features will track engagement and amplify reach.\n\n- Future site enhancements include creating interactive tools and calculators, localized branch promotion pages, and a centralized resource hub for self-service tutorials and FAQs (47:21).\n    - These will improve customer empowerment and reduce support demand.\n\n- Partnerships with vendors like Fiserv and Beaver Creek will be leveraged to provide tutorial videos and digital guides, which will be updated and integrated into the site (51:38).\n    - This content supports customer onboarding for online and mobile banking products.\n\n- The team acknowledged the need for improved **content structuring and categorization** to better align product groups and avoid confusing mixes, especially in mortgage offerings (10:28).\n    - Clear headers and logical groupings will simplify discovery and reduce customer effort.\n\n- Key stakeholders like **Jackie** and **Sergio** will have focused working sessions to align on legal content and investor relations pages to ensure compliance and consistent branding (33:00).\n\n- The agency and internal teams will consolidate feedback and send follow-ups next week to gather outstanding content and structural details for the next phase of design and build (56:04).","outline":null,"keywords":["Website Redesign","Content Strategy","User Experience","Branding Consistency","Site Map Architecture","Mortgage Portal Integration"],"overview":"- **Website Usability Issues:** Current layout frustrates users; structural redesign needed for clarity and engagement. \n\n- **Centralized Promotions Page:** Proposal for a dedicated page to enhance compliance visibility and streamline campaign tracking.\n\n- **Simplified Mortgage Content:** Teams to reorganize mortgage info with clear bullet points for easier navigation tailored to customer needs.\n\n- **Inconsistent Branding:** Need for standardizing visuals across sections to strengthen brand identity and improve customer experience.\n\n- **Site Architecture Development:** Creating a comprehensive site map to organize content and support efficient updates going forward.\n\n- **Dynamic Content Strategy:** Monthly audits planned to keep website content fresh, relevant, and engaging for users.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Santana**\nDocument and note user experience issues with current cash management product page layouts (03:18)\nInclude remote help tool in top navigation and resource pages for easier customer access (29:10)\nLead site map creation exercise defining page hierarchy and classification by verticals (personal, business, about) (12:06)\nCoordinate with agency and internal teams to integrate mortgage loan portal hyperlink and explore URL parameter solutions for routing (53:20)\nWork on branding consistency across website pages to align with new brand guidelines (15:55)\nCollaborate with content teams to identify missing content and new page needs including community events and tools (45:49)\nSupport in strategizing navigation options for Ponzi Bank Direct integration including microsite positioning and user journey selection (34:44)\nPrepare for ongoing monthly/quarterly content audits for site maintenance post-launch (27:35)\nFollow up with Beaver Creek on videos/tutorials for online and mobile banking customer guidance (50:52)\n\n**Christina**\nShare follow-up communications next week with meeting insights and additional requests for content and feedback (56:45)\nSchedule smaller working sessions with Mortgage, Investor Relations, and other teams to refine specific content and legal requirements (33:00)\nExplore options with IT/marketing teams on integration and automation opportunities like rate tables and social sharing tools (13:29)\n\n**Jackie**\nProvide legal compliance input for Investor Relations content and help define navigation prominence requirements (32:54)\n\n**Ingrid**\nCollect additional contact center feedback on customer navigation issues and usability concerns for website improvements (29:10)\n\n**Other Team Members**\nContribute outstanding content items and product/service details from their verticals to complete website inventory (45:49)\n"},"duration":57.529998779296875,"speakers":[],"sentences":[{"text":"Okay, so today''s meeting is focused on content and experience.","index":0,"end_time":6.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And essentially what we want to cover today is the overall look, feel, design, layout, structure of the site and any specific content needs that your teams have individually.","index":1,"end_time":19.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we have our agency on the line and they''re going to kick off the agenda.","index":2,"end_time":25.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, thanks, Christina.","index":3,"end_time":28.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me share my screen here.","index":4,"end_time":29.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll pull the agenda up.","index":5,"end_time":30.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":6,"end_time":37.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hopefully everyone can see my screen.","index":7,"end_time":39.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this is the third workshop in the series that we put together to really just hear from different teams at Ponce bank across three key areas.","index":8,"end_time":49.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Today, like Christina mentioned, we''re going to focus on the content and the customer user experience side of things.","index":9,"end_time":55.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the project that we''re working on involves HubSpot from a CRM or marketing contacts perspective.","index":10,"end_time":64.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s a lot of the data that we''re able to track for customers.","index":11,"end_time":68.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then what we''ll get into more of today is on the website side with the content that we need to share with prospects or existing customers.","index":12,"end_time":77.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we have received, I believe, over 35 different responses from the survey that we sent out and have gotten some.","index":13,"end_time":86.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Some early feedback on some of the key areas that we would like to see adjusted for prospects and customers.","index":14,"end_time":93.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And what we wanted to do is really step through that today and get some of your qualitative feedback on some of the specific things that you feel.","index":15,"end_time":101.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Number one, we must keep and make sure that we even highlight more in a new version of the website or if there are key gaps that, you know in your specific area of content that we need to build new content around or, you know, fit this content in a different way on.","index":16,"end_time":120.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"On the upcoming website.","index":17,"end_time":121.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So where I would like to start is probably at the top here, just understanding basically how you all would describe customers, really think about your services and how they navigate through Ponce bank.","index":18,"end_time":136.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And when we think about the digital experience that ties to your customers.","index":19,"end_time":141.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I''ll just flesh up the existing website that we have.","index":20,"end_time":144.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":141.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Obviously, right now we really have our navigation broken down from a consumer personal standpoint, business.","index":21,"end_time":153.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we have the educational piece Financial Mastery, and then we break into the nonprofit areas there.","index":22,"end_time":160.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll open it up to the folks on the call who can take us through maybe some gaps in your specific area that you would like to see adjusted or highlighted in the new version of the website.","index":23,"end_time":173.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I can start.","index":24,"end_time":175.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hi, this is Maria.","index":25,"end_time":177.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":175.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If you go to business, into the cash management solutions.","index":26,"end_time":182.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now if you scroll down.","index":27,"end_time":187.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep, keep going.","index":28,"end_time":192.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if you go down, let''s say, to the positive pay, you see how.","index":29,"end_time":197.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You have to Keep clicking.","index":30,"end_time":198.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, go back up.","index":31,"end_time":199.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You see how you have to keep clicking and the information just keeps.","index":32,"end_time":202.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":199.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"New information keeps coming up.","index":33,"end_time":204.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":203.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, that can be a little bit confusing for the customers.","index":34,"end_time":208.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s on a lot of the products that we have there.","index":35,"end_time":211.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":36,"end_time":212.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we can definitely.","index":37,"end_time":213.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"On all the cash management products, I would definitely like to see if we can change that layout a little bit.","index":38,"end_time":218.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":39,"end_time":220.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s from like a customer or from a user experience standpoint, it''s like the scroll and reveal, so I can''t see the content in front of me.","index":40,"end_time":228.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I actually have to scroll in order for that to get revealed.","index":41,"end_time":231.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That doesn''t feel like a great experience.","index":42,"end_time":233.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It sounds like.","index":43,"end_time":234.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, and it probably isn''t too good for, you know, accessibility and kind of all of that either, you know, so we have that tool that helps with that.","index":44,"end_time":245.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But that''s a good, that''s a good point.","index":45,"end_time":248.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Tristan, make that as a note for basically just all site infrastructure and.","index":46,"end_time":254.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Then.","index":47,"end_time":255.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":254.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just noting that this is only Poncet Bank''s website.","index":48,"end_time":260.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":49,"end_time":260.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you know, I want teams that are, you know, covering the, the mortgage side also, you know, Investor Relations foundation or any of the other websites that are not focusing on right now.","index":50,"end_time":271.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Top feel, you know, able to, to chime in if you have comments.","index":51,"end_time":274.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hi, this is Jackie.","index":52,"end_time":279.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":278.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just piggyback, piggybacking off of what Maria said.","index":53,"end_time":282.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":279.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think what we do is that we tend to have, we, we tend to put a lot of information in one page and like Maria said, you just got to keep scrolling down and down and down until you actually get where you need to get to.","index":54,"end_time":296.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":283.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then from a compliance standpoint, what we also see is that then a lot of the disclaimers are like all the way down to the bottom.","index":55,"end_time":306.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":297.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s not a user friendly website actually.","index":56,"end_time":310.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":307.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I''m hoping that, you know, with this whole rebranding and what we need to do that, you know, it''s a.","index":57,"end_time":318.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":311.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Little bit more user friendly.","index":58,"end_time":319.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s like so much information out there.","index":59,"end_time":321.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":319.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, no, that, that''s great feedback because, you know, there are regulatory requirements with the, especially when you want digital campaigns to have, you know, disclosures one click away from wherever the source is.","index":60,"end_time":334.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so just one of the things that we want to do, if you can make a note of it, is to have a promotions page essentially which will give us one landing page we could turn on and off to be able to, you know, have all of the promotions promotional language for any type of campaign, you know, in one, in one place.","index":61,"end_time":355.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then that be the driving force for you know, specific digital campaigns so we can track it better.","index":62,"end_time":362.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s, that''s just one of the things I wanted to add there.","index":63,"end_time":367.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But anyone else have any comments relative to, to your area?","index":64,"end_time":371.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Even if it''s not necessarily on pr?","index":65,"end_time":373.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I can have add to what you''re all saying.","index":66,"end_time":378.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":374.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think we''re all saying the same thing.","index":67,"end_time":380.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":378.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"In agreement about the flow.","index":68,"end_time":382.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":380.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We talked about it a little bit yesterday too.","index":69,"end_time":385.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":383.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And you know, ideally from a consumer standpoint, like you go on the page and you click mortgage, it would be nice probably to just like have them have a link and then bring them somewhere like more like both, not necessarily bullet points but like bullet point format to me is just easier.","index":70,"end_time":404.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":385.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if they want, if they''re a first time home buyer, they, they can just click on first time home buyer or if they want to refi, they can just click on refi and then it would bring them to like more data.","index":71,"end_time":417.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":405.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that that may be a good flow.","index":72,"end_time":422.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":418.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":73,"end_time":423.8,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":423.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Santana, is that in reference to the, the main landing page here or where were you thinking that would exist?","index":74,"end_time":431.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And you know, we''ve talked about this with the marketing team.","index":75,"end_time":436.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":433.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s a little convoluted right now because we have like a separate mortgage world page and now it''s transitioned to Ponce and that''s being revamped which you know, we''ve had meetings and spoke about.","index":76,"end_time":452.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":436.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what it should look and feel like.","index":77,"end_time":455.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":453.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I figured just to align with everybody on here too, just sharing the same information.","index":78,"end_time":462.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":455.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Christina probably can elaborate on the, the confusion with.","index":79,"end_time":468.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":464.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I think I, I think I get, I get what you''re saying to me.","index":80,"end_time":472.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Santana, for her specific area because of, you know, the, the amount of information that, you know, a customer gets in the mortgage process, right.","index":81,"end_time":482.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s a confusing topic.","index":82,"end_time":484.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So simplicity for her is, you know, is key.","index":83,"end_time":487.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":84,"end_time":487.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":487.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so what I would say is that when we think about developing content, right, for each one of your teams there''s going to be an opportunity for, you know, us to modify kind of how those pages looks relative to the needs of your specific area.","index":85,"end_time":502.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you know, if Sunita''s team needs simplicity, high level bullets and more direct links to where they can get more information, bigger articles, applications, events and things like that, that''s, you know, a good strategy.","index":86,"end_time":516.779,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But if, you know, other teams need more kind of articles and content, that''s going to be more wordy.","index":87,"end_time":524.619,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.859,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":88,"end_time":524.939,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.619,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Then we can do that too.","index":89,"end_time":526.459,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.179,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What I will say is that what you guys should start to think about as you get into helping us Devise the content for your areas is like, what are the, the need to know things?","index":90,"end_time":540.219,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.499,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What are the products and services, services that need to be listed under your vertical?","index":91,"end_time":544.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.019,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, are you going to have, you know, topics and articles that, you know, maybe we can start to write towards, we can include that as well.","index":92,"end_time":553.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then anything that''s, that''s missing.","index":93,"end_time":555.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right now we have a lot of things missing under the personal and business.","index":94,"end_time":559.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we also have, you know, a lot of opportunity under the about and get in touch sections to make it more friendly for people to find information through like articles and resources.","index":95,"end_time":570.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Putting a community engagement kind of page out there to show what we do, a press page, news and stories is where, where we''re going to be starting to kind of write more articles.","index":96,"end_time":582.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''ll take away some of the, the verbiage that we have in the main paragraphs.","index":97,"end_time":587.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The reason why sometimes sites are developed with a lot of content is because that actually helps with organic search.","index":98,"end_time":594.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the more words you have on a page, the more times you, you know, you could possibly get picked up in organic search, which is essentially helping drive traffic to the site.","index":99,"end_time":603.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But what we''ve seen with, you know, AI and ChatGPT and things of that nature, people are not necessarily searching the same way.","index":100,"end_time":612.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They''re searching more for, for questions and answers.","index":101,"end_time":616.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so what we want to start to do is to think about how we could develop content that''s going to solve a problem or answer a question versus just be facts on a page.","index":102,"end_time":627.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So think about that too as we start to, you know, develop the content.","index":103,"end_time":631.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So my team just add to that.","index":104,"end_time":637.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":633.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We were starting from scratch because to create new pages and information that, that will go on the, the pages.","index":105,"end_time":646.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":637.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because one of the issues we had before was the formatting was not.","index":106,"end_time":654.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":648.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Structured.","index":107,"end_time":658.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Properly like we had.","index":108,"end_time":659.8,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":658.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We had situations where a category would be 30 year fixed and then it would be refi and then it would be investment property which like the subject matter are all in different groups and categories.","index":109,"end_time":674.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":660.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it didn''t line up properly.","index":110,"end_time":676.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":674.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And like the last conversation I was having with Jane, I was saying to her, technically right now all the products we do are 30 year fixed.","index":111,"end_time":684.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":676.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if that''s going to be a header and then everything that''s 30 year fix under it, that''s fine.","index":112,"end_time":690.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":685.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or we''re gonna say we do first mortgages, refis, HELOCs, and so forth.","index":113,"end_time":696.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":690.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So like it has a more better flow to it.","index":114,"end_time":700.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":696.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If that makes sense.","index":115,"end_time":701.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":700.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, that''s, that makes sense.","index":116,"end_time":705.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s kind of the goal is to getting is to get into structure.","index":117,"end_time":708.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are we leading by kind of a product specific category or something, something different.","index":118,"end_time":714.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that will help drive like what lives under the tree.","index":119,"end_time":717.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So one of the things and interesting.","index":120,"end_time":719.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe you could talk a little bit more to this.","index":121,"end_time":721.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, first exercises in building out websites is a site map structure.","index":122,"end_time":726.179,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And essentially what that is, is it''s basically like the strawman and all of like the, the subheadings and headings of the page.","index":123,"end_time":735.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.179,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so then we can start to kind of build that hierarchy to say, okay, everything under personal is going to be this, this and this.","index":124,"end_time":743.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Under business is this, this and this.","index":125,"end_time":745.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":126,"end_time":745.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then that helps provide kind of the framework and then we layer in the content based off of that framework.","index":127,"end_time":752.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":128,"end_time":752.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that exercise is going to be something that''s going to be coming up that will take a first step at building and then you guys could align on, you know, on that for accuracy.","index":129,"end_time":761.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then what?","index":130,"end_time":764.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Eventually I''ll need everybody to start to provide outside of just, you know, the services that you offer are, are things that are maybe not on our site, upcoming things that you might need to get more involved in with the site.","index":131,"end_time":781.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So think about rate changes.","index":132,"end_time":783.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So right now we have rates all over the site.","index":133,"end_time":786.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":783.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, there''s a lot of manual things.","index":134,"end_time":788.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s, it''s a little bit of a riskier thing.","index":135,"end_time":790.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":136,"end_time":790.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So my goal is to maybe build rate tables that we can automatically update.","index":137,"end_time":794.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":138,"end_time":794.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it''ll update anywhere that rate is.","index":139,"end_time":796.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So there''s a lot of other opportunities where we kind of structure the site and put content in one place, but have it kind of almost pull from that central source and be on multiple pages.","index":140,"end_time":809.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then if we have to change it, it''s easier to be, you know, edited.","index":141,"end_time":813.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I definitely agree and that''s why you guys are part of this conversation, because there''s a lot of opportunity to get alignment.","index":142,"end_time":820.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":143,"end_time":822.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And just to speak to that a little bit, Christina, like right now what we want to identify is definitely the major gaps and disconnects that we have and get a sense of the inventory of content that we need.","index":144,"end_time":834.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And like Christina mentioned just to, I have a shell of like what the site map is and that deliverable that comes out of our next phase.","index":145,"end_time":842.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But basically we build this for every single key page on the website and so within each one and you can kind of visualize these as blocks that, that move around.","index":146,"end_time":852.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":842.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then within each one of these we actually provide description of the, of the content.","index":147,"end_time":859.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s what happens next.","index":148,"end_time":862.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":859.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when we talk about information architecture and the Site map and the flow.","index":149,"end_time":867.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This is what drives that process.","index":150,"end_time":870.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.749,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then from here we go to design and build.","index":151,"end_time":873.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I just wanted to, I thought it was a good point, Christina, that you brought up just to help folks visualize what, what happens in that, that phase.","index":152,"end_time":881.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so, you know, what we''re working on now is, is that audit and assessment.","index":153,"end_time":886.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what are the big things that we need to focus on?","index":154,"end_time":889.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What do we make sure that we, we need to fit into a new structure and make sure that, that you all give us that feedback so we don''t miss anything.","index":155,"end_time":897.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s, you know, what we want to make sure we have today.","index":156,"end_time":900.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":897.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"In another conversation, but it sounds like, you know, on the mortgage side, like you mentioned, Cindy, you''re almost starting from scratch with a lot of content that you need.","index":157,"end_time":910.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What else comes to mind?","index":158,"end_time":913.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Some of the other areas that we have or even, you know, still within mortgage that, that you feel is a major gap or just a disconnect with your, your prospects and customers on the digital side.","index":159,"end_time":924.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hey, Tristan, if I may.","index":160,"end_time":927.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":926.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This is Nanette.","index":161,"end_time":928.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":927.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So in working from the, from the, the retail side, one of the things, and I know that it''s not related solely just to the content itself, but currently our website, there''s a use of multiple colors and, and it creates a disconnect with our current branding.","index":162,"end_time":946.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":929.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, for example, you see here, we use a lot of the blue, a lot of the yellow.","index":163,"end_time":951.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":946.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But once you go into the actual accounts, for example, if you go to personal and to get more visibility into the personal tracking, we, we jump into other colors that are more vibrant, that not necessarily sends, you know, the message of this is Bon says website.","index":164,"end_time":966.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":951.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, like, as a customer, I''m a customer.","index":165,"end_time":969.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":967.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"When I go to Chase''s website, I know that I am in Chase''s website.","index":166,"end_time":973.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":969.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":167,"end_time":973.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I go to bank of America.","index":168,"end_time":974.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":973.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know that I''m banking with bank of America because the content and also the colors used are consistently across.","index":169,"end_time":980.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":974.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, for example, if you scroll down a little bit more, you see, like the simply here we''re going into now multiple colors.","index":170,"end_time":988.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":981.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so, you know, from the customer''s perspective doesn''t necessarily send the message that the branding is consistent.","index":171,"end_time":998.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":988.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, we actually did a brand exercise just so everybody knows.","index":172,"end_time":1004.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I don''t know, Tristan, if you had that, you know, available, that whole brand guide that we just worked on, because it had some examples.","index":173,"end_time":1012.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But.","index":174,"end_time":1013.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1012.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":1013.45,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1013.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are you okay if I share some of that?","index":176,"end_time":1014.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":177,"end_time":1015.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1015.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that that''s obviously just caveating.","index":178,"end_time":1018.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s still, you know, could change slightly, but we went through a brand exercise to kind of identify some new colors, still keeping, you know, some consistency with what we''re offering today.","index":179,"end_time":1029.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s not such a big lift to change everything and then some different applications and treat.","index":180,"end_time":1035.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1029.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":181,"end_time":1040.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But as I pull that up then anything else that comes to mind in that, that retail side from a content perspective.","index":182,"end_time":1047.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":183,"end_time":1048.26,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1047.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":184,"end_time":1048.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1048.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then so I, I think Maria Santana touched basis on this earlier.","index":185,"end_time":1053.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1048.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But so for example.","index":186,"end_time":1054.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1053.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":187,"end_time":1055.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1054.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think it''s also important that we provide our clients with the proper guidance so they trust and they rely on our website if they can''t come into the bank.","index":188,"end_time":1063.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1055.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if you click on for example, see if you go to our personal and you go to the last one, personal loan and mortgages or you stop sharing.","index":189,"end_time":1075.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, let me see.","index":190,"end_time":1076.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1075.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, let me.","index":191,"end_time":1077.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1076.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m working on two screens and I don''t want to miss what you''re talking through here.","index":192,"end_time":1083.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1077.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I have the guideline.","index":193,"end_time":1087.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1084.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I pulled that up.","index":194,"end_time":1087.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1087.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So let me share back my screen.","index":195,"end_time":1089.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1087.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sorry for throwing you for a loop, Tristan.","index":196,"end_time":1097.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I just thought.","index":197,"end_time":1097.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, you''re testing my, my mouse and keyboard skills right now in real time.","index":198,"end_time":1102.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But we''re good.","index":199,"end_time":1102.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":200,"end_time":1103.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sorry Nanette, you mentioned go to.","index":201,"end_time":1105.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":202,"end_time":1106.07,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1105.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Go.","index":203,"end_time":1106.35,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1106.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Personal loans and mortgages.","index":204,"end_time":1107.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1106.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":1108.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So here, the, the, the landing page here starts talking about, you know, becoming a homeowner.","index":206,"end_time":1119.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1112.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":207,"end_time":1119.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1119.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So and if you scroll a little bit down and it goes into this is our mortgage loan which I guess it prompts us, Anita, to the Mortgage world website.","index":208,"end_time":1130.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1119.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If you scroll a little bit down, planning for the big event.","index":209,"end_time":1134.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1130.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A little bit, little bit down.","index":210,"end_time":1135.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1134.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So once you click on learn more for our personal loans, this is more services we offer on the retail side.","index":211,"end_time":1141.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1135.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And now it prompts us to go to the mortgage side of the website.","index":212,"end_time":1145.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1141.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So to the customer''s point, it may be a little bit, it''s, it''s disconnected.","index":213,"end_time":1154.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1149.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":214,"end_time":1154.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because at the retail we offer the personal.","index":215,"end_time":1156.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1154.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then for the mortgage world Bankers is more about financing, purchasing properties, becoming a first time homeowner.","index":216,"end_time":1164.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1156.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":217,"end_time":1165.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":218,"end_time":1166.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So here they won''t find anything related to personal loans.","index":219,"end_time":1169.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1166.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right, got it.","index":220,"end_time":1171.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":1172.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1172.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that does, you know, it opens up in a new tab.","index":222,"end_time":1174.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1172.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Different, slightly different experience visually as well.","index":223,"end_time":1177.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And, and that is, you know where, where we want to head is create more of a seamless experience for folks so that it feels like ponce bank is connected.","index":224,"end_time":1185.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Even if you are on the personal side or if you''re looking for, you know, that, that loan mortgage piece, we''re able to still feel like one place on the offering.","index":225,"end_time":1194.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1185.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And, and it all has to do with the same thing.","index":226,"end_time":1197.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1194.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s just the flow and the feel and it''s.","index":227,"end_time":1200.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1197.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I would think it''s overwhelming for the customer especially like including what Nanette said as far as the color.","index":228,"end_time":1207.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1200.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It all interrupts your peace of mind when you''re looking at the website if your, your brain is jumping all over the place, you know, so it''s not a, it''s not a comforting experience to look at the website if you have to be like your mind has to go higher level thinking than having it be a flow and like a smooth, you know.","index":229,"end_time":1232.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1207.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So yeah, it''s, it''s a lot of band aids that, you know, unfortunately we''re just put on top of.","index":230,"end_time":1238.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so that''s why we''re, you know, we''re thinking about it from a user experience to see, you know, the, the flow.","index":231,"end_time":1244.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1239.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But let''s, let''s just quickly preview that, that new brand guide just to, to give everyone a kind of just snip snapshot of some of the things that we''re looking to maybe do with the brand, to modernize it a little bit.","index":232,"end_time":1260.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":233,"end_time":1264.28,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1264.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so can everyone see this PDF here?","index":234,"end_time":1266.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":235,"end_time":1268.16,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1267.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":236,"end_time":1268.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, yep, we really wanted to refine the brand like Christina mentioned, at a modernized touch but then also staying authentic with, with pieces of New York and the community.","index":237,"end_time":1281.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So really trying to connect both things, you know, move it to a modernized feel, but then still have some of that, that classic approach.","index":238,"end_time":1289.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1281.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So in the brand guidelines we have a whole system that we pulled out here that goes everywhere from the logo, identity usage, color system, visual language, not only from icons but the photography and then also an illustration style.","index":239,"end_time":1304.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And this is what we will see come together with the content that we''re talking about today to create more of that cohesive experience.","index":240,"end_time":1311.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me just talk through some key things.","index":241,"end_time":1314.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So logo treatment, not a lot change here.","index":242,"end_time":1317.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, this, this is Ponce bank and we are working with this identity, but it all became what do we extend this into and how do we modernize from here?","index":243,"end_time":1329.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1317.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And this starts to build out what it looks like with, with Ponsse bank moving and shifting into a new experience.","index":244,"end_time":1338.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1330.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And as you can start to see on the right, an illustration style that actually uses drawings, sketch art to give a realistic portrayal of real life images in New York.","index":245,"end_time":1355.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1338.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so these wouldn''t be stock pieces.","index":246,"end_time":1357.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"These would be taken from actual images of the bank or streets of New York.","index":247,"end_time":1362.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1357.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s where you can start to.","index":248,"end_time":1364.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1362.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll go through the color system here, but this is a big piece as well, is to have a consistent color treatment throughout and then let me just go to typography.","index":249,"end_time":1377.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me flash through some of the key visual language here.","index":250,"end_time":1380.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this is how we would start to build out some of the illustrations for consistency purposes.","index":251,"end_time":1386.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this is what you would see used across all different products and services.","index":252,"end_time":1389.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A consistent illustration style that uses the color scheme that we have in place and doesn''t vary across a lot of different situations that you see now.","index":253,"end_time":1402.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1391.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then you can see with the icons themselves, we gave them a stronger line, point, line, but then they''re still minimal enough to let some of the content illustrations, you know, take control visually.","index":254,"end_time":1419.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And as we start to look at photography, we really wanted a documentary style look and feel like a 50 millimeter photo that you would commonly see where it''s, it''s real people and real places, whether that''s coming into the branch, walking on a street that is familiar, this is the type of vibe that we would actually pull in.","index":255,"end_time":1442.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1419.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that because we are a community bank, we''re connected to the community, we''re actually seeing ourselves in images as well.","index":256,"end_time":1450.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then so this is how you can see some of that photography getting built out with the, with subtle treatments that we have from a stylistic standpoint.","index":257,"end_time":1458.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then now we can start to see the use of illustration types where we''re actually taking real photos from inside a branch and converting that into drawings and sketches to give like a very throwback feel, but also a modern touch with a lot of the graphics that we''re incorporating on top of.","index":258,"end_time":1480.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1458.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then if you can start to see this built out even a little bit more where we''re able to pull through some spotlight colors, whether it is a, you know, a cab in New York that we, we pull that yellow through, or if it''s a sign, a ponce bank, indoor sign, something along those lines, you can start to see how this builds out to familiar settings and places within New York.","index":259,"end_time":1503.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1480.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then lastly, this is how you''ll see that translate into a hero type image for a specific product or solution area.","index":260,"end_time":1513.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"On the website, we''re able to still have that classic throwback, realistic drawing and sketches, but then we''re, we''re able to modernize it with the illustration styles and iconography on top of that.","index":261,"end_time":1525.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1513.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so this is where we''ve landed so far.","index":262,"end_time":1528.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And like Christina mentioned, we''re still going through some refinements, but this is the direction we''re headed to.","index":263,"end_time":1533.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1528.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s at consistency.","index":264,"end_time":1534.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1533.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"See overall with all the different entities that we''re pulling together.","index":265,"end_time":1537.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1534.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, no, Tristan, thanks for sharing that.","index":266,"end_time":1540.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1538.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know it wasn''t like really Part of the conversation today, but I thought it would be nice to kind of mention it since, you know, that came up.","index":267,"end_time":1545.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But what you can see here is that we''re trying to kind of balance our history, kind of the, the old school vibe with modern.","index":268,"end_time":1555.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then also there''s some options, you know, where you would want to be a little more sophisticated, more like the commercial side and stuff of that nature.","index":269,"end_time":1563.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s why we still have the use of, you know, stock photography.","index":270,"end_time":1566.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And there''s always options to also take our own photography.","index":271,"end_time":1570.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1566.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":272,"end_time":1570.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what we''re trying to do is come up with more consistency, less options for colors and icons and, and things like that.","index":273,"end_time":1579.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1571.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it starts to.","index":274,"end_time":1581.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"To the next point, build out our brand identity in the market.","index":275,"end_time":1586.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And people could know like when they see this, it''s ponce.","index":276,"end_time":1589.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1586.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":277,"end_time":1589.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1589.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so this will actually be.","index":278,"end_time":1590.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1589.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":279,"end_time":1591.48,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1591.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''ll be translated kind of in a lot of other things, but it''s definitely going to be more clean and fresh.","index":280,"end_time":1597.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The pages are going to have content on it, but the content is going to be more meaningful.","index":281,"end_time":1602.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The, you know, the links are going to direct, you know, more consistently and there''ll be less clicks to get where you need to go.","index":282,"end_time":1611.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1602.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the goal is, and that''s what we''re having this call is to, to point out the gaps so we can ensure that when we build the navigation we''re not adding things after the fact.","index":283,"end_time":1620.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1611.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":284,"end_time":1620.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1620.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because that''s sometimes when you.","index":285,"end_time":1622.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1620.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"More clicks because things are just added wherever.","index":286,"end_time":1625.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1623.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The good news is is that now, you know, Victor did an amazing job with, you know, building out a lot of these pages.","index":287,"end_time":1632.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But, you know, there is a certain level of skill that working with an agency provides in terms of the technicality and the programming and things, you know, that might be beyond Victor''s scope.","index":288,"end_time":1644.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The other thing I will say is that this website is not going to just be, you know, launched in April and then forgotten about.","index":289,"end_time":1651.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s going to be a collaborative process that throughout the life cycle.","index":290,"end_time":1655.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1652.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":291,"end_time":1655.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So like at the end of 2026, the website is going to look completely different from when it launched because you guys are going to be on a monthly basis responsible for auditing any pages that you cover.","index":292,"end_time":1669.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A monthly basis might sound crazy, maybe it''ll move to quarterly.","index":293,"end_time":1672.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But essentially like, things change very frequently.","index":294,"end_time":1675.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, new products and services are added, you know, regulations change, change, campaigns change.","index":295,"end_time":1682.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so there''s always changes happening to this site.","index":296,"end_time":1684.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1682.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I think it''s important to have that buy in from the teams and so just, just throwing that out there as you Know, we''re building out the new site.","index":297,"end_time":1693.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s definitely going to be more collaboration to make sure that the pages always remain accurate.","index":298,"end_time":1697.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now I think at this point we can get back to the agenda and I want to hear from other teams.","index":299,"end_time":1705.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1699.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, we have lending, we, we talk a lot about what about, you know, foundation careers, we have investor relations, Ponce Bank Direct.","index":300,"end_time":1714.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1705.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s a lot of other websites that we manage that are just going to be built into this.","index":301,"end_time":1718.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1715.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''d love to hear from those teams if there''s anything to add.","index":302,"end_time":1722.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1718.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If not, we''ll move into the agenda.","index":303,"end_time":1724.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1722.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":304,"end_time":1725.81,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1725.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Christina, this is Ingrid and the perspective for the contact center.","index":305,"end_time":1729.69,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1725.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know that the customer, we assist the customer logging in into the online banking.","index":306,"end_time":1733.69,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1729.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All the way on the bottom on the hyperlink you have one of the tools that we use really often which is the remote help.","index":307,"end_time":1740.65,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1734.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the remote help, it''s one of the tools that we use to co browsing the customers when they''re not being able to navigate on their own on our website.","index":308,"end_time":1749.77,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1741.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if that come branding, if that link could be moved and be included, one of the top, on the top, you know, when we touch base it about online banking and things like that, that will be great because it is really hard for customers sometimes to find that part in order for them to get the assistance that they need.","index":309,"end_time":1770.07,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1750.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Got it.","index":310,"end_time":1771.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":311,"end_time":1771.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1771.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So more top line navigation in like a resource page would be helpful which is something that we''re planning to build out.","index":312,"end_time":1782.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1771.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''ll make a note of that.","index":313,"end_time":1784.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then you know on the landing page you have something on the top that it says get in touch with us or if you click digger and you have like contact us and things like that.","index":314,"end_time":1795.82,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1786.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''d be able to incorporate the, you know, remote help in order for us to have better assets for the customer for them to log in.","index":315,"end_time":1802.94,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1795.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":316,"end_time":1803.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s on the bottom but it''s not at the top like so it should be in both menus.","index":317,"end_time":1808.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So yeah, so.","index":318,"end_time":1809.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1808.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Tristan, make a note of that.","index":319,"end_time":1810.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1809.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know that some of the things are on the site but they''re not in the appropriate places.","index":320,"end_time":1814.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They should be in more than one place.","index":321,"end_time":1816.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":322,"end_time":1816.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1816.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s a good piece of feedback and ingres, if you have anything else to share from the team, maybe you know, comments or suggestions from customers, things that have come up, you definitely feel free to, you know, share those offline.","index":323,"end_time":1831.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1819.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We can build out to help kind of remedy some of the common issues that, you know, maybe you get calls about.","index":324,"end_time":1838.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1831.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thank you.","index":325,"end_time":1839.13,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1838.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thank you.","index":326,"end_time":1839.49,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1839.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And also, you know, if the Same thing line Nanette and Santana says about the consistency.","index":327,"end_time":1843.29,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1839.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If you click on the person or and you click on the online and mobile banking and you click on the business.","index":328,"end_time":1848.61,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1843.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This descript.","index":329,"end_time":1850.01,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1849.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean that''s different images.","index":330,"end_time":1851.49,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1850.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like even though both platform covered about.","index":331,"end_time":1854.17,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1851.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"For example if you scroll down it covered about debit cards, it covered about bill pays and all that.","index":332,"end_time":1860.29,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1854.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s different.","index":333,"end_time":1861.65,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1860.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like the image are different.","index":334,"end_time":1863.49,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1861.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like in here you see that it''s only that says manage your money debit card estate.","index":335,"end_time":1867.57,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1863.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But if you go to the business side then you see like a picture.","index":336,"end_time":1871.41,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1867.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If you go to.","index":337,"end_time":1872.91,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1872.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":338,"end_time":1873.23,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1872.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then you scroll down what it says about the same features.","index":339,"end_time":1876.83,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1873.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So look at the ways.","index":340,"end_time":1878.67,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1877.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Scroll a little bit more.","index":341,"end_time":1879.79,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1878.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now it should be somewhere down here.","index":342,"end_time":1883.79,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1879.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, you click.","index":343,"end_time":1886.35,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1885.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think you click.","index":344,"end_time":1887.15,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1886.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s the one that it says business online banking.","index":345,"end_time":1889.55,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1887.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s business online banking.","index":346,"end_time":1891.83,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1890.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There you go.","index":347,"end_time":1892.51,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1891.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And the support that it took about the debit cards, the E statement which is the same that it should be at the retail but in here, look at the way that they presented here turn your car debit card.","index":348,"end_time":1905.52,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1893.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s not a consistency of what you see on the personal side of what you see it on the business eye.","index":349,"end_time":1910.44,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1905.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, got that.","index":350,"end_time":1912.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So common things that are common across both like let''s make them feel similar in nature from.","index":351,"end_time":1919.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1912.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That is correct.","index":352,"end_time":1920.76,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1920.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":353,"end_time":1921.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1921.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, it''s funny because a lot of the things that you know are offered consumer versus business are pretty much the, the same.","index":354,"end_time":1931.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1923.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So some companies will do like a online and mobile banking page but then have a split for consumer, a split for business and then you know, this way it''s, it''s kind of a one place if they''re, if they fall in both categories because a lot of times business customers have personal accounts.","index":355,"end_time":1948.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1931.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":356,"end_time":1948.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1948.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we can think about that as a, as a navigation too.","index":357,"end_time":1952.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1948.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is there anyone that can, you know, speak to or want to, you know, mention anything about Ponce Bank Direct or foundation or investor relations?","index":358,"end_time":1965.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1954.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Christina, this is Jackie.","index":359,"end_time":1969.57,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1968.209,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The same thing that Ingrid just said.","index":360,"end_time":1972.21,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1969.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like the investor relations is not showing on this website like that you have to click into about and then you have to find it there.","index":361,"end_time":1980.45,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1972.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s not.","index":362,"end_time":1981.41,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1980.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, it has to be more clearly identified because it''s a legal requirement.","index":363,"end_time":1986.92,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1982.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if we can get this up, up front instead of hiding it behind another link.","index":364,"end_time":1993.72,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1988.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, so like a main navigation or like a button in the, in the top right hand side or something of.","index":365,"end_time":2001.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1993.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That nature somewhere that you can easily be seen.","index":366,"end_time":2003.24,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2001.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, yeah, no, that makes sense.","index":367,"end_time":2005.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2003.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then you know Jag, when we talk about the the content for this page, you know, obviously it''s going to be very different.","index":368,"end_time":2012.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2006.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s certain legal requirements and things that we have to kind of work through.","index":369,"end_time":2015.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2012.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''ll probably have a little quick working session just with, with you and Sergio just to make sure that we''re all line because there''s.","index":370,"end_time":2024.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2015.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right now it looks completely different than the branding.","index":371,"end_time":2027.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2024.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I would like to have it look the same but also be separated if there''s any, you know, disclosures or things that don''t apply.","index":372,"end_time":2037.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2027.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Plus you''ll probably want to use the corporate logo instead.","index":373,"end_time":2042.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2037.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just the Pon bank for that page.","index":374,"end_time":2044.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2042.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":375,"end_time":2046.24,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2045.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":376,"end_time":2047.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2046.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"When it comes.","index":377,"end_time":2050.76,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2050.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m sorry, when it comes to Pon Ban red, the Pon Ban right now is going to be included in our main page.","index":378,"end_time":2056.8,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2050.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''ll, it''ll be included in our website as a, like a micro site.","index":379,"end_time":2065.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2057.919,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So essentially we''re going to keep the Pon Bank Direct brand and kind of experience just because when we toyed back and forth about getting rid of it, we, we found that, you know, when it comes to the national marketing and out of state and all that kind of stuff, it could be a little bit confusing.","index":380,"end_time":2083.819,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2065.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so what will happen is somewhere in the main page it''ll.","index":381,"end_time":2088.419,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2084.138,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''ll be, you know, access our digital bank or, you know, whatever, and it''ll click on it and then a new kind of microsite landing page will come up, similar to how it does with more good world bankers when we clicked off.","index":382,"end_time":2102.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2088.419,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But it''ll live within our site so the customer will know it''s.","index":383,"end_time":2106.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2102.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s still the same trusted bank as Ponce, but it''s just a different offering and we can market differently that way.","index":384,"end_time":2111.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2106.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if you''re working on anything related to integrated into.","index":385,"end_time":2118.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2113.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Into Positive Bank Direct, it won''t really be impacted because we''re just going to keep, keep it kind of separate.","index":386,"end_time":2122.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2118.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":387,"end_time":2123.98,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2123.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because that''s, that''s my concern because you know that we implemented Glia and there''s a couple of things that we''re going to comparate it on the site.","index":388,"end_time":2130.26,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2123.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thank you.","index":389,"end_time":2130.82,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2130.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":390,"end_time":2131.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2130.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":391,"end_time":2131.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2131.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, we''re good.","index":392,"end_time":2132.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2131.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Christine, if I may, with.","index":393,"end_time":2134.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2132.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"With Direct, would that live in the header navigation or would we spot like that somewhere out?","index":394,"end_time":2139.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2134.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like is it.","index":395,"end_time":2139.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2139.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Does.","index":396,"end_time":2140.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2140.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Where does it fit?","index":397,"end_time":2141.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2140.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like main nav.","index":398,"end_time":2143.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2141.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, you know, I, I thought a little bit about this.","index":399,"end_time":2147.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2144.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s a couple of ways we can handle it and maybe that''s a good kind of question for the team.","index":400,"end_time":2150.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2147.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So typically when, when a customer comes to this site, you could.","index":401,"end_time":2154.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2150.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ve seen Some bigger banks do this.","index":402,"end_time":2156.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2155.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You start with a kind of a navigational question because they''re there for a reason and, you know, you want to be able to customize the content based off of what they''re looking for.","index":403,"end_time":2166.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2156.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we can have something pop up when they come to the website.","index":404,"end_time":2170.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2166.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Instead of it going directly to the landing page, it can go and say, you know, what are you looking for to do today?","index":405,"end_time":2175.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2170.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":406,"end_time":2175.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2175.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are you an investor?","index":407,"end_time":2177.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2175.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are you looking for, you know, a certain product?","index":408,"end_time":2180.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2177.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":409,"end_time":2180.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2180.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then whatever they, they answer could, you know, determine what page that they, they come to.","index":410,"end_time":2185.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2180.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or we can just have a menu kind of built out somewhere on the, the page where the customer could then just toggle between different websites that we offer.","index":411,"end_time":2198.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2186.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right?","index":412,"end_time":2199.54,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2199.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, so if they want to go to the foundation, they would click Foundation.","index":413,"end_time":2203.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2200.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It could be another menu item.","index":414,"end_time":2204.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2203.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":415,"end_time":2205,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2204.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You don''t want to add too many because then the mobile experience becomes a little bit wonky.","index":416,"end_time":2208.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2205,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But we can think about that when we talk about the site architecture.","index":417,"end_time":2212.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2208.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Tristan.","index":418,"end_time":2212.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2212.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But those are some of the examples that I''ve seen other banks use and it worked either way.","index":419,"end_time":2220.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2212.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And when does just thinking about it from a user standpoint, when do I go directly versus another route on here, is it just being out of state?","index":420,"end_time":2231.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2221.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, is that the trigger where I would want the digital offerings?","index":421,"end_time":2235.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2231.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or when does direct get introduced?","index":422,"end_time":2237.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2235.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I guess, yeah, when we, when we run, you know, specific campaigns that are, you know, for rates and products on that are online only and not in branch.","index":423,"end_time":2247.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2237.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s when we do campaigns that are going to be outside of branch market areas.","index":424,"end_time":2252.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2247.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I guess what, what will happen is, is that if we''re going to use a product that''s specific to Ponzi Bank Direct in our marketing, we''d be using the landing page for Ponzi Bank Direct, we wouldn''t send the customer to Ponzi Bank''s landing page.","index":425,"end_time":2265.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2252.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They could just so happen to navigate off of the direct site and start to look elsewhere.","index":426,"end_time":2270.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2265.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If they were interested in learning about what we did locally in the community, or if they wanted to see kind of, you know, more about the bank, we, when we get same thing for investor relations, when we''re doing something for investor relations, we would use the investor relations site Foundation.","index":427,"end_time":2287.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2270.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Same thing.","index":428,"end_time":2287.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2287.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If a customer searches us and they search for the foundation, it''ll come up and direct them there.","index":429,"end_time":2295.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2288.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s all about us building the site for search to be able to, then to direct to the right landing page.","index":430,"end_time":2302.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2297.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If they come to the bank''s website, just, you know, by typing in Ponsse Bank Direct.","index":431,"end_time":2306.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2302.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s what I was saying before.","index":432,"end_time":2307.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2306.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like do we want to make it where it''s like they choose the journey that they want to go go on whether they''re an investor, whether they''re looking for local banking, whether they''re looking for you know, community or foundation.","index":433,"end_time":2319.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2308.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like we can do that too.","index":434,"end_time":2320.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2319.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s a, you know, an option or we can just have it live on the menus and you know, a customer can pick and choose what we offer.","index":435,"end_time":2329.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Did that, did that answer or.","index":436,"end_time":2333.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2331.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think so.","index":437,"end_time":2334.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2334.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":438,"end_time":2335.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2334.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll just have to figure out because, because you''re right there, there are several ways we could do that.","index":439,"end_time":2339.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2335.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s all about like how, how prominent do we want it to be?","index":440,"end_time":2343.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2339.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because you''re right, if we are doing direct promotions and programs and we control where they land then we can send them directly to a place.","index":441,"end_time":2352.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2343.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that the big thing is if they go to ponce bank.com when.","index":442,"end_time":2357.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2353.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or.","index":443,"end_time":2358.14,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2357.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or how do we introduce direct as an option or do we need to.","index":444,"end_time":2364.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2359.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s kind of that, that question there.","index":445,"end_time":2366.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2364.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":446,"end_time":2366.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2366.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And the beauty about you know, HubSpot and we could talk about this a little bit more offline because it, it would probably require some you know, program configuration.","index":447,"end_time":2375,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2366.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But for example if they come to the site from an out of state ip, you know, we could customize it to have them automatically default to you know, a different landing page than Ponzi bank.","index":448,"end_time":2386.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2375,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or we can have that pop up to say you know, hey, you know, are you look interested in you know, local banking or not?","index":449,"end_time":2395.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2388.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then they can decide we can come up with a different journey flows.","index":450,"end_time":2401.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2395.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But that''s a good question because we want to make sure that the experience for people that would necessarily be somewhat interested in, in some topics, they don''t get lost.","index":451,"end_time":2412.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2401.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":452,"end_time":2414.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2413.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And you''re right there, there are a couple ways we could do that.","index":453,"end_time":2416.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2414.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"IP address, you know, also recognize visitors if they, we already know where they, they need to go that we could hide that type of pop up there.","index":454,"end_time":2426.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2416.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s also, you know, for sending folks from a campaign we could use you know the URL tag to, to essentially route them somewhere or present a pop ups.","index":455,"end_time":2438.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2426.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s a lot of different ways we can handle that.","index":456,"end_time":2441.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2438.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Do we feel like Direct needs to be in the main nav as an option or, or do you feel like we need to select folks based on like some of that other data?","index":457,"end_time":2451.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2441.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just trying to figure out when we know a customer fits direct or, or it doesn''t like how do we.","index":458,"end_time":2458.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2452.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Even if we don''t think about technology.","index":459,"end_time":2460.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2458.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is there a way that we determine that?","index":460,"end_time":2462.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2460.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I guess we''ll have to have more discovery on that.","index":461,"end_time":2466.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2464.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I would, I would say a lot of it is going to be the customers, you know, self selecting, you know, especially if we get limited data into the system, if we have obviously a match we can try with, you know, populating the right page or the page that we think is best for them.","index":462,"end_time":2483.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2466.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But again like that would only be applicable to Ponzi Bank Direct and Ponzi bank.","index":463,"end_time":2487.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2483.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like we would not be able to do the same thing for investor relations and Foundation.","index":464,"end_time":2493.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2487.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Those site visitors would be people that would actually have like ponzi bank.com investor relationship or you know, ponzi.com foundation or we can even white label, you know, domains for different pages.","index":465,"end_time":2509.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2493.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I did that when I was at mcu.","index":466,"end_time":2512.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2511.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We had a separate kind of microsite for foundation.","index":467,"end_time":2515.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2512.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But you can type in a different URL if you wanted to go directly there.","index":468,"end_time":2520.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2516.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we can work on those custom URLs too to make it a little bit easier for like those specific teams to put those URLs in their like communications or signatures or whatever it is.","index":469,"end_time":2531.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2521.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Christina, we could have further discussion about where to place it because currently we have a lot of customers for Ponce Bank Direct that they go through our regular website and they click what it says, login and enter the credential for Ponce Bank Direct and they not be able to log in thinking that it''s only one site.","index":470,"end_time":2548.51,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2533.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we could have further discussion how could better assess our customer and what or to have that Ponce event Direct hyperlink and then we will take it from there.","index":471,"end_time":2557.41,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2548.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, no, that, that''s a, that''s a good point.","index":472,"end_time":2560.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2558.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Most of the customer like when you, when they ask for assistant, it''s because they on the wrong website.","index":473,"end_time":2566.77,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2562.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":474,"end_time":2568.849,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2568.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And normally.","index":475,"end_time":2569.57,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2568.849,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hi, I''m Joanna.","index":476,"end_time":2571.45,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2569.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And normally right now on Poncet Buying direct, if the customer goes to poncefine Direct, they are information that provides the customer about Ponce Bank.","index":477,"end_time":2581.65,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2571.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it kind of tells them that we are the same bank.","index":478,"end_time":2585.09,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2581.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The customer from Ponce Bank Direct goes to Ponce Bank.","index":479,"end_time":2588.49,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2585.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There is nowhere on the website that says anything about Ponce Bank Direct.","index":480,"end_time":2592.37,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2588.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So they are 100 completely confused or where they are or if the bank is a split bank or we are same entity.","index":481,"end_time":2601.57,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2592.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we just want to make them understand that we are all the same same bank.","index":482,"end_time":2606.21,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2602.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s just that we provide different product based on where they are or how.","index":483,"end_time":2610.65,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2606.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They want to banking.","index":484,"end_time":2611.65,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2610.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If they want to do it digital or if they want to come into the branches.","index":485,"end_time":2614.85,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":2611.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":486,"end_time":2616.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2615.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s why I was saying, like, we.","index":487,"end_time":2618.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2616.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ve been consistently putting band aids on top of things.","index":488,"end_time":2620.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2618.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when we launched Ponzi Bank Direct, it was never thought to like, say, hey, how does this impact the ponzi bank.com and then, you know, change that to make it flow, you know, so that''s one of the things that my team''s gonna be, you know, constantly doing, is figuring out when new things come up, how do we make them flow with what we have already.","index":489,"end_time":2637.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2620.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, the other thing that I was, you know, referring to is that when the customer comes, ponbank.com that whole kind of helping them understand what journey they want to take by pre, you know, asking probing questions like, are you interested in banking online?","index":490,"end_time":2653.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2638.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or, you know, are you interested in banking locally?","index":491,"end_time":2656.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2653.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Could just be like an interesting way to help them ensure that they end up on the right page.","index":492,"end_time":2662.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2656.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s something that I want to start to think about when we talk Tristan, about the site infrastructure and give the team some options that we can maybe test out.","index":493,"end_time":2670.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2662.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, got that.","index":494,"end_time":2674.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2671.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, those are, those are key things and it''s all that is the architecture we''re thinking about and we do want like these are good observations that you have.","index":495,"end_time":2683.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2674.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, when customers are confused or not finding what they need to, those are the types of things we need to solve.","index":496,"end_time":2689.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2683.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s what we''ll look to do there.","index":497,"end_time":2692.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2690.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What else jumps out at you all from across some of these key areas that you see in the navigation?","index":498,"end_time":2698.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2692.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now?","index":499,"end_time":2698.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2698.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think a good question I would like to ask is what gaps do we see with content that doesn''t exist?","index":500,"end_time":2707.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2698.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Do you feel the state of content in your area is now it''s like the content''s there, it''s just not organized in the best way.","index":501,"end_time":2716.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2708.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or do you feel like there are definitely items missing that aren''t even present on the existing website?","index":502,"end_time":2722.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2716.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like what are those true gaps that we have?","index":503,"end_time":2724.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2722.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s a little bit of both.","index":504,"end_time":2730.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2728.949,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":505,"end_time":2733.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2733.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sorry, John.","index":506,"end_time":2734.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2733.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s a little bit of both.","index":507,"end_time":2734.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2734.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, I think, yeah, we''ve come to the consensus that there is things that are a little bit, bit out of order here or like just not that easy to navigate.","index":508,"end_time":2742.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2734.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And in terms of like, call to actions that should be placed from top to from bottom to top or whatnot.","index":509,"end_time":2748.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2743.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then obviously, I know Christina mentioned a couple times, foundation and then even investor relations, things of that, like those micro sites that should be incorporated in the bigger umbrella.","index":510,"end_time":2758.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2749.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Tristan, to add to that, there are a ton of products and services that we offer that are not on the sites, we have all of our, we were just talking about this with the, you know, external affairs team.","index":511,"end_time":2773.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2761.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All of our, what we call ESD partnership loan programs.","index":512,"end_time":2778.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2773.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have, you know, partnerships and things with, um, other, you know, organizations that, you know, are not necessarily on there.","index":513,"end_time":2786.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2779.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Um, we have, um, certain, you know, like Santana mentioned, there''s certain mortgage products that are confusing, not, not on there.","index":514,"end_time":2795.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2787.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have a couple of other products that are coming up.","index":515,"end_time":2800.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2796.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, Ingress mentioned Glia on the direct side, it''s a service more so than a product.","index":516,"end_time":2807.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2801.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have Zell for business coming that''s not on there.","index":517,"end_time":2810.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2807.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then there''s probably opportunity to start to think about how we add things like other applications or other lead forms for products that we have just general information on by default.","index":518,"end_time":2825.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2811.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So like on the commercial loan side, there''s a lot of just general, like, hey, contact us for this, but we don''t really give the customer a lot of information about what it is we even offer or what the experience like between us and another bank would be.","index":519,"end_time":2839.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2825.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so that''s an opportunity.","index":520,"end_time":2842.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2841.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then somehow along the lines we''re going to have to start to think about other pages that we don''t have that I want.","index":521,"end_time":2852.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2843.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So like the community page that I talked about, right, where we get to put articles, you know, events that we''re having where they could be put in one kind of calendar and then the website will populate with them and then when they have they happen, they would roll off into like another section.","index":522,"end_time":2872.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2852.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for example, like we would have upcoming events, but then like it would roll into a past event after it happens, right?","index":523,"end_time":2879.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2872.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So some of that automation right now, everything is manual.","index":524,"end_time":2881.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2879.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A lot of the times, like even when Victor puts up an alert, right?","index":525,"end_time":2885.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2882.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like we, we just have so much going on, we''ll forget to take it down, set ourselves reminders, right?","index":526,"end_time":2892.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2885.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So things like that, I want to have, you know, maybe some RSS feed integration with our social channels, you know, contact us forms, you know, email enrollments, you know, things of that nature.","index":527,"end_time":2908.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2892.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''re also going to make sure that we have the accessibility functionality, API set up with the new site, right?","index":528,"end_time":2916.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2908.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have to work through that.","index":529,"end_time":2917.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2916.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we want to start to do more, like I said, content around trending topics, information that people want, right?","index":530,"end_time":2928.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2918.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So one of the biggest things that I, and I actually just shared this with VAL before because it relates to a lot of the financial mastery and community engagement programs.","index":531,"end_time":2935.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2928.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But coming up with a annual content calendar where we''re going to start to write articles, start leadership pieces, which we''ll be able to one use for more engagement on the site but two, also be able to, to send out to our front facing teams for them to use as approved content for social.","index":532,"end_time":2954.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2935.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it might be nice to start to add sort of like a social share option onto the site.","index":533,"end_time":2961.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2955.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So anybody could share directly from our site to social media and we can kind of see how many people have done that.","index":534,"end_time":2969.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2961.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s usually like a little ticker at the bottom.","index":535,"end_time":2972.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2970.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Another thing that we have to start to think about is how we build, build out the local branch experience pages.","index":536,"end_time":2979.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2973.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I want to start to be able to kind of customize some of our location pages, be able to like if we''re going to offer specific promotions to that branch.","index":537,"end_time":2990.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2979.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for example, like 207 we can have specific areas that we could do that on those pages.","index":538,"end_time":2995.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2990.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We do need to have an area where we update our hours and things and that would kind of translate through to other, other pages rates.","index":539,"end_time":3005.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2996.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, things of that nature about us is also disjointed.","index":540,"end_time":3010.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3005.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, we have more in our history to share.","index":541,"end_time":3015.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3011.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think it''s just we position it differently depending on what brand we''re talking about.","index":542,"end_time":3020.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3015.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we can kind of build that out.","index":543,"end_time":3021.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3020.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Ponce Radio and all of that.","index":544,"end_time":3024.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3023.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t, I don''t necessarily know where that''s going to go, but we can talk about that.","index":545,"end_time":3028.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3024.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then there''s a mission driven program that we''re working on.","index":546,"end_time":3033.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3029.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We started that, but it got put on hold.","index":547,"end_time":3036.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3033.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So there''s a landing page that we have that''s not necessarily on the news on the site right now.","index":548,"end_time":3040.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3036.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I have to work for that, you know, in rebuilding what that''s gonna look like.","index":549,"end_time":3045.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3040.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then I want an area of the site that''s going to have resources for the customer.","index":550,"end_time":3055.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3046.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So tools, calculators, which I think come out of the box with, with some of our lending los systems.","index":551,"end_time":3063.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3055.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We could talk about that.","index":552,"end_time":3064.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3063.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Santana and.","index":553,"end_time":3065.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3064.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then just other helpful tools.","index":554,"end_time":3069.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3066.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So things like ingress just mentioned.","index":555,"end_time":3071.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3069.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":556,"end_time":3071.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3071.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have that.","index":557,"end_time":3072.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3071.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How does a customer, for example, when we launch digital issuance, how do.","index":558,"end_time":3079.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3073.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How does a customer, if they lose their debit card get a digitally issued issued one?","index":559,"end_time":3083.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3079.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":560,"end_time":3083.71,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":3083.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So there''s instructions and things that you know, we can give the customer to better help them self serve, so to speak.","index":561,"end_time":3091.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3083.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s a bunch of the things that I''m looking to do.","index":562,"end_time":3094.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3091.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We also have partnerships with fiserv.","index":563,"end_time":3098.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3094.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not sure kind of, you know, how much we want to dig deep into that, but there''s a lot of tutorials and just different videos that were apparently available through Beaver Creek Ingres.","index":564,"end_time":3109.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3098.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m not sure if you know anything about this, but there''s a lot of videos and things that are available for us to kind of help guide customers through like the online thinking mobile banking experience.","index":565,"end_time":3120.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3109.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we''re going to start to hopefully, you know, use some of those if they''re still applicable.","index":566,"end_time":3127.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3122.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We might have to update them a little bit, but there''s a lot of things that we''re not using that we have, we just have never put them on.","index":567,"end_time":3134.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3127.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s like.","index":568,"end_time":3135.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3134.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Great to hear about that.","index":569,"end_time":3138.28,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":3137.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":570,"end_time":3139.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3139,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll sync with you and Chris and we can figure out, you know, what''s available through Beaver Creek and then what, you know, might need to be changed with some screenshots that, you know, we''re making some updates with, with the XD and stuff.","index":571,"end_time":3151.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3141.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But that''s, you know, that''s another thing.","index":572,"end_time":3155.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3152.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The last thing I wanted to throw out there is Tristan, if you click on the login, so it''s personal and business, but that''s relative to online banking.","index":573,"end_time":3168.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3158.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Santana and anyone else from the mortgage team, is there a thought process around giving integration into the loan portal?","index":574,"end_time":3179.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3168.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because I know sometimes, especially in is it encompass?","index":575,"end_time":3184.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3179.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t know if that''s the one we use, but if it is, the customers typically in the application process have like a loan portal where they would go to upload documents, check the loan status, things like that.","index":576,"end_time":3193.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3184.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We can also, you know, integrate some of those, you know, logins or at least put a hyperlink.","index":577,"end_time":3200.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3194.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if a customer needs to follow up on things, it''s readily available.","index":578,"end_time":3205,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3201.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But wasn''t sure if that, you know, something you wanted to do.","index":579,"end_time":3207.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3205.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are you asking me?","index":580,"end_time":3211.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3209.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I''m asking if it''s, if it''s available and if, you know, if it''s something that we wanted to, to think about coding in.","index":581,"end_time":3216.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3211.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":582,"end_time":3218.57,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3217.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean I want to take advantage of any thing that makes the process more seamless and you know, efficient and like more technology driven and less manual.","index":583,"end_time":3232.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3218.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"For sure.","index":584,"end_time":3232.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3232.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There is a bridge between something on the website through the Consumer Connect portal for encompassing and it has like where, you know, and I think it hasn''t been updated for a while but it has where you can meet the team and you have like the loan officer''s name and you click on the name of the loan officer and you can, ideally you could do an application and it would funnel to that specific loan officer and then again if it is updated and working perfectly, it would connect them to where they could upload docs and it goes right to the filing compass.","index":585,"end_time":3275.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3233.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And of course we haven''t taken advantage to perfect it, but it''s, there is technology behind it.","index":586,"end_time":3284.46,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3276.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for that I would say let.","index":587,"end_time":3286.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3284.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If you want to connect me to the, to the rep for that.","index":588,"end_time":3289.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3286.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because that''s usually it''s like a third party landing page that we would customize with some of the marketing assets and kind of brand look and feel.","index":589,"end_time":3297.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3289.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We could send them our brand guide and then they can kind of make some of the tweaks and then what we could do is, you know, just hyperlink to that as like a, you know, tool.","index":590,"end_time":3307.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3297.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":591,"end_time":3308.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3307.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A resource for mortgage applicants.","index":592,"end_time":3310.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3308.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that it is like the owner from that aspect just controlling the, the website and updating.","index":593,"end_time":3318.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3310.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Dean usually is the point person for Encompass and then everything has to, you know, so far it''s like connecting and just collaborating between me, Dean or IT and marketing to, to perfect it basically would be.","index":594,"end_time":3338.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3319.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I was just gonna say, Santana, with those, you know, third party systems that we have to route people to through a URL, there, there might be an option to put something in a URL parameter that that third party system then ingests and then they can route it, you know, to the, to the right person.","index":595,"end_time":3354.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3338.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for example, if there''s a rep that we can put in the parameter itself and then that is a, an ID that they can use in their system to route that.","index":596,"end_time":3364.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3355.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s one possible way to do that.","index":597,"end_time":3365.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3364.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s how the systems can talk to each other.","index":598,"end_time":3368.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3366.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Awesome.","index":599,"end_time":3369.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3369.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, it hasn''t been a priority, but you know, it.","index":600,"end_time":3373.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3369.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think it''s somewhere on the list of things to smooth out.","index":601,"end_time":3377.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3373.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, well that, that''s all, you know, this, I think this has been one of the kind of more robust meetings where we got a lot of good, you know, insights.","index":602,"end_time":3387.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3378.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I appreciate everybody''s, you know, feedback and comments and things like that.","index":603,"end_time":3392.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3388.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Victor, Tristan and I, we''re going to go through kind of digest everything.","index":604,"end_time":3396.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3392.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think we''re going to actually send out follow ups next week because I, I was gonna say I was a little bit ambitious when I said I was gonna send out some things by end of day today because I started to realize that we probably, you know, would not have enough time to gather the thoughts from this meeting.","index":605,"end_time":3412.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3396.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you''ll hear back sometime probably next week with just some takeaways and additional requests for content information, things like that.","index":606,"end_time":3421.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3412.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then what will happen is the agency and I will sync and then we''ll build out next session.","index":607,"end_time":3428.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3422.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll send out a series of meetings.","index":608,"end_time":3429.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3428.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If there''s additional meetings that need to be happening, especially if they''re, like smaller teams.","index":609,"end_time":3433.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3429.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we''ll go from there.","index":610,"end_time":3435.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3434.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":611,"end_time":3442.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3442.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thanks, everyone.","index":612,"end_time":3443.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3442.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Have a great weekend.","index":613,"end_time":3445.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3444.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Appreciate your time.","index":614,"end_time":3446,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3445.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thank you.","index":615,"end_time":3447.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3446.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, have a good one.","index":616,"end_time":3448.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3447.84,"speaker_name":null}],"dateString":"2025-11-21T19:02:18.000Z","host_email":null,"meeting_link":null,"participants":[],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KAKWQF6TJJDGF8TPFTD8JA5A","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Identified UX pain points like scrolling content; agency tasked to improve layout clarity.","Brand consistency gaps flagged; updated guidelines and illustrations to streamline customer experience.","Teams agreed content must be audience-specific; structure to reflect loan, mortgage, or retail needs.","Investor relations and remote support tools to be repositioned for higher visibility and compliance.","Site map and architecture review initiated; audit underway to unify fragmented micro-sites and flows."],"highlights":[{"quote":"On all the cash management products, I would definitely like to see if we can change that layout.","speaker":"Maria"},{"quote":"Currently our website, there''s a use of multiple colors... creates a disconnect with our branding.","speaker":"Nanette"},{"quote":"This website is not going to just be launched in April and then forgotten about.","speaker":"Christina"}],"topics":["ux","branding","navigation","architecture","multi-site"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Content & User Experience**\n\nThe meeting identified key content gaps and usability issues on the current Ponce Bank website that hinder customer navigation and engagement.\n\n- **Maria** highlighted the confusing scroll-and-reveal layout on cash management product pages, where users must keep clicking to see new information, which negatively impacts accessibility and user experience (03:18).\n    - This layout causes frustration and could deter customers from exploring products fully.\n    - The team agreed this needs a structural redesign to display content more clearly and reduce excessive scrolling.\n    - Tristan was tasked with noting this for overall site infrastructure improvements.\n    - Fixing this will improve customer satisfaction and potentially increase product inquiries.\n\n- **Jackie** emphasized that dense information and hidden disclaimers at the bottom of pages reduce usability and compliance visibility (04:39).\n    - She proposed a centralized promotions page to consolidate campaign information and disclosures for better tracking and regulatory compliance.\n    - This page would allow toggling promotions on or off to support digital campaigns with clearer messaging.\n    - Creating this resource aligns with regulatory needs and marketing agility, improving campaign effectiveness.\n\n- The mortgage team, represented by **Santana** and **Cindy**, called for simplified content structures with clear bullet-point navigation targeting specific customer needs like first-time buyers or refinancing (06:05).\n    - They stressed reorganizing mortgage content to group similar products logically, e.g., by loan type or purpose, to improve flow.\n    - This restructuring would reduce confusion and speed up customer decision-making.\n    - The team will soon begin sitemap development to establish hierarchical content frameworks.\n    - This will serve as the foundation for consistent and intuitive navigation.\n\n- **Nanette** and others noted inconsistent branding and color usage across personal and business sections undermines brand trust and creates a disjointed customer experience (15:09).\n    - The current site uses multiple conflicting colors, which confuse users about brand identity.\n    - A recent brand guide aims to modernize the look while preserving community ties, standardizing colors, icons, and imagery (20:32).\n    - The new style includes hand-drawn illustrations and documentary-style photos to evoke authenticity.\n    - Consistent visual language will strengthen brand recognition and user comfort across all site sections.\n\n- **Ingrid** requested elevating key service links like remote help to top navigation positions to improve customer access and reduce support calls (28:54).\n    - Currently, critical tools are buried at the bottom of pages, making them hard to find.\n    - The plan includes building a dedicated resource page with prominent placement.\n    - This will enhance self-service capabilities and reduce friction for customers needing assistance.\n\n- The group agreed that common features such as online banking and debit card information should be presented consistently between personal and business sections to avoid confusion (31:30).\n    - Harmonizing content presentation will make cross-segment customers feel more seamless and reduce cognitive load.\n    - This consistency supports customers who hold both personal and business accounts.\n\n## **Site Architecture & Integration**\n\nThe team is prioritizing a clear, adaptable site architecture to organize existing content and support future updates efficiently.\n\n- The next major step is creating a comprehensive **site map** that defines page hierarchies and content groupings for personal, business, mortgage, and other verticals (12:06).\n    - This sitemap will serve as a blueprint for content placement and navigation design.\n    - Teams will review and validate the sitemap for accuracy and completeness.\n    - This will enable centralized content management and reduce duplication.\n\n- There is a strong focus on automating rate updates with centralized rate tables that propagate changes site-wide to reduce manual errors and delays (12:06).\n    - This system will improve accuracy and speed for rate changes.\n    - It also reduces operational risk and maintenance burdens.\n\n- The team will introduce a **content audit and gap analysis** to identify missing products, partnership programs, and services currently absent from the website (13:29).\n    - This includes emerging mortgage products, ESD partnership loans, and new service launches like Glia and Zell for business.\n    - The goal is to ensure all offerings are represented clearly to prospects and customers.\n\n- Integration opportunities include syncing branch event calendars, alerts, social media feeds, and content sharing features to increase engagement (47:21).\n    - Automation will help content stay current and reduce manual upkeep.\n    - Adding social share buttons will boost organic reach and visibility.\n\n- Accessibility compliance and API setups are key technical priorities to meet legal standards and improve user experience (48:48).\n    - This ensures the site is usable by all customers and integrates smoothly with backend systems.\n\n- Online banking login areas will be enhanced with potential links to loan portals like Encompass to streamline customer access to loan status and document uploads (53:04).\n    - **Santana** emphasized using technology to reduce manual processes and improve customer self-service.\n    - Coordination with IT and third-party vendors will be necessary to brand and customize these integrations.\n\n## **Branding & Visual Identity**\n\nThe meeting confirmed a strategic push to modernize and unify Ponce Bank’s brand identity across all digital touchpoints.\n\n- The new **brand guide** establishes a consistent color palette, typography, iconography, and illustration style that balances modern design with authentic local elements (20:32).\n    - This includes sketch-style illustrations from real New York scenes to build community connection.\n    - The brand refresh aims to create a clean, fresh, and recognizable look across all products and pages.\n\n- The design will reduce the current visual clutter and inconsistent color usage that weakens brand recognition (16:09).\n    - Consistency will be maintained across personal, business, mortgage, and investor relations sites.\n    - This will help customers instantly identify they are within the Ponce Bank ecosystem regardless of entry point.\n\n- Photography style will shift to documentary, candid images to reflect real customers and branches, enhancing emotional connection (23:39).\n    - This approach contrasts with generic stock photos and supports authenticity.\n\n- The branding refresh supports the website’s goal to reduce clicks and simplify navigation, improving overall user satisfaction (26:20).\n    - A consistent brand language will also support marketing campaigns and communications.\n\n## **Multi-Brand & Microsite Strategy**\n\nThe team addressed how to cohesively manage multiple brands and specialized sites under the Ponce Bank umbrella.\n\n- **Ponce Bank Direct** will remain a separate microsite within the main Ponce Bank website to preserve its distinct digital-only offering (34:44).\n    - This microsite will have its own landing page but remain visually connected to Ponce Bank.\n    - The approach prevents customer confusion while supporting national marketing outside local branch areas.\n\n- There are ongoing discussions on how to position **Ponce Bank Direct** and other entities like **Foundation** and **Investor Relations** in navigation (35:56).\n    - Options include pop-up journey selectors on entry, separate menu items, or IP-based routing to tailor the experience.\n    - The team is evaluating user flow impacts and mobile navigation constraints to finalize placement.\n\n- The goal is to help customers self-select the right journey, whether local banking, digital-only, community foundation, or investor relations (37:15).\n    - This segmentation will reduce confusion and improve conversion for targeted campaigns.\n\n- Clear branding and navigation are especially important as some customers currently get confused between Ponce Bank and Ponce Bank Direct sites, leading to login and service issues (43:08).\n    - The team plans further discussions to create clear pathways and links between brands.\n    - Messaging will emphasize that all entities are part of the same bank, just with different service channels.\n\n## **Content Strategy & Ongoing Governance**\n\nThe meeting set the foundation for a dynamic, evolving content strategy with shared team ownership.\n\n- The website will not be static; teams will be responsible for **monthly or quarterly audits** of their pages to keep content accurate and up to date (27:35).\n    - This process will address frequent product changes, regulatory updates, and campaign shifts.\n    - Collaboration between marketing, IT, and business units is essential for success.\n\n- The team plans to develop an **annual content calendar** focused on trending topics, leadership pieces, and community engagement articles to drive ongoing site traffic and social sharing (48:48).\n    - Content will focus on answering customer questions rather than just listing facts to match modern search behaviors.\n    - Social share features will track engagement and amplify reach.\n\n- Future site enhancements include creating interactive tools and calculators, localized branch promotion pages, and a centralized resource hub for self-service tutorials and FAQs (47:21).\n    - These will improve customer empowerment and reduce support demand.\n\n- Partnerships with vendors like Fiserv and Beaver Creek will be leveraged to provide tutorial videos and digital guides, which will be updated and integrated into the site (51:38).\n    - This content supports customer onboarding for online and mobile banking products.\n\n- The team acknowledged the need for improved **content structuring and categorization** to better align product groups and avoid confusing mixes, especially in mortgage offerings (10:28).\n    - Clear headers and logical groupings will simplify discovery and reduce customer effort.\n\n- Key stakeholders like **Jackie** and **Sergio** will have focused working sessions to align on legal content and investor relations pages to ensure compliance and consistent branding (33:00).\n\n- The agency and internal teams will consolidate feedback and send follow-ups next week to gather outstanding content and structural details for the next phase of design and build (56:04).","outline":null,"keywords":["Website Redesign","Content Strategy","User Experience","Branding Consistency","Site Map Architecture","Mortgage Portal Integration"],"overview":"- **Website Usability Issues:** Current layout frustrates users; structural redesign needed for clarity and engagement. \n\n- **Centralized Promotions Page:** Proposal for a dedicated page to enhance compliance visibility and streamline campaign tracking.\n\n- **Simplified Mortgage Content:** Teams to reorganize mortgage info with clear bullet points for easier navigation tailored to customer needs.\n\n- **Inconsistent Branding:** Need for standardizing visuals across sections to strengthen brand identity and improve customer experience.\n\n- **Site Architecture Development:** Creating a comprehensive site map to organize content and support efficient updates going forward.\n\n- **Dynamic Content Strategy:** Monthly audits planned to keep website content fresh, relevant, and engaging for users.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Santana**\nDocument and note user experience issues with current cash management product page layouts (03:18)\nInclude remote help tool in top navigation and resource pages for easier customer access (29:10)\nLead site map creation exercise defining page hierarchy and classification by verticals (personal, business, about) (12:06)\nCoordinate with agency and internal teams to integrate mortgage loan portal hyperlink and explore URL parameter solutions for routing (53:20)\nWork on branding consistency across website pages to align with new brand guidelines (15:55)\nCollaborate with content teams to identify missing content and new page needs including community events and tools (45:49)\nSupport in strategizing navigation options for Ponzi Bank Direct integration including microsite positioning and user journey selection (34:44)\nPrepare for ongoing monthly/quarterly content audits for site maintenance post-launch (27:35)\nFollow up with Beaver Creek on videos/tutorials for online and mobile banking customer guidance (50:52)\n\n**Christina**\nShare follow-up communications next week with meeting insights and additional requests for content and feedback (56:45)\nSchedule smaller working sessions with Mortgage, Investor Relations, and other teams to refine specific content and legal requirements (33:00)\nExplore options with IT/marketing teams on integration and automation opportunities like rate tables and social sharing tools (13:29)\n\n**Jackie**\nProvide legal compliance input for Investor Relations content and help define navigation prominence requirements (32:54)\n\n**Ingrid**\nCollect additional contact center feedback on customer navigation issues and usability concerns for website improvements (29:10)\n\n**Other Team Members**\nContribute outstanding content items and product/service details from their verticals to complete website inventory (45:49)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"bf239776-71df-4b97-9587-ac52c78fb35a","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
