INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Ponce Bank - Hubspot Series: Content & Experience',
  '## **Website Content & User Experience**

The meeting identified key content gaps and usability issues on the current Ponce Bank website that hinder customer navigation and engagement.

- **Maria** highlighted the confusing scroll-and-reveal layout on cash management product pages, where users must keep clicking to see new information, which negatively impacts accessibility and user experience (03:18).
    - This layout causes frustration and could deter customers from exploring products fully.
    - The team agreed this needs a structural redesign to display content more clearly and reduce excessive scrolling.
    - Tristan was tasked with noting this for overall site infrastructure improvements.
    - Fixing this will improve customer satisfaction and potentially increase product inquiries.

- **Jackie** emphasized that dense information and hidden disclaimers at the bottom of pages reduce usability and compliance visibility (04:39).
    - She proposed a centralized promotions page to consolidate campaign information and disclosures for better tracking and regulatory compliance.
    - This page would allow toggling promotions on or off to support digital campaigns with clearer messaging.
    - Creating this resource aligns with regulatory needs and marketing agility, improving campaign effectiveness.

- The mortgage team, represented by **Santana** and **Cindy**, called for simplified content structures with clear bullet-point navigation targeting specific customer needs like first-time buyers or refinancing (06:05).
    - They stressed reorganizing mortgage content to group similar products logically, e.g., by loan type or purpose, to improve flow.
    - This restructuring would reduce confusion and speed up customer decision-making.
    - The team will soon begin sitemap development to establish hierarchical content frameworks.
    - This will serve as the foundation for consistent and intuitive navigation.

- **Nanette** and others noted inconsistent branding and color usage across personal and business sections undermines brand trust and creates a disjointed customer experience (15:09).
    - The current site uses multiple conflicting colors, which confuse users about brand identity.
    - A recent brand guide aims to modernize the look while preserving community ties, standardizing colors, icons, and imagery (20:32).
    - The new style includes hand-drawn illustrations and documentary-style photos to evoke authenticity.
    - Consistent visual language will strengthen brand recognition and user comfort across all site sections.

- **Ingrid** requested elevating key service links like remote help to top navigation positions to improve customer access and reduce support calls (28:54).
    - Currently, critical tools are buried at the bottom of pages, making them hard to find.
    - The plan includes building a dedicated resource page with prominent placement.
    - This will enhance self-service capabilities and reduce friction for customers needing assistance.

- The group agreed that common features such as online banking and debit card information should be presented consistently between personal and business sections to avoid confusion (31:30).
    - Harmonizing content presentation will make cross-segment customers feel more seamless and reduce cognitive load.
    - This consistency supports customers who hold both personal and business accounts.

## **Site Architecture & Integration**

The team is prioritizing a clear, adaptable site architecture to organize existing content and support future updates efficiently.

- The next major step is creating a comprehensive **site map** that defines page hierarchies and content groupings for personal, business, mortgage, and other verticals (12:06).
    - This sitemap will serve as a blueprint for content placement and navigation design.
    - Teams will review and validate the sitemap for accuracy and completeness.
    - This will enable centralized content management and reduce duplication.

- There is a strong focus on automating rate updates with centralized rate tables that propagate changes site-wide to reduce manual errors and delays (12:06).
    - This system will improve accuracy and speed for rate changes.
    - It also reduces operational risk and maintenance burdens.

- The team will introduce a **content audit and gap analysis** to identify missing products, partnership programs, and services currently absent from the website (13:29).
    - This includes emerging mortgage products, ESD partnership loans, and new service launches like Glia and Zell for business.
    - The goal is to ensure all offerings are represented clearly to prospects and customers.

- Integration opportunities include syncing branch event calendars, alerts, social media feeds, and content sharing features to increase engagement (47:21).
    - Automation will help content stay current and reduce manual upkeep.
    - Adding social share buttons will boost organic reach and visibility.

- Accessibility compliance and API setups are key technical priorities to meet legal standards and improve user experience (48:48).
    - This ensures the site is usable by all customers and integrates smoothly with backend systems.

- Online banking login areas will be enhanced with potential links to loan portals like Encompass to streamline customer access to loan status and document uploads (53:04).
    - **Santana** emphasized using technology to reduce manual processes and improve customer self-service.
    - Coordination with IT and third-party vendors will be necessary to brand and customize these integrations.

## **Branding & Visual Identity**

The meeting confirmed a strategic push to modernize and unify Ponce Bank’s brand identity across all digital touchpoints.

- The new **brand guide** establishes a consistent color palette, typography, iconography, and illustration style that balances modern design with authentic local elements (20:32).
    - This includes sketch-style illustrations from real New York scenes to build community connection.
    - The brand refresh aims to create a clean, fresh, and recognizable look across all products and pages.

- The design will reduce the current visual clutter and inconsistent color usage that weakens brand recognition (16:09).
    - Consistency will be maintained across personal, business, mortgage, and investor relations sites.
    - This will help customers instantly identify they are within the Ponce Bank ecosystem regardless of entry point.

- Photography style will shift to documentary, candid images to reflect real customers and branches, enhancing emotional connection (23:39).
    - This approach contrasts with generic stock photos and supports authenticity.

- The branding refresh supports the website’s goal to reduce clicks and simplify navigation, improving overall user satisfaction (26:20).
    - A consistent brand language will also support marketing campaigns and communications.

## **Multi-Brand & Microsite Strategy**

The team addressed how to cohesively manage multiple brands and specialized sites under the Ponce Bank umbrella.

- **Ponce Bank Direct** will remain a separate microsite within the main Ponce Bank website to preserve its distinct digital-only offering (34:44).
    - This microsite will have its own landing page but remain visually connected to Ponce Bank.
    - The approach prevents customer confusion while supporting national marketing outside local branch areas.

- There are ongoing discussions on how to position **Ponce Bank Direct** and other entities like **Foundation** and **Investor Relations** in navigation (35:56).
    - Options include pop-up journey selectors on entry, separate menu items, or IP-based routing to tailor the experience.
    - The team is evaluating user flow impacts and mobile navigation constraints to finalize placement.

- The goal is to help customers self-select the right journey, whether local banking, digital-only, community foundation, or investor relations (37:15).
    - This segmentation will reduce confusion and improve conversion for targeted campaigns.

- Clear branding and navigation are especially important as some customers currently get confused between Ponce Bank and Ponce Bank Direct sites, leading to login and service issues (43:08).
    - The team plans further discussions to create clear pathways and links between brands.
    - Messaging will emphasize that all entities are part of the same bank, just with different service channels.

## **Content Strategy & Ongoing Governance**

The meeting set the foundation for a dynamic, evolving content strategy with shared team ownership.

- The website will not be static; teams will be responsible for **monthly or quarterly audits** of their pages to keep content accurate and up to date (27:35).
    - This process will address frequent product changes, regulatory updates, and campaign shifts.
    - Collaboration between marketing, IT, and business units is essential for success.

- The team plans to develop an **annual content calendar** focused on trending topics, leadership pieces, and community engagement articles to drive ongoing site traffic and social sharing (48:48).
    - Content will focus on answering customer questions rather than just listing facts to match modern search behaviors.
    - Social share features will track engagement and amplify reach.

- Future site enhancements include creating interactive tools and calculators, localized branch promotion pages, and a centralized resource hub for self-service tutorials and FAQs (47:21).
    - These will improve customer empowerment and reduce support demand.

- Partnerships with vendors like Fiserv and Beaver Creek will be leveraged to provide tutorial videos and digital guides, which will be updated and integrated into the site (51:38).
    - This content supports customer onboarding for online and mobile banking products.

- The team acknowledged the need for improved **content structuring and categorization** to better align product groups and avoid confusing mixes, especially in mortgage offerings (10:28).
    - Clear headers and logical groupings will simplify discovery and reduce customer effort.

- Key stakeholders like **Jackie** and **Sergio** will have focused working sessions to align on legal content and investor relations pages to ensure compliance and consistent branding (33:00).

- The agency and internal teams will consolidate feedback and send follow-ups next week to gather outstanding content and structural details for the next phase of design and build (56:04).',
  '2025-11-21 19:02:18+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Document and note user experience issues with current cash management product page layouts (03:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Include remote help tool in top navigation and resource pages for easier customer access (29:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Lead site map creation exercise defining page hierarchy and classification by verticals (personal, business, about) (12:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with agency and internal teams to integrate mortgage loan portal hyperlink and explore URL parameter solutions for routing (53:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Work on branding consistency across website pages to align with new brand guidelines (15:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate with content teams to identify missing content and new page needs including community events and tools (45:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Support in strategizing navigation options for Ponzi Bank Direct integration including microsite positioning and user journey selection (34:44)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare for ongoing monthly/quarterly content audits for site maintenance post-launch (27:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with Beaver Creek on videos/tutorials for online and mobile banking customer guidance (50:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Share follow-up communications next week with meeting insights and additional requests for content and feedback (56:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Schedule smaller working sessions with Mortgage, Investor Relations, and other teams to refine specific content and legal requirements (33:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Explore options with IT/marketing teams on integration and automation opportunities like rate tables and social sharing tools (13:29)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide legal compliance input for Investor Relations content and help define navigation prominence requirements (32:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Collect additional contact center feedback on customer navigation issues and usability concerns for website improvements (29:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Contribute outstanding content items and product/service details from their verticals to complete website inventory (45:49)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
