-- Meeting: Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting (2025-11-21 14:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2025-11-21 14:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KA1DF2XRHP5TB3ZDX8CZT5YR',
    'Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Tristan Pelligrino","Eli Bebinger","Axel Völker","Axel Völker","Tristan Pelligrino"}'::text[],
    2033,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/8971821371',
    '{"id":"01KA1DF2XRHP5TB3ZDX8CZT5YR","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Freemium Product Positioning and User Access**\n\nThe team decided to emphasize providing users with access to the **full product features** rather than limiting functionality in the freemium offering, aiming to improve user engagement and enterprise interest (03:11).\n\n- **Axel Völker** clarified that current freemium access is manually controlled and limited due to beta-stage features, mostly targeting smaller companies and individuals rather than enterprise users.\n- The strategy will highlight that users get to **try the full version** without overwhelming them with organization-wide access, creating a “Trojan horse” effect for sales to initiate deeper conversations, as explained by **Tristan Pelligrino** (04:48).\n- Language changes will shift from “free” to more inviting phrases like “get started now” or “try now” to better reflect the trial nature without implying full free use or premium tiers (06:29).\n- The decision was influenced by market feedback indicating enterprise customers often face frustration when they cannot see the product, so unlocking features upfront is expected to reduce friction and improve conversion (07:12).\n\n## **Post-Registration Engagement and Outreach Workflow**\n\nThe group agreed to design a **structured post-registration email drip campaign** complemented by manual sales outreach to help users adopt the product more effectively (10:13).\n\n- **Eli Bebinger** emphasized the need for clear objectives and resources guiding new users since many cannot navigate the product independently after sign-up.\n- The proposed sequence would deliver **4–5 key onboarding emails** over several days, featuring best practices and short demo videos to highlight essential features and build user momentum (11:03).\n- Due to lack of automation in HubSpot, the team plans to use **N8N workflows** to enroll registrants and send these emails automatically, ensuring consistent follow-up (12:30).\n- **Axel Völker** will refine feature positioning in the emails and landing page to align messaging with freemium capabilities and user expectations (13:15).\n\n## **Landing Page and Advertising Refresh**\n\nThe landing page and ads are set for a **development rollout on Monday**, with final content tweaks and feedback integration planned to ensure alignment with product features and messaging (13:37).\n\n- **Axel Völker** is reviewing the landing page text to add missing features like resource management and adjust iconography to better represent the full product offering (14:06).\n- Visual elements including images perceived as AI-generated will be adjusted post-deployment, as these are not development blockers (14:56).\n- The geographic messaging will be revised from “distributed by IT companies across Germany, UK and US” to a more inclusive phrase like “global teams,” reflecting market relevance and avoiding confusion (15:38).\n- The email copy for the campaign has been shared in Google Drive and PDF formats, with the team consolidating feedback ahead of launch (18:44).\n- The campaign launch timing was discussed, and the team agreed to **launch midweek after the US Thanksgiving holiday**, balancing audience availability and campaign momentum (22:33).\n\n## **Explainer Video and AI Feature Messaging**\n\nThe explainer video script will be adjusted to **moderate claims around AI bot functionality**, ensuring messaging does not overpromise features still in early beta (23:56).\n\n- **Axel Völker** highlighted the need to identify specific AI use cases that can be confidently promoted without misleading users.\n- The AI bot section will remain brief (around six to eight seconds) and focused on currently available capabilities, with non-implemented features like RFP parsing removed from the script (25:29).\n- The video production will include side-by-side workflows for visual and voiceover elements, as explained by **Tristan Pelligrino** (24:58).\n\n## **Product Onboarding Content Strategy**\n\nThe team plans to create a **library of short, focused product walkthrough videos** showcasing key use cases for different user segments to improve product understanding and marketing reach (26:54).\n\n- **Axel Völker** outlined two main product modules: **skill and CV management**, which is niche, and **resource management**, which is broader and more widely used.\n- Walkthroughs will emphasize realistic onboarding steps users can take, such as uploading CVs or managing employee schedules, using demo data to illustrate enterprise features that require large datasets (27:38).\n- Existing videos, like the resource request demo shared by **Eli Bebinger**, will be repurposed and supplemented with new ones tailored for marketing and onboarding use (30:27).\n- These videos can also be sliced into shorter clips for retargeting ads, increasing the flexibility and impact of marketing assets (29:34).\n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed to **reschedule the next sync meeting to Tuesday, November 28th at 10:00 AM CET**, accommodating participant availability and preparing for the campaign launch (32:16).\n\n- **Tristan Pelligrino** will send a fresh calendar invite owned by him to avoid conflicts with Colin’s invites.\n- Feedback on the landing page, ads, and email content will be incorporated promptly to maintain the planned Monday development start and midweek campaign launch (32:53).\n- The team will continue iterative improvements on live assets post-deployment to stay ahead of schedule and ensure a smooth rollout (15:32).","outline":null,"keywords":["freemium model","landing page","post-registration outreach","drip email campaign","explainer video","resource management"],"overview":"- **Freemium Product Strategy:** Users will access full features in freemium, enhancing engagement without overwhelming enterprise clients.  \n- **Post-Registration Campaign:** A structured email drip campaign will aid user onboarding, featuring 4-5 key emails with demos.  \n- **Landing Page Update:** Updates to the landing page and ads are scheduled for Monday, with launches planned for after Thanksgiving.  \n- **Explainer Video Adjustments:** The video script will moderate AI claims, focusing on currently available features to avoid misleading users.  \n- **Onboarding Video Library:** Short product walkthroughs will be created to showcase key use cases, enhancing marketing and user understanding.  \n- **Next Meeting:** Rescheduled for November 28th at 10:00 AM CET; focus on feedback integration for campaign launch preparations.","action_items":"\n**Axel Völker**\nProvide detailed feedback and adjustments on freemium features and landing page content (13:15)\nReview and give final input on ads and email sequences by Monday development start (18:43)\nUpdate AI agent use cases in explainer video script to reflect current beta functionality and avoid overpromising (23:56)\nSubmit suggestions for adjustments in icons and layout on landing page as features expand (14:06)\nShare existing resource request video with the team for marketing use (30:27)\n\n**Eli Bebinger**\nFacilitate sharing of resource request video in Teams and support creation of post-registration drip email campaign content (30:59)\nCoordinate structure and objectives for post-registration outreach; propose sequence of onboarding emails introducing core features and best practices (10:00)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nCoordinate landing page iteration and ensure development schedule stays on track starting Monday (13:37)\nShare email sequence document and ad materials with team for review and consolidate feedback (18:46)\nSchedule follow-up meeting for Tuesday, Nov 28, at 10 AM and send updated meeting invite (32:41)\nManage creation of demo videos for feature walkthroughs and support building post-registration drip email campaign via N8N (29:22)\n"},"duration":33.880001068115234,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":1,"name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"id":2,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":3,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":4,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Good, good.","index":0,"end_time":1.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Got folks hopping in here.","index":1,"end_time":5.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Julie, is it?","index":2,"end_time":9.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.08,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No.","index":3,"end_time":9.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.28,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Julie.","index":4,"end_time":10.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":9.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi, Guj.","index":5,"end_time":11.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, cool.","index":6,"end_time":13.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":12.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Nice meeting you, Eli.","index":7,"end_time":16.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":14.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, you as well.","index":8,"end_time":17.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hello.","index":9,"end_time":20,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":19.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hello, Axel.","index":10,"end_time":22.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How are you doing today?","index":11,"end_time":23.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m good, thanks.","index":12,"end_time":25.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":24.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How are you?","index":13,"end_time":25.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":25.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Good.","index":14,"end_time":26.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":26.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Doing well, doing well.","index":15,"end_time":29.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":16,"end_time":31.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Got a few things to go through this morning.","index":17,"end_time":33.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":31.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Anyone else jumping on?","index":18,"end_time":35.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":33.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are we good here?","index":19,"end_time":36.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Not from our side.","index":20,"end_time":38.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":37.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":21,"end_time":40.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Colin is enjoying a day off, so.","index":22,"end_time":43.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Lucky him.","index":23,"end_time":44.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right, all right, let''s share my screen here.","index":24,"end_time":50.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you bought Julie?","index":25,"end_time":52.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":53.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":53.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":27,"end_time":56.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"She''s a member of our team, so.","index":28,"end_time":60.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":56.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yep, got a lot of different moving parts going on for you all.","index":29,"end_time":64.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":61.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So have her join today.","index":30,"end_time":66.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"She''s been also helping out, but, you know, we''ll get.","index":31,"end_time":70.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Keep things rolling here and excited to.","index":32,"end_time":75.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":71.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To go through a bunch of stuff here today.","index":33,"end_time":76.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Four or three main things I wanted to go through when I was talking with Colin.","index":34,"end_time":83.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":78.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Got the outreach metrics.","index":35,"end_time":85.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":84.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can go through some of the summary level information.","index":36,"end_time":88.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":85.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just get your feedback there on what.","index":37,"end_time":91.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''Ve done so far in the campaign.","index":38,"end_time":92.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":91.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then I know obviously we are.","index":39,"end_time":95.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":93.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Refreshing the campaign and we have a lot of assets that we''re rolling out for that.","index":40,"end_time":101.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so Axel had sent a note last night.","index":41,"end_time":104.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":101.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It sounds like you''ve gone through perhaps the landing page in some of the material in the ads.","index":42,"end_time":109.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":104.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I just started on the landing page, really just before the call, I had a. Yeah, that''s.","index":43,"end_time":117.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I noticed that the features were kind of like limited.","index":44,"end_time":122.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It has like basic search and things.","index":45,"end_time":124.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I wondered if you should do promoted as a freemium limited, which we do on the website.","index":46,"end_time":134.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":124.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We say it''s freemium for up to 20 people, but it''s really not.","index":47,"end_time":138.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Technically it''s.","index":48,"end_time":141.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":140.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s no, no real difference.","index":49,"end_time":142.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":141.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There is.","index":50,"end_time":143.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":142.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, there''s.","index":51,"end_time":143.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s actually limited, but that''s not so much because it''s a freemium.","index":52,"end_time":147.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s more like that some beta features.","index":53,"end_time":149.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Are hidden, so we could basically enable everything.","index":54,"end_time":152.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":149.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we also don''t have anything like.","index":55,"end_time":158.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, upgrade now, or this is a.","index":56,"end_time":160.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":158.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Premium feature, you don''t have access or something like that.","index":57,"end_time":163.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":160.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So for the user, it''s not really.","index":58,"end_time":165.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":163.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Product led, premium type of.","index":59,"end_time":168.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":165.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":60,"end_time":169.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":168.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s not like tiers involved.","index":61,"end_time":170.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":169.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Essentially.","index":62,"end_time":171.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":170.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s like we''re going to give you.","index":63,"end_time":172.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":171.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Access to the, to the full boat.","index":64,"end_time":174.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then is there a.","index":65,"end_time":176.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":175.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is there a time period?","index":66,"end_time":177.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":176.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Maybe.","index":67,"end_time":178.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Talk to me about.","index":68,"end_time":179.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We just reach out to them and ask them and, and check and there''s not a.","index":69,"end_time":183.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s not like a ton of people signing up every day.","index":70,"end_time":186.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":183.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s.","index":71,"end_time":187.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":186.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We control it all manually at, at the moment.","index":72,"end_time":190.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":187.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":73,"end_time":191.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It is still somewhat limited, so you don''t have to for resource management.","index":74,"end_time":196.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But more since that is not.","index":75,"end_time":201.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not completely out of beta, that whole feature.","index":76,"end_time":203.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s actually even limited for most of our customers.","index":77,"end_time":208.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How do you feel?","index":78,"end_time":212.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":211.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I dropped a note in teams.","index":79,"end_time":214.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":212.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you saw that.","index":80,"end_time":215.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yet, but how do you feel about leaning into that fact that.","index":81,"end_time":219.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":215.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we''ve done that in the past, if you''re not limiting functionality or users.","index":82,"end_time":226.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":220.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or if there aren''t multiple workspaces, that you''re perhaps only giving a workspace, not multiple.","index":83,"end_time":233.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you do essentially unlock all features, is that something you would be willing to lean into and almost be bold about it?","index":84,"end_time":245.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":234.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What are your thoughts there?","index":85,"end_time":247.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":246.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, I think the.","index":86,"end_time":248.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":247.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think for enterprise sales, they.","index":87,"end_time":251.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They don''t really sign up at the.","index":88,"end_time":255.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s.","index":89,"end_time":256.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":255.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the people that sign up are more.","index":90,"end_time":258.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":256.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Mostly smaller companies, sometimes individuals.","index":91,"end_time":262.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":258.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And when.","index":92,"end_time":262.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":262.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if that helps.","index":93,"end_time":266.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"With.","index":94,"end_time":269.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":269.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":95,"end_time":270.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, if we say it''s a freemium, we can always say, you can always contact them and say, hey, you want to see the full product?","index":96,"end_time":277.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":270.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or something like that.","index