at we''re currently not.","index":564,"end_time":1555.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1551.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Doing with the board, but we''re doing some other stuff.","index":565,"end_time":1556.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1555.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we can.","index":566,"end_time":1557.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1556.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, adjust that.","index":567,"end_time":1559.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1557.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so that''ll be the key thing.","index":568,"end_time":1561.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1559.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To think about is, you know, whatever slices of, you know, functionality we show just lined up so that it sounds like this is probably the, the piece.","index":569,"end_time":1573.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Here, which is literally.","index":570,"end_time":1574.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1573.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This will probably be like six to eight seconds.","index":571,"end_time":1577.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1575,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I say.","index":572,"end_time":1578,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1577.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s not.","index":573,"end_time":1578.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1578,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This is the only box.","index":574,"end_time":1579.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1578.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think we want to adjust it a bit.","index":575,"end_time":1581.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1579.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The rest should be.","index":576,"end_time":1582.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1581.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":577,"end_time":1583.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1582.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":578,"end_time":1585.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1584.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":579,"end_time":1585.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the one new thing that I want to fold in is that like.","index":580,"end_time":1588.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1585.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"A post registration flow that we can work on and get some ideas there.","index":581,"end_time":1595.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1588.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How do you all want to like carve out the four to five things.","index":582,"end_time":1599.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1595.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That we would highlight?","index":583,"end_time":1600.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like if we, if we have a, if we think about this, how to.","index":584,"end_time":1608.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1602.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Get the most out of decidalo.","index":585,"end_time":1609.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1608.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":586,"end_time":1615.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1614.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So there''s, there''s essentially like two modules.","index":587,"end_time":1621.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1618.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"One is the skill and CV management.","index":588,"end_time":1623.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1621.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And one is the resource management.","index":589,"end_time":1626.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1624.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And really.","index":590,"end_time":1627.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1626.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And most people start or sign up.","index":591,"end_time":1630.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1628.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"With the skill and CV management part, but that''s much more niche product than resource management, which is much broader.","index":592,"end_time":1637.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1630.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":593,"end_time":1638.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1637.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can maybe have, we can maybe separate that and have something like.","index":594,"end_time":1643.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1640.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, have you, I don''t know, have you tried uploading CVS or have you tried designing your template?","index":595,"end_time":1650.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1643.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then we could have one about resource management, how to update, how to keep track of your employee schedule, Something like that.","index":596,"end_time":1658.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1650.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":597,"end_time":1659.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1658.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s a good way to think about is like how to.","index":598,"end_time":1662.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1660.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How to do your first task, like where to jump in head first essentially with desi$.","index":599,"end_time":1668.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1662.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like here, here''s how you can, you know, upload a CV and get this.","index":600,"end_time":1675.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":601,"end_time":1675.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1675.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The tricky part is that for some of the use cases, you actually need a lot of data in the tool.","index":602,"end_time":1681.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1675.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s why we have the demo data in there.","index":603,"end_time":1684.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1681.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But that''s just dummy data so that they can test it.","index":604,"end_time":1687.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1684.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But for example, we have a very like powerful search, complex search functionality where you can really paste in half page of requirements and it will find people for that requirements.","index":605,"end_time":1701.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1689.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But that is more.","index":606,"end_time":1702.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s really an enterprise feature for large companies that need to identify people across the globe for very specific requirements.","index":607,"end_time":1711.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1702.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that is not something that you could easily try out with your own.","index":608,"end_time":1716.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1712.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Data because you have to first feed in a lot of data.","index":609,"end_time":1720.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1716.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we have to really see not only like what''s nice use case, but also what realistically works for someone who signed up.","index":610,"end_time":1729.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1721.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What can he do?","index":611,"end_time":1730.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1730.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is he willing to do?","index":612,"end_time":1731.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1730.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He could probably upload a few CVS.","index":613,"end_time":1734.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1731.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And try it out with like a few people.","index":614,"end_time":1737.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1734.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":615,"end_time":1738.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But he cannot do a full enterprise.","index":616,"end_time":1740.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1738.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, no thing like data set.","index":617,"end_time":1744.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1741.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Full enterprise data set with their data.","index":618,"end_time":1745.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1744.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, do you want, you want to think through that a little bit?","index":619,"end_time":1748.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1746.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There are a couple ways we could do it.","index":620,"end_time":1749.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1748.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If, if we want to show, you know, show features.","index":621,"end_time":1753.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1749.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could use like a short walkthrough video that perhaps you all do with test data and show them how it works.","index":622,"end_time":1759.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1753.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, something like that work as well.","index":623,"end_time":1762.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1760.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":624,"end_time":1763.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1762.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":625,"end_time":1764.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1763.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s true.","index":626,"end_time":1764.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1764.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you send a video, we.","index":627,"end_time":1766.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1764.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It doesn''t matter what data they have in.","index":628,"end_time":1767.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1766.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can just show them a video and say here''s how it could look.","index":629,"end_time":1771.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you upload all your 5,000 people.","index":630,"end_time":1773.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1771.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or something like that.","index":631,"end_time":1774.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1773.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":632,"end_time":1775.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1774.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And if we do that, Axel, these are also assets that we could use elsewhere.","index":633,"end_time":1779.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1775.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean it''s just.","index":634,"end_time":1780.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1779.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could even slice these up for.","index":635,"end_time":1783.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Short ad pieces and things like that.","index":636,"end_time":1785.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1783.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I use them in different ways.","index":637,"end_time":1787.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I kind of like, like short videos that like a product tours where you have a very one use case, two minutes or so and you show it in the tool that I think is.","index":638,"end_time":1799.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1787.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like the, the most creditable where you really see it''s working in the tour.","index":639,"end_time":1805.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1799.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s not, it''s not smoke and mirrors that like exist.","index":640,"end_time":1810.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1805.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it is.","index":641,"end_time":1811.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1810.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, well we can start to even build out that library.","index":642,"end_time":1816.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1813.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, if we even want to think through the first four or five to do that, it might be the approach.","index":643,"end_time":1821.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1816.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s use data that we have and.","index":644,"end_time":1824.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1821.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"One of you walk through the tool.","index":645,"end_time":1826.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1824.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":646,"end_time":1827.699,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1827.379,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have this one video that Eli shared about the resource request and we could do similar Things with different.","index":647,"end_time":1833.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1827.699,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you''ve seen that, but Eli, maybe you can share that.","index":648,"end_time":1838.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1835.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think we shared it with and.","index":649,"end_time":1840.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1838.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''S actually.","index":650,"end_time":1844.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1843.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''ve actually done it for.","index":651,"end_time":1845.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1844.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"As part of our documentation.","index":652,"end_time":1846.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1845.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But this one is a pretty high.","index":653,"end_time":1847.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1846.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Level one so that it also works.","index":654,"end_time":1849.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1847.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For this more marketing purpose.","index":655,"end_time":1852.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1850.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":656,"end_time":1853.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1852.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, share that one with us.","index":657,"end_time":1856.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1855.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Eli, you put that in teams for.","index":658,"end_time":1858.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1856.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For me.","index":659,"end_time":1858.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1858.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":660,"end_time":1860.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1859.63,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right now.","index":661,"end_time":1860.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1860.11,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Have you shared that before?","index":662,"end_time":1862.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1860.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ve.","index":663,"end_time":1862.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1862.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We probably put it in the.","index":664,"end_time":1863.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1862.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":665,"end_time":1864.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1863.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We put it probably somewhere in the channel, I think.","index":666,"end_time":1866.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1864.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":667,"end_time":1867.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1866.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If it''s.","index":668,"end_time":1867.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1867.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If I recall.","index":669,"end_time":1868.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1867.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think you did.","index":670,"end_time":1869.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1868.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, we have it on YouTube now also.","index":671,"end_time":1870.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1869.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":672,"end_time":1871.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1870.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Didn''t even know that that''s what I was.","index":673,"end_time":1873.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1871.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The generating CVs for resource requests.","index":674,"end_time":1877.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1875.07,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That video.","index":675,"end_time":1877.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1877.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that one.","index":676,"end_time":1878.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1877.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, Bettina uploaded it to YouTube.","index":677,"end_time":1880.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1878.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":678,"end_time":1880.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1880.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":679,"end_time":1881.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1880.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, well, yeah, we can build.","index":680,"end_time":1884.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1882.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean just start to work through those as well is a good idea because.","index":681,"end_time":1889.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1884.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I like.","index":682,"end_time":1890.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1889.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like you said, Axel, I like those.","index":683,"end_time":1891.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1890.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Short pieces where they''re walking through their personal specific and you know, actually showing the product which is also just good to reinforce and that can also be even retargeting ads as well that we put in if we even cut those down a little bit.","index":684,"end_time":1908.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So a lot of flexibility there.","index":685,"end_time":1910.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1908.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":686,"end_time":1912.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1911.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, well, I know we''re over a few minutes.","index":687,"end_time":1915.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1913,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are you good to provide feedback on that stuff?","index":688,"end_time":1918.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1916.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll still move ahead with Dev on Monday.","index":689,"end_time":1921.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1918.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I go through the landing page and the ads and stuff.","index":690,"end_time":1927.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1922.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":691,"end_time":1928.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1927.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then we''ll be ready.","index":692,"end_time":1929.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1928.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll keep.","index":693,"end_time":1930.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1929.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll keep moving and get this stuff rolling.","index":694,"end_time":1932.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1930.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So catch some people on Turkey day.","index":695,"end_time":1935.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1933.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, should be.","index":696,"end_time":1936.999,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1936.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So you''re not working on Friday, I guess.","index":697,"end_time":1938.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1936.999,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":698,"end_time":1939.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1938.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Should we have a meeting then next?","index":699,"end_time":1940.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1939.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know, Tuesday or so.","index":700,"end_time":1942.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1940.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":701,"end_time":1943.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1942.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We had.","index":702,"end_time":1944.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1943.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Actually Tuesday would be good.","index":703,"end_time":1948.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1946.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That way we get everything in place.","index":704,"end_time":1950.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1948.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You want to reschedule our Friday meeting or are you working Friday?","index":705,"end_time":1954.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1950.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I am not.","index":706,"end_time":1956.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1954.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I don''t think anyone.","index":707,"end_time":1957.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1956.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So maybe you want to just reschedule the one from Friday to Tuesday.","index":708,"end_time":1960.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1958.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, do that right now, the 28th one.","index":709,"end_time":1969.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1961.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s all right.","index":710,"end_time":1972.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1970.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Colin.","index":711,"end_time":1973.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1973.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Let me send.","index":712,"end_time":1977.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1976.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are we okay to do that at 9?","index":713,"end_time":1979.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1977.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"9Am that is.","index":714,"end_time":1982.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1979.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Where is that plus 6?","index":715,"end_time":1983.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1982.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Same time we had here today.","index":716,"end_time":1984.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1983.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":717,"end_time":1986.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1985.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":718,"end_time":1987.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1986.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, let me do that.","index":719,"end_time":1989.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1987.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m gonna.","index":720,"end_time":1990.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1989.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Would you mind if I kept the fresh invite?","index":721,"end_time":1992.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1990.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because that other invite is owned by Colin.","index":722,"end_time":1994.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1992.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I don''t.","index":723,"end_time":1994.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can we do it an hour later.","index":724,"end_time":1996.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1994.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because the have actually jumping at 9:10am yeah.","index":725,"end_time":1999.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1996.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s better.","index":726,"end_time":2000.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1999.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":727,"end_time":2001.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2001.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, just send a new one.","index":728,"end_time":2003.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2002.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":729,"end_time":2004.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2003.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll send a new sync up as soon as we.","index":730,"end_time":2007.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2004.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We jump off here, so we''ll have that, and then we''ll cross through.","index":731,"end_time":2011.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2007.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Anything that you found or, you know, we need to adjust before we.","index":732,"end_time":2016.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2011.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We roll out everything towards the end of the week there.","index":733,"end_time":2019.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2016.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":734,"end_time":2020.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2019.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, thank you, everyone.","index":735,"end_time":2022.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2020.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Chat soon.","index":736,"end_time":2023.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2023,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Bye.","index":737,"end_time":2025.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2025.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Appreciate.","index":738,"end_time":2025.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2025.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"}],"dateString":"2025-11-21T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/8971821371","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com,osbaldeston@data-assessment.com,pollex@data-assessment.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com","osbaldeston@data-assessment.com","pollex@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KA1DF2XRHP5TB3ZDX8CZT5YR","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Finalized messaging shift to emphasize full product access over ambiguous ''free'' language on site.","Agreed to launch full campaign post-Thanksgiving with ads, landing page, and email refreshed.","Axel to provide final landing page feedback before Monday development handoff proceeds as scheduled.","Team identified onboarding gaps and will design a post-registration flow using demo videos and email.","Confirmed short walkthrough videos as key assets for showing real product functionality at scale."],"highlights":[{"quote":"You can try it right now... it''s the full product.","speaker":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"quote":"We want to at least be demonstrating the full capability.","speaker":"Eli Bebinger"},{"quote":"We can just show them a video and say here''s how it could look.","speaker":"Axel Völker"}],"topics":["launch","onboarding","messaging","video","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T22:49:11Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Freemium Product Positioning and User Access**\n\nThe team decided to emphasize providing users with access to the **full product features** rather than limiting functionality in the freemium offering, aiming to improve user engagement and enterprise interest (03:11).\n\n- **Axel Völker** clarified that current freemium access is manually controlled and limited due to beta-stage features, mostly targeting smaller companies and individuals rather than enterprise users.\n- The strategy will highlight that users get to **try the full version** without overwhelming them with organization-wide access, creating a “Trojan horse” effect for sales to initiate deeper conversations, as explained by **Tristan Pelligrino** (04:48).\n- Language changes will shift from “free” to more inviting phrases like “get started now” or “try now” to better reflect the trial nature without implying full free use or premium tiers (06:29).\n- The decision was influenced by market feedback indicating enterprise customers often face frustration when they cannot see the product, so unlocking features upfront is expected to reduce friction and improve conversion (07:12).\n\n## **Post-Registration Engagement and Outreach Workflow**\n\nThe group agreed to design a **structured post-registration email drip campaign** complemented by manual sales outreach to help users adopt the product more effectively (10:13).\n\n- **Eli Bebinger** emphasized the need for clear objectives and resources guiding new users since many cannot navigate the product independently after sign-up.\n- The proposed sequence would deliver **4–5 key onboarding emails** over several days, featuring best practices and short demo videos to highlight essential features and build user momentum (11:03).\n- Due to lack of automation in HubSpot, the team plans to use **N8N workflows** to enroll registrants and send these emails automatically, ensuring consistent follow-up (12:30).\n- **Axel Völker** will refine feature positioning in the emails and landing page to align messaging with freemium capabilities and user expectations (13:15).\n\n## **Landing Page and Advertising Refresh**\n\nThe landing page and ads are set for a **development rollout on Monday**, with final content tweaks and feedback integration planned to ensure alignment with product features and messaging (13:37).\n\n- **Axel Völker** is reviewing the landing page text to add missing features like resource management and adjust iconography to better represent the full product offering (14:06).\n- Visual elements including images perceived as AI-generated will be adjusted post-deployment, as these are not development blockers (14:56).\n- The geographic messaging will be revised from “distributed by IT companies across Germany, UK and US” to a more inclusive phrase like “global teams,” reflecting market relevance and avoiding confusion (15:38).\n- The email copy for the campaign has been shared in Google Drive and PDF formats, with the team consolidating feedback ahead of launch (18:44).\n- The campaign launch timing was discussed, and the team agreed to **launch midweek after the US Thanksgiving holiday**, balancing audience availability and campaign momentum (22:33).\n\n## **Explainer Video and AI Feature Messaging**\n\nThe explainer video script will be adjusted to **moderate claims around AI bot functionality**, ensuring messaging does not overpromise features still in early beta (23:56).\n\n- **Axel Völker** highlighted the need to identify specific AI use cases that can be confidently promoted without misleading users.\n- The AI bot section will remain brief (around six to eight seconds) and focused on currently available capabilities, with non-implemented features like RFP parsing removed from the script (25:29).\n- The video production will include side-by-side workflows for visual and voiceover elements, as explained by **Tristan Pelligrino** (24:58).\n\n## **Product Onboarding Content Strategy**\n\nThe team plans to create a **library of short, focused product walkthrough videos** showcasing key use cases for different user segments to improve product understanding and marketing reach (26:54).\n\n- **Axel Völker** outlined two main product modules: **skill and CV management**, which is niche, and **resource management**, which is broader and more widely used.\n- Walkthroughs will emphasize realistic onboarding steps users can take, such as uploading CVs or managing employee schedules, using demo data to illustrate enterprise features that require large datasets (27:38).\n- Existing videos, like the resource request demo shared by **Eli Bebinger**, will be repurposed and supplemented with new ones tailored for marketing and onboarding use (30:27).\n- These videos can also be sliced into shorter clips for retargeting ads, increasing the flexibility and impact of marketing assets (29:34).\n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed to **reschedule the next sync meeting to Tuesday, November 28th at 10:00 AM CET**, accommodating participant availability and preparing for the campaign launch (32:16).\n\n- **Tristan Pelligrino** will send a fresh calendar invite owned by him to avoid conflicts with Colin’s invites.\n- Feedback on the landing page, ads, and email content will be incorporated promptly to maintain the planned Monday development start and midweek campaign launch (32:53).\n- The team will continue iterative improvements on live assets post-deployment to stay ahead of schedule and ensure a smooth rollout (15:32).","outline":null,"keywords":["freemium model","landing page","post-registration outreach","drip email campaign","explainer video","resource management"],"overview":"- **Freemium Product Strategy:** Users will access full features in freemium, enhancing engagement without overwhelming enterprise clients.  \n- **Post-Registration Campaign:** A structured email drip campaign will aid user onboarding, featuring 4-5 key emails with demos.  \n- **Landing Page Update:** Updates to the landing page and ads are scheduled for Monday, with launches planned for after Thanksgiving.  \n- **Explainer Video Adjustments:** The video script will moderate AI claims, focusing on currently available features to avoid misleading users.  \n- **Onboarding Video Library:** Short product walkthroughs will be created to showcase key use cases, enhancing marketing and user understanding.  \n- **Next Meeting:** Rescheduled for November 28th at 10:00 AM CET; focus on feedback integration for campaign launch preparations.","action_items":"\n**Axel Völker**\nProvide detailed feedback and adjustments on freemium features and landing page content (13:15)\nReview and give final input on ads and email sequences by Monday development start (18:43)\nUpdate AI agent use cases in explainer video script to reflect current beta functionality and avoid overpromising (23:56)\nSubmit suggestions for adjustments in icons and layout on landing page as features expand (14:06)\nShare existing resource request video with the team for marketing use (30:27)\n\n**Eli Bebinger**\nFacilitate sharing of resource request video in Teams and support creation of post-registration drip email campaign content (30:59)\nCoordinate structure and objectives for post-registration outreach; propose sequence of onboarding emails introducing core features and best practices (10:00)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nCoordinate landing page iteration and ensure development schedule stays on track starting Monday (13:37)\nShare email sequence document and ad materials with team for review and consolidate feedback (18:46)\nSchedule follow-up meeting for Tuesday, Nov 28, at 10 AM and send updated meeting invite (32:41)\nManage creation of demo videos for feature walkthroughs and support building post-registration drip email campaign via N8N (29:22)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"12291b66-e1e7-41be-8b87-417a58e1a051","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
