INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Freemium Product Positioning and User Access**

The team decided to emphasize providing users with access to the **full product features** rather than limiting functionality in the freemium offering, aiming to improve user engagement and enterprise interest (03:11).

- **Axel Völker** clarified that current freemium access is manually controlled and limited due to beta-stage features, mostly targeting smaller companies and individuals rather than enterprise users.
- The strategy will highlight that users get to **try the full version** without overwhelming them with organization-wide access, creating a “Trojan horse” effect for sales to initiate deeper conversations, as explained by **Tristan Pelligrino** (04:48).
- Language changes will shift from “free” to more inviting phrases like “get started now” or “try now” to better reflect the trial nature without implying full free use or premium tiers (06:29).
- The decision was influenced by market feedback indicating enterprise customers often face frustration when they cannot see the product, so unlocking features upfront is expected to reduce friction and improve conversion (07:12).

## **Post-Registration Engagement and Outreach Workflow**

The group agreed to design a **structured post-registration email drip campaign** complemented by manual sales outreach to help users adopt the product more effectively (10:13).

- **Eli Bebinger** emphasized the need for clear objectives and resources guiding new users since many cannot navigate the product independently after sign-up.
- The proposed sequence would deliver **4–5 key onboarding emails** over several days, featuring best practices and short demo videos to highlight essential features and build user momentum (11:03).
- Due to lack of automation in HubSpot, the team plans to use **N8N workflows** to enroll registrants and send these emails automatically, ensuring consistent follow-up (12:30).
- **Axel Völker** will refine feature positioning in the emails and landing page to align messaging with freemium capabilities and user expectations (13:15).

## **Landing Page and Advertising Refresh**

The landing page and ads are set for a **development rollout on Monday**, with final content tweaks and feedback integration planned to ensure alignment with product features and messaging (13:37).

- **Axel Völker** is reviewing the landing page text to add missing features like resource management and adjust iconography to better represent the full product offering (14:06).
- Visual elements including images perceived as AI-generated will be adjusted post-deployment, as these are not development blockers (14:56).
- The geographic messaging will be revised from “distributed by IT companies across Germany, UK and US” to a more inclusive phrase like “global teams,” reflecting market relevance and avoiding confusion (15:38).
- The email copy for the campaign has been shared in Google Drive and PDF formats, with the team consolidating feedback ahead of launch (18:44).
- The campaign launch timing was discussed, and the team agreed to **launch midweek after the US Thanksgiving holiday**, balancing audience availability and campaign momentum (22:33).

## **Explainer Video and AI Feature Messaging**

The explainer video script will be adjusted to **moderate claims around AI bot functionality**, ensuring messaging does not overpromise features still in early beta (23:56).

- **Axel Völker** highlighted the need to identify specific AI use cases that can be confidently promoted without misleading users.
- The AI bot section will remain brief (around six to eight seconds) and focused on currently available capabilities, with non-implemented features like RFP parsing removed from the script (25:29).
- The video production will include side-by-side workflows for visual and voiceover elements, as explained by **Tristan Pelligrino** (24:58).

## **Product Onboarding Content Strategy**

The team plans to create a **library of short, focused product walkthrough videos** showcasing key use cases for different user segments to improve product understanding and marketing reach (26:54).

- **Axel Völker** outlined two main product modules: **skill and CV management**, which is niche, and **resource management**, which is broader and more widely used.
- Walkthroughs will emphasize realistic onboarding steps users can take, such as uploading CVs or managing employee schedules, using demo data to illustrate enterprise features that require large datasets (27:38).
- Existing videos, like the resource request demo shared by **Eli Bebinger**, will be repurposed and supplemented with new ones tailored for marketing and onboarding use (30:27).
- These videos can also be sliced into shorter clips for retargeting ads, increasing the flexibility and impact of marketing assets (29:34).

## **Meeting Scheduling and Next Steps**

The team agreed to **reschedule the next sync meeting to Tuesday, November 28th at 10:00 AM CET**, accommodating participant availability and preparing for the campaign launch (32:16).

- **Tristan Pelligrino** will send a fresh calendar invite owned by him to avoid conflicts with Colin’s invites.
- Feedback on the landing page, ads, and email content will be incorporated promptly to maintain the planned Monday development start and midweek campaign launch (32:53).
- The team will continue iterative improvements on live assets post-deployment to stay ahead of schedule and ensure a smooth rollout (15:32).',
  '2025-11-21 14:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide detailed feedback and adjustments on freemium features and landing page content (13:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and give final input on ads and email sequences by Monday development start (18:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Update AI agent use cases in explainer video script to reflect current beta functionality and avoid overpromising (23:56)","completed":false},{"text":"Submit suggestions for adjustments in icons and layout on landing page as features expand (14:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Share existing resource request video with the team for marketing use (30:27)","completed":false},{"text":"Facilitate sharing of resource request video in Teams and support creation of post-registration drip email campaign content (30:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate structure and objectives for post-registration outreach; propose sequence of onboarding emails introducing core features and best practices (10:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate landing page iteration and ensure development schedule stays on track starting Monday (13:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Share email sequence document and ad materials with team for review and consolidate feedback (18:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Schedule follow-up meeting for Tuesday, Nov 28, at 10 AM and send updated meeting invite (32:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage creation of demo videos for feature walkthroughs and support building post-registration drip email campaign via N8N (29:22)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
