-- Meeting: MiD // Kersten Talent Capital: Marketing Kickoff (2025-11-18 18:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '72cdc11e-fd4f-4d90-8688-1fc1484de2b0',
    '2025-11-18 18:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KA703CWQKPQX9NY6F9ZHCNZA',
    'MiD // Kersten Talent Capital: Marketing Kickoff',
    '{"Michael Kersten","Tristan Pelligrino","Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    3164,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81227121766?pwd=PAE6vnCK0QmrtUG7Z8MawrUMKoDZxP.1',
    '{"id":"01KA703CWQKPQX9NY6F9ZHCNZA","title":"MiD // Kersten Talent Capital: Marketing Kickoff","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Migration and HubSpot Integration**\n\nThe team agreed to prioritize migrating the website into **HubSpot** to consolidate tools, improve integration with the CRM, and reduce costs by potentially moving from **Enterprise to Professional tier** (01:04).\n\n- **Michael Kersten** emphasized moving the website into HubSpot since he is already paying for that tool, enabling tighter integration with campaigns and dashboards (02:14).  \n- The current website and marketing cloud setup by the Colombian team is functional but siloed; consolidation aims to reduce tool bloat and overspending, as noted by **Colin Costigan** (05:06).  \n- HubSpot’s lead object functionality, recently introduced, will be leveraged for campaigns, but the team is open to adjusting the CRM structure based on best practices for campaign flow and data tracking (07:55).  \n- **Tristan Pelligrino** clarified that HubSpot’s Sales module is essential for workflows on the sales side, and Michael has Enterprise licenses covering this, allowing complex deal tracking and revenue management (09:07).  \n- Michael’s role primarily focuses on deal management and revenue tracking within HubSpot Sales, while marketing-driven campaigns and lead generation will be handled by the agency team (09:57).  \n- The team will evaluate if all current HubSpot modules are necessary to optimize costs and functionality, with transparency on any recommendations (13:19).  \n- The migration will include a website plan document outlining architecture, URL strategy, messaging, and scalable landing page templates for rapid future content deployment (31:07).  \n- Colin and Tristan will coordinate with Michael to prepare for the migration, ensuring Ryan and the Colombian team are informed and that transitions happen smoothly (52:15).  \n\n## **Branding, Messaging, and Website Content Strategy**\n\nThe group identified the need to elevate the website’s messaging and branding to better reflect Michael’s firm as a specialized boutique enterprise operating nationally and in global markets, not a one-person shop (14:19).\n\n- Michael wants to highlight recent wins in the **utility and PE sectors**, showcasing success stories to raise awareness beyond word-of-mouth referrals (14:33).  \n- The homepage should communicate the firm’s enterprise-level capabilities and broad industry reach, balancing specific industry focus with general appeal to capture diverse market opportunities like AI, renewable energy, and data centers over the next three years (19:03).  \n- Michael expressed concern that using his full name in branding might create a perception of a small, solo operation; he prefers shifting to the **KTC Search** brand to project a larger firm image and leverage the keyword “search” for SEO benefits (23:07).  \n- The team will research competitive domain usage and brand recognition to recommend whether to fully rebrand to KTC Search or maintain the current name with adjusted messaging (28:26).  \n- Michael is open to changing the website’s color scheme and design to align with industry standards seen in top retained search firms, favoring lighter colors and dynamic visuals like videos and rotating images to increase engagement (29:41).  \n- The team will produce a website plan document detailing messaging, design, and architecture to support ongoing content development and rapid response to market changes or new industry focuses (31:07).  \n- Weekly meetings will start the first week of December to maintain alignment on branding, website development, and campaign progress (51:07).  \n\n## **Content Engine and Thought Leadership Series**\n\nA content series will be developed to build brand recognition and position Michael’s firm as an industry thought leader through interviews, market insights, and topical discussions (34:12).\n\n- Michael prefers the agency team to host interviews with prospects, clients, or industry experts to reduce his time commitment and avoid sales perceptions during content delivery (34:59).  \n- To protect sensitive information related to Michael’s ID.me involvement and pre-IPO interests, content with his direct name will be limited until **end of Q1 2026**, after which more public branding can occur (36:25).  \n- Michael identified potential mouthpieces within his network, including a polished protege and a marketing writer, to serve as proxies in content delivery, maintaining his low profile while sharing expertise (40:35).  \n- The content plan will include show themes, target audiences, publishing cadence, and design elements to ensure consistent, market-relevant messaging (40:35).  \n- Michael can engage industry experts and board members from his network to provide qualitative insights for content, leveraging their knowledge to build credible trends reports and thought leadership (43:54).  \n- The team will run workshops to refine content strategy and identify key themes such as leadership velocity, infrastructure growth, and industry shifts relevant to PE-backed companies (46:22).  \n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Campaign Strategy**\n\nThe ABM campaign will focus on targeted outreach using data-driven insights and customized content to attract retained and contingent clients, particularly in the PE and utility sectors (42:26).\n\n- The campaign will leverage a **Portfolio Talent Trends Report** built from qualitative feedback gathered during content conversations and expert interviews, serving as a key asset to engage prospects (43:02).  \n- Michael will provide access to his network of seasoned executives in utilities and professional services to contribute insights, enriching the report’s credibility and relevance (44:54).  \n- The ABM approach will include clear identification of companies and contacts to target, as well as those to exclude, ensuring efficient use of resources and avoiding conflicts with existing client relationships (48:32).  \n- The campaign’s success will be tracked and iterated rapidly, with the team ready to pivot based on market response and performance metrics (32:45).  \n- The team emphasized transparency and cost-effectiveness by evaluating necessary HubSpot modules and tech stack components to avoid overspending (13:19).  \n\n## **Operational Coordination and Process Improvements**\n\nClear communication and defined roles between Michael, the agency team, and the Colombian team will support a smooth technology transition and campaign execution (02:14).\n\n- Michael will notify Ryan and others when the migration to HubSpot begins to ensure proper handoff and avoid duplicated efforts (52:30).  \n- The agency team will provide documented recommendations on HubSpot usage, including lead object structure and workflows, with Michael’s approval before implementing changes (51:55).  \n- The team will set up a shared portal for full transparency on goals, deliverables, and feedback, improving collaboration and tracking progress in 15-minute increments (49:41).  \n- A weekly meeting cadence starting early December will ensure ongoing alignment, quick issue resolution, and accountability (51:07).  \n- The agency manages vendor relationships and subscriptions like Clay on Michael’s behalf, optimizing tech stack usage without requiring Michael to negotiate separately (33:40).  \n- Michael has roughly **50,000 to 60,000 contacts** in Zoom that can be integrated into campaigns, maximizing existing assets and reducing incremental data costs (33:55).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Website Migration","ABM Campaign","Content Engine","Branding Strategy","Private Equity"],"overview":"- **Website Migration to HubSpot:** Focus on moving website to HubSpot to streamline tools and reduce costs from Enterprise to Professional tier.  \n- **Branding and Messaging Revamp:** Shift branding to KTC Search to reflect enterprise-level capabilities and leverage SEO; explore updated design aesthetics.  \n- **Content Engine Development:** Create content series featuring interviews and insights to establish thought leadership while maintaining a low profile.  \n- **ABM Campaign Strategy:** Implement targeted outreach using data-driven insights, focusing on the PE and utility sectors with a Portfolio Talent Trends Report.  \n- **Operational Coordination:** Establish clear roles and communication to ensure smooth migration and campaign execution, with scheduled weekly updates starting December.  \n- **Integration of Contacts:** Utilize Michael''s 50,000-60,000 Zoom contacts to enhance campaigns, maximizing current resources while minimizing additional costs.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare HubSpot object and workflow change recommendations with Michael and team (52:14)\nDevelop and deliver website plan document including architecture, messaging, URL strategy, and page templates (31:07)\nSet up weekly recurring meeting with Michael starting first week of December on Tuesdays at 10 AM, send calendar invites (51:32)\nProvide brand/website rebranding research and recommendations regarding KTC Search versus existing branding (23:59)\nInitiate content plan development detailing show names, themes, target audience, and publishing cadence (40:35)\nFacilitate setup of portfolio total platform access for Michael with single sign-on and goal loading (50:30)\nCoordinate with Michael and internal teams on notification and logistics for migrating website to HubSpot (52:14)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nCollaborate on HubSpot features and workflow structure aligning marketing and sales objectives (09:05)\nAssist in defining sales vs marketing roles for communications and sequencing within HubSpot (10:00)\nAssist in content engine creation and management focusing on guest interviews, market topics, and stealth content scheduling (34:12)\nSupport in packaging portfolio talent trends report and leadership gap assessment for ABM campaigns (43:00)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nProvide disallowed target companies and contacts list to avoid marketing overlaps (48:32)\nFacilitate access and share contacts from Zoom database for use in campaigns (33:55)\nIdentify internal point(s) of contact or authorize communication with Ryan regarding website migration preparations (52:14)\nEngage with selected industry experts and board members to support industry insights and content development (45:17)\n"},"duration":52.7400016784668,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Michael Kersten"},{"id":1,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Just got somebody across the board and he wants to push out his billing.","index":0,"end_time":4.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I had a horse trade a little bit with him.","index":1,"end_time":5.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I apologize.","index":2,"end_time":6.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s.","index":3,"end_time":7.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":4,"end_time":8.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We understand how that stuff goes.","index":5,"end_time":10.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":6,"end_time":10.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":11.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Appreciate the email though.","index":8,"end_time":12.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I just saw that come in.","index":9,"end_time":12.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I told Colin and G what was up.","index":10,"end_time":15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we were just hanging out here.","index":11,"end_time":16.079,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, no worries.","index":12,"end_time":16.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.079,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Colin''s going to run this for the most part.","index":13,"end_time":19.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But Colin''s our.","index":14,"end_time":20.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Our head of accounts and he''s got.","index":15,"end_time":23.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We worked internally on our agenda and, and the nice thing, Michael, we''ll be able to jump in on these projects because we''ve already kind of set the stage as to what our priorities are.","index":16,"end_time":32.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we have Guillay as well, one of our strategists and we''re.","index":17,"end_time":37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll go through our agenda here and get things rolling before the Thanksgiving week.","index":18,"end_time":42.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you jumping on.","index":19,"end_time":44.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So Colin, you should have ability to share and then we can get rolling.","index":20,"end_time":51.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":21,"end_time":51.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":22,"end_time":51.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":52.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And first thing, Michael, great to meet you.","index":24,"end_time":54.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":52.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like I know you already because I just, I watched all these recordings and, and saw some great things, exciting projects and conversations.","index":25,"end_time":60.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":54.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So really looking forward to getting into it.","index":26,"end_time":62.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":60.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":27,"end_time":63.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, so I have our agenda here.","index":28,"end_time":66.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":64.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I probably won''t share my screen the whole time because I like to be able to look at you and, and know what''s going on and, and really just be able to read your face on these conversations and, and know what direction we want to go in.","index":29,"end_time":76.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But really the big pieces that we want to focus on to what Tristan said, projects that we can start right away and that is the website migration coming up with this content engine and thought leadership series and then also getting an ABM campaign put together.","index":30,"end_time":90.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":76.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know some other things that you''ve mentioned is you''ve got.","index":31,"end_time":94.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You feel like you''re in like 20 different tools all the time and we need to consolidate kind of across the board there.","index":32,"end_time":99.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a big push for moving the website into HubSpot.","index":33,"end_time":102.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":99.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re already paying for enterprise, probably could move to professional and still keep a lot of the same features.","index":34,"end_time":108.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But having the CRM and the website connected in one system is definitely a bonus.","index":35,"end_time":113.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know that having it connected to your ATS and everything is also a big need there.","index":36,"end_time":118.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":114.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just a few questions that I want to dive into as we get into this.","index":37,"end_time":123.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":118.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know that you have a few different teams.","index":38,"end_time":125.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You have Ryan who had built the website initially.","index":39,"end_time":128.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You have the Columbian team who has been doing a lot of work in HubSpot as Well, and so I just wanted to establish, like, we.","index":40,"end_time":134.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":128.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where''s the line drawn between what marketers in demand is doing in HubSpot and website things versus the Colombian team?","index":41,"end_time":141.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":42,"end_time":142.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Got it.","index":43,"end_time":142.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So from the.","index":44,"end_time":143.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"From the website, what Kristen, Tristan and I had talked about is, you know, we can move that to wherever you guys.","index":45,"end_time":150.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, the ideal thing is to move it into HubSpot, which I would assume you guys would do all that.","index":46,"end_time":154.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I haven''t said anything to Ryan yet.","index":47,"end_time":157.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I mean, you guys have full access.","index":48,"end_time":159.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys can move what we need.","index":49,"end_time":160.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I can let him know.","index":50,"end_time":161.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, like I said, he''s done a good job.","index":51,"end_time":162.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But like we''ve talked about is we''re trying to take it to, as I say, the next level.","index":52,"end_time":167.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I''m paying for a tool, so why not put it in the tool that I''m already paying for?","index":53,"end_time":171.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I think you guys have access to everything you need on the back end.","index":54,"end_time":174.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If not, let me know and we can kind of take it from there.","index":55,"end_time":177.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"With the folks in Columbia, they''ve been kind of setting up a lot of the stuff, you know, for, you know, the sales motion in regards to the sales hub.","index":56,"end_time":185.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They haven''t touched anything in the marketing cloud of HubSpot that''s native.","index":57,"end_time":189.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They haven''t done anything.","index":58,"end_time":190.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I purposely haven''t done them anything.","index":59,"end_time":191.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Cause I''m assuming everything that we''re doing in there in regards to that motion would kind of be driven by you guys moving the website in there, then the campaigns and all that.","index":60,"end_time":199.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then that would correlate and tie back into the dashboard.","index":61,"end_time":202.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The one thing I haven''t had a call with them yet again, it''s later in the week, was they were supposed to.","index":62,"end_time":209.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you saw my workflows, if you were in there, I have a couple different workflows in regards on the sales side.","index":63,"end_time":213.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"One is the lead workflow they were supposed to make like a duplicate, that one.","index":64,"end_time":218.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way.","index":65,"end_time":219.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, you already saw.","index":66,"end_time":220.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":67,"end_time":221.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Named Tristan.","index":68,"end_time":221.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way, anything that you guys were pushing in, it would kind of went into that.","index":69,"end_time":225.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That dashboard.","index":70,"end_time":227.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we could say, hey, anything that I''ve worked, you know, I''m currently working, you know, referrals or whatever is kind of in my lead one.","index":71,"end_time":233.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And if I''m working some other stuff and then obviously what you guys are doing kind of pushes and then both kind of collapse into the, you know, hey, you''ve raised your hand, the client''s talking now.","index":72,"end_time":243.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re going to go through the bid process.","index":73,"end_time":244.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They bid, they''ve accepted, and it Drops down into delivery workflow.","index":74,"end_time":248.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you guys see all those workflows.","index":75,"end_time":250.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was going to have them start on a project in December, kind of core taking the data out of my ATS and pumping it in, you know, through the API to dump it all into the, into, into HubSpot in the sales thing.","index":76,"end_time":267.069,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way I can track all the activity that I have going in my ATS in regards to placements and open roles and then that be bilateral.","index":77,"end_time":274.669,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":267.069,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I knew we were kicking this off, they were chopping the bits and I kind of delayed them to say, hey, we weren''t going to start until December on that and I can push that, you know, but I didn''t know when we were kicking stuff off and kind of where that line was.","index":78,"end_time":289.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.669,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, you know, I''m open to direction as to, you know, what you guys can do, what you want to do, what you don''t want them to touch.","index":79,"end_time":297.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And we can kind of take it from there because, I mean, they''re, they''re doing a halfway decent job unless you guys disagree, you know, and they''re fairly inexpensive.","index":80,"end_time":305.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":81,"end_time":305.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":82,"end_time":307.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":306.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, from what we''ve seen inside of HubSpot, I don''t think like anything is broken or messy or anything like that.","index":83,"end_time":311.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":307.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wouldn''t say they''re doing a bad job with anything.","index":84,"end_time":313.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We always, you know, with a, a scrappy approach, we always like to say, well, how can we consolidate this best from a, a tech stack so there''s no bloat, no overspending.","index":85,"end_time":323.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":314.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can see you''re using, you know, the lead functionality of HubSpot, which is a relatively new feature for them kind of thing, got introduced at the end of 2024.","index":86,"end_time":331.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":323.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I heard that you were also a Salesforce user before that, so that might be why you want to lean a little bit more into like leads and contacts and things like that.","index":87,"end_time":339.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":332.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me, let me add something to that.","index":88,"end_time":341.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is as you, as you can see and in the system, there''s not a lot of data in there.","index":89,"end_time":348.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We got a couple of accounts and we''ve been kind of playing with.","index":90,"end_time":350.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I.","index":91,"end_time":351.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Most of a lot of my stuff has been sitting in my ATS because that''s where I got, imagine my QuickBooks from when I''m invoicing.","index":92,"end_time":356.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So there''s not a whole lot of stuff in here.","index":93,"end_time":358.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we kind of went to leads route just because that''s kind of the way, you know, Salesforce was it.","index":94,"end_time":363.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But what I will say is, is I haven''t started pushing any data in here.","index":95,"end_time":368.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if there''s something that you say, hey, we don''t need leads, that''s fine.","index":96,"end_time":373.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, part of the way I got leads was Salesforce, but also Sales Loft kind of uses leads as, hey, if it''s coming in, it''s a lead.","index":97,"end_time":381.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You kind of work it, and then it turns into an opportunity when they raise their hands.","index":98,"end_time":384.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s kind of how they''ve built it.","index":99,"end_time":386.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But once again, as we''re building this for the future, if you guys have recommendations and say, hey, we don''t need leads, we''re going to call it this.","index":100,"end_time":394.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m totally fine with it, you know, so it''s one of those things where you guys can kind of tell me, hey, if.","index":101,"end_time":400.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If we''re.","index":102,"end_time":400.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If the goal is to build it a little bit differently as to how you guys would run the campaigns and flow, and we need to change terms, let me know.","index":103,"end_time":407.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I can have them change because I still have them on the, you know, on the.","index":104,"end_time":411.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"On the hook for some hours still, where if we need to change something, you guys would just have to put a document together saying, hey, we want to change this, this, this.","index":105,"end_time":419.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I give it to them, and they''ll do it on the back end because like I said, I bought hours from them, and they haven''t used all their hours.","index":106,"end_time":425.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I have some.","index":107,"end_time":425.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then if it gets to the point where we say, hey, Mike, we can take some of this over and we''ll just use some of your monthly hours, I''m fine with that, too.","index":108,"end_time":433.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":426.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, I''m not tied to them.","index":109,"end_time":435.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I was referred into them.","index":110,"end_time":438.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They were fairly inexpensive.","index":111,"end_time":439.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''ve done a fairly decent job.","index":112,"end_time":441.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I didn''t have the time to do it.","index":113,"end_time":443.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I had somebody else out of California do it, and she''s probably in there.","index":114,"end_time":446.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You can probably see her in some of this stuff.","index":115,"end_time":448.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She just.","index":116,"end_time":449.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She wasn''t.","index":117,"end_time":449.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Jackie.","index":118,"end_time":450.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She just, you know, she wasn''t listening, and she was.","index":119,"end_time":453.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She was just building it the way she would do.","index":120,"end_time":455.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And, you know, a lot of the stuff that she had in there was wrong, so they''ve had to kind of tear it apart or redo it.","index":121,"end_time":461.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So they''ve cleaned a lot of stuff up, you know, so that''s why I kind of went with a bigger outfit than trying to just get an independent because.","index":122,"end_time":468.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Nice woman, but she just wasn''t listening.","index":123,"end_time":470.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She kind of do it the way she wanted to do it, and it''s like, that''s not the way I run my business, so.","index":124,"end_time":475.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, I totally hear you.","index":125,"end_time":476.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":475.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, I mean, we can come up with a Recommendation to be completely transparent.","index":126,"end_time":481.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can work with lead objects or without lead objects.","index":127,"end_time":484.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was one of the attractive pieces of HubSpot, especially in the last few years, was you didn''t have a loss of data between like this contact and when they become a lead.","index":128,"end_time":493.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like it may happen in Salesforce unless you have like some custom buttons that you build into there because it''s all tracked through a life cycle stage.","index":129,"end_time":499.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":493.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That being said, we can still definitely utilize the leads object and that can be, you know, when we''re running these ABM campaigns and we have this set list of contacts we''re reaching out to, we can update them in their contacts and then when they reach a threshold of activity or they''ve filled out a form or something, create a lead off of that record.","index":130,"end_time":517.979,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s popped up right into your dashboard.","index":131,"end_time":520.059,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.219,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":132,"end_time":520.899,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.219,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, I kind of like that flow.","index":133,"end_time":522.179,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.899,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But once again, and you listen to the video, so you probably heard me say a thousand times, if you guys have a better way of doing it, we have, now''s the time to change it because there''s really nothing in there.","index":134,"end_time":532.059,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.179,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if you think, if you guys want to go another route, we can do that.","index":135,"end_time":535.379,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.059,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because I''m not using it right now anyhow because I''ve been having them build it out.","index":136,"end_time":539.739,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.379,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, it''s your guys''s call.","index":137,"end_time":542.019,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.739,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you guys can powwow among yourselves and let me know if we want to change direction.","index":138,"end_time":545.739,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.019,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, we will do.","index":139,"end_time":547.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":545.739,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing Colin, we do want to ask about is so with the, the lead object, the, the one thing is workflows on the sales side, I believe you still need that.","index":140,"end_time":558.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You need the sales module.","index":141,"end_time":562,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so Michael does have that with Enterprise.","index":142,"end_time":564.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s also like what drives some of this too.","index":143,"end_time":567.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Michael, a lot of our clients don''t have both sales and marketing.","index":144,"end_time":571.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":145,"end_time":571.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Pro.","index":146,"end_time":571.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":147,"end_time":572.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And so you''re kind of relegated to just the contact object.","index":148,"end_time":576.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you want to build workflows off of that one question that we didn''t get into and call, I want to ask this is on the sales side.","index":149,"end_time":586.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are you planning to do separate sequences over there or maybe where, where is that, like line going to be drawn from an activity standpoint?","index":150,"end_time":597.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So what I, what I''ve.","index":151,"end_time":599.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I''ve been in view, what I envision is, is you guys are going to be, we''re going to say, hey, here''s everything we''re building that I''m assuming in the marketing cloud and you guys are sending the campaigns out.","index":152,"end_time":609.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then back to like Colin said is, hey, if somebody fills out a web form or something like that that would drop into that lead bucket and tell me hey, this is something.","index":153,"end_time":618.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":609.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But really what I wanted to use HubSpot sales for really was to manage the deals.","index":154,"end_time":624.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Here''s where they are in the workflow, here''s the revenue, here''s the push.","index":155,"end_time":627.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":624.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I wasn''t going to start messaging people out.","index":156,"end_time":630.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean obviously it''s tracking my email traffic and stuff like that.","index":157,"end_time":633.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we''re tracking.","index":158,"end_time":634.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So all that''s getting into the atr, into the CRM.","index":159,"end_time":637.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I wasn''t planning on sending any messaging out through the sales side and maybe I didn''t realize that was there.","index":160,"end_time":644.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I viewed that was all on the marketing side that if we were going to do business development and stuff that was really probably being driven from the marketing side.","index":161,"end_time":651.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But that may be on my naivety that I didn''t know if I have something over there, I didn''t know how to use it.","index":162,"end_time":657.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":163,"end_time":657.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m looking for direction on that.","index":164,"end_time":659.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, it''s like HubSpot''s built, kind of build it based on how a lot of orgs have their marketing and sales team set up.","index":165,"end_time":666.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":659.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s like the sales side has leads and then they do their own like BDR outreach from there and they do enable sequences like a one to one sequences and stuff.","index":166,"end_time":675.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then on the marketing side you, you actually don''t have access to those sequences for prospecting.","index":167,"end_time":682.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because on the marketing side everyone needs to effectively be opted in right to get like a newsletter and such.","index":168,"end_time":688.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But the One thing that HubSpot does give you on the market side is, is non marketing contacts.","index":169,"end_time":694.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so our team does use those a lot to insert custom events and things like that that we''re doing on the outbound side.","index":170,"end_time":703.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So Colin, I think you, me and Guille will just have to figure out, you know, the best structure for this because we kind of have like everything at our disposal which isn''t totally normal.","index":171,"end_time":714.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":703.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Typically we just have the marketing Hub Pro that we''re using.","index":172,"end_time":717.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":714.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I think we''ll probably share a lot of the similar setups that, that we would have.","index":173,"end_time":722.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":174,"end_time":723.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, because what, what I''m looking at, you know, you guys are driving my, I guess my lead engine from a standpoint and then once you get somebody that raises their hand then obviously I would jump in on that.","index":175,"end_time":734.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I really don''t plan on doing any BDR reach out or something like that.","index":176,"end_time":738.909,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If I go to a conference or something like that, like you know, Jason, CEO of the public accounting firm that I support, you know, he''s at a PE firm right now or PE event in Chicago.","index":177,"end_time":750.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.909,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"He''s grabbing me the list because he''s a speaker.","index":178,"end_time":752.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I''m gonna.","index":179,"end_time":753.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m gonna.","index":180,"end_time":753.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I may.","index":181,"end_time":754.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Guys, here''s a list of PE firms that he spoke to that play in the professional services realm.","index":182,"end_time":760.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We may want to market to them, you know, stuff like that.","index":183,"end_time":762.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But, I mean, other than that, I would always come to you guys and let you generate it on that side.","index":184,"end_time":767.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then really, the CRM, you know, you know, I''m putting in my deals, I''m closing the deals, I''m using that for tracking my revenue and stuff like that.","index":185,"end_time":775.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then unless you guys tell me I got a play that I need to reach out to somebody, I really wasn''t doing a whole lot of anything else because most of my stuff right now is coming in through referrals anyhow.","index":186,"end_time":784.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I may have a handful of clients where, you know, somebody may refer to me and I may go chase them, but I''m not going to really put it in a cadence.","index":187,"end_time":792.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s more about, you know, email traffic.","index":188,"end_time":793.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then we set something up, and then I would load them into the system as a potential opportunity.","index":189,"end_time":798.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":190,"end_time":800.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":799.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So lectures and said, we''ll regroup.","index":191,"end_time":802.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":800.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also always think about this from an economy standpoint.","index":192,"end_time":804.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, if you''re paying for something and we don''t deem it to be fully necessary, we''re just going to let you know and be transparent about that.","index":193,"end_time":810.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like that.","index":194,"end_time":811.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":811.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like that.","index":195,"end_time":813.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":196,"end_time":814.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":813.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you did answer one of the questions I had later on, which was, are you doing any activity separate from us?","index":197,"end_time":818.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":814.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s good to know.","index":198,"end_time":819.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":818.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting back to, like, a website mindset, you know, you have this website, I know you''re not tied to, like, anything like the branding or anything like that.","index":199,"end_time":827.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re not coming up in a lot of search results.","index":200,"end_time":829.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was like a check the box type of effort.","index":201,"end_time":831.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":829.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That being said, we definitely want to transcend and come to the next level of this.","index":202,"end_time":834.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when we''re taking that mindset, you know, we can obviously migrate all the content in its existing form.","index":203,"end_time":841.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But there are a few things that you talked about where, you know, compared to why do you stand out from Korn Fairy?","index":204,"end_time":847.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":841.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s because you guys are laser focused.","index":205,"end_time":848.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":847.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we also don''t want to build the website to almost be a silo.","index":206,"end_time":851.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":207,"end_time":851.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we want to represent all of those people.","index":208,"end_time":853.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to get from your standpoint, you know, if we''re thinking because a website is organic.","index":209,"end_time":859.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":210,"end_time":859.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re not Just going to like build it and say like, okay, cool, now it''s December, we''re done and we''re never going to touch this website again.","index":211,"end_time":864.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to build new pages as we go.","index":212,"end_time":865.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":864.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to get an understanding of like, priority order of new content that you''ve been yearning for that you just haven''t had time to build onto the site.","index":213,"end_time":873.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, well, like I was telling the team and you heard, and the thing is, is I''ve done a lot of work recently in this past year in the utility space.","index":214,"end_time":881.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So some of my three, three of my big PE firms, they are all buying utility, you know, manufacturing.","index":215,"end_time":886.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So as you guys are moving stuff over, there''s a couple of pages on there that you have to click on the tab and then it opens up, it says PE firms.","index":216,"end_time":894.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If we''re developing or change stuff, I''d like to be able to, you know, somehow tie in some stuff that we''re the go to firm for PE firms to work for, but we''re also the go to firm for utility, you know, manufacturers that are manufacturing, you know, components for the grid, the utility grid.","index":217,"end_time":910.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re, we''re the, we''re the firm to come to because I have success stories around what we''ve done on that.","index":218,"end_time":915.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it''s.","index":219,"end_time":916.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Some of that stuff is there.","index":220,"end_time":917.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I think that''s like when we talked about that first kind of go out campaign, I have recent wins on that.","index":221,"end_time":924.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I have a, you know, two PE firms that would say wonderful things about me.","index":222,"end_time":928.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So why not try to capitalize on that, those wins?","index":223,"end_time":931.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So those would be some of the things to say, hey, how do we show that, you know, KTC is a specialty in these spaces.","index":224,"end_time":940.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way when you guys are doing things, we''re growing awareness in the marketplace.","index":225,"end_time":946.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":941.289,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And right now I''m not doing that.","index":226,"end_time":948.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m doing it by word of mouth.","index":227,"end_time":949.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I have people I''ve worked with and board members that like me and they''re telling me their, their peers.","index":228,"end_time":954.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m getting that brand recognition from there, but other than that, I''m not getting anything else.","index":229,"end_time":958.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And if you go to my website, yeah, you can probably find some of that.","index":230,"end_time":962.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I don''t think, I really, I don''t think we did a good job of saying, hey, I''m the, I''m the firm to go to when you have these type of needs.","index":231,"end_time":967.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, I''m totally open to whatever.","index":232,"end_time":970.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like I said, you know, you guys have full Runway to do whatever the hell you need.","index":233,"end_time":974.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, yeah.","index":234,"end_time":976.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":974.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which is great.","index":235,"end_time":976.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":976.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s A refreshing thing to hear.","index":236,"end_time":978.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":977.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":237,"end_time":980.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":979.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the approach that we would take, I mean we, with outreach, specifically with account based marketing outreach, we''re going to control where these people are going.","index":238,"end_time":987.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, when we''re saying we''re the perfect fit for engineering, you know, that''s a campaign tailored to those PE firms that work with those companies.","index":239,"end_time":995.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re sending them to that specific page, we''re showing them those specific ads, things like that.","index":240,"end_time":999.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":995.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on the homepage we could probably have more of a general breakdown that still has a module in it that alludes to like all of the different industries that we can focus on.","index":241,"end_time":1008.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":999.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I know another thing you said is like it never slows down though on companies needing sales or finance people or other people to bring in.","index":242,"end_time":1014.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we don''t want to like just pigeonhole you too much into one.","index":243,"end_time":1017.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1014.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":244,"end_time":1018.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":245,"end_time":1018.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And that''s where we were talking about when, when we, you know, kind of set the goals of.","index":246,"end_time":1021.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I was hoping to get out of you guys is, hey, hopefully you guys secure a couple retained search clients for me in the PE space.","index":247,"end_time":1028.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1021.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But then maybe on the, on the other side to the sales and the finance, those are maybe, hey, you can bring me five contingent clients that are looking for salespeople or sales leader where I need to prove myself with them.","index":248,"end_time":1040.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s where I''m kind of looking at it.","index":249,"end_time":1042.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yes, I agree, 100.","index":250,"end_time":1043.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I want to custom pages for that when we''re marketing to them.","index":251,"end_time":1048.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But at the same time I want to keep my site broad enough that I get picked up on other stuff too.","index":252,"end_time":1053.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1048.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because right now I think we have a three year window.","index":253,"end_time":1055.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1053.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Why?","index":254,"end_time":1055.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There''s a lot of data centers.","index":255,"end_time":1057.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"AI is booming.","index":256,"end_time":1058.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There''s going to be a lot of involvement over the next three years, you know, but you know, hey, if a new administration comes in in 29, you know, that could all change again.","index":257,"end_time":1066.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now we could all go to renewables again and you know, solar, who, who knows what the world''s going to bring.","index":258,"end_time":1072.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1066.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, I want to be able to capitalize on what, what we can capitalize on.","index":259,"end_time":1076.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Same time, don''t shut down the thing where, you know, I''ve done a lot of success in sales.","index":260,"end_time":1082.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like I said, like one of the, the guys I was talking about while I was late, I did work.","index":261,"end_time":1086.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I worked for him at Citrix.","index":262,"end_time":1088.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"He''s got his own firm.","index":263,"end_time":1090.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1089.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just told him, I said, look, I''m giving you a deal here.","index":264,"end_time":1092.979,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1090.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''re going to be a spokesperson and my fir, this marketing firm is going to interview you.","index":265,"end_time":1097.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.979,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s what you know, so he''s a person that would be able to talk about.","index":266,"end_time":1099.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And everything I''ve done for him has been sales, sales, sales individual.","index":267,"end_time":1104.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So he''d be a good spokesperson to basically say Mike''s the guy to go to if you''re trying to build out a sales organization.","index":268,"end_time":1110.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":269,"end_time":1111.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1110.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":270,"end_time":1111.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1111.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Michael, one question that.","index":271,"end_time":1114.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1112.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":1114.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1114.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If I could.","index":273,"end_time":1115.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":1115.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1115.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We didn''t ask in the last one.","index":275,"end_time":1117.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1115.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, if you do go to the home page.","index":276,"end_time":1119.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":277,"end_time":1119.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1119.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And when.","index":278,"end_time":1120.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What would you feel like would be the best reflection of what you would like to see for ktc?","index":279,"end_time":1127.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1121.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, is it.","index":280,"end_time":1128.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do you feel like that.","index":281,"end_time":1130.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1129.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That where it is now is good?","index":282,"end_time":1133.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1130.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We just need to have better detail in, In.","index":283,"end_time":1136.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"In, like, very specific pages.","index":284,"end_time":1137.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1136.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or do you feel like you want to move that messaging even onto the homepage more?","index":285,"end_time":1143.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1137.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, I. I think we got to get it on the homepage some more.","index":286,"end_time":1146.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1143.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, part of the graphics that he has in there is why I had him grab some of this, because I don''t want us to be viewed as just a regional firm because obviously we''re doing stuff nationally.","index":287,"end_time":1156.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s why I had him drop some stuff of European stuff, because, like I said, I''ve done st and some of those things.","index":288,"end_time":1161.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s why I have.","index":289,"end_time":1162.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I think, and this is where I would need your guys''s recommendations.","index":290,"end_time":1165.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I think we need to bring some of that to the front page.","index":291,"end_time":1168.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1165.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because if somebody just happens to come across my website when they''re Google searching, what they''re going to see is the.","index":292,"end_time":1174.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is the landing page where they go.","index":293,"end_time":1176.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And if I''m not mentioning some of that out there, they may not drill any further, you know.","index":294,"end_time":1181.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And once again, you guys do this for a living, so I''m heavily, heavily relying on your guys''s guidance as to how to set this up.","index":295,"end_time":1188.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And, you know, Colin, as I told you know, Tristan was, I view these last 90 days, you know, the rest of the year, this is the time to, you know, get the house cleaned up.","index":296,"end_time":1196.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t really care if you.","index":297,"end_time":1198.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We don''t send.","index":298,"end_time":1198.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t care if we don''t do any campaigns until January.","index":299,"end_time":1200.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t really care, really.","index":300,"end_time":1202.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The place is, let''s get the house set up.","index":301,"end_time":1204.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1202.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Let''s make sure the messaging''s right, the website''s right.","index":302,"end_time":1207.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way when you guys hit January 1st, we got our shit straight.","index":303,"end_time":1211.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1207.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And if somebody hits our site, they''re going to feel good about, you know, doing business with us.","index":304,"end_time":1216.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":305,"end_time":1217.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1216.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, go ahead.","index":306,"end_time":1218.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1217.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I was just going to say I Think the big thing that we''re missing now, like if you scroll to the top, Colin, that we want to hit on right away is the who''s not necessarily a right or wrong, Michael.","index":307,"end_time":1236.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s kind of what we''re trying to figure out.","index":308,"end_time":1238.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because right now you do have.","index":309,"end_time":1240.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1238.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If I want to distill what I see now is just like a website visitor or possible prospect.","index":310,"end_time":1246.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I see forward thinking enterprises across global markets.","index":311,"end_time":1251.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like it''s a little buried there, but like that''s what I see.","index":312,"end_time":1254.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1251.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do you feel like that lines up with where you want to be on the homepage or.","index":313,"end_time":1259.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think some of that does because I want to, I want them to view that.","index":314,"end_time":1262.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re, you know, we may be small but we are an enterprise.","index":315,"end_time":1265.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Big, big.","index":316,"end_time":1267.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1266.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we, we may be small but we operate like a large company.","index":317,"end_time":1270.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1267.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We can get shit done, we can find the right people, we, we play with the big boys.","index":318,"end_time":1274.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1270.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re not just some SMB mid market company.","index":319,"end_time":1277.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, because that is the one commonality that, that like I saw across your prospect like a PE firm, you know, it''s good, it''s a certain critical mass where you''re, you''re going to probably be considered enterprise.","index":320,"end_time":1291.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You''re, you know, you''re touching on global markets.","index":321,"end_time":1293.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like a lot of the industries that you''re playing in cross borders.","index":322,"end_time":1297.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s a complex nature to the folks that you need to place.","index":323,"end_time":1301.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right?","index":324,"end_time":1302.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1302.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they need a certain leadership complexity.","index":325,"end_time":1306.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They, these are folks that have experience, you know, they''re, they''re hard positions to fill.","index":326,"end_time":1313.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1306.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s why you''re, you''re coming in, into the fold there.","index":327,"end_time":1316.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1313.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I do have one quick question for you in messaging.","index":328,"end_time":1319.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So as you guys did your research and you went, you know, corn''s a separate thing but you looked at some of the other top firms, you know, and you drill into it.","index":329,"end_time":1327.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"A lot of the names are where the founders or the owners of their individual firms are named.","index":330,"end_time":1332.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I always get, you know, when you throw your name in there and service companies, you see it in public accounting firms, you see in law firms, they always kind of use their name.","index":331,"end_time":1340.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But if we did do a little rebranding on this, part of me almost like to maybe put, because I own that other domain is KTC Search or something.","index":332,"end_time":1349.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I always get a little worried that when you put your name in there, everybody gets okay, this is just a one man shop and they get stuff like that.","index":333,"end_time":1357.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I am thinking a little bit about that and you know, it''s the same thing as with the mark.","index":334,"end_time":1362.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1357.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like I said, I don''t spend hours and hours of redeveloping a bunch of new marks.","index":335,"end_time":1365.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I''m open to some of that too.","index":336,"end_time":1368.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1365.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And that was one of the reasons I bought that KTC search where it was that way we kind of got my last name off the webpage, we got my last name or so it''s not just so focused where it''s just a one person, you know, I mean, hey, if I had three other partners and there was four other names up there and they maybe not so big, but I also get that paranoia and then you guys can walk me off the ledge.","index":337,"end_time":1387.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you disagree is, you know, you got one name up there.","index":338,"end_time":1391.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1387.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is this just a one man guy that''s, you know, trying to make himself look a lot bigger than he really is.","index":339,"end_time":1396.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Where if I bury it and say KTC Search or some other the domains we miss it around, it may give the Persona the perception that we''re much bigger than we really are.","index":340,"end_time":1406.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Where if you just have my last name up there, in my opinion makes me look like I''m smaller.","index":341,"end_time":1410.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":342,"end_time":1412.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1411.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s an interesting question.","index":343,"end_time":1413.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Colin, we could talk about this because I think if you do want to make a change, now would be the time.","index":344,"end_time":1419.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I agree.","index":345,"end_time":1420.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you know, because there''s not a lot of like brand searches on Kirsten right now that we would be even worried about.","index":346,"end_time":1428.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":347,"end_time":1429.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1428.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If that''s an.","index":348,"end_time":1432.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1431.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think we would want to build some more workshops around that though, Michael.","index":349,"end_time":1437.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like if you want to go down that path.","index":350,"end_time":1439.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":351,"end_time":1440.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1439.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, like let''s, let''s do some research on, on like for example, if you have KTC search, let''s see what, what that looks like.","index":352,"end_time":1448.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, we would want to ask ourselves, do you want search as a part of that domain?","index":353,"end_time":1454.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because that does like impact some of the services you provide.","index":354,"end_time":1460.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":355,"end_time":1461.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1460.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because like you do have the ongoing services that aren''t always necessarily.","index":356,"end_time":1466.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I guess everything could be considered search.","index":357,"end_time":1468.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1466.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Everything kind of falls into search.","index":358,"end_time":1470.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean at the end of the day we are searching for people regardless if it''s direct hire, fractional or contract, it''s still search.","index":359,"end_time":1476.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1470.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m not opposed to that because I think, you know, I don''t know, I may not have sent it to you, but you know, when I was and I had that one guy, when I had that rush, whatever, I kind of sent a bunch of things.","index":360,"end_time":1488.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1477.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Search seems to be come up in a lot of keywords.","index":361,"end_time":1491.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like if somebody''s doing a keyword.","index":362,"end_time":1493.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1491.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":363,"end_time":1494.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You see executive search or retain search, search always seems to pop up.","index":364,"end_time":1498.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1494.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s why when I was like messing when I was trying to buy a bunch of domains.","index":365,"end_time":1501.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was like, all right, KTC Search would probably not be a bad idea because search is always going to come up and maybe I would get picked up even a little bit more because I have that keyword search in there.","index":366,"end_time":1512.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m not opposed to like Trish like you said is I don''t have that much brand recognition out there anyhow.","index":367,"end_time":1518.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1512.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I mean really we''re not changing a whole lot.","index":368,"end_time":1520.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1518.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean hey, we''re dropping instead of Kirsten Town Capital you''re putting KT Search in front of it.","index":369,"end_time":1524.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"A lot of that stuff is some easy probably search and replace and I think some of this content you guys are going to blow up and redo anyhow.","index":370,"end_time":1530.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It may make sense to do that because then I think it gives me a bigger perception that I''m not just a one man shop with just having one name up there.","index":371,"end_time":1539.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1531.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And right now when you refer to yourself or do you use KTC a lot?","index":372,"end_time":1545.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1540.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because I know our conversations you started to.","index":373,"end_time":1548.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1545.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We noticed that.","index":374,"end_time":1549.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, I start using that just because it''s easier to say than Kirsten Town Capital and you know, just KTC and you know I, it''s easier as referred to.","index":375,"end_time":1557.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean when you talk to people you always see people kind of go to the acronyms of then what the whole name of their company is.","index":376,"end_time":1564.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1557.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And to me it''s long winded to try to type that out.","index":377,"end_time":1567.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Kirsten Talent Capital.","index":378,"end_time":1568.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s a lot to type where KTC Search boom.","index":379,"end_time":1571.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s very quick and printing and if somebody asks hey, that''s what it stands for.","index":380,"end_time":1575.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1571.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I kind of like that acronym because it''s just easier to say I think it flows better than trying to get the whole thing out.","index":381,"end_time":1582.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a few things that, that come to mind of like you know there''s, there''s.","index":382,"end_time":1588.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1585.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You already own the domain so like there''s definitely some things we could even do there to connect both websites.","index":383,"end_time":1594.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One question I have though is, you know, does, does that come up as an objection in any of your calls of like people thinking you''re too small based on the name or.","index":384,"end_time":1604.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1594.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, nobody''s ever has.","index":385,"end_time":1606.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Maybe it''s just my paranoia because I, I always try to compete myself against the big boys, you know and I do well competing and I beat them out in cases I lose.","index":386,"end_time":1615.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1606.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But when I look at my side or I look at who I am and you know, when I compare against you know, the Corns and stuff like that, they have that global Recognition and even some of the, you know, you know, some of the bigger European firms that you guys identify in the top five, there''s multiple names in their title.","index":387,"end_time":1632.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1615.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you can see that they''re much bigger organizations where I don''t show a bunch of people on my website, hey, here''s all the team members, here''s that.","index":388,"end_time":1640.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1632.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m constantly thinking that, you know, when you look at those other competitors and they go to their website and they hit Korn Ferry, you hit the page, you know, there''s freaking 100 people that work there, partners.","index":389,"end_time":1651.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well that''s not my thing.","index":390,"end_time":1652.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1651.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So once again it kind of makes me feel like, hey, Kirsten, Talent Capital must just be a one man show.","index":391,"end_time":1657.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1652.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And yes, we are selling ourselves.","index":392,"end_time":1659.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1657.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And part of the messaging that you guys would help me in that enablement is we are a boutique firm.","index":393,"end_time":1663.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1659.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We are very specialized, we''re very good.","index":394,"end_time":1665.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re not going to be Korn Ferry, we''re not going to be, you know, Reynolds Russell''s.","index":395,"end_time":1670.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1665.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re not those big firms.","index":396,"end_time":1671.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But because we''re not, we''re able to move fast, we''re able to get a better pricing, we get shit done a lot quicker.","index":397,"end_time":1677.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1671.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We get you better talent because we don''t have all that bureaucrats.","index":398,"end_time":1680,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1677.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Very similar when you''re recruiting people out.","index":399,"end_time":1681.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, why are you leaving Amazon?","index":400,"end_time":1683.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, I''m sick of all the red tape.","index":401,"end_time":1684.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1683.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I can''t get anything done.","index":402,"end_time":1686.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s why I want to go to a smaller company so I can sell against that.","index":403,"end_time":1690.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I''m always first seeing as first perceptions or something.","index":404,"end_time":1693.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1690.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And if they hit my site and hit there, this guy looks too small.","index":405,"end_time":1697.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We better go to the big one.","index":406,"end_time":1698.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1697.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s kind of that old nachos.","index":407,"end_time":1699.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1698.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If I hire IBM, I''m not going to get fired even if IBM shits the bet.","index":408,"end_time":1704.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1699.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, it''s kind of that analogy, you know.","index":409,"end_time":1706.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1704.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yep.","index":410,"end_time":1707.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1706.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":411,"end_time":1708.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1707.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what I would say, you know, obviously we''ll, we''ll regroup and come up with a recommendation there.","index":412,"end_time":1712.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1708.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On, on.","index":413,"end_time":1713.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1712.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we think it''s worthwhile to switch the brand entirely?","index":414,"end_time":1715.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1713.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what I will say is if you''re having conversations where you are referring to yourself as KTC because of the sales cycle or not even always the sales cycle, but like the need that arises for these PE firms, you might have a conversation this week but they not, they might not have a need until end of Q1 next year.","index":415,"end_time":1731.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1715.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They need to know and if they remember you as ktc, we need you to populate in that search.","index":416,"end_time":1735.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1731.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly.","index":417,"end_time":1736.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1735.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":418,"end_time":1737.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1736.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And that, and to Me, that and you guys.","index":419,"end_time":1739.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys, you''re not going to hurt my feelings.","index":420,"end_time":1740.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1739.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m, you know, never anything you say.","index":421,"end_time":1742.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1740.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You can be very direct with me.","index":422,"end_time":1743.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys tell me.","index":423,"end_time":1745.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1744.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I think that''s a hell of a lot easier to remember than Kirsten Town Capital.","index":424,"end_time":1747.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1745.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":425,"end_time":1748.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1748.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":426,"end_time":1749.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1748.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll just have to check if there''s any other KTCs out there that we''ll need to compete against.","index":427,"end_time":1753.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":428,"end_time":1753.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1753.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":429,"end_time":1755.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1754.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, yeah, obviously we''ve taken a deep dive into a lot of your competitors.","index":430,"end_time":1758.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1755.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know one thing I, I heard and I completely agree with is I know the original design of your site had like black and red colors and you had to switch to blue.","index":431,"end_time":1766.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1758.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great move in the financial space or in the job searching space as well.","index":432,"end_time":1770.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1766.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But are there any other example websites that you''ve seen and you''re like, you know, like the colors, the architecture, the way this flows, the way they use imagery, is there anything that''s, like, stood out to you?","index":433,"end_time":1780.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1770.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":434,"end_time":1781.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, I think if you look at the top five top 10 retained search firms, which you guys had in your research, and, you know, I can send.","index":435,"end_time":1787.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, they all seem to be thing.","index":436,"end_time":1789.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1787.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They seem to use lighter colors.","index":437,"end_time":1790.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1789.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They have a lot of pictures, they have a lot of video, steel videos.","index":438,"end_time":1796.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1790.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Kind of like when you go to my site, you see those things flipping on and out.","index":439,"end_time":1799.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When he first did the first run, he had a lot of stakes, steel pictures.","index":440,"end_time":1802.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1799.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m like, oh, look, we got to get some stuff that''s rotating in because if you go to the competitors, they all have something in there that looks like that.","index":441,"end_time":1810.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m once again, you guys do this for a living.","index":442,"end_time":1813.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I am open for anything.","index":443,"end_time":1815.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And that''s why I wanted to be very clear is you can change the mark, you can change the colors.","index":444,"end_time":1819.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1815.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If we''re porting it over, you can change whatever you want.","index":445,"end_time":1823.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1819.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I am not tied to anything.","index":446,"end_time":1824.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1823.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And the nice thing is, is there''s not that many people that have seen my site, so they''re not going to know any different.","index":447,"end_time":1828.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1824.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If all of a sudden you change the colors or we change the marks, I don''t have that many people going to my site.","index":448,"end_time":1833.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1828.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys see the demographics.","index":449,"end_time":1835.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1833.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it.","index":450,"end_time":1836.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1835.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It died.","index":451,"end_time":1836.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1836.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not losing anything.","index":452,"end_time":1837.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1836.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So to Tristan''s point, if we''re going to do it, let''s just do it now.","index":453,"end_time":1841.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1837.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And, you know, let''s.","index":454,"end_time":1842.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1841.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If we''re going to move it, I''d rather do it now.","index":455,"end_time":1844.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1842.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way we''re doing this now in 25, and we''re not talking about this in 26 or 27.","index":456,"end_time":1850.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1844.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":457,"end_time":1851.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1850.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We should have done this.","index":458,"end_time":1851.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1851.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We should have done that.","index":459,"end_time":1852.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1851.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And we''re reinventing the wheel.","index":460,"end_time":1853.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1852.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, I think we have the best of both worlds.","index":461,"end_time":1855.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1853.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys have a clean slate.","index":462,"end_time":1857.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1855.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''re not trying to clean up the.","index":463,"end_time":1858.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1857.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s clean.","index":464,"end_time":1859.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1859.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You can build it however you want, do whatever you want.","index":465,"end_time":1862.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1859.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I''m giving you guys the key to the kitchen, and I need your expertise to help me get to that next level.","index":466,"end_time":1867.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1862.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":467,"end_time":1868.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1867.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s fantastic.","index":468,"end_time":1868.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1868.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what we''ll put all of this into is what we call a website plan document.","index":469,"end_time":1872.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1868.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''ll go through architecture, web frames, URL recommendations, messaging, actually taking it into HubSpot and building it out, and even creating templates for landing pages that we want to create in the future.","index":470,"end_time":1885.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1872.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we have a new industry you want to tap into, just like your example, if legislation changes and there''s a huge shift in the economy, we need to be able to spin something up quickly, quick.","index":471,"end_time":1893.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1886.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or say you''ve been talking to one PE firm and you''re like, hey, let''s create a webpage completely dedicated to them.","index":472,"end_time":1899.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1893.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":473,"end_time":1900.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1899.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can spin that up in a short amount of time.","index":474,"end_time":1902.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1900.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also all the landing pages we''ll develop for our campaigns moving forward.","index":475,"end_time":1906.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1902.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''ll all be outlined in this website plan document that we''ll put together.","index":476,"end_time":1910.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1906.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":477,"end_time":1911.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1910.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I throw out to Colin, you and you and Tristan, both you guys can talk, take offline if you want.","index":478,"end_time":1915.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1911.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is.","index":479,"end_time":1915.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1915.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I know we have in this first go around, you know, you guys were trying to put in some ABP and some campaigns and stuff.","index":480,"end_time":1921.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1915.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m not opposed.","index":481,"end_time":1922.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1921.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you guys, you know, this first month, 80 hours, 100 hours, whatever the hell I have.","index":482,"end_time":1926.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1922.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If we want to dedicate that all to redoing the website and doing that, I don''t have a problem pushing that stuff by because as I said it multiple times, we had our discovery, our workshops is it''s all about getting the house ready, getting the foundation.","index":483,"end_time":1940.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1926.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I don''t think we''re there.","index":484,"end_time":1942.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1940.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And if that means that we have to shift, you know, campaigns until January, I don''t really care.","index":485,"end_time":1947.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1942.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, it''s really about let''s spend the money wisely.","index":486,"end_time":1950.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1947.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I think redoing some of the site, re cleaning some of it up, positioning it differently, is, in my opinion, well spent money on my part.","index":487,"end_time":1958.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1950.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you guys disagree, I''m.","index":488,"end_time":1959.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1958.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m looking for a partner that''s going to be honest with me.","index":489,"end_time":1961.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1959.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if I get off the rails, I need you guys to bring me back onto the Rails.","index":490,"end_time":1965.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1961.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I gotcha.","index":491,"end_time":1967.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1965.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":492,"end_time":1967.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1967.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we like to move quick because, you know, I''ll tell you, Michael, we might even move a little too quick sometimes, right?","index":493,"end_time":1972.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1967.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I like to get things into market.","index":494,"end_time":1973.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1972.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to test them.","index":495,"end_time":1974.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1974.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to see what works.","index":496,"end_time":1975.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1974.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":497,"end_time":1976.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1975.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not.","index":498,"end_time":1976.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1976.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not the company that''s going to just turn on a campaign and be, like, cool, we''ll see how it did in a month or three months.","index":499,"end_time":1980.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1976.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re gonna make a lot of changes, you know, and as soon as we find something that''s working, we''re gonna start looking for something else to.","index":500,"end_time":1986.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1981.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To work as well, because can''t put all our eggs in one basket.","index":501,"end_time":1989.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1986.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to have a lot of things out there.","index":502,"end_time":1991.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1989.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":503,"end_time":1991.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1991.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I have one other quick question, and just not to steal your thunder, but part of what you guys do, do I need to be buying a subscription to Clay?","index":504,"end_time":2000.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1992.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because I know you guys used it because, like I said, my.","index":505,"end_time":2002.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2000.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m on Zoom right now, and, you know, I have that stuff and you guys can tie into that.","index":506,"end_time":2005.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2002.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But, I mean, do I need.","index":507,"end_time":2007.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2005.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or I know you guys work with that.","index":508,"end_time":2008.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2007.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Do I need to be negotiating deals with some of these other vendors?","index":509,"end_time":2012.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2008.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Are you guys working that behind the scenes for me?","index":510,"end_time":2014,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2012.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or what do I need to do?","index":511,"end_time":2015.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2014,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or, you know, can we leverage what I have with Zoom?","index":512,"end_time":2017.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2015.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, you guys ought to give me some direction on that, too.","index":513,"end_time":2020.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2017.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":514,"end_time":2020.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2020.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we don''t need you to subscribe to Clay.","index":515,"end_time":2024.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2021.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a subscription.","index":516,"end_time":2025.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2024.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We get credits, and we basically charge points back.","index":517,"end_time":2027.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2025.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''re buying points every month from us.","index":518,"end_time":2029.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2027.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That just comes out of your tech stack.","index":519,"end_time":2031.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2029.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we buy a few thousand contacts, we sell it to you at a discounted rate.","index":520,"end_time":2033.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2031.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":521,"end_time":2034.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2034.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":522,"end_time":2034.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2034.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":523,"end_time":2035.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2034.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":524,"end_time":2035.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2035.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I can give you.","index":525,"end_time":2036.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2035.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If we need more context.","index":526,"end_time":2037.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2036.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like I said, I have almost 50, 60,000 contacts with Zoom, and I''m not using any of them.","index":527,"end_time":2042.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2037.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, yeah, we need to pull from that.","index":528,"end_time":2043.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2042.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We can definitely use that.","index":529,"end_time":2045.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2043.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Where?","index":530,"end_time":2045.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2045.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That way, you know, I''ve already paid for it, so I''m not burning credits and use those credits somewhere else, but we can talk about that.","index":531,"end_time":2051.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2045.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Whatever''s easiest for you guys.","index":532,"end_time":2052.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2051.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":533,"end_time":2053.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2052.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":534,"end_time":2054.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2053.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just being cognizant of time, too.","index":535,"end_time":2055.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2054.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to also talk about the content engine.","index":536,"end_time":2058.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2055.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you have.","index":537,"end_time":2058.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2058.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I believe the date was March of this large client and kind of having, like, content or video series where maybe we don''t want to have everything out there.","index":538,"end_time":2066.469,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2059.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to talk about putting this content series together and having you have conversations or having us have conversations with Prospects or us interviewing you, there''s a few different ways that we can approach this.","index":539,"end_time":2077.669,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2067.909,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So really wanted to get first your comfortability with like hosting a conversation with.","index":540,"end_time":2083.189,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2078.789,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This could be a prospect, this could be a current customer, this could be someone just in the space that is experiencing pain points.","index":541,"end_time":2089.789,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2083.189,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe they don''t even know who KTC is.","index":542,"end_time":2092.269,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2089.789,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s just a good conversation to get your brand recognition out there there.","index":543,"end_time":2095.269,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2092.269,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you.","index":544,"end_time":2096.389,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2095.909,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you lean towards hosting this yourself, having us host it?","index":545,"end_time":2099.669,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2096.389,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, I would probably, for sake of time and things, I would probably have you guys host some of this stuff and then I can kind of come in behind the scenes because what.","index":546,"end_time":2109.989,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2099.749,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I found, at least with some of the PE firms, is sometimes they''d be willing to say, hey, I''m working on this.","index":547,"end_time":2115.029,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2110.069,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m not going to be on the call to try to sell you.","index":548,"end_time":2117.229,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2115.429,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"These guys are helping me build my brand.","index":549,"end_time":2119.349,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2117.229,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''re kind of helping me figure out what''s hurting in your thing.","index":550,"end_time":2122.389,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2119.349,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it''s on both of our parts.","index":551,"end_time":2124.229,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2122.389,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sometimes they''re a little bit more willing to take call with you guys than necessarily if I''m hosting it because then they feel like I''m trying to sell them something.","index":552,"end_time":2131.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2124.309,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":553,"end_time":2132.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2131.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s completely fair.","index":554,"end_time":2133.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2132.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":555,"end_time":2134.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2134.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like I said, we don''t have to stay in one lane there either.","index":556,"end_time":2137.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2134.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you do have time to freeze up, you want to come in and do an.","index":557,"end_time":2140.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2137.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you want to do a solo episode and we just give you a list of questions of what we find going on in the market and you just a couple minutes record yourself talking through it.","index":558,"end_time":2147.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2140.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can, you know, produce it and get that out on social.","index":559,"end_time":2149.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2147.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope, we can definitely do that too.","index":560,"end_time":2151.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2150.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Some of the stuff, like I was telling the team, is I have to be careful what I push out in my brand until least after 1Q26, just because of my ID me stuff.","index":561,"end_time":2163.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2151.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I have a lot of their pre IPO and I have some other levers that are taking place and that all gets taken, paid out in March 31st.","index":562,"end_time":2171.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2164.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Blake, who the CEO over there, even though he''s got his hands on a thousand things, he doesn''t like anybody else to have their hands in.","index":563,"end_time":2176.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2171.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if that ever surfaced and somebody saw that, they would terminate me immediately.","index":564,"end_time":2181.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2176.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And there''s a lot of money on the table over there, so I got to keep that underneath the radar.","index":565,"end_time":2185.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2181.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, yeah, I got you.","index":566,"end_time":2186.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2185.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why I have this.","index":567,"end_time":2187.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2186.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can see I have stealth library in here as well.","index":568,"end_time":2189.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2187.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So is that all content or is that specific interviews or that that''s probably specific stuff.","index":569,"end_time":2194.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2190.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I was saying is the more I can get you guys to do stuff, we can push it out.","index":570,"end_time":2198.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2194.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s partly, you know, to be full disclosure.","index":571,"end_time":2200.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2198.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Why I like getting.","index":572,"end_time":2201.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2200.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I hate having my name on the website because if somebody comes across, it pops up.","index":573,"end_time":2205.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2201.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s why even more, I kind of like that TT''s or that at KTK search or whatever, we come up with a little better.","index":574,"end_time":2213.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2205.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once again, it takes my last name up and somebody doesn''t come across me is just the Internet and social media is so crazy nowadays.","index":575,"end_time":2222.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2213.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You be careful and next thing you get served up on something and we''re talking a couple millions dollars of stuff that''s paid to me.","index":576,"end_time":2229.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2222.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t want to take any risk of that getting messed up.","index":577,"end_time":2232.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2229.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s why the more I personally, my name''s not popping up and my name isn''t showing up is the better until I get that pay and then I don''t care, you know?","index":578,"end_time":2241.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2232.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Right.","index":579,"end_time":2242.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2241.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And as you''re well versed in, I know, you know, you shared company goals once you hit like 10, 20, 30 million and maybe having someone come in, make an investment or take the company over, you don''t want it always like just wrapped around who is Michael Kirsten.","index":580,"end_time":2255.149,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2242.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":581,"end_time":2255.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2255.149,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":582,"end_time":2255.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2255.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":583,"end_time":2256.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2255.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":584,"end_time":2256.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2256.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why I feel like, you know, if you look at some of the stuff that Michael, which is the one content writer that''s been pushing stuff out on my website just to get some freaking activity out there, I''ve had to go back because a lot of times it''s always Kirsten this or Mic or this.","index":585,"end_time":2269.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2256.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m like, guys, we have to write this where it''s not just me.","index":586,"end_time":2272.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2269.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yes, people are buying me because I''m the thing.","index":587,"end_time":2274.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2272.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But eventually this company hopefully will be bigger.","index":588,"end_time":2277.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2274.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I can''t go to a buyer and say, hey, you''re going to buy me.","index":589,"end_time":2280.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2277.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And it''s like I walk out the door.","index":590,"end_time":2281.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2280.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, then that''s.","index":591,"end_time":2282.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2281.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There''s all the intellectual property.","index":592,"end_time":2284.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2282.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we have to have that Persona, that brand where I may be the one that''s making it all happen, but we need to make it perception on the street.","index":593,"end_time":2294.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2284.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There''s much bigger people making that happen, just not just one person.","index":594,"end_time":2297.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2294.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":595,"end_time":2297.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2297.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Having that curtain in there.","index":596,"end_time":2298.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2297.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":597,"end_time":2299.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2298.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":598,"end_time":2300.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2299.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, you know, as far as what the actual, like, flagship part of the series is or theme and angle, you know, there''s a few different things that we can go down.","index":599,"end_time":2307.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2300.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some shows that we produce, I don''t know if Tristan, if you shared the Number we host and produce 50 shows a month.","index":600,"end_time":2313.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2307.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so some of them are like, this is what we talk about every time we just bring on someone else to talk about their angle.","index":601,"end_time":2320.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2314.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other approaches are like we have this kind of, of world we can operate in with it, with within pe, right.","index":602,"end_time":2326.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2320.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can talk about timeline struggles that they have.","index":603,"end_time":2328.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2326.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can talk about leadership velocity and I mean because leadership positions are the hardest to fill and then once you fill those, you''re pretty much working back to the bottom because that new leader''s coming in evaluating everyone and they''re probably going to hope for some replacements.","index":604,"end_time":2342.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2328.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We talk about infrastructure growth, we can talk about new industries that you want to focus in.","index":605,"end_time":2346.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2342.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have one of these that you lean in or do you like the ability to talk about whatever is like hot in the market?","index":606,"end_time":2352.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2346.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like the building what''s talking on hot in the market because in my world I have to jump where that''s hot because that''s where people are spending money.","index":607,"end_time":2360.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2353.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And since I chase private equity, I have to, I have to follow where they''re going because that''s where they''re going to make the investments at.","index":608,"end_time":2366.259,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2360.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s one of the reasons I really follow a lot of the analysts from Pitchbook, you know, just in their monthly write ups and what, what targets, you know, because they''ll put things in heat maps, hey, here''s the detector and here''s what''s going on.","index":609,"end_time":2378.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2366.259,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We follow that pretty quickly.","index":610,"end_time":2380.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2379.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I try to follow that very, you know, regularly because that''ll kind of tell me, hey, where are PE investing and where can I take my skills that I''ve been successful and how can I tailor that in?","index":611,"end_time":2390.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2380.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because like I''ve said is you only need to have, you know, three to five solid PE firms that are, you know, doing, you know, three to five deals a year and they''ll give you more business than you know what to do with.","index":612,"end_time":2401.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2390.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep, awesome.","index":613,"end_time":2403.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2401.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so out of this, what we''ll come out with of a deliverable is a content plan.","index":614,"end_time":2407.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2404.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This will outline like not only show name but like what is the show about?","index":615,"end_time":2410.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2407.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Who do we talk to?","index":616,"end_time":2411.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2410.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How often are we recording this and putting series or episodes out?","index":617,"end_time":2415.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2412.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are we really trying to do?","index":618,"end_time":2417.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2416.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Who are we speaking to?","index":619,"end_time":2418.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2417.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all that will be outlined in a document.","index":620,"end_time":2420.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2418.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll also produce some design files and everything that can be used.","index":621,"end_time":2424.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2420.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But keeping in mind that end of Q1 timeline and not having a lot of things out there with your name on it, we''ll have this kind of stealth library that we''ll build and Then we''ll have a bunch of content to release after that date.","index":622,"end_time":2435.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2424.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":623,"end_time":2436.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2435.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The other thing that we can do too, is because she''s good on camera, is I brought in a person.","index":624,"end_time":2440.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2436.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t want to call her a protege, but somebody who, you know, has kind of always been in, you know, followed me in different tracks.","index":625,"end_time":2449.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2441.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, like, I turned a job down a dish.","index":626,"end_time":2450.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2449.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She kind of came in and kind of took thing and then, you know, she''s been trying to get to hook up with me for quite a while to work with me.","index":627,"end_time":2456.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2450.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I just brought her on about a month ago and, you know, kind of she''s helping with me a lot of my RPO stuff and I''m kind of helping entertainment.","index":628,"end_time":2464.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2456.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She''s very polished.","index":629,"end_time":2466.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2464.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She speaks well.","index":630,"end_time":2467.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2466.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She''s somebody that I could stand up and say, hey, here''s all the stuff.","index":631,"end_time":2470.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2467.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She could be my mouthpiece, for lack of a better term.","index":632,"end_time":2472.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2470.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We could use her.","index":633,"end_time":2473.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2472.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then Michael, who''s been writing the papers, he''s pretty well spoken too.","index":634,"end_time":2479.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2474.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"He''s a marketing guy.","index":635,"end_time":2480.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2479.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I mean, we, I, I have some people that I could step in for me, I could give them, you know, here''s the questions.","index":636,"end_time":2488.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2480.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I can give them the talking points, the answers to all that, and they''re really just being my mouthpiece.","index":637,"end_time":2493.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2488.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that keeps me off camera, but then it still allows you gu to push stuff out there.","index":638,"end_time":2497.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2493.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I kind of like that idea a little bit because then once again, I''m staying behind the curtain.","index":639,"end_time":2500.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2497.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I may be giving them the detail, giving them the answers, and all they''re doing is being the mouthpiece to me.","index":640,"end_time":2505.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2501.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But that puts a layer of protection for me until we get through this first quarter.","index":641,"end_time":2509.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2505.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":642,"end_time":2510.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2509.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what I will just, you know, add on to that is we don''t want to completely remove you from this one part of the content series that we''re super excited about is I heard in the call you said, I talked to this guy eight years ago and he just like remembered my name or saw something and then came and now we have a deal in the works.","index":643,"end_time":2526.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2510.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, we need to be able to use your name recognition or we, you know, feel confident about that.","index":644,"end_time":2532.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2527.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":645,"end_time":2533.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2533.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":646,"end_time":2533.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2533.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, we can definitely position in the show.","index":647,"end_time":2535.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2533.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it could be not like a single host and really anyone and we can talk about really anything going on in the space.","index":648,"end_time":2540.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2535.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":649,"end_time":2541.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2540.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Nope, nope.","index":650,"end_time":2541.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2541.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Totally fine.","index":651,"end_time":2542.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2541.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":652,"end_time":2542.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2542.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you guys are professionals.","index":653,"end_time":2543.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2542.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''ll know how to what we can share and what we can.","index":654,"end_time":2545.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2543.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s totally fine.","index":655,"end_time":2546.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2545.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":656,"end_time":2547.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2546.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":657,"end_time":2548.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2547.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then looking at adm campaign.","index":658,"end_time":2549.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2548.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, one thing that Tristan had in the, the roadmap was this portfolio talent trends report.","index":659,"end_time":2555.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2549.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We like to create things, you know, if you want to get in the mindset of the prospect, something that they cannot say no to, interact or download or fill out.","index":660,"end_time":2563.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2555.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it feels like you''re giving your time, you''re.","index":661,"end_time":2567.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2564.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re even burning some of your assets to give them this information.","index":662,"end_time":2570.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2567.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the way that we can build it is that it really doesn''t.","index":663,"end_time":2572.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2570.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s, it''s actually replicable over time.","index":664,"end_time":2574.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2572.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing we were thinking through was the portfolio talent trends report.","index":665,"end_time":2578.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2576.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tristan, did you want to lean into that a little bit?","index":666,"end_time":2581.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2579.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":667,"end_time":2582.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2582.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the trends report, Michael, what we had envisioned is using perhaps some of those early conversations that we do on the content side to get some qualitative feedback or trends from some of your friendlies, right?","index":668,"end_time":2596.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2583.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":669,"end_time":2597.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2596.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We could package that into a report and this wouldn''t be anything like, we''re not going to ask folks to fill out a complex survey or something, but it''s like, hey, here''s trends, what I''m seeing, and here''s some industry experts that we also pulled in.","index":670,"end_time":2609.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2597.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then what we could do is use that as a foundation to get other people to weigh in on that research.","index":671,"end_time":2616.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2610.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":672,"end_time":2616.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2616.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So here''s a trends report.","index":673,"end_time":2618.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2616.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I was curious what you thought about it, and if you would like to participate in Perhaps a version 2 of this or, you know, be part of the distribution or something.","index":674,"end_time":2627.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2618.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, it''s like a, a key asset that we can use as a conversation starter.","index":675,"end_time":2632.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2628.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That was the, the, the idea there.","index":676,"end_time":2634,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2632.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":677,"end_time":2635.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2634.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, the nice thing is, is when we come to the utility stuff, some of this CROs that I placed, you know, Mike Edmonds over at McLean and then Randy over at EMC, those are seasoned veterans that have been in the utility space for 30 years.","index":678,"end_time":2651.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2635.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We could get, get them hooked up with you guys, and you guys could fire questions.","index":679,"end_time":2656.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2651.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They could tell us what''s hot, what''s not.","index":680,"end_time":2658.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2656.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They live this, and they both like to talk where you got.","index":681,"end_time":2663.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2659.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We could probably collect a lot of data about the industries and the pains and what''s going on, and then you guys can package that to help it, spin it as to, hey, here''s some of the needs or here''s some of the problems, and then we can kind of come back and figure out how do we bake in my services to fix some of those.","index":682,"end_time":2678.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2663.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But both of those people, you know, I can easily, you know, say, hey, I need you to invest an hour.","index":683,"end_time":2684.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2678.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''ll buy You a frickin steak dinner.","index":684,"end_time":2686.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2684.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Can you get on that phone with these guys and just talk about the industry?","index":685,"end_time":2689.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2686.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because, because here''s what I''m trying to do.","index":686,"end_time":2691.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2689.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And both of them would, would be willing to help.","index":687,"end_time":2694.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2691.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then, you know, I got another guy placed, you know, in an EVP sales role, kind of another veteran of the industry would be willing to say.","index":688,"end_time":2701.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2694.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I got a couple, you know, board members that, you know, we, I may not be able to get an hour out of their time, but I may be able to get 30 minutes of them where hey, could you, you know, talk about the industry, tell us some of the things and then maybe you know, spin some stuff about hey, what Mike was able to do for you and stuff.","index":689,"end_time":2717.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2702.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I mean some of those, the board members, I gotta walk a little thing, but I have a couple friendlies over there.","index":690,"end_time":2722.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2717.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then Jason from Richie May, he''ll, he''ll freaking give me all, he''ll be a good person because he''ll be able to tell you everything I''ve done on the professional services realm, how I''m a deal difference what the services that I''ve run.","index":691,"end_time":2736.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2722.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean he''ll give you all kinds of data point.","index":692,"end_time":2739.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2736.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then same with Felicia, who''s the CMO over there, marketer to marketer.","index":693,"end_time":2745.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2739.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She knows what you''re trying to build.","index":694,"end_time":2746.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2745.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She''ll be able to give you a bunch of stuff because she''s worked with me the last three years as to what, what we''ve done, what''s the difference maker?","index":695,"end_time":2753.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2746.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I think there''s friendlies in my network that I think we could, you know, we''d have to say, hey, what are we trying to accomplish?","index":696,"end_time":2759.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2753.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I could probably bring it friendly in to get us a lot of details to give you guys insight in the industry.","index":697,"end_time":2764.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2759.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then we could have another call to say, okay, based on these, here''s the questions.","index":698,"end_time":2767.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2764.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then we do another cut where I''m answering those questions or however you guys want to do.","index":699,"end_time":2771.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2767.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I think the key is if I can get you subject matter experts to really give you data dumps, may be more beneficial than we just doing a bunch of research and trying to figure out what''s up on the web.","index":700,"end_time":2782.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2771.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s, that''s actually typically exactly how we structure these.","index":701,"end_time":2785.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2782.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have two workshops often, so we''ll come in with some initial ideas, we''ll ask a lot of questions and then we''ll come back and say, here''s how we can actually position this.","index":702,"end_time":2793.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2785.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, what do you guys think of this process?","index":703,"end_time":2795.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2793.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would, would someone get value out of this.","index":704,"end_time":2797.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2795.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s great.","index":705,"end_time":2798.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2797.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other one that I was thinking through was a leadership gap assessment and that kind of goes back to the point I made earlier of, of the velocity.","index":706,"end_time":2804.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2798.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":707,"end_time":2804.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2804.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like, or the, the opportunity of if you do land someone at a leadership position, they''re coming in evaluating all the employees beneath them.","index":708,"end_time":2812.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2804.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s giving you a lot more opportunity to then bring in more employees.","index":709,"end_time":2814.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2812.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I was thinking something along those lines.","index":710,"end_time":2817.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2814.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, not a fully fleshed out idea of like, this is exactly how it look, but wanted to get these on your radar.","index":711,"end_time":2822.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2817.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":712,"end_time":2822.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2822.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Totally fine.","index":713,"end_time":2823.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2822.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m open to all that stuff.","index":714,"end_time":2824.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2823.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":715,"end_time":2824.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2824.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":716,"end_time":2824.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2824.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then, you know, not to be a broken record is, you know, let you guys kind of go back again, but really want you guys to look hard at thinking if we need to change some of that branding, we need to change on the website.","index":717,"end_time":2835.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2824.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m eager to get you guys to the thing to.","index":718,"end_time":2837.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2835.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we know what''s going to work.","index":719,"end_time":2838.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2837.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you, you know, we go into 26, we''d be successful.","index":720,"end_time":2841.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2838.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I''m also paranoid as hell that if I misstep and we don''t do it the right way, then you know, I''m going to impact us more in 26.","index":721,"end_time":2850.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2841.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I just want to throw that out there.","index":722,"end_time":2852.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2850.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I''m sorry to keep repeating myself, but I just want you guys to know I am open to whatever we need to do if we have to change some stuff.","index":723,"end_time":2858.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2852.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I totally hear and I think, you know, we''re excited about that idea too.","index":724,"end_time":2862.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2858.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to just reconvene.","index":725,"end_time":2863.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2862.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you.","index":726,"end_time":2863.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2863.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Can you guys hang on one second?","index":727,"end_time":2864.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2863.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just have a laptop being delivered there at the door, so let me just sign for it.","index":728,"end_time":2867.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2864.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"One second.","index":729,"end_time":2868.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2867.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No problem.","index":730,"end_time":2868.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2868.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":731,"end_time":2881.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2880.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Sorry about that, guys.","index":732,"end_time":2913.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2912.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No worries.","index":733,"end_time":2914.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2913.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I just have one more question regarding the ABM stuff.","index":734,"end_time":2920.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2916.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, it''s obviously important to know who we want to reach out to, but it''s equally as important to know who we don''t want to reach out to.","index":735,"end_time":2926.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2921.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So seeing 111 contacts in HubSpot, I imagine there''d be more people maybe that you don''t want us to interact with.","index":736,"end_time":2933.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2927.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have a list of those companies?","index":737,"end_time":2935.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2933.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, in regards to like the.","index":738,"end_time":2938.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2937.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Some of the existing.","index":739,"end_time":2939.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2938.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I can generate a list of companies we don''t want to go after.","index":740,"end_time":2942.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2939.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, some of the.","index":741,"end_time":2944.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2942.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"On the services side and then some of the companies over on the.","index":742,"end_time":2948.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2944.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The PE side.","index":743,"end_time":2949.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2948.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There''s probably a handful.","index":744,"end_time":2950.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2949.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like I said, I don''t have a whole lot of data in there, but there''s some Customers that I''ve worked with that, you know, I''ve lost some touch with where we can definitely throw those back in.","index":745,"end_time":2958.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2950.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So really the data that''s in HubSpot or some of the existing clients, and we were just pushing data and testing.","index":746,"end_time":2964.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2958.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So like I said, a lot of stuff in there, there''s, there''s nothing really off limits.","index":747,"end_time":2969.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2965.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Obviously, I don''t need you to mark it out to Oak tree.","index":748,"end_time":2971.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2969.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t need you to mark it out to, you know, transatlantic, because I''m already working with those.","index":749,"end_time":2976.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2971.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Right.","index":750,"end_time":2976.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2976.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But you know, there''s other companies that we can definitely go, you know, market to.","index":751,"end_time":2980.399,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2976.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":752,"end_time":2980.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2980.399,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":753,"end_time":2981.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2981.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so this was awesome.","index":754,"end_time":2984.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2982.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you so much for your time.","index":755,"end_time":2985.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2984.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Michael.","index":756,"end_time":2985.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2985.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s two more things that I wanted to get done.","index":757,"end_time":2988,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2985.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One is you will be receiving an invite to our portfolio total.","index":758,"end_time":2992.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2988.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is, you know, just.","index":759,"end_time":2994.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2992.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ll have a login with a single sign on.","index":760,"end_time":2995.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2994.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll send it over to you, just get it set up within 24 hours or if you don''t, just send it again.","index":761,"end_time":2999.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2995.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''re very transparent in everything that we do.","index":762,"end_time":3002.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3000.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll get your goals loaded in here.","index":763,"end_time":3004.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3002.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll be able to reflect on those accurately, you know, within a 15 minute increment.","index":764,"end_time":3008.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3004.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything that we''re waiting on you to review will live here with a link to go click and leave feedback.","index":765,"end_time":3012.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3008.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, when we have things in here of what do we land on for the ABM plan or what was the email sequence that all live in this final deliverables.","index":766,"end_time":3020.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3013.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll have all the episodes in there.","index":767,"end_time":3022.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3020.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything is baked into this tool and it''ll be a great resource for you to see anything that we''re doing, full transparency.","index":768,"end_time":3028.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3022.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool, cool, cool.","index":769,"end_time":3030.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3029.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you guys know the.","index":770,"end_time":3032.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3030.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Just so you guys have them.","index":771,"end_time":3036.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3035.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":772,"end_time":3036.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3036.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I had the other domains which I think I maybe I shared.","index":773,"end_time":3040.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3037.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I got that KT search.com and then the other one is kt- capitals.com and then KT talent C at the end of the talent.com, which I don''t really care for that one.","index":774,"end_time":3053.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3040.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I also have Kirsten Talent Capitals Co is the other domain, which once again, that''s kind of a long.","index":775,"end_time":3061.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3053.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m thinking if we shorted, I think the KTC search.com is probably the winner.","index":776,"end_time":3065.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3061.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But you know, we''ll let you guys decide.","index":777,"end_time":3067.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3065.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":778,"end_time":3068.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3067.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One other thing I wanted to lock in is setting up a weekly meeting cadence with you.","index":779,"end_time":3073.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3069.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we are actually Tristan and I are not available next week.","index":780,"end_time":3077.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3073.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So looking at the first week of December, do you Have.","index":781,"end_time":3081.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3078.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if maybe like a Tuesday or a Thursday would be better for you.","index":782,"end_time":3087.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3082.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which ones are better for you guys?","index":783,"end_time":3090.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3088.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Tuesdays or Thursdays?","index":784,"end_time":3091.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3090.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, yeah, we have openings on Tuesdays.","index":785,"end_time":3096.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3092.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":786,"end_time":3096.749,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3096.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does.","index":787,"end_time":3097.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3097.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does the time we had this meeting work for you?","index":788,"end_time":3100.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3098.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What time?","index":789,"end_time":3101.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3100.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We started at 10 o''.","index":790,"end_time":3103.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3101.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Clock.","index":791,"end_time":3103.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3103.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, that works.","index":792,"end_time":3104.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3103.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":793,"end_time":3105.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3104.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so I''ll send that invite over and I''ll make it recurring for every week.","index":794,"end_time":3108.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3105.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If anything ever comes up, just let us know.","index":795,"end_time":3109.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3108.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re flexible.","index":796,"end_time":3110.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3109.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can get that adjusted.","index":797,"end_time":3112.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3111.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":798,"end_time":3113.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3113.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":799,"end_time":3114.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3114.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so a couple actions there.","index":800,"end_time":3116.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3115.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you guys will come back and let me know if we want to change any of the stuff with the HubSpot, and then if there''s, you know, if I need to cut them off and change something, you guys are going to let me know that.","index":801,"end_time":3125.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3116.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then you guys will come back and let me know if we want to flip everything into, you know, to the other domain or whatever.","index":802,"end_time":3130.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3125.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So those are some of the action items.","index":803,"end_time":3131.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3130.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys will come back to me to let me know what we''re going to do in regards to that.","index":804,"end_time":3134.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3131.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Correct.","index":805,"end_time":3134.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3134.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then.","index":806,"end_time":3134.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3134.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":807,"end_time":3135.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3134.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just let me know if I have to say anything.","index":808,"end_time":3137.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3135.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you need extra stuff, I can say something to Ryan or whatever.","index":809,"end_time":3140.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3137.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Let me know when you''re getting ready to do stuff.","index":810,"end_time":3141.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3140.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I''ll just kind of give them a heads up that we''re moving everything over to HubSpot, so.","index":811,"end_time":3144.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3141.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":812,"end_time":3145.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3144.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll also get started on all those documents that we talked about for the planes.","index":813,"end_time":3149.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3145.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":814,"end_time":3150.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3150.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":815,"end_time":3151.339,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3150.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, appreciate it.","index":816,"end_time":3152.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3151.339,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, thank you so much.","index":817,"end_time":3152.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3152.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hope you have a great rest of your day.","index":818,"end_time":3153.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3152.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":819,"end_time":3155.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3154.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":820,"end_time":3155.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3155.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Bye.","index":821,"end_time":3155.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3155.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-11-18T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81227121766?pwd=PAE6vnCK0QmrtUG7Z8MawrUMKoDZxP.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,michael@kerstentalentcapital.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","michael@kerstentalentcapital.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KA703CWQKPQX9NY6F9ZHCNZA","organizer_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Agreed to centralize CRM and website on HubSpot, enabling campaign sync and lead tracking.","Michael approved potential rebrand to KTC Search; team to recommend path by first week of December.","Team to build website plan with custom templates and architecture for scalable campaigns and SEO.","Content strategy to include stealth library ahead of Q1; multiple contributors identified to represent brand.","Leadership gap and talent trends reports planned as cornerstone assets for ABM efforts and outreach."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I''m giving you guys the key to the kitchen, and I need your expertise to help me get to that next level.","speaker":"Michael Kersten"},{"quote":"We''re not the company that''s going to just turn on a campaign and be, like, cool, we''ll see how it did in a month.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We kind of have everything at our disposal which isn''t totally normal.","speaker":"Tristan Pelligrino"}],"topics":["delivery","branding","content","crm","abm","strategy"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-24T21:13:54Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Migration and HubSpot Integration**\n\nThe team agreed to prioritize migrating the website into **HubSpot** to consolidate tools, improve integration with the CRM, and reduce costs by potentially moving from **Enterprise to Professional tier** (01:04).\n\n- **Michael Kersten** emphasized moving the website into HubSpot since he is already paying for that tool, enabling tighter integration with campaigns and dashboards (02:14).  \n- The current website and marketing cloud setup by the Colombian team is functional but siloed; consolidation aims to reduce tool bloat and overspending, as noted by **Colin Costigan** (05:06).  \n- HubSpot’s lead object functionality, recently introduced, will be leveraged for campaigns, but the team is open to adjusting the CRM structure based on best practices for campaign flow and data tracking (07:55).  \n- **Tristan Pelligrino** clarified that HubSpot’s Sales module is essential for workflows on the sales side, and Michael has Enterprise licenses covering this, allowing complex deal tracking and revenue management (09:07).  \n- Michael’s role primarily focuses on deal management and revenue tracking within HubSpot Sales, while marketing-driven campaigns and lead generation will be handled by the agency team (09:57).  \n- The team will evaluate if all current HubSpot modules are necessary to optimize costs and functionality, with transparency on any recommendations (13:19).  \n- The migration will include a website plan document outlining architecture, URL strategy, messaging, and scalable landing page templates for rapid future content deployment (31:07).  \n- Colin and Tristan will coordinate with Michael to prepare for the migration, ensuring Ryan and the Colombian team are informed and that transitions happen smoothly (52:15).  \n\n## **Branding, Messaging, and Website Content Strategy**\n\nThe group identified the need to elevate the website’s messaging and branding to better reflect Michael’s firm as a specialized boutique enterprise operating nationally and in global markets, not a one-person shop (14:19).\n\n- Michael wants to highlight recent wins in the **utility and PE sectors**, showcasing success stories to raise awareness beyond word-of-mouth referrals (14:33).  \n- The homepage should communicate the firm’s enterprise-level capabilities and broad industry reach, balancing specific industry focus with general appeal to capture diverse market opportunities like AI, renewable energy, and data centers over the next three years (19:03).  \n- Michael expressed concern that using his full name in branding might create a perception of a small, solo operation; he prefers shifting to the **KTC Search** brand to project a larger firm image and leverage the keyword “search” for SEO benefits (23:07).  \n- The team will research competitive domain usage and brand recognition to recommend whether to fully rebrand to KTC Search or maintain the current name with adjusted messaging (28:26).  \n- Michael is open to changing the website’s color scheme and design to align with industry standards seen in top retained search firms, favoring lighter colors and dynamic visuals like videos and rotating images to increase engagement (29:41).  \n- The team will produce a website plan document detailing messaging, design, and architecture to support ongoing content development and rapid response to market changes or new industry focuses (31:07).  \n- Weekly meetings will start the first week of December to maintain alignment on branding, website development, and campaign progress (51:07).  \n\n## **Content Engine and Thought Leadership Series**\n\nA content series will be developed to build brand recognition and position Michael’s firm as an industry thought leader through interviews, market insights, and topical discussions (34:12).\n\n- Michael prefers the agency team to host interviews with prospects, clients, or industry experts to reduce his time commitment and avoid sales perceptions during content delivery (34:59).  \n- To protect sensitive information related to Michael’s ID.me involvement and pre-IPO interests, content with his direct name will be limited until **end of Q1 2026**, after which more public branding can occur (36:25).  \n- Michael identified potential mouthpieces within his network, including a polished protege and a marketing writer, to serve as proxies in content delivery, maintaining his low profile while sharing expertise (40:35).  \n- The content plan will include show themes, target audiences, publishing cadence, and design elements to ensure consistent, market-relevant messaging (40:35).  \n- Michael can engage industry experts and board members from his network to provide qualitative insights for content, leveraging their knowledge to build credible trends reports and thought leadership (43:54).  \n- The team will run workshops to refine content strategy and identify key themes such as leadership velocity, infrastructure growth, and industry shifts relevant to PE-backed companies (46:22).  \n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Campaign Strategy**\n\nThe ABM campaign will focus on targeted outreach using data-driven insights and customized content to attract retained and contingent clients, particularly in the PE and utility sectors (42:26).\n\n- The campaign will leverage a **Portfolio Talent Trends Report** built from qualitative feedback gathered during content conversations and expert interviews, serving as a key asset to engage prospects (43:02).  \n- Michael will provide access to his network of seasoned executives in utilities and professional services to contribute insights, enriching the report’s credibility and relevance (44:54).  \n- The ABM approach will include clear identification of companies and contacts to target, as well as those to exclude, ensuring efficient use of resources and avoiding conflicts with existing client relationships (48:32).  \n- The campaign’s success will be tracked and iterated rapidly, with the team ready to pivot based on market response and performance metrics (32:45).  \n- The team emphasized transparency and cost-effectiveness by evaluating necessary HubSpot modules and tech stack components to avoid overspending (13:19).  \n\n## **Operational Coordination and Process Improvements**\n\nClear communication and defined roles between Michael, the agency team, and the Colombian team will support a smooth technology transition and campaign execution (02:14).\n\n- Michael will notify Ryan and others when the migration to HubSpot begins to ensure proper handoff and avoid duplicated efforts (52:30).  \n- The agency team will provide documented recommendations on HubSpot usage, including lead object structure and workflows, with Michael’s approval before implementing changes (51:55).  \n- The team will set up a shared portal for full transparency on goals, deliverables, and feedback, improving collaboration and tracking progress in 15-minute increments (49:41).  \n- A weekly meeting cadence starting early December will ensure ongoing alignment, quick issue resolution, and accountability (51:07).  \n- The agency manages vendor relationships and subscriptions like Clay on Michael’s behalf, optimizing tech stack usage without requiring Michael to negotiate separately (33:40).  \n- Michael has roughly **50,000 to 60,000 contacts** in Zoom that can be integrated into campaigns, maximizing existing assets and reducing incremental data costs (33:55).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Website Migration","ABM Campaign","Content Engine","Branding Strategy","Private Equity"],"overview":"- **Website Migration to HubSpot:** Focus on moving website to HubSpot to streamline tools and reduce costs from Enterprise to Professional tier.  \n- **Branding and Messaging Revamp:** Shift branding to KTC Search to reflect enterprise-level capabilities and leverage SEO; explore updated design aesthetics.  \n- **Content Engine Development:** Create content series featuring interviews and insights to establish thought leadership while maintaining a low profile.  \n- **ABM Campaign Strategy:** Implement targeted outreach using data-driven insights, focusing on the PE and utility sectors with a Portfolio Talent Trends Report.  \n- **Operational Coordination:** Establish clear roles and communication to ensure smooth migration and campaign execution, with scheduled weekly updates starting December.  \n- **Integration of Contacts:** Utilize Michael''s 50,000-60,000 Zoom contacts to enhance campaigns, maximizing current resources while minimizing additional costs.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare HubSpot object and workflow change recommendations with Michael and team (52:14)\nDevelop and deliver website plan document including architecture, messaging, URL strategy, and page templates (31:07)\nSet up weekly recurring meeting with Michael starting first week of December on Tuesdays at 10 AM, send calendar invites (51:32)\nProvide brand/website rebranding research and recommendations regarding KTC Search versus existing branding (23:59)\nInitiate content plan development detailing show names, themes, target audience, and publishing cadence (40:35)\nFacilitate setup of portfolio total platform access for Michael with single sign-on and goal loading (50:30)\nCoordinate with Michael and internal teams on notification and logistics for migrating website to HubSpot (52:14)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nCollaborate on HubSpot features and workflow structure aligning marketing and sales objectives (09:05)\nAssist in defining sales vs marketing roles for communications and sequencing within HubSpot (10:00)\nAssist in content engine creation and management focusing on guest interviews, market topics, and stealth content scheduling (34:12)\nSupport in packaging portfolio talent trends report and leadership gap assessment for ABM campaigns (43:00)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nProvide disallowed target companies and contacts list to avoid marketing overlaps (48:32)\nFacilitate access and share contacts from Zoom database for use in campaigns (33:55)\nIdentify internal point(s) of contact or authorize communication with Ryan regarding website migration preparations (52:14)\nEngage with selected industry experts and board members to support industry insights and content development (45:17)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"be49bcf0-7304-4926-9247-aec57006ac76","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
